char_102_texas_CN_001.voiceText: My next mission is to protect you, Doctor.

char_102_texas_CN_002.voiceText: I don't say much? That's because I'd rather avoid thinking about most things.

char_102_texas_CN_003.voiceText: Our job is to deliver life and death.

char_102_texas_CN_004.voiceText: I usually listen to Sora's songs when I'm driving.

char_102_texas_CN_005.voiceText: Cigarette? Oh, no, this is chocolate. You've gotta replenish your energy regularly. Which reminds me... do you want some coffee?

char_102_texas_CN_006.voiceText: How long have I worked for Penguin Logistics? When did I start...? I don't even know how long it's been.

char_102_texas_CN_007.voiceText: Watch out for the Red Wolf. She's not evil, but... she's not like us.

char_102_texas_CN_008.voiceText: No matter how hard I run, my past will catch up to me one day.

char_102_texas_CN_009.voiceText: My independent lifestyle and rowdy friends have brought me a lot of trouble... but I kind of like it this way.

char_102_texas_CN_010.voiceText: Is it time for a break?

char_102_texas_CN_011.voiceText: Code name Texas. I'm responsible for driving, moving cargo, and keeping our people safe. Try to get the mission briefings as concise as possible, please.

char_102_texas_CN_018.voiceText: I'm not good at barking orders.

char_102_texas_CN_031.voiceText: A few of them got through.

char_102_texas_CN_032.voiceText: I may have underestimated this operation.

char_102_texas_CN_033.voiceText: Do you need any supplies? Just let me know.

char_500_noirc_CN_001.voiceText: What's up, Doctor? Me, I'm just on standby.

char_500_noirc_CN_002.voiceText: My shield? Fun fact: I personally provide a portion of the energy it needs.

char_500_noirc_CN_003.voiceText: What I look like beneath the mask? Well, I... Actually, let's keep it secret for a bit longer.

char_500_noirc_CN_004.voiceText: Man, nothing better than a break after you finish a mission.

char_500_noirc_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, if I get to know you better, I figure my shield's gonna get even sturdier.

char_500_noirc_CN_008.voiceText: Course I know where my limit's at. But I don't want Yato to worry about me, which is what matters. We'll worry about the rest some other time!

char_500_noirc_CN_009.voiceText: There's always the need for guys like me, you know? Nah, I'm not trying to act high and mighty. What I'm saying is: when you have a VIP plus a lot of danger, you need a guy to stand between them, that's all.

char_500_noirc_CN_010.voiceText: Sometimes you've just gotta take off the mask and catch a breather.

char_500_noirc_CN_011.voiceText: Defender Noir Corne, reporting for duty. You need VIP protection, I'm your guy.

char_500_noirc_CN_012.voiceText: Cool... So this stuff is what Grandpa Rangers was talking about earlier.

char_500_noirc_CN_019.voiceText: Holding the line is a Defender's most important job!

char_500_noirc_CN_029.voiceText: Even guys like me are happy to get through tough battles like these.

char_500_noirc_CN_032.voiceText: This wouldn't have happened if I'd worn my good mask! God dammit!

char_500_noirc_CN_036.voiceText: You wanna get some drinks after work?

char_503_rang_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, I greatly admire your genius. It's my honor to be your guard.

char_503_rang_CN_002.voiceText: A man of my experience can tell you'll be a great leader one day, Doctor.

char_503_rang_CN_003.voiceText: I have an unusual skin tone, you say? Hah. Just a souvenir from back when I snuck into a biolab, and... Please, I'm joking around.

char_503_rang_CN_004.voiceText: I need to wear this scarf, even when I sleep, or else my neck will get cold.

char_503_rang_CN_007.voiceText: This face of mine might be a little too exotic for your typical townsfolk. Heh, I tend to draw a curious crowd when I wander.

char_503_rang_CN_008.voiceText: I'm surprised how polite you are to this old man! Not many besides Durin ask after my health.

char_503_rang_CN_009.voiceText: When I go barefoot, I can sense enemies through their vibrations on the ground.

char_503_rang_CN_010.voiceText: Hmm... Snoring is a bad habit. The other rangers will hear you.

char_503_rang_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Rangers, the Sniper. Call whenever you need me.

char_503_rang_CN_018.voiceText: Good. Let me show you what an old man can do.

char_503_rang_CN_029.voiceText: Challenge after challenge. Exactly what we wanted. Right, Noir Corne?

char_503_rang_CN_031.voiceText: A few of them got through. I'd call that decent.

char_503_rang_CN_032.voiceText: Oh no, I'm out of breath...

char_503_rang_CN_033.voiceText: If you need anything, just say the word.

char_503_rang_CN_034.voiceText: Urgh! Please, leave my tail be...

char_503_rang_CN_036.voiceText: You like me that much, huh? Weird taste, I gotta say.

char_503_rang_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor, how can I help you?

char_501_durin_CN_001.voiceText: Morning, Doctor... Mind if I lay out my sleeping bag here...? Thanks. The rest is up to you...

char_501_durin_CN_002.voiceText: How do I fight? Using Arts, of course... Want me to show you the power of earth?

char_501_durin_CN_003.voiceText: What time is it...? See, I don't work mornings, noons, afternoons, or nights...

char_501_durin_CN_004.voiceText: You'll make an S-sized uniform for me...? No thanks. My oversized one works as a sheet when I take naps... plus, it's really warm.

char_501_durin_CN_007.voiceText: Dooooctoooooor? I need a break! I'm competing in the Speedy Sleep Contest.

char_501_durin_CN_008.voiceText: Doctor, check this out. This isn't my normal wand, it's a pendulum. You're feeling very sleepy and will nap in five minutes without giving me any work... Zzzz...

char_501_durin_CN_009.voiceText: I was hoping I could tell you about my homeland, Doctor.

char_501_durin_CN_010.voiceText: After you went to sleep, I somehow didn't feel sleepy at all anymore... Hmmmph...

char_501_durin_CN_011.voiceText: Hello? Hellooooo? Can you hear me? Down here. Down heeeeere! Nice meeting you, big Doctor. I'm Durin the Caster.

char_501_durin_CN_017.voiceText: The secret to staying healthy is to sleep whenever you can.

char_501_durin_CN_018.voiceText: Captain's orders: everyone, save your energy and take a nap!

char_501_durin_CN_019.voiceText: I wanna dig a hole in the ground and make a shelter to sleep in, if you don't mind.

char_501_durin_CN_029.voiceText: Why do we have annoying missions like this? Can't we do something easier...? Still, it's nice that we won.

char_501_durin_CN_030.voiceText: Of course we won. I worked real hard supporting you with my Arts.

char_501_durin_CN_031.voiceText: Doctor, are you still worried about those ones that got through?

char_501_durin_CN_032.voiceText: Ugghh... Sorry... I'll try harder next time...

char_501_durin_CN_033.voiceText: The Land of Giants... Here I aaaaaaaaaaaaaaam!

char_501_durin_CN_036.voiceText: I'm in a good mood, so how about a magic trick?

char_502_nblade_CN_001.voiceText: Hey, Doctor. Do me a favor and just tell me what you need done.

char_502_nblade_CN_002.voiceText: I'll be watching you even when I'm off duty.

char_502_nblade_CN_004.voiceText: My skin is sensitive to sunlight. So please assign me to nighttime missions, whenever you can.

char_502_nblade_CN_007.voiceText: There's limits to what I'm capable of, but even so, I want to help ease the burden you carry, Doctor.

char_502_nblade_CN_008.voiceText: I can't help but feel just a little envious when I see how the other Operators fight...

char_502_nblade_CN_009.voiceText: I need no particular reason to fight for you, Doctor. I hope to see an exciting frontline battle someday...

char_502_nblade_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, let me be your guardian, now and forever...

char_502_nblade_CN_011.voiceText: Vanguard Yato here. Are you the one I'm protecting?

char_502_nblade_CN_018.voiceText: We're ready to execute your plans, Doctor.

char_502_nblade_CN_020.voiceText: Targets spotted. Get ready for battle.

char_502_nblade_CN_029.voiceText: As long as we follow the Doctor's orders, we won't have any problems.

char_502_nblade_CN_030.voiceText: The Doctor's brilliant command was the key to victory.

char_502_nblade_CN_031.voiceText: Victory is the most welcome news.

char_502_nblade_CN_032.voiceText: I apologize... We failed to execute your plan, Doctor...

char_502_nblade_CN_033.voiceText: Please send me somewhere that sunlight can never touch.

char_502_nblade_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, thank you for always taking care of us.

char_502_nblade_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor, I will be your shield.

char_122_beagle_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, I'm your guard for the day! Don't worry, I won't let any sketchy people near you! Just relax!

char_122_beagle_CN_002.voiceText: My training score for today...? Um, I mean, we could talk about something else...

char_122_beagle_CN_003.voiceText: I can't shake the pre-battle jitters, and that makes Captain Fang really nervous too... What should I do? Doctor!

char_122_beagle_CN_004.voiceText: Hibiscus and Lava always complain to me about each other, but both of them are my good friends, and neither of them are wrong... Doctor, what should I do?

char_122_beagle_CN_005.voiceText: Instructor Dobermann always told us, 'Even when after you finish your training, your number one goal on the battlefield is to stay alive.' Urgh... How can I become as strong and awesome as she is?

char_122_beagle_CN_007.voiceText: I'm still a rookie Operator, but I'm working hard! Hehehe, I'd really love a compliment or two, if you agree.

char_122_beagle_CN_008.voiceText: My Oripathy? It doesn't bother me all that much, I'm used to it. I just want to be with the people I care about until my disease gets cured... Ughh...

char_122_beagle_CN_009.voiceText: I didn't have much confidence before I came here, but I'm so glad that I can protect you and everyone on Rhodes Island! It's my dream to protect everyone! I really wish days like these could last forever.

char_122_beagle_CN_010.voiceText: Aww... seeing the Doctor sleeping all vulnerable like that makes me want to doodle something on a certain someone's face...

char_122_beagle_CN_011.voiceText: My codename is Beagle! I know I didn't do very well on my assessment, but I'll still do my best at my internship!

char_122_beagle_CN_012.voiceText: I did it! I've become stronger!

char_122_beagle_CN_013.voiceText: Finally, FINALLY! Now nobody's going to call me 'the Rookiest Rookie in the Rookieverse' anymore!

char_122_beagle_CN_018.voiceText: Huh? I am the leader? I don't feel right about Fang not being the leader...

char_122_beagle_CN_029.voiceText: It's my duty to protect everyone! My resolve will never falter, no matter the odds!

char_122_beagle_CN_030.voiceText: All enemies have been defeated! We Rhodes Island Operators are the finest!

char_122_beagle_CN_031.voiceText: Hooray, we won! Although a few enemies managed to get away... *sigh*...

char_122_beagle_CN_033.voiceText: What can I do for you?

char_122_beagle_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, can I come to your place to study every day?

char_123_fang_CN_001.voiceText: Is there anything I can help you with, Doctor?

char_123_fang_CN_002.voiceText: Thank you for believing in me! I'll keep up my work!

char_123_fang_CN_003.voiceText: Hibiscus and Lava are fighting again... What a pain. Why are they like this? They're sisters.

char_123_fang_CN_004.voiceText: Instructor Dobermann puts us through mock battles a lot, but I can never get a handle on her skill. Doctor, next time you and Amiya observe our training, would you please give us some notes?

char_123_fang_CN_005.voiceText: Someone on my team is late again, huh? I'll make sure that gets fixed.

char_123_fang_CN_007.voiceText: Lava and I are both Infected, but I didn't get a talent for Arts like she did...

char_123_fang_CN_008.voiceText: Rhodes Island is our home and shelter, Doctor. I will protect everyone here with my life.

char_123_fang_CN_009.voiceText: The ever-honest and reliable Beagle, the perceptive Kroos, the resourceful Lava and the energetic Hibiscus. I like everyone in this team... as long as Hibiscus doesn't force her health food innovations on me.

char_123_fang_CN_010.voiceText: Shhh! The Doctor's resting. We can talk outside.

char_123_fang_CN_011.voiceText: Lancer Fang, captain of Reserve Op Team A1. My team and I will do our best to serve Rhodes Island.

char_123_fang_CN_013.voiceText: Your approval means so much to me, Doctor. This promotion proves my hard work is paying off.

char_123_fang_CN_018.voiceText: I know the captain's duty well. Rest easy.

char_123_fang_CN_019.voiceText: Team, check your gear before departing.

char_123_fang_CN_029.voiceText: With the right plan, even rookies like us can win a tough fight!

char_123_fang_CN_030.voiceText: We have accomplished our objective as planned.

char_123_fang_CN_031.voiceText: We can't call a mission complete if we let even a single enemy get through. Beagle, let's do better on the next one.

char_123_fang_CN_032.voiceText: I'm sorry I failed you, Instructor Dobermann...

char_123_fang_CN_033.voiceText: Yes. I'm back. Is Kroos here too?

char_123_fang_CN_042.voiceText: I'm ready whenever you need me, Doctor.

char_124_kroos_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, it's such a nice day, so can't we take a little nap?

char_124_kroos_CN_002.voiceText: Hmm...? We're about to leave? But I just got up... Wait, is this the Doctor's office? How'd I get here?

char_124_kroos_CN_003.voiceText: Why am I always squinting? Because I don't want anyone to see my eyes. Nope, nobody~

char_124_kroos_CN_004.voiceText: I'm really careless and get hurt a lot... But Hibiscus heals me every time, so I'm not afraid of getting injured. Oh gosh, that 'Curing Cuisine' of hers though, I'm terrified of it...

char_124_kroos_CN_005.voiceText: Doctor! Someone left 10 alarm clocks by my bed! Who would do something so awful?!

char_124_kroos_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, let's play a game~ Put an apple on your head and we'll start~

char_124_kroos_CN_008.voiceText: I'm always looking for fun things to do as a way to ease the pain of my Oripathy, I guess. Plus, I love seeing other people smile~

char_124_kroos_CN_009.voiceText: One day, our journey with Rhodes Island will come to an end, and hopefully we'll all get to have a warm, neverending dream, lying in the sunshine~ That's my number one dream~

char_124_kroos_CN_010.voiceText: Can't believe the Doctor's a heavier sleeper than me...

char_124_kroos_CN_011.voiceText: Hi-hiii~ I'm Kroos~ I might be inexperienced, but I'll do the best I can~

char_124_kroos_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion~ What a lovely dream~ Huh? I'm not dreaming?

char_124_kroos_CN_018.voiceText: Huhhh~? Fang would make a better captain than me!

char_124_kroos_CN_020.voiceText: Why can't everyone try to get along...?

char_124_kroos_CN_024.voiceText: I won't sleep on the job~

char_124_kroos_CN_031.voiceText: Hmm, I guess this was a bit of a letdown...

char_124_kroos_CN_032.voiceText: S-sorry... I'll fight harder next time...!

char_124_kroos_CN_033.voiceText: Can I get my beauty sleep in here?

char_121_lava_CN_001.voiceText: Need something? If you don't ,how about some divination?

char_121_lava_CN_002.voiceText: Just tell me when there's work to do. But don't ever put her and me on the same team. I hate her guts. And don't get me started on all the weird food she makes me eat... Just thinking about it makes me... euurghh...

char_121_lava_CN_003.voiceText: No one told me Hibiscus was at Rhodes Island before I got here... It's too late for me to quit now.

char_121_lava_CN_004.voiceText: If you grow up sheltered, you don't know how to taunt, how to destroy, and how to handle yourself in a real fight. Am I right, Doctor?

char_121_lava_CN_005.voiceText: Have you ever heard the saying 'little sisters are justice'? If that's true, then my big sis is evil by default... at least as far as I'm concerned.

char_121_lava_CN_007.voiceText: Instruments? I can play the piano a little. My teacher in Leithanien said learning an instrument can improve your Arts affinity. It also apparently eases the impact that Oripathy has on your mind...

char_121_lava_CN_008.voiceText: I'm starving... Huh, what's this? You keep sweets in here? Nom... I'm in the middle of training. Should I really be eating this?

char_121_lava_CN_009.voiceText: See, like, I don't have a big beef with Hibiscus... It's all water under the bridge. I'm fine with her as long as she doesn't force me to eat her medicine and food. After all, she was the one... who saved my life...

char_121_lava_CN_010.voiceText: I almost envy your ability to sleep like a log...

char_121_lava_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Lava, a Caster, here to join you simply because I'm bored and want something to do… But I heard my sworn nemesis is here too, though... Can I just quit now?

char_121_lava_CN_013.voiceText: Did you forget? I don't need a cause to work for, and I don't need a team... but... thanks, I guess...

char_121_lava_CN_017.voiceText: As far as teamwork's concerned... I don't mind, as long as nobody messes up.

char_121_lava_CN_018.voiceText: I'm not good at this sort of stuff, but if you insist...

char_121_lava_CN_019.voiceText: Let's go. Keep an eye on my back.

char_121_lava_CN_020.voiceText: I can see their souls. They're mine to reap.

char_121_lava_CN_026.voiceText: Even the dead can't save you.

char_121_lava_CN_029.voiceText: The supreme form of Arts. I'm interested in seeing what it's like.

char_121_lava_CN_030.voiceText: I foresaw this result earlier. A perfect victory.

char_121_lava_CN_031.voiceText: Well… My fortune telling isn't always right. Sometimes there's a lot of external noise that affects the outcome.

char_121_lava_CN_032.voiceText: Dammit... These evil spirits are too strong...

char_121_lava_CN_033.voiceText: Oh, come on. I'd rather be alone.

char_121_lava_CN_036.voiceText: Eh, you're not scoring any points with me like that!

char_120_hibisc_CN_001.voiceText: Did you call for me, Doctor? I feel so happy to be with you!

char_120_hibisc_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor! Dr. Kal'tsit said that you need to look after your health more. In two words, E-A-T L-E-S-S! So there!

char_120_hibisc_CN_003.voiceText: You know, Doctor, if my sister starts getting all bossy with you, you have to tell me! She needs my treatment or else!

char_120_hibisc_CN_004.voiceText: Dr. Kal'tsit teaches me a ton of practical stuff, although it's tough to actually learn! At least I've always had a knack for nutrition, so I think I'm doing well with that!

char_120_hibisc_CN_005.voiceText: I feel better about everyone here, compared to when I just joined Rhodes Island! And they all eat my healthy food on schedule! But... why does everyone pull these weird faces when they finish?

char_120_hibisc_CN_007.voiceText: Tadaaaaaah! A special healthy meal just for you, Doctor! Decaf coffee and a hamburger without meat, cheese, pickles, or lettuce! Oh, and a mixed salad made of 12 different vegetables!

char_120_hibisc_CN_008.voiceText: Hey, Doctor, where does your family live? Are they doing well? I know there's things you can't tell them about because they're your family... but, still, I think you've got to reach out. You have to try, at least.

char_120_hibisc_CN_009.voiceText: Isn't it lonely cooking all by yourself? Let me help you out! Oh, right, and let's get Lava in here too!

char_120_hibisc_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, did you fall asleep? Have a good rest then. You need to sleep plenty to stay healthy.

char_120_hibisc_CN_011.voiceText: This is intern Hibiscus. From now on, I'll be in charge of managing yours and every Operator's health at Rhodes Island. Thank you for your cooperation!

char_120_hibisc_CN_012.voiceText: Oh, I see! So that's how you do it!

char_120_hibisc_CN_013.voiceText: It's my honor to be promoted! I'm looking forward to working under you for the health management of us all, Doctor!

char_120_hibisc_CN_017.voiceText: I won't fail you! I'll protect everyone!

char_120_hibisc_CN_018.voiceText: Acknowledged! I'll take good care of everyone! First, I need to get my special sustained-release medicine ready...

char_120_hibisc_CN_019.voiceText: Please take good care of yourself while I'm gone!

char_120_hibisc_CN_026.voiceText: I can heal that wound in no time!

char_120_hibisc_CN_029.voiceText: Even if everyone gets wounded, I can heal them all with my staff!

char_120_hibisc_CN_030.voiceText: Looking after everyone's health is my greatest motivation.

char_120_hibisc_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, do you want to have a taste of my new vitamin drink?

char_120_hibisc_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor! Would you mind tasting this?

char_208_melan_CN_001.voiceText: H-Hello, Doctor... It's nice meeting you...

char_208_melan_CN_002.voiceText: Um... Sorry... I'm not a good talker...

char_208_melan_CN_003.voiceText: Yes... My parents are Victorian merchants. But I haven't been able to contact them for a long time... I picked this code name because it reminds me of home.

char_208_melan_CN_004.voiceText: Th-That masked Operator... makes me feel... nervous...

char_208_melan_CN_005.voiceText: It's not that... I'm trying to avoid people, it's just, I'm not sure... what I should do...

char_208_melan_CN_007.voiceText: Sorry to make you worry again, Ansel... But you don't have to give me special treatment. Many more people need your help.

char_208_melan_CN_008.voiceText: Oripathy granted me powerful senses, but they're slipping away, little by little... Even so, I will not crumble... There's so much more I want to talk about with everyone...

char_208_melan_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, could you take this bottle of perfume, please? I brought it from home... This type of perfume lifts spirits. I often take a sniff when I feel down.

char_208_melan_CN_010.voiceText: Merry? Keep it down... The Doctor is very tired.

char_208_melan_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Melantha... From now on, my blade is yours.

char_208_melan_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you very much... Um, were the others promoted as well? I think they all deserve it just the same.

char_208_melan_CN_018.voiceText: The leader? But I'm not particularly good at giving orders...

char_208_melan_CN_019.voiceText: Let's work to make the world a more peaceful place.

char_208_melan_CN_020.voiceText: Ansel... I'm counting on you now.

char_208_melan_CN_029.voiceText: No matter what difficulties are in store for me, I will keep on advancing.

char_208_melan_CN_030.voiceText: We won? Thank goodness for that...

char_208_melan_CN_032.voiceText: We failed... How did things end up this way?

char_208_melan_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, thank you for always taking care of me... Um, actually... I'd like to keep taking on the fight.

char_209_ardign_CN_001.voiceText: Hello! It's my shift now, Doctor!

char_209_ardign_CN_002.voiceText: What does my 'Cardigan' codename mean? Ahh, It's actually the name of my clan. It's a family tradition to use it as a codename.

char_209_ardign_CN_003.voiceText: Wow, I found one of my people on another team! I've got to invite her to hang out with me sometime!

char_209_ardign_CN_004.voiceText: I was born in the north of Leithanien, a place full of snowy forests. Oh, that reminds me, I can teach you to ski, Doctor!

char_209_ardign_CN_005.voiceText: A lot of people say stuff like 'it's a Defender's job to hold her ground,' but that's such an outdated concept. Speed is what you need! This is the age of maneuver warfare! Mobility is the key to victory!

char_209_ardign_CN_007.voiceText: *Sniff sniff*... I recognize that perfume, it's gotta be Melantha! I hope we can become closer friends... 'Cause then we'll be able to work better as a team!

char_209_ardign_CN_008.voiceText: Hehe, I really enjoy playing with kids. Back in my hometown, I took my brothers and sisters sledding every year. I really miss it! Oh, speaking of sleds... I wonder if Adnachiel can make one for me.

char_209_ardign_CN_009.voiceText: I have plenty of things I don't like. Oripathy, for instance... But there's no point in worrying too much. I would rather live my days in happiness! Plus, I've got you with me, Doctor!

char_209_ardign_CN_011.voiceText: Heeellooo! I've never been in such a big mobile facility before! I'm so excited! Merry of the Cardigan here. Are you the Doctor?

char_209_ardign_CN_013.voiceText: Yay! I will keep fighting hard for my next promotion! I'm sure it will come in time!

char_209_ardign_CN_017.voiceText: Awesome! Finally, my time has come!

char_209_ardign_CN_018.voiceText: Ansel! Come on! I promise I won't lead everyone on a wild-goose chase!

char_209_ardign_CN_019.voiceText: Formation ready! Advance to the objective!

char_209_ardign_CN_020.voiceText: Let's go! ...Steward, what was I supposed to do next?

char_209_ardign_CN_029.voiceText: I knew we could do it. Right, Adnachiel?

char_209_ardign_CN_031.voiceText: Thanks, Medics! You saved my life...

char_209_ardign_CN_033.voiceText: Steward, what should I do next?

char_209_ardign_CN_036.voiceText: Melantha? Huh? Why are you here, Doctor?!

char_210_stward_CN_001.voiceText: Welcome back, Doctor. Steward at your service.

char_210_stward_CN_002.voiceText: Steward is my surname, as well as my Operator codename. Doctor, I'm sure you can tell from it what my ancestors did for a living.

char_210_stward_CN_003.voiceText: I didn't expect to see another from my clan here. Is she looking for someone? I know how that feels... Oh, never mind.

char_210_stward_CN_004.voiceText: People often say our fur has the 'color of snow.' Doctor, have you ever seen snow?

char_210_stward_CN_005.voiceText: Lava has a very distinct fighting style. I thought she was going to cast with her book, but her real Arts Unit is a dagger. Her style reminds me of the mystic who taught me Arts.

char_210_stward_CN_007.voiceText: It is my honor to work for you, Doctor. But if possible, I do hope you pay some extra care to Melantha. She's always alone…

char_210_stward_CN_008.voiceText: Adnachiel is a mysterious one... No one can tell what he is thinking.

char_210_stward_CN_009.voiceText: Ansel... It's okay... I stopped caring about my identity as an Infected long ago. In fact, I received a lot of help because of it. Before the infection takes away what's dear to me, I will use it to create a place where everyone can live in peace.

char_210_stward_CN_010.voiceText: Are you tired? Do take a good rest, Doctor. Rhodes Island will need your skills tomorrow.

char_210_stward_CN_011.voiceText: Caster Steward reporting in. I'm glad to be working with you.

char_210_stward_CN_012.voiceText: I have learned a lot. Thank you.

char_210_stward_CN_013.voiceText: I'm glad that you are satisfied with my work. Instructor Dobermann will be happy too.

char_210_stward_CN_017.voiceText: What can I do for you?

char_210_stward_CN_018.voiceText: Cardigan, always read the situation before you act.

char_210_stward_CN_019.voiceText: Well, I'll be sure to bring you some good news.

char_210_stward_CN_020.voiceText: They probably won't make it to tomorrow.

char_210_stward_CN_029.voiceText: With the right strategy, we'll make it through any tight spot.

char_210_stward_CN_030.voiceText: A perfect victory. Good work, everyone!

char_210_stward_CN_031.voiceText: Ansel, please check the casualties for me. We must prepare for the next battle.

char_210_stward_CN_032.voiceText: Did we make a mistake somewhere...?

char_210_stward_CN_033.voiceText: Is that you, Cardi— WAI-WAIT! WAIT! Don't touch the equipment!

char_210_stward_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, is there anything I can do for you?

char_211_adnach_CN_001.voiceText: That device you're holding seems to be in poor shape. Would you mind if I take a look at it?

char_211_adnach_CN_002.voiceText: Hey, Ansel. Cardigan looks good today. Anything I can help you with?

char_211_adnach_CN_003.voiceText: We have a squad of very interesting people, especially Melantha. She always seems to be hiding from me, but I can sniff her out.

char_211_adnach_CN_004.voiceText: Cardigan, what are you doing? You look so happy.

char_211_adnach_CN_005.voiceText: Not every Laterano has the right to use guns, rare weapons that they are. In my hometown, we're pretty good at making knockoff gun parts. The crossbow crafting industry is also on the rise. The result is what I have here - a crossbow with a tactical rail attachment.

char_211_adnach_CN_007.voiceText: Would you like to try some of my handmade sweets? I'm kind of ashamed that I can only make 25 types of desserts. It feels like I've disgraced the Laterano people.

char_211_adnach_CN_008.voiceText: What's wrong with my halo? I don't know why, but it seems to have deviated slightly. According to Dr. Kal'tsit, it probably has something to do with my abnormal hippocampus.

char_211_adnach_CN_009.voiceText: Instead of watching you from afar, I feel much better standing by your side, Doctor.

char_211_adnach_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, you strike an impressive figure, even when you rest like that.

char_211_adnach_CN_011.voiceText: My name is Adnachiel. I'm a Sniper from Laterano. Although I'm not yet certified to carry a gun, I can match the veterans with my crossbow!

char_211_adnach_CN_012.voiceText: Put me to good use and I'll be more than happy.

char_211_adnach_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you very much for the promotion.

char_211_adnach_CN_018.voiceText: If anything breaks, bring it to me. I may be able to fix it for you.

char_211_adnach_CN_019.voiceText: It's time to go. Are you ready?

char_211_adnach_CN_029.voiceText: Everything went just as you planned, Doctor.

char_211_adnach_CN_030.voiceText: We have the Doctor's orders to thank for this.

char_211_adnach_CN_031.voiceText: Our operation was a success, but something feels a bit off...

char_211_adnach_CN_033.voiceText: This place has a great vibe.

char_211_adnach_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor? I'm so happy to be with you!

char_211_adnach_CN_042.voiceText: May the Lord bless you, Doctor.

char_212_ansel_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, it's time for your injection. Oh, um, are you alright?! Are you scared of needles?

char_212_ansel_CN_002.voiceText: Like Dr. Kal'tsit is always telling you, Doctor, you really need some exercise. I'm new here, but you still need to listen to my advice.

char_212_ansel_CN_003.voiceText: Cardigan! We've told you, if you move like that when you strike, you'll wind up getting hurt.

char_212_ansel_CN_004.voiceText: Good grief... Doctor, you need to take care of yourself. You can't make us do it for you.

char_212_ansel_CN_005.voiceText: Are you worried about my health after so many night shifts? You shouldn't be. My race has a unique way of producing hormones, which allows us to handle night activities better. So I can hand my shift over to Hibiscus at just the right time.

char_212_ansel_CN_007.voiceText: You must stop with the midnight snacks. Don't go bringing up my eating habits. I eat at night because of my race! Yes, it's a racial trait!

char_212_ansel_CN_008.voiceText: I'm Ansel. It's a little embarrassing to admit, but I chose to become a Medic because I've been sickly since I was young. But now that I'm an Operator, I'll make sure not to burden you. So please treat me just the same way you treat the others.

char_212_ansel_CN_009.voiceText: I know everyone does what they can. But I heard from Dr. Kal'tsit that Steward and Melantha's conditions aren't looking too good... My job is to make their lives as easy as possible. Doctor, let's redouble our efforts, together.

char_212_ansel_CN_010.voiceText: Adnachiel, could you ask Cardigan to settle down for a moment? The Doctor is resting.

char_212_ansel_CN_011.voiceText: I am Ansel, a medical intern. I'll be assisting with surgery and internal medicine, among other things. I look forward to working with you.

char_212_ansel_CN_012.voiceText: I hope I didn't cause you any trouble.

char_212_ansel_CN_013.voiceText: I'm glad that you care so much for the wellbeing of us Medics.

char_212_ansel_CN_018.voiceText: Medical support should be the top priority for any tactical squad.

char_212_ansel_CN_019.voiceText: Alright, all medicine has been prepared.

char_212_ansel_CN_026.voiceText: Your medication is here. Take it!

char_212_ansel_CN_029.voiceText: Phew, thank goodness I brought enough medicine. Please don't worry.

char_212_ansel_CN_030.voiceText: I was very impressed by everyone's performance. It was fantastic.

char_212_ansel_CN_031.voiceText: Please hold on, I'll treat your injuries right away.

char_212_ansel_CN_032.voiceText: We've sustained injuries! I need to get the wounded to the rear. Cover me!

char_212_ansel_CN_033.voiceText: I'm checking on the medical supplies here.

char_212_ansel_CN_034.voiceText: Whoa, Doctor, please don't mess with me!

char_212_ansel_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, I'm very glad that you like me.

char_108_silent_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, these are your tasks for the day. Yeah. A whole pile of work. Let's get to it.

char_108_silent_CN_002.voiceText: Is Ifrit making trouble again? Sorry. I'll discipline her later.

char_108_silent_CN_003.voiceText: Zzzzz... Huh? Um, I was taking a nap... I'm still not used to working during the day.

char_108_silent_CN_004.voiceText: My reasons for quitting Rhine Lab? So much happened since I signed on, I don't even know where to start...

char_108_silent_CN_005.voiceText: Have you ever heard of a woman named Saria? Like me, she was once a scientist at Rhine Lab, and she was one of the people responsible for the creation of Ifrit...

char_108_silent_CN_006.voiceText: Our biology research at Rhine Lab went so far as to implant Originium Shards into living bodies... Sorry, we'd better change the subject.

char_108_silent_CN_007.voiceText: Saria? You mean she's here at Rhodes Island too? Is she here for Ifrit...? She walked out without a second thought, so why has she returned...?!

char_108_silent_CN_008.voiceText: I will not allow Ifrit to see Saria. Please trust me, this is for Ifrit's own good...!

char_108_silent_CN_009.voiceText: Are you trying to cure Oripathy too? I heard that you were involved in the development of medical technology at Rhodes Island. Heheh... You may be what we researchers have been waiting for.

char_108_silent_CN_010.voiceText: ...Doctor, did you fall asleep? All right. Leave the rest of the work to me.

char_108_silent_CN_011.voiceText: I am Olivia Silence, an Originium scientist from the Rhine Lab Medical Research Institute. My hope is to rid the world of Oripathy... even if it means risking my life in the process.

char_108_silent_CN_012.voiceText: I will make good use of this new power.

char_108_silent_CN_013.voiceText: Is my medicine effective? Wonderful. This news brings me even greater joy than my promotion.

char_108_silent_CN_014.voiceText: Doctor, I am looking forward to the day when the world is finally cured of Oripathy. In fighting and studying with you, I think that day may not be far off.

char_108_silent_CN_018.voiceText: Come on, team, let's fight with all our might.

char_108_silent_CN_019.voiceText: Is Originium to be blamed for this battle?

char_108_silent_CN_020.voiceText: Observe and determine the form of Infection. Such data will be useful for my experiments.

char_108_silent_CN_029.voiceText: In order to defeat stronger enemies, must we make further use of Originium's power...?

char_108_silent_CN_030.voiceText: Medical team, please take tissue samples from the Infected, we need to see the composition of the Infection in this area.

char_108_silent_CN_031.voiceText: All wounded personnel, please remain calm. The medical team will get to you.

char_108_silent_CN_032.voiceText: ...Now is not the time for despair. We must withdraw immediately.

char_108_silent_CN_033.voiceText: This room... No, this design makes me sleepy!

char_134_ifrit_CN_001.voiceText: Why is this office so damn cold?! Hey, I'mma burn it down, alright?

char_134_ifrit_CN_002.voiceText: Huh? Is this book expensive? Heehee. Call me Mistress Ifrit and I'll give it back to you!

char_134_ifrit_CN_003.voiceText: What? You want me to read this book? What I hate most is... What? Did... did Silence say so? Um... How... How is this word pronounced?

char_134_ifrit_CN_004.voiceText: I hate it when those dumbasses in white coats stare at me... Yeah, that means you! Jackass! Cut it out! Go stare at someone else!

char_134_ifrit_CN_005.voiceText: Um... I know! I won't scare people with fire anymore!

char_134_ifrit_CN_006.voiceText: Back down! You... Why are you getting so close to me? Are you going to put me on the lab table as well...?

char_134_ifrit_CN_007.voiceText: Saria's here? Let me talk to- Silence said I can't? C'mon, what's the big deal? Bring me to her and just keep it off the record!

char_134_ifrit_CN_008.voiceText: What's going on between Silence and Saria? I don't understand... Hey! You know how to get them to make up? Tell me... won't you?

char_134_ifrit_CN_009.voiceText: You can do whatever you like with me, but you better well be nice to Silence. When she wants something, you go get it for her! Do that, and I'll follow your orders from this day forward!

char_134_ifrit_CN_010.voiceText: You piece of...! Who said you could ignore me and take a goddamn nap?!

char_134_ifrit_CN_011.voiceText: You're in the presence of Ifrit! Silence told me Rhodes Island's a nice place, but I absolutely hate white-coat scientists like you people... well, Silence is an exception...

char_134_ifrit_CN_012.voiceText: Enhancing? Hmm, you mean you can make my flames burn brighter?

char_134_ifrit_CN_013.voiceText: What's this? Promotion Manual for Rhodes Island Operators? What the hell? Why are there so many rules after promotion? Screw this!

char_134_ifrit_CN_014.voiceText: Hee hee. That's right! I don't give a damn about those rules. All I know is that you need my help!

char_134_ifrit_CN_018.voiceText: I'm the captain? So, just do like Silence would, right?

char_134_ifrit_CN_019.voiceText: Hey! I'm the captain, which means I'M giving the orders here!

char_134_ifrit_CN_020.voiceText: Yo, how about a fiery barbecue!

char_134_ifrit_CN_024.voiceText: Hell loaded and ready to fire!

char_134_ifrit_CN_025.voiceText: Does it hurt? I bet it does!

char_134_ifrit_CN_027.voiceText: Nobody can hear you scream for help!

char_134_ifrit_CN_029.voiceText: I need more! Much more! I am invincible!

char_134_ifrit_CN_030.voiceText: I'll gladly burn those walking bags of trash into ash. It's gonna be real warm!

char_134_ifrit_CN_031.voiceText: Nothing but cinders left now. I could've done the job single-handedly!

char_134_ifrit_CN_032.voiceText: Damn... You... It's you who made me look stupid!

char_134_ifrit_CN_034.voiceText: What are you doing!? Let go of me!

char_134_ifrit_CN_036.voiceText: Heheh, you're surprisingly nice. Wanna play a game?

char_202_demkni_CN_001.voiceText: I've checked your schedule. Isn't it time you took a break? If you'll excuse me.

char_202_demkni_CN_002.voiceText: Evolution is the law of nature. But Rhine Lab attempted to tamper with this law, even to take control of it. What a foolish endeavor…

char_202_demkni_CN_003.voiceText: As a researcher, have you ever participated in some experiments you probably shouldn't have? No? That's good.

char_202_demkni_CN_004.voiceText: Don't you think it's too noisy at Rhodes Island? Everyone should be quiet and focused during work. You should enforce discipline on your subordinates.

char_202_demkni_CN_005.voiceText: My true power has nothing to do with first aid. However, I have slightly adjusted the operation of this power to accommodate it to your command.

char_202_demkni_CN_006.voiceText: You think Calcification Arts only makes organisms weaker? You're wrong. I can condense calcium into a tough enamel. The enemies can try as they want, but no one can break my shield.

char_202_demkni_CN_007.voiceText: You've seen me arguing with Silence? Yes, we do that a lot... Sorry for causing trouble for you and Rhodes Island

char_202_demkni_CN_008.voiceText: Please tell Ifrit on my behalf, 'No matter what happens, I will protect you'... Meet her? No, I'm not ready for that.

char_202_demkni_CN_009.voiceText: Even in the most desperate of situations, one must stand fast to be a symbol of strength for the people they hold dear. That is where I draw my line and how I live my life. You'll do the same, won't you?

char_202_demkni_CN_010.voiceText: I'll go back to my room if there's no further assignments.

char_202_demkni_CN_011.voiceText: I am Saria, formerly of the Rhine Lab Medical Research Institute Experiment Team. As for now... I need Rhodes Island's help to bring the astray back to the orthodox.

char_202_demkni_CN_013.voiceText: Good, you must continue motivating your subordinates with your ideas if you hope to maintain influence over them.

char_202_demkni_CN_014.voiceText: Promotion? I don't want any special treatment. But for Ifrit's sake, I do need your help to correct all those twisted laws and rules.

char_202_demkni_CN_017.voiceText: I am within my rights to oversee and bring up my own opinion on your command.

char_202_demkni_CN_018.voiceText: Send me the operation briefing, I will review it.

char_202_demkni_CN_019.voiceText: All operators must maintain strict discipline.

char_202_demkni_CN_020.voiceText: Are they the ones who caused such destruction and started all this conflict?

char_202_demkni_CN_025.voiceText: Just who are you weaklings going to stop like that?

char_202_demkni_CN_029.voiceText: Your tactics appear modern, yet the ideas behind them are primitive at their roots. Just who are you?

char_202_demkni_CN_030.voiceText: All must return to the existing order. None may disobey the rules.

char_202_demkni_CN_031.voiceText: The routed enemies may be calling for reinforcements. We must not drop our guard before we find the last of them.

char_202_demkni_CN_033.voiceText: This room has interesting decor. I'd be more fond of a futuristic style, though.

char_202_demkni_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, you might do a bit of research into the past in your free time. You will find many a thing of great interest.

char_128_plosis_CN_001.voiceText: Greetings Doctor. How may I assist you?

char_128_plosis_CN_002.voiceText: Deep Sleep Mode enabled... Zzzzz... Setting advanced config and power interface... Zzzzz…

char_128_plosis_CN_003.voiceText: My racial traits, in conjunction with my infection, may cause me to fall asleep in mid-conversation. Do not be alarmed.

char_128_plosis_CN_004.voiceText: I met Dr. Silence at Rhine Lab. I assisted her with data and risk analysis on a secret project.

char_128_plosis_CN_005.voiceText: Warning! Formatting Rhodes Island database... Don't worry. It's just a joke. Please don't panic.

char_128_plosis_CN_006.voiceText: I recommend you refactor my data if optimization fails to increase my performance. This will improve communication efficiency, and Ptilopsis will... Zzzz...

char_128_plosis_CN_007.voiceText: The way I speak? It is a side effect of Originium poisoning. By no means do I enjoy articulating my thoughts this way.

char_128_plosis_CN_008.voiceText: Warning, system has recovered from a fatal error. Reconfiguring to last normal system boot point. Do not be alarmed.

char_128_plosis_CN_009.voiceText: It is, in fact, quite burdensome to speak in this manner. But this is a necessary measure to prevent the system nexus from being devoured by that other voice. Doctor, if I lose control, please guide me back onto the right path.

char_128_plosis_CN_010.voiceText: System... is now in Sleep Mode...

char_128_plosis_CN_011.voiceText: I am Ptilopsis, former data analyst at Rhine Lab. Please submit your orders via the Command Line.

char_128_plosis_CN_013.voiceText: Update installation complete. Ptilopsis's system permissions have been revised.

char_128_plosis_CN_014.voiceText: Warning. Reverting Rhodes Island database to previous save state. Time since save state: two years… Just joking. Please calm down. System update complete.

char_128_plosis_CN_017.voiceText: New data used to assemble package build.

char_128_plosis_CN_019.voiceText: Direct memory access for application map and enemy coordinates authorized. Please stand by.

char_128_plosis_CN_029.voiceText: Even such a challenging scenario couldn't stop you, Doctor. Perhaps one day you will find the solution to the non-deterministic polynomial time problem.

char_128_plosis_CN_030.voiceText: Your logical deduction was absolutely correct. What a perfect calculation.

char_128_plosis_CN_031.voiceText: A number of errors have been detected. Please confirm.

char_128_plosis_CN_032.voiceText: A fatal error occurred during the operation. Reboot the system to proceed.

char_128_plosis_CN_033.voiceText: Is this place like a disk array?

char_128_plosis_CN_036.voiceText: Detecting affection increase for the Doctor within Ptilopsis. Would you like to skip to the next dialogue choice?

char_128_plosis_CN_042.voiceText: Date rollover complete. The Doctor is now online. Detecting emotional surge within Ptilopsis.

char_242_otter_CN_001.voiceText: Structural design, industrial R&D, scientific research. You name it, and I can do it, Doctor.

char_242_otter_CN_002.voiceText: The Engineering Department never approve my proposals. Do they have any bias toward me? What should I do... Oh! Actually, Doctor, would you please submit this suggestion on improvement for me? It's a deal then!

char_242_otter_CN_003.voiceText: There are many workshops like mine in Rhine Lab, but what takes others six weeks to finish, I can have it done in one. I'm not boasting!

char_242_otter_CN_004.voiceText: DO NOT interrupt me when I'm doing my research, or I'll have my Meeboos bite you! And I will bite you too!

char_242_otter_CN_005.voiceText: At night I'm always full of inspiration... and the… urgency to sleep! No, I can't bear it... Where's the pillow... I need to rest...

char_242_otter_CN_006.voiceText: Hm? Why are these cuties called Meeboos? That's because they go 'meeee-boooo' when they boot up. So I named them after that. Fitting, don't you think? Just listen and you'll get it. You press this switch to... NONONONO, That's the self-destruct button! Ahhhhhh run！

char_242_otter_CN_007.voiceText: That girl who just passed by... that was Silence, right? If only back then... Oh, sorry, the non-disclosure agreement is still in effect. I should keep my mouth shut.

char_242_otter_CN_008.voiceText: I feel kinda empty when I've got nothing to do... I guess that's just how engineers are. I bet even you have to idle your time away on occasion, Doctor. Huh? You don't?

char_242_otter_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, may I request... No! Not 10 square meters! I asked for too much last time, so this time... all I need is 3! W-Wait! Don't leave yet! 1 square meter, just 1 more for my research will do! Please, Doctor, I'm begging you...

char_242_otter_CN_010.voiceText: Geez... where's the coffeemaker... Oh, there it is... You want some too, Doctor?

char_242_otter_CN_011.voiceText: Lutra Workshop of Rhine Lab, at your service. Yup, I run the workshop on my own. No assistance needed. Amazing, right?

char_242_otter_CN_012.voiceText: This structure... Interesting. I'll look into it.

char_242_otter_CN_013.voiceText: This raise came just in time! I can afford to upgrade my equipment now.

char_242_otter_CN_014.voiceText: I promised that you'd not be disappointed. Now look what I have! Surely kept my end of the bargain, didn't I?

char_242_otter_CN_018.voiceText: Commanding both Operators and my Meeboos at the same time is a bit much even for me...

char_242_otter_CN_019.voiceText: Hopefully we can get some useful experiment data!

char_242_otter_CN_020.voiceText: Come on, Meeboo, show them what Rhine Lab's technology can do!

char_242_otter_CN_027.voiceText: If anything breaks, just make another one!

char_242_otter_CN_028.voiceText: My Meeboos are more than just machines!

char_242_otter_CN_029.voiceText: Come on, Meeboo! Show everyone your victory dance!

char_242_otter_CN_030.voiceText: Nice! We practically rolled over them!

char_242_otter_CN_031.voiceText: The device is slightly damaged. I'll fix it in no time.

char_242_otter_CN_032.voiceText: Oh no! My Meeboo...! I'll need to make more...

char_242_otter_CN_033.voiceText: Now I want a new workshop!

char_242_otter_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, let me touch your head! Inspiration can strike, you know!

char_215_mantic_CN_001.voiceText: Umm... I've been here... for two hours now...

char_215_mantic_CN_002.voiceText: Sorry... it doesn't really feel like I'm here... But that's not because of my power...

char_215_mantic_CN_003.voiceText: My power is to... become undetectable to people... in certain environments...

char_215_mantic_CN_004.voiceText: I've never had any friends... I mean, who wants a friend that they can't even see...

char_215_mantic_CN_005.voiceText: My tail... will curl up when out of battle... So don't be afraid...

char_215_mantic_CN_006.voiceText: Doctor... leave the dangerous work to me... After all... my power was made for that...

char_215_mantic_CN_007.voiceText: I collected these... ID tags I have around my neck... Holding onto such proof of other people's existence... is something... I enjoy...

char_215_mantic_CN_008.voiceText: Don't let that girl named 'Nightmare' near me... She's... dangerous... My power... doesn't work on her... Why...

char_215_mantic_CN_009.voiceText: I... I really want to cure my illness. However, I'm afraid... to lose my power... if I am cured... Will I still be of use then...?

char_215_mantic_CN_010.voiceText: I hate the loneliness... of being ignored...

char_215_mantic_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Manticore... My power is to kill people silently... Don't be afraid, you're not... my target...

char_215_mantic_CN_012.voiceText: Thank you... And please, keep me company...

char_215_mantic_CN_013.voiceText: I've waited for this promotion... I always thought... that my power wasn't good enough...

char_215_mantic_CN_014.voiceText: I'm... helpful to you... right? I don't have anywhere else to go... My home is here... at Rhodes Island... Please... let me protect it with you...

char_215_mantic_CN_018.voiceText: Nobody will like me... as their captain...

char_215_mantic_CN_020.voiceText: Please use tactics that utilize my power... even if it's a cowardly one... I don't mind...

char_215_mantic_CN_027.voiceText: I don't... like doing this... either...

char_215_mantic_CN_029.voiceText: Even on such a terrifying battlefield... you kept a clear head and made good decisions. You're awesome, Doctor...!

char_215_mantic_CN_030.voiceText: I'll do whatever it takes to win... I suppose...

char_215_mantic_CN_031.voiceText: Let me take care of... the ones that got away...

char_215_mantic_CN_032.voiceText: I'm sorry... It's all my fault...

char_215_mantic_CN_036.voiceText: Thank you for paying attention to me... I know it's your duty... but it still makes me happy...!

char_149_scave_CN_001.voiceText: Better to get your job done first than wasting time on chitchat.

char_149_scave_CN_002.voiceText: You'd better remember that failing to adapt makes you a useless burden.

char_149_scave_CN_003.voiceText: Work, eat, run, repeat. Big fricking whoop. Isn't that how life is for anyone these days?

char_149_scave_CN_004.voiceText: My job was to take care of 'troubles' for my employers. Eventually they started to call me Scavenger.

char_149_scave_CN_005.voiceText: Just like the two sides of a coin, no matter how splendid the face is, the backside is always stained with dirt.

char_149_scave_CN_006.voiceText: I've adapted to this place really well since I joined? Pfft, rubbish. It's just that I've gotten used to working on the surface.

char_149_scave_CN_007.voiceText: That's Provence, isn't it…? The wretched girl who got Infected while rescuing people from a Catastrophe... Look at that massive tail she's got...

char_149_scave_CN_008.voiceText: You know, Doctor... I hated the idea of working with other people, at first. I figured our methods would clash. But at some point, I came to realize that's not the case.

char_149_scave_CN_009.voiceText: If only she were still alive... Now all I can do is carry on alone, carrying her dreams on my back.

char_149_scave_CN_010.voiceText: How can you sleep so soundly when you're defenseless…?

char_149_scave_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Scavenger. Leave the dirty work to me. Just pay me like my other employers and we'll be good.

char_149_scave_CN_013.voiceText: This still isn't enough. I need to become stronger...

char_149_scave_CN_014.voiceText: Thanks, Doctor. I feel like I have a reason to fight now.

char_149_scave_CN_017.voiceText: Do I need to quip just 'cause I joined the team?

char_149_scave_CN_019.voiceText: Conceal yourselves so the enemy won't find you.

char_149_scave_CN_020.voiceText: Hmph, time for a clean up.

char_149_scave_CN_027.voiceText: There is no turning back for you!

char_149_scave_CN_029.voiceText: Gotta say that mission was a special one.

char_149_scave_CN_030.voiceText: Hmph. They have only their own weakness to blame.

char_149_scave_CN_031.voiceText: Tch, some of them got away. I'm disappointed in you.

char_149_scave_CN_033.voiceText: Just give me a dark corner.

char_149_scave_CN_036.voiceText: What? You want me to dispose of you too?

char_149_scave_CN_042.voiceText: You got a job for me?

char_204_platnm_CN_001.voiceText: *Yaaawn*... Doctor, could I take a quick break?

char_204_platnm_CN_002.voiceText: Don't worry about my bow. I keep it well maintained. It's much tougher than you, so stop asking about it already.

char_204_platnm_CN_003.voiceText: There are so many interesting people at Rhodes Island. Would be nice if I could make a friend or two to travel with.

char_204_platnm_CN_004.voiceText: Nowadays, the Knights of Kazimierz are little more than a bunch of musclehead jocks, or clowns obsessed with billboards and firework shows. Man, it's so lame.

char_204_platnm_CN_005.voiceText: I was planning to return home after finishing this job, but now I've changed my mind. Why, you ask? You should know better than to ask a girl a question like that.

char_204_platnm_CN_006.voiceText: Want to know the origin of my codename? You see, there are different ranks for the Knight Assassins in Kazimierz. There's three Darksteel and two Lazurite assassins above me, but I and I alone bear the rank of Platinum, from now till the day I die. So I figured it'd make a good codename.

char_204_platnm_CN_007.voiceText: Ah, it's Miss Nearl! No, no, I wasn't going to lay a hand on her. I'm just worried she's going to charge at me with her hammer.

char_204_platnm_CN_008.voiceText: Kazimierz is... a boring place. *Sigh*, I'm almost mad at how much more amusing life here at Rhodes Island is.

char_204_platnm_CN_009.voiceText: Have you thought about how you're going to maintain your relations with everyone here at Rhodes Island? You know, all suits of armor have small gaps which leave you vulnerable, and that's where the enemies always try to jam their blades. One hit to your weak point can bring down everything you've painstakingly built.

char_204_platnm_CN_010.voiceText: I'm so bored. Hoping something amusing happens.

char_204_platnm_CN_011.voiceText: Assassin of the Armorless Union of Kazimierz here as per our agreement. What am I called? Hmm... Call me Platinum, then. Nice to meet you.

char_204_platnm_CN_012.voiceText: Good. My bow feels even lighter. Thank you.

char_204_platnm_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion? Isn't the rank of Platinum already intimidating enough? Oh, you are an interesting one.

char_204_platnm_CN_014.voiceText: Hah. Do you have the guts to gaze upon the true face of the one called Platinum, my dear Doctor?

char_204_platnm_CN_018.voiceText: Really? I'm commanding? It's not my strongest suit, but all right.

char_204_platnm_CN_019.voiceText: Will this battle be an interesting one?

char_204_platnm_CN_020.voiceText: You may as well attack at the same time. You're all too weak anyway.

char_204_platnm_CN_029.voiceText: Nice. I had quite an enjoyable time.

char_204_platnm_CN_030.voiceText: Checkmate. I'm sorry, but victory is mine.

char_204_platnm_CN_031.voiceText: What a pity that we left some alive.

char_204_platnm_CN_032.voiceText: Don't give up... He who laughs last laughs best.

char_204_platnm_CN_033.voiceText: The atmosphere here is surprisingly good.

char_204_platnm_CN_036.voiceText: Want to go on a walk? If you're busy, there's always next time.

char_172_svrash_CN_001.voiceText: There are better ways to kill time. Care to try one?

char_172_svrash_CN_002.voiceText: Why the constant sullen face? Can't you at least smile for me? Good. That's what I want to see... Yes, there's no one better suited to solve your problems than me... Isn't that right?

char_172_svrash_CN_003.voiceText: That girl... Amiya, I believe her name was? She's no ordinary girl. If you don't put shackles on her wrists today, you will find yourself placing a crown upon her head tomorrow.

char_172_svrash_CN_004.voiceText: The stability of the alliance between Karlan and Rhodes Island depends solely on your state of mind, and mine. As such, we should at least try to get along, my friend.

char_172_svrash_CN_005.voiceText: I suppose... it's high time I signed this contract. Of course, I do know that the terms are in yours, and Rhodes Island's favor.

char_172_svrash_CN_006.voiceText: I'm well aware that this contract offers me nothing... But what does that matter? I shall nonetheless accept this unequal treaty. The reason being that I, SilverAsh, recognize that you warrant it.

char_172_svrash_CN_007.voiceText: Is Ensia giving you trouble? My apologies. It was originally my own responsibility to foster and guide her, but it's unlikely I will be able to do so. So I must ask... could you do it in my stead, {@nickname}?

char_172_svrash_CN_008.voiceText: Could you show me to Rhodes Island's deck? No, I'd just like to get a view of the area. Tenzin needs to spread his wings every once in a while as well. He must be longing to soar through the night sky.

char_172_svrash_CN_009.voiceText: If this continues, there will come a day when you and I confront one another... I seem delighted, you say? Hah, perhaps I am. You would be a worthy opponent, that's for certain. Let us make the most of our time before that day comes.

char_172_svrash_CN_010.voiceText: When the aether darkens, 'tis an omen that snowfall draws near...'

char_172_svrash_CN_011.voiceText: I, SilverAsh, have joined your cause as a sworn ally. Whatever your plans may be, do not disappoint me.

char_172_svrash_CN_012.voiceText: For one to travel such an arduous path, one absolutely must have experience.

char_172_svrash_CN_013.voiceText: Ostentatious titles are one thing, but the trust accompanying them is what concerns me. You surely know that.

char_172_svrash_CN_014.voiceText: It takes a daring soul to drag me into their war. That being so, I, SilverAsh, will show my prowess for all of Rhodes Island to see.

char_172_svrash_CN_017.voiceText: We all have our roles to play. Use my abilities as best you see fit.

char_172_svrash_CN_018.voiceText: You wish me to act as your proxy? Very well. But you must pay me due tribute later.

char_172_svrash_CN_019.voiceText: Compassion saves no one on the battlefield.

char_172_svrash_CN_020.voiceText: Show me what you're made of. Amuse me, if you even can.

char_172_svrash_CN_025.voiceText: 'The fool flaunting his gallantry reaches none with his vanity...'

char_172_svrash_CN_026.voiceText: 'Fool, for what reason hast thou come?'

char_172_svrash_CN_027.voiceText: 'Art thou mine worthy enemy, or art thou naught but a jester?'

char_172_svrash_CN_029.voiceText: The fiercer the battle, the more jubilant the victory.

char_172_svrash_CN_030.voiceText: A satisfying battle. It brought palpitations even to my heart.

char_172_svrash_CN_032.voiceText: Retreat at once, while there is still time.

char_172_svrash_CN_033.voiceText: For a place to rest my feet, it is acceptable.

char_172_svrash_CN_036.voiceText: Let me rest for a brief while. I'm more tired than I thought. My apologies.

char_172_svrash_CN_042.voiceText: You haven't changed one bit, my friend.

char_173_slchan_CN_001.voiceText: Uh... Doctor, you really need to work out more, you know.

char_173_slchan_CN_002.voiceText: Everyone's really nice here at Rhodes Island. Too nice to prank. Oh, is it time for lunch? I'll help!

char_173_slchan_CN_003.voiceText: Mountaineering's not just a hobby of mine, it's my career! You heard me: career!

char_173_slchan_CN_004.voiceText: The hoop on my leg? Oh, you mean what it's for? It's just for decoration. I've got this crystal over here, see. Wanna touch?

char_173_slchan_CN_005.voiceText: My brother sent Matterhorn to look after me, didn't he…? Ugh, why can't he just come out and tell me what he's thinking? It drives me mad.

char_173_slchan_CN_006.voiceText: I've always wanted to climb the holy Mt. Karlan, and I've only wanted it even more since my sister left us and became the Saintess. So Doctor, train me more, yeah? So one day I can reach the peak of Mt. Karlan and bring my sister home.

char_173_slchan_CN_007.voiceText: When it comes to Mountaineering, I won't lose to anyone! No one knows these tools better than me. They make great weapons too!

char_173_slchan_CN_008.voiceText: Yeah, Oripathy really changed me. But if I keep wallowing in self-pity, that wouldn't be like me, right? So, no matter what lies in wait in the future... I should continue working hard on my chosen path.

char_173_slchan_CN_009.voiceText: Ah, it's snowing... We Silverashes can't go back to the way we were... I get that. Everything's changed. Only the snow is the same—the same snowflakes that I watched falling back home.

char_173_slchan_CN_010.voiceText: Doctoooor? Doctooooor! Heeeey! Fine, if you're just gonna sleep, then so be it. Bye-bye!

char_173_slchan_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Cliffheart, and I live to conquer the peaks! It's nice to meet you!

char_173_slchan_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion? Wow! Let's celebrate with some cake. Look, I grabbed these from Logistics. It's fine!

char_173_slchan_CN_014.voiceText: Well, well, you really know what you're doing, Doctor! That's right, I'm really talented. You'd better use my power well!

char_173_slchan_CN_017.voiceText: All right? I'm feeling motivated! Time to climb all the way to the top!

char_173_slchan_CN_018.voiceText: Eh? You want me to lead? This is all so sudden...

char_173_slchan_CN_019.voiceText: Say goodbye to the reckless Cliffheart. I'm taking things seriously from here on out.

char_173_slchan_CN_020.voiceText: I'll show them what I can do!

char_173_slchan_CN_026.voiceText: My hook never misses! I've got this!

char_173_slchan_CN_027.voiceText: Amateurs are doomed to fall to their death!

char_173_slchan_CN_029.voiceText: There ain't no mountain too high, no situation too bleak!

char_173_slchan_CN_030.voiceText: Of course we won with me around!

char_173_slchan_CN_031.voiceText: Wow, they sure are good at running away!

char_173_slchan_CN_033.voiceText: It's so warm here... I'll hang out over here for a while!

char_173_slchan_CN_036.voiceText: I'm gonna teach you all about Mountaineering next time, Doctor! You'll love it, I promise!

char_174_slbell_CN_001.voiceText: Hm? You're here to pray? Sorry, I'm busy right now.

char_174_slbell_CN_002.voiceText: Hm? Yes, I'm the current Karlan Saintess. But everyone swamped by work deserves a little break from time to time, don't you think?

char_174_slbell_CN_003.voiceText: Wasting time on trivial affairs is what I call slacking off. What I'm doing right now is… taking the opportunity to recharge.

char_174_slbell_CN_004.voiceText: Work hard, play hard, right? Don't force all those rigid rules on me.

char_174_slbell_CN_005.voiceText: The Karlan Goddess? We share a good relationship, thanks to my duty as the Saintess.

char_174_slbell_CN_006.voiceText: I'd be happy to help you, but the life of a Karlan Saintess is a busy one. Well, I guess I'll make an exception for you this once, but please make it short.

char_174_slbell_CN_007.voiceText: My sis... Ensia... you people at Rhodes Island are all pretty fond of her, right? So it's not like she received any special treatment from that guy. And now... well, I think I get it now. It's fine like this. I'll just keep watching over her. It's fine.

char_174_slbell_CN_008.voiceText: I twisted my ankle once when I was a kid. My brother carried me on his back all night, going from house to house until someone agreed to take us in. I decided that very moment that I wanted to grow up to become someone like my brother! But now... heh, forget it.

char_174_slbell_CN_009.voiceText: Huh? How did you find me? I'll freeze your toes—Um? Coffee? For me? Thanks. Oh, right, Doctor, wanna hang out here with me for a while? The view is pretty nice. But let's keep it a secret, okay? A secret between just the two of us—aw, this coffee is so bitter!

char_174_slbell_CN_010.voiceText: It's rare to get to rest like this.

char_174_slbell_CN_011.voiceText: Shh, I sneaked out—oh, um, hi, HR Director! I... I'm here to lend my powers to Rhodes Island. Pramanix, Karlan Saintess, at your service. Bless you, my friend.

char_174_slbell_CN_012.voiceText: I hear a voice... repeating something in my head...

char_174_slbell_CN_013.voiceText: 'You shall emerge victorious one day.' This is the pledge of Karlan, and what I'm praying for as well.

char_174_slbell_CN_014.voiceText: Since when did you need blessings too? Can you wait a bit? I'll get ready.

char_174_slbell_CN_017.voiceText: May the Holy Mt. Karlan be with us.

char_174_slbell_CN_018.voiceText: Follow the bells and you'll find the way.

char_174_slbell_CN_019.voiceText: Let me pray towards the mountains for you.

char_174_slbell_CN_026.voiceText: Here come the bells, cold winds binding my enemies.

char_174_slbell_CN_027.voiceText: These powers are a gift from the Holy Mountain.

char_174_slbell_CN_028.voiceText: As the bells ring, the impenetrable armor shall be no more.

char_174_slbell_CN_029.voiceText: It was simple, thanks to the Spirits' power.

char_174_slbell_CN_030.voiceText: The light of Karlan was shining on us.

char_174_slbell_CN_031.voiceText: If only we could have won without bloodshed... just my wish...

char_174_slbell_CN_032.voiceText: It's not looking good... I suggest we retreat at once.

char_174_slbell_CN_036.voiceText: Close your eyes and I'll bring you somewhere new... Do keep your eyes closed, okay?

char_198_blackd_CN_001.voiceText: It's not the duty of a guard to stand here and do nothing. Why don't we chat a bit?

char_198_blackd_CN_002.voiceText: With perfect positioning and a suitable environment, my letters will arrive just fine. After all, it's my job, right? I need to do well to survive.

char_198_blackd_CN_003.voiceText: Are you hungry? If you want something to eat, just say the word. I can't compete with Matterhorn in the kitchen, but I can at least cook a decent meal.

char_198_blackd_CN_004.voiceText: The comms equipment here at Rhodes Island is way too good. At this rate, I'm going to lose my job...

char_198_blackd_CN_005.voiceText: Anything else you need? Just don't keep me on the line for too long.

char_198_blackd_CN_006.voiceText: Huh? There's a faint smell on the letters? No, you must be imagining things.

char_198_blackd_CN_007.voiceText: I owe my life to Master SilverAsh. If necessary, I would do anything for him.

char_198_blackd_CN_008.voiceText: You want me to transport... all these? That's a lot, Doctor! Come on, I'm not a miracle worker!

char_198_blackd_CN_009.voiceText: Seems I'm no match for you. I suppose it's time to retire my business smile for now... *Ahem*... I'd like to show you my true face, from now on.

char_198_blackd_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, there's a new message for... Ah, never mind.

char_198_blackd_CN_011.voiceText: Esteemed Leader of Rhodes Island, your ally—Courier of the Snow Realm—is here at your service. If you get into any sort of trouble during your contract with Master SilverAsh, just snap your fingers and I'll be there.

char_198_blackd_CN_012.voiceText: Whoa, that's an incredible job well done.

char_198_blackd_CN_013.voiceText: You'd save a lot of trouble if you sent me onto the battlefield.

char_198_blackd_CN_014.voiceText: As a Messenger of the Snow Realm, I'm sure to appear whenever you need me.

char_198_blackd_CN_018.voiceText: I won't blemish the name of the Snow Realm.

char_198_blackd_CN_019.voiceText: Too bad some people just can't live and let live.

char_198_blackd_CN_020.voiceText: They'll pay for what they've done.

char_198_blackd_CN_029.voiceText: I'll bring news of our victory to Rhodes Island right away!

char_198_blackd_CN_030.voiceText: Let's grab a nice dinner after we clean up the battlefield. My treat!

char_198_blackd_CN_031.voiceText: Anyone injured? I've got medicine and bandages.

char_198_blackd_CN_032.voiceText: Let's get out of here first. Here, this way! Hurry!

char_198_blackd_CN_033.voiceText: I'll greet my roommates and neighbors first.

char_198_blackd_CN_036.voiceText: Alright, I'll whip up a meal for you later.

char_198_blackd_CN_042.voiceText: Call me whenever you need me.

char_199_yak_CN_001.voiceText: I've moved your belongings where you wanted. No worries, it wasn't heavy.

char_199_yak_CN_002.voiceText: The shield is a symbol of a steadfast guardian.

char_199_yak_CN_003.voiceText: I've been responsible for protecting Young Master SilverAsh... I mean, Master SilverAsh... ever since he was young.

char_199_yak_CN_004.voiceText: It's not exactly polite to talk about Miss Enya behind her back, but... *sigh* I do pity Miss Enya for what she has suffered. She really deserves a better life.

char_199_yak_CN_005.voiceText: If my shield gets damaged, I should take it to the artisan called Vulcan for repairs. Is that correct?

char_199_yak_CN_006.voiceText: This is far beyond my expectation. That artisan is truly skilled. I need to thank her properly.

char_199_yak_CN_007.voiceText: Life at Rhodes Island is fun. The Snow Realm is rather bland in comparison.

char_199_yak_CN_008.voiceText: Master did send me to protect Ensia. But I honestly don't think she's the type who would sit there and ask to be protected.

char_199_yak_CN_009.voiceText: I am slowly starting to understand why Master SilverAsh holds you in such high regard. Doctor, from this day, feel free to command me as your shield.

char_199_yak_CN_010.voiceText: Sometimes, I suddenly start missing my life in the Snow Realm.

char_199_yak_CN_011.voiceText: Ally, I salute you in true Snow Realm fashion. My codename is Matterhorn, and I am one of the guards dispatched here by Master SilverAsh.

char_199_yak_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you for the approval, Doctor. I am greatly flattered.

char_199_yak_CN_014.voiceText: I will not step back, not even if this shield shatters the very next second. Not because of my loyalty, but because of my conviction.

char_199_yak_CN_026.voiceText: I'm not here just for show!

char_199_yak_CN_027.voiceText: With my conviction, I shall bring any monster to its knees!

char_199_yak_CN_028.voiceText: You don't have what it takes!

char_199_yak_CN_029.voiceText: I wasn't even giving my all!

char_199_yak_CN_030.voiceText: Their strikes can barely tickle me.

char_199_yak_CN_031.voiceText: I'll pull off a perfect victory next time for you, I promise.

char_199_yak_CN_032.voiceText: I should not have taken the enemies lightly. Now I pay the price.

char_199_yak_CN_033.voiceText: Very nice room, this one. Furnished tastefully, with a peaceful atmosphere.

char_199_yak_CN_036.voiceText: This is my signature dish. How do you like it?

char_219_meteo_CN_001.voiceText: It's time for my shift. If I'm interrupting your work, I can wait outside.

char_219_meteo_CN_002.voiceText: Have you gone through every new operator's personnel files and info?

char_219_meteo_CN_003.voiceText: Nowhere in the world is completely safe with a war going on. Not even Rhodes Island. Please remember that.

char_219_meteo_CN_004.voiceText: To be frank, you're surrounded by people from all walks of life. That can be quite dangerous, don't you think?

char_219_meteo_CN_005.voiceText: I'm surprised that so many other Sarkaz have come to Rhodes Island. What's more surprising is that they actually get along…

char_219_meteo_CN_006.voiceText: My bowgun may not be easy to operate, but it's just as powerful as the Laterano guns. I use it to defend the glory of my people.

char_219_meteo_CN_007.voiceText: I see Firewatch is here. I can't believe she's using the name of our old guerrilla group as her codename. It's like time stopped for her the day her home was destroyed...

char_219_meteo_CN_008.voiceText: As for what happened between Firewatch and I... she'll tell you when she's ready. All I can say is that I was not the one who led the rebels to her village... but no one would believe the words of a Sarkaz, right?

char_219_meteo_CN_009.voiceText: She wants her revenge, and I have my duty. Even though we've met again at Rhodes Island, it probably won't affect anything. Our paths aren't likely to cross.

char_219_meteo_CN_010.voiceText: What's that sound? Is someone monitoring this room? Or am I just… imagining things?

char_219_meteo_CN_011.voiceText: Codename Meteorite, a freelance mercenary. I'm Sarkaz, as you can see. Do you still want to hire me?

char_219_meteo_CN_012.voiceText: My aim with my bowgun has improved.

char_219_meteo_CN_013.voiceText: You want to promote me? I see that I made the right choice to work here.

char_219_meteo_CN_014.voiceText: Thank you so much for this, really. I can't believe someone like me could work a stable job here at Rhodes Island. I'll do everything I can to repay your trust in me.

char_219_meteo_CN_018.voiceText: Me, a leader? To be honest, I'm not that good at giving orders.

char_219_meteo_CN_019.voiceText: I'll do my best to take care of everyone.

char_219_meteo_CN_020.voiceText: Enemy status confirmed. All units, prepare to engage.

char_219_meteo_CN_029.voiceText: I don't want to see anything laid to waste in the fires of war ever again. Let us put an end to this, once and for all.

char_219_meteo_CN_030.voiceText: Trying to escape after I laid you to siege? Don't be silly.

char_219_meteo_CN_031.voiceText: Someone's escaped. Not the time to let our guard down.

char_219_meteo_CN_032.voiceText: Retreat! Back to the stronghold and regroup.

char_158_milu_CN_001.voiceText: I'm keeping an eye on our surroundings. So far everything seems fine.

char_158_milu_CN_002.voiceText: You should know that some of those eyes on you hold nothing but malice. You're not safe, not even at Rhodes Island.

char_158_milu_CN_003.voiceText: Don't be afraid of those hostiles hiding in the shadow. No matter how those criminals try to hide, they can't escape my eyes.

char_158_milu_CN_004.voiceText: I'll have my revenge... even if I must lose my life for it.

char_158_milu_CN_005.voiceText: My clan, my friends, they all perished in the woods of our hometown... The only ones who mourned them were the trees, which gave unto them their leaves.

char_158_milu_CN_006.voiceText: This crossbow is manufactured for the sole purpose of punishing sinners. The day will come when I use it to pass my final judgement on those who deserve it.

char_158_milu_CN_007.voiceText: Meteorite... we used to be friends. On the day my hometown was destroyed, we were part of the small group that managed to escape.

char_158_milu_CN_008.voiceText: Since then, I've never stopped searching for the traitor who led the rebel army to our town. Could it be Meteorite? No, I... It couldn't be her...

char_158_milu_CN_009.voiceText: ...Oh, did I fall asleep? Sorry, I've been spending more time patrolling these days... It's fine, you say? But... um, thank you for caring.

char_158_milu_CN_010.voiceText: I'd like to take a nap...

char_158_milu_CN_011.voiceText: Firewatch here. I'm a sniper. To avenge my fallen clan, I need all the power I can get.

char_158_milu_CN_013.voiceText: Thanks for appointing me to this position.

char_158_milu_CN_014.voiceText: Thank you for the promotion. I hope you'll keep using my powers for the right thing.If you don't, however...

char_158_milu_CN_029.voiceText: I'm not done until I have my revenge...

char_158_milu_CN_031.voiceText: Mission accomplished, request search for remaining hostiles.

char_158_milu_CN_033.voiceText: I'm not used to being in a room with so many people...

char_158_milu_CN_036.voiceText: Uh, please don't touch my antlers... it tickles...

char_115_headbr_CN_001.voiceText: I'm here to help. So? Whose ass are we kicking next?

char_115_headbr_CN_002.voiceText: You can't go out without permission? What? Aren't you the one in charge? Screw the rules, let's just get out.

char_115_headbr_CN_003.voiceText: You said something? My headphone was on.

char_115_headbr_CN_004.voiceText: The leader of Rhodes Island looks younger than even Istina. How can you let a kid like that go to battle? Huh?

char_115_headbr_CN_005.voiceText: Why do I stare at you all the time? 'cause I'm onto you, gotta see what you're doing.

char_115_headbr_CN_006.voiceText: Every soldier wants to be the general. And I trust you have no opinion on me taking your position?

char_115_headbr_CN_007.voiceText: Plans for the future? Don't have any. You got a problem with that? I'm still young, no need to plan ahead.

char_115_headbr_CN_008.voiceText: I found Istina and her gang along my travels. There are quiet a few of them. Where are the others, you ask? I dealt with them. Had no choice, they refused to behave themselves.

char_115_headbr_CN_009.voiceText: Huh? Chernobog? Who'd ever wanna go back to that miserable city? We've got new lives here at Rhodes Island. So, let's keep it together, Doctor.

char_115_headbr_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Zima, leader of the Ursus Student Self-Governing Group. I can make do without one, but my comrades need a place to call home. Let's cut the crap, gimme a job to do. I know lodging here ain't free.

char_115_headbr_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? Cool. So I'll keep getting promoted if I keep doing a good job knocking heads, yeah?

char_115_headbr_CN_014.voiceText: I'll be frank: if I keep getting promoted, I might end up replacing you someday. Oh, you think I'm joking? Sorry, pal, I'm dead serious here.

char_115_headbr_CN_017.voiceText: Don't care if I'm leading or following. Whatever.

char_115_headbr_CN_022.voiceText: I'm heading into the thick of it!

char_115_headbr_CN_025.voiceText: The hell are you afraid of?!

char_115_headbr_CN_029.voiceText: Who else has a death wish? No line over here!

char_115_headbr_CN_031.voiceText: Anyway, this place is ours now.

char_115_headbr_CN_032.voiceText: Man, you guys suck. Get lost!

char_115_headbr_CN_033.voiceText: What do you want me to do here?

char_115_headbr_CN_036.voiceText: Hey, you're getting better at giving orders these days. I bet you also see the fun in fighting now, eh?

char_195_glassb_CN_001.voiceText: Здравствыйте (Greetings), I'm here for my shift… That's a peculiar look on your face. Do I seem so unreliable?

char_195_glassb_CN_002.voiceText: We don't throw ourselves into battle because we want to. We just have a stronger will to survive than most. If you understand, that alone would be enough.

char_195_glassb_CN_003.voiceText: Zima, the girls, and I all came from different schools. But all the students in the city knew the legends of генерал Зима (General Zima). Doesn't that sound cool? Literally. Zima is Ursine for 'winter', you see. Hm, yes.

char_195_glassb_CN_004.voiceText: How did we escape from Chernobog? Hmm... you really don't want to know. Sometimes the truth is better left untold.
