char_195_glassb_CN_005.voiceText: Oh? I'm reading a mystery novel… As a matter of fact, it taught me some lessons that proved useful in getting me through that terrible time.

char_195_glassb_CN_006.voiceText: My favorite books? Hmm, I enjoy topics like politics, economics, and dialectical materialism… Baking magazines and stuff like that are nice too.

char_195_glassb_CN_007.voiceText: Home? Мой родной город (My hometown)? Obviously, we can't go back there. You know as well as I do that there's nothing left of it. Even if we rebuilt Chernobog, I still…

char_195_glassb_CN_008.voiceText: Rhodes Island is safe. And there are so many books here in your office... If I could, I'd really prefer to stay here…

char_195_glassb_CN_009.voiceText: What will I do in the future? Hmm… No idea. My books don't have an answer for that. I hope someone will give offer me one, someday…

char_195_glassb_CN_010.voiceText: Such a twist is beyond my imagination. 'Every last one of the passengers on this train, you're all murderers!'

char_195_glassb_CN_011.voiceText: I am Istina. I'm still a student, but I was recruited for my ability to use Arts… Да(Yes), it is rather strange for a student to serve here, isn't it?

char_195_glassb_CN_012.voiceText: You want me to be stronger?

char_195_glassb_CN_013.voiceText: Do you feel like you understand me better now? Наивный (Naive), you're far from really knowing me.

char_195_glassb_CN_014.voiceText: Now that you've offered me such recognition, I will reveal my true power. Allow me to demonstrate by reducing this office to a fine powder… Just kidding. There are too many precious books here. I would never do something so awful.

char_195_glassb_CN_018.voiceText: Hmm… The team is somewhat different from what I imagined.

char_195_glassb_CN_019.voiceText: Let's show our determination, earnestness, and boundless passion.

char_195_glassb_CN_020.voiceText: May the star of victory shine upon us.

char_195_glassb_CN_023.voiceText: I have a distaste for war.

char_195_glassb_CN_028.voiceText: Time to teach you a lesson.

char_195_glassb_CN_029.voiceText: Why do they fight... even when it may cost them their lives? What do they gain from it?

char_195_glassb_CN_030.voiceText: Doctor, if you have to commend us, now is the time.

char_195_glassb_CN_031.voiceText: Those enemies who fled... We probably won't see them again.

char_195_glassb_CN_032.voiceText: Neither our numbers nor our efforts were sufficient…

char_195_glassb_CN_033.voiceText: A secret room, where, shall we say, interesting things happen.

char_195_glassb_CN_036.voiceText: It's too noisy here, Я лучше почитаю в кабинет доктора (I'd rather read in the Doctor's office).

char_196_sunbr_CN_001.voiceText: Hey, Doctor! You hungry? I heard your stomach growling from a mile away! It sounded like thunder!

char_196_sunbr_CN_002.voiceText: My shield? I can lift it easily! Here we... go! There, look! Relax, I'm not gonna drop it or anything, so don't run away!

char_196_sunbr_CN_003.voiceText: Those baddies wreaking havoc in our city... unforgivable! I'll smash them with my frying pan!

char_196_sunbr_CN_004.voiceText: Zima said she'll protect me, but I don't need to be babysat! I kept everyone safe with my shield tons of times on our way to this place! What? This isn't a shield, it's a vault door? No it isnnnn't! I can't believe even you're calling it that!

char_196_sunbr_CN_005.voiceText: Doctor, you wanna have a taste of my cooking? Hehehe, soon you'll be able to. I asked Closure if I could take up duty in the cafeteria!

char_196_sunbr_CN_006.voiceText: Tadaaah! Here comes Gum's specialty: bacon and eggs! So, do you like it? Ehehehe! I can't control how rare it gets on the battlefield, but it normally turns out perfect!

char_196_sunbr_CN_007.voiceText: Me and the other 4 haven't always been a group, you know.

char_196_sunbr_CN_008.voiceText: Why am I always so cheery? Actually... after the things I've seen... how could I possibly be cheery... But I want my friends to forget about all that awful stuff, and I need to smile a whole bunch to make that happen!

char_196_sunbr_CN_009.voiceText: I... I miss my parents, and I do want to find them. I think about it all the time... but if I leave now, I don't think I can accomplish anything by myself... so... Doctor, could you please teach me to fight? I don't want to be known as the girl who spends all her time in the kitchen!

char_196_sunbr_CN_010.voiceText: Are you sleeping, Doctor? In that case it won't be considered slacking off if I sit around and read a bit, right?

char_196_sunbr_CN_011.voiceText: My name's Gummy! You must be the Doctor. Thank you and everyone from Rhodes Island for helping us! I don't have any special skills, but I'll do what I can as good as I can!

char_196_sunbr_CN_012.voiceText: I can feel my power surging! I might even be able to lift you up, Doctor!

char_196_sunbr_CN_013.voiceText: I'll become a three-star chef in Rhodes Island after the promotion, right? Haha, just kidding!

char_196_sunbr_CN_014.voiceText: I want to do much, much more besides cooking! I don't know if I'm strong enough to do everything you want me to, but I'll give it my all!

char_196_sunbr_CN_018.voiceText: Huh?! You're making me the leader?!

char_196_sunbr_CN_019.voiceText: You just wait for our return, Doctor!

char_196_sunbr_CN_029.voiceText: The enemy should just surrender! With the Doctor on our side, they'll never beat us!

char_196_sunbr_CN_030.voiceText: I don't want to do this... but if we don't fight, the enemy will hurt us!

char_196_sunbr_CN_031.voiceText: Yay! We won! I'm so happy!

char_196_sunbr_CN_032.voiceText: Ughh... I'll try to treat everyone's injuries... Doctor? Is the Doctor okay?!

char_196_sunbr_CN_033.voiceText: Wow, what a big room! It can fit so many people!

char_196_sunbr_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor! I know my food tastes great, but don't eat too much of it! You'll get fat!

char_196_sunbr_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor, you want something to eat?

char_147_shining_CN_001.voiceText: Greetings, Doctor... Is there anything you'd like to discuss?

char_147_shining_CN_002.voiceText: You look quite pale... You say your chest hurts? Don't overwork yourself, please get some rest. Don't be afraid, I'm right beside you. Everything will be okay...

char_147_shining_CN_003.voiceText: You've seen my healing Arts somewhere before?... That must have been your imagination. Yes, our memories do deceive us on occasion…

char_147_shining_CN_004.voiceText: 'Confessarius?' Where did you learn this word? My apologies, but I'm afraid I cannot continue this topic.

char_147_shining_CN_005.voiceText: We Sarkaz combined our inherent Arts affinity with the power of Originium to develop new healing Arts,  we've been doing this for quite some time to succour those who drag themselves in the mire.

char_147_shining_CN_006.voiceText: Now, you ask? Now we have nothing left. That war bereaved us of all hope.

char_147_shining_CN_007.voiceText: Who is Nearl to me? Well... She's a travel companion, and I trust her with my very life.

char_147_shining_CN_008.voiceText: There are those who will sacrifice their all to deliver others from their pain. And Nearl, she is just the kind.

char_147_shining_CN_009.voiceText: Once upon a time, I followed someone who shone bright as the beacon of hope, until wicked machinations took the light away. But this time, the incandescence will cease nevermore, even at the cost of my life...

char_147_shining_CN_010.voiceText: This quiet… it reminds me of my time back home.

char_147_shining_CN_011.voiceText: I am Shining, the roaming medic. I look familiar to you? It is possible our paths have crossed.

char_147_shining_CN_012.voiceText: The power to merely heal wounds... is not enough.

char_147_shining_CN_013.voiceText: A medic's hand cannot reach all those in need.

char_147_shining_CN_014.voiceText: Yes. I must be more than a medic—I will live on as a guardian. As has always been my goal. Doctor, please bear witness to my oath.

char_147_shining_CN_017.voiceText: To the battlefield, are we not?

char_147_shining_CN_018.voiceText: A battle for our own delieverence, is it not?

char_147_shining_CN_020.voiceText: May the war grant us the redemption we seek... or will it?

char_147_shining_CN_024.voiceText: 'Tis but a flash in the drift of time.

char_147_shining_CN_025.voiceText: Your life is mine to protect.

char_147_shining_CN_027.voiceText: Grief, ever echoes in our souls.

char_147_shining_CN_028.voiceText: Agony, ever etched on our hearts.

char_147_shining_CN_029.voiceText: Our wills and spirits are ever burning against the fiercest enemies.

char_147_shining_CN_030.voiceText: No matter the sins, all will fall to ashes with lives at the end of time.

char_147_shining_CN_031.voiceText: Return not to the battlefields. You will find no redemption here.

char_147_shining_CN_032.voiceText: Victory and loss... are insignificant moments in an endless cycle.

char_147_shining_CN_033.voiceText: I will be fine, so long as I have a quiet place to be alone.

char_147_shining_CN_036.voiceText: It's been some time since I've known such serenity. I can even hear your heartbeat.

char_147_shining_CN_042.voiceText: How are you feeling today, Doctor?

char_148_nearl_CN_001.voiceText: Salutations, Doctor. May the light be with you.

char_148_nearl_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor, I ask that you give me the most dangerous assignment available, such that my shield and I can best protect those in need.

char_148_nearl_CN_003.voiceText: The title of 'Knight' should be a symbol of honor. And yet now, it's been reduced to a mere commodity...

char_148_nearl_CN_004.voiceText: As long as the light continues to guide me, I will neither bow to cruelty nor kneel to violence.

char_148_nearl_CN_005.voiceText: I'm grateful as always for your service, Doctor.

char_148_nearl_CN_006.voiceText: The Kazimierz chivalric spirit should have been a force of salvation for all who suffer in this world. But now, it's nothing more than a rotten legacy, used to benefit the rich. Nothing is more shameful.

char_148_nearl_CN_007.voiceText: Shining, too, is a beam of light that guides me forward. She carries the hope I've long sought.

char_148_nearl_CN_008.voiceText: Something flickered in Shining's eyes when she heard the name Rhodes Island. I had no idea what it meant...

char_148_nearl_CN_009.voiceText: In this time and age of a world plagued by Oripathy, may the ray of hope from Rhodes Island light the way.

char_148_nearl_CN_010.voiceText: Let us embrace this momentary respite.

char_148_nearl_CN_011.voiceText: Margaret Nearl, the Radiant Knight of Kazimierz...and now a Rhodes Island Operator. I will defend your life and your honor with my shield.

char_148_nearl_CN_012.voiceText: Thank you for granting me power.

char_148_nearl_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you, Doctor. These new powers shall bring relief to those who suffer. This I shall engrave upon my heart.

char_148_nearl_CN_014.voiceText: Shining once said that dawn remains distant. But I believe that, one day, we will revive the dying glory with our very own hands.

char_148_nearl_CN_017.voiceText: I shall protect them from all harm.

char_148_nearl_CN_018.voiceText: I shall not blemish Rhodes Island's name.

char_148_nearl_CN_022.voiceText: I shall give my all to you.

char_148_nearl_CN_029.voiceText: A true knight will not bend to the threat of violence. Now, repent for your sins, in front of my warhammer.

char_148_nearl_CN_030.voiceText: Let us go forth. And there will be one day…

char_148_nearl_CN_031.voiceText: A true knight will not chase one who's lost the will to fight. Everyone deserves a chance to choose a new path.

char_148_nearl_CN_032.voiceText: We must not give up now.

char_148_nearl_CN_034.voiceText: I sense an intru- Oh, Doctor?!

char_148_nearl_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, umm... may I enter your office? I've heard you have a vast collection of literature.

char_179_cgbird_CN_001.voiceText: I apologize... It's my job to attend to you, but my body simply won't move like I want it to...

char_179_cgbird_CN_002.voiceText: I once breathed in some kind of Originium toxin... it damaged my memory and the nervous system in my lower extremities... at least that is what Dr. Kal'tsit told me. So I often wonder... what was my life like before then?

char_179_cgbird_CN_003.voiceText: This little blue bird often comes over and chats with me. Sometimes, I dream about turning into a bird myself... flying free in the skies, without a care...

char_179_cgbird_CN_004.voiceText: Once upon a time, I was imprisoned in an empty room. I only saw another human being when they needed my healing...

char_179_cgbird_CN_005.voiceText: With this staff in my hand, I can heal as many as I will. Is this... really an ability I was born with?

char_179_cgbird_CN_006.voiceText: Shining told me that the sins we carry... the guilt of starting the war, as devils... will one day catch up to us and we will have to face judgment. Those people who imprisoned me said the same thing. But...

char_179_cgbird_CN_007.voiceText: Amiya... I feel a sense of deja vu whenever I see her. Perhaps we met sometime in the past?

char_179_cgbird_CN_008.voiceText: The memories I have are mere fragments. My people... Originium... my mission, the rebellion, the war... but tell me, why are you in one of my memories too?

char_179_cgbird_CN_009.voiceText: How did I end up like this? Why must I suffer all that I do? Doctor, do you have the answers?

char_179_cgbird_CN_010.voiceText: Do you too dream of flying freely through the skies like a bird?

char_179_cgbird_CN_011.voiceText: Liz... that's my real name. Everything else is just cloudy, indistinct memories...

char_179_cgbird_CN_012.voiceText: Why is there a need for me to grow stronger?

char_179_cgbird_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? I see. It sounds like something to rejoice over. But... I apologize, I don't feel any joy within...

char_179_cgbird_CN_014.voiceText: Thank you for personally informing me of my promotion, Doctor. But... to me, it doesn't matter as much as the story of the world outside that this little bird is telling me right now.

char_179_cgbird_CN_018.voiceText: I shall do anything you command me to.

char_179_cgbird_CN_019.voiceText: I need only do as the manual said, yes?

char_179_cgbird_CN_020.voiceText: The battlefield... a place where lives are taken...

char_179_cgbird_CN_024.voiceText: It's not my wish to take lives.

char_179_cgbird_CN_025.voiceText: My power is all yours now.

char_179_cgbird_CN_027.voiceText: You will not come to harm.

char_179_cgbird_CN_029.voiceText: No matter how difficult the battle gets, I will always…

char_179_cgbird_CN_030.voiceText: To fight to the very end... that's our destiny.

char_179_cgbird_CN_031.voiceText: Perhaps they've already escaped this cage called fate...

char_179_cgbird_CN_033.voiceText: Rooms... They too are a type of cage.

char_179_cgbird_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor... is this... what is known as 'intimacy'?

char_112_siege_CN_001.voiceText: You're still not done assigning tasks? I'll wait a bit longer then.

char_112_siege_CN_003.voiceText: Our meals used to be fairly nice in the past... but the quality's gone downhill since we joined Indra's group.

char_112_siege_CN_004.voiceText: I had a dream... a dream where the sun rises, and in the distance beyond the horizon... there was my hometown. The place I might never get to return to, ever again.

char_112_siege_CN_005.voiceText: Before I knew it, I'd gotten accustomed to this drifter's life... It's a strange thing. In the past I never imagined this was how I'd end up.

char_112_siege_CN_006.voiceText: Gawain and company? I wouldn't say they ran into me, more like they picked me up off the streets.

char_112_siege_CN_007.voiceText: I used to stand side by side with Indra's team when we fought in the streets of Victoria... Looking back, I suppose it's a fairly fond memory to me.

char_112_siege_CN_008.voiceText: Stay on your guard! I know you've done the best you can, but there may be unknown dangers beyond our abilities.

char_112_siege_CN_009.voiceText: If we're ever put in a tough situation... then I may well act on my own motives. And if it comes to that, Doctor, I hope you'll join me too in... no, never mind for now.

char_112_siege_CN_010.voiceText: Hm? You fell asleep?... I wonder if you ever dream of your hometown, too.

char_112_siege_CN_011.voiceText: I've passed the strength test, right? So assign me some missions. Don't let this hammer get too bored. My codename? They call me the Siege. Curious name, but it's got a nice ring to it.

char_112_siege_CN_014.voiceText: Another promotion? All right, thanks... Life is strange like that, you know? Once upon a time, I was the one assigning new ranks to people.

char_112_siege_CN_017.voiceText: Tell me, is this battle inevitable?

char_112_siege_CN_018.voiceText: You'd better get used to my combat style.

char_112_siege_CN_019.voiceText: For want of a nail... the kingdom was lost.

char_112_siege_CN_020.voiceText: Run while you can. Better to be a coward with a pulse than a martyr with a grave.

char_112_siege_CN_024.voiceText: We'll take them out all at once.

char_112_siege_CN_025.voiceText: My weapon chooses its worthy wielder.

char_112_siege_CN_027.voiceText: A warrior must be ready to face death on the battlefield!

char_112_siege_CN_028.voiceText: My rule is the balance your lives hang in.

char_112_siege_CN_029.voiceText: Can bluff, can't take one blow.

char_112_siege_CN_030.voiceText: Those who refuse to surrender don't deserve mercy.

char_112_siege_CN_032.voiceText: I'm... more tired than I thought. I apologize...

char_112_siege_CN_033.voiceText: Do you mind if I get my forty winks in here?

char_112_siege_CN_036.voiceText: It's too noisy out there for my tastes... I think the silence of your office suits me more. Let me stay in here for a bit, will you?

char_155_tiger_CN_001.voiceText: If you got enemies about, just scream. I'll keep ya safe.

char_155_tiger_CN_002.voiceText: Where's that kid gone off to? Y'know, her... the really tanned shorty who's always trailing our Master... 'Morgan' is her nam- Oi! Stop right there!

char_155_tiger_CN_003.voiceText: You scratch my back, I'll scratch yours, we keep it real that way, yeah? You treat me with respect, I'll do the same for you.

char_155_tiger_CN_004.voiceText: Seems our Majesty's really into your place. Don't see that every day, seeing as we're never anywhere same for long.

char_155_tiger_CN_005.voiceText: Work or what have ya, you've gotta have guts!

char_155_tiger_CN_006.voiceText: Whoa, whoa, chew before you swallow, mate! HEY! SOMEONE BRING US MORE MEAT! This girl's got an empty belly to fill!

char_155_tiger_CN_007.voiceText: Bleeding Morgan... she might seem like a layabout mostly, but she's our tactician when push comes to shove. Gets the job done. Gets on my nerves otherwise, though, and she loves it. Tch...

char_155_tiger_CN_008.voiceText: Doesn't she look brilliant, like a liege with a hammer in hand? I'm even more keen to see the look of her holding a sword, though.

char_155_tiger_CN_009.voiceText: Out with it! Don't beat around the bush, just say it: who do you want dealt with?

char_155_tiger_CN_010.voiceText: Tch. look at you spacing out like an idiot... Your own bloody fault if a tiger bites you.

char_155_tiger_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Indra. I don't have any of those weird crazy powers -- I let my fists do the talking. Nice to meet ya!

char_155_tiger_CN_013.voiceText: Promotions are great, almost as great as fighting is!

char_155_tiger_CN_014.voiceText: Don't be afraid. I'll protect ya.

char_155_tiger_CN_018.voiceText: So, who's in the market for a walloping?

char_155_tiger_CN_019.voiceText: Mind your own sodding business and let me be!

char_155_tiger_CN_020.voiceText: Come on! Show me what you've got!

char_155_tiger_CN_029.voiceText: That's the stuff! That's what I call a kick!

char_155_tiger_CN_030.voiceText: You don't go home happy without some bloodshed!

char_155_tiger_CN_031.voiceText: Tch, we've got some who fled. Bunch of cowards.

char_155_tiger_CN_032.voiceText: Not bad... But I'll get you back for this!

char_155_tiger_CN_033.voiceText: What's this room about? More of a squeeze than anywhere I've been.

char_155_tiger_CN_034.voiceText: Oi! You got a bleedin' death wish?

char_155_tiger_CN_036.voiceText: C'mere, lemme get my arms around you! Yes, I mean hug you!

char_101_sora_CN_001.voiceText: Heya, Doctor! So, what are you up to? Looks like fun!

char_101_sora_CN_002.voiceText: Are there any karaoke venues at Rhodes Island? It would be great if we had a place to sing the night away when we don't have battles to fight!

char_101_sora_CN_003.voiceText: My duty as an idol was to make my fans happy with my songs and performances. But I'm an Operator now... what should my duty be, then?

char_101_sora_CN_004.voiceText: Doctor, anything I can help with? Don't you underestimate me—I'm considered quite physically capable at Penguin Logistics!

char_101_sora_CN_005.voiceText: Yup, my special skill is singing! Let's see, I can do a cappella, lead vocals, choir singing, pop music, and I can even rap, yo! Though I guess that's not a very useful skill for an Operator... If only I had a more practical skill...

char_101_sora_CN_006.voiceText: Ears...? Uh, I can't tell you... even if you ask Texas, she's not gonna tell you! I'll explain if I get the chance someday...

char_101_sora_CN_007.voiceText: You know, Texas actually saved my life and taught me so much I never knew. Which is why... I want to stay by her side whenever I have the chance... I'm uhh, trying to show my gratitude for her, that's all!

char_101_sora_CN_008.voiceText: You think I look upset? Um... it's because... Exusiai went on a mission with Texas today, right? If only I were as skilled as Exusiai, I could...

char_101_sora_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor! Could you teach me to use weapons? My songs have no practical use except for support and encouragement. If I could fight with weapons... Huh? You're not good at fighting either?!

char_101_sora_CN_010.voiceText: ...Texas, are you listening to my songs?

char_101_sora_CN_011.voiceText: Hiiii! I'm the loveable idol from Monster Siren Records: Sora! Oops, sorry, introducing myself like this at Rhodes Island must be kinda weird. Hmm...

char_101_sora_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? You mean like debuting as a trainee idol?

char_101_sora_CN_014.voiceText: I feel as excited as I did during my first live performance! I'm just so happy that you trust me this much, Doctor! It's like all my hard work has paid off! ...Huh? My ears? What about them?

char_101_sora_CN_017.voiceText: As a member of the squad, I'll start by learning the very basics.

char_101_sora_CN_018.voiceText: The leader? You mean like being the lead singer?

char_101_sora_CN_019.voiceText: Singing on the battlefield... now that's something new!

char_101_sora_CN_020.voiceText: If only my songs could put an end to all this fighting...

char_101_sora_CN_024.voiceText: All right, let's make some noise!

char_101_sora_CN_025.voiceText: Come on, we can do it!

char_101_sora_CN_029.voiceText: I heard your cheering loud and clear, everyone! Thank you!

char_101_sora_CN_030.voiceText: Awesome! A smashing victory! Texas, were you watching me?

char_101_sora_CN_032.voiceText: I'm sorry... my performance wasn't good enough...

char_101_sora_CN_033.voiceText: This place is much bigger than the dorms at Penguin Logistics!

char_101_sora_CN_042.voiceText: I hope you have a fantastic day, Doctor!

char_103_angel_CN_001.voiceText: Leader! Give us something to do~

char_103_angel_CN_002.voiceText: Leader! Let's throw a party! We can play some hip-hop and eat apple pie! The best life is the party life! No party, no life!

char_103_angel_CN_003.voiceText: Locked and loaded, ready for action! What's the objective today, Leader?

char_103_angel_CN_004.voiceText: Some people believe that money can buy everything. But that saying doesn't apply to me! If I want someone to rest in pieces, no amount of money can save them~

char_103_angel_CN_005.voiceText: My first wish: for eight new guns! We angels all have a special gun we grow up with, but owning just one gun is so lame, right?

char_103_angel_CN_006.voiceText: My second wish... find someone to help me turn off this light over my head!

char_103_angel_CN_007.voiceText: The only reason Texas lives so carefree and swagged out is that she's got me watching over her. That's the obvious truth, right?

char_103_angel_CN_008.voiceText: If you ever run into an angel with black horns oozing ominous vibes, please tell her for me: I've never forgotten her.

char_103_angel_CN_009.voiceText: Us Penguin Logistics girls ain't so bad, right? Wanna come be our boss? Ehehe, just kidding.

char_103_angel_CN_010.voiceText: ...Lord, is this someone we gotta save too?

char_103_angel_CN_011.voiceText: Our slogan is 'Long live the Penguin Empire.' Are you our client? You can call me Exusiai. I'm nothing like that Lupo ice queen. I'm always down for some fun!

char_103_angel_CN_014.voiceText: Leader... No, savior, I pledge to this gun in my hand to protect you until the very end of this world.

char_103_angel_CN_017.voiceText: Squad combat? I'm very familiar with that.

char_103_angel_CN_018.voiceText: No one makes a better leader than me! You've got a good eye.

char_103_angel_CN_019.voiceText: Let's go! Take them all by storm!

char_103_angel_CN_020.voiceText: I already called dibs on the most lucrative real estate in Hell, and you guys all get a share. Rest easy!

char_103_angel_CN_029.voiceText: Wonderful! This is the chance of a lifetime. Charge on!

char_103_angel_CN_030.voiceText: May my hail of bullets bring you eternal peace.

char_103_angel_CN_031.voiceText: The sound of victory is the sweetest melody. Alright, let's grab some drinks to celebrate when we get back!

char_103_angel_CN_032.voiceText: Even a well-crafted gun will jam sometimes. Life is no different, so don't worry about it~

char_103_angel_CN_036.voiceText: Leader, wanna try out my weapon?

char_201_moeshd_CN_001.voiceText: Relax, Boss, I got your back, no matter where you're goin'. But, ya gotta pay upfront. Keep that in mind.

char_201_moeshd_CN_002.voiceText: You work hard, you get paid. Don’t wanna be livin' under no bridge, y'know?

char_201_moeshd_CN_003.voiceText: Look at your crew, all decked out tip to tail in shiny tech! Give us a feel!

char_201_moeshd_CN_004.voiceText: Nothin' feels as good as buyin' new gear! I just feel like gettin' my hands on whatever I see. Wonder if I've got some kind of shopping addiction...

char_201_moeshd_CN_005.voiceText: Another month, another pile of bills... Aaand to pay 'em, another pile of stuff to sell on the side! Top quality at rock-bottom prices!

char_201_moeshd_CN_006.voiceText: Moving this, lifting that. If we gonna be haulin' goods all day, might as well be somethin' nice and useful, or maybe somethin' tasty!

char_201_moeshd_CN_007.voiceText: Hey, Boss! Check out this thing I found, it's to die for! Wanna bite? Heheh, y'know, the only thing that comes even slightly close to good gear is good food.

char_201_moeshd_CN_008.voiceText: Boss, c'mere for a sec, will ya? Take a look at my stock here. I got garments, home goods, office supplies, op gear, and a little bit of everything! And listen, for you? I'll give you a bulk discount!

char_201_moeshd_CN_009.voiceText: Listen, Boss, I owe you! You been so generous with those referrals, I can buy everythin' I ever wanted! You're a real mensch, Boss! Really, you're my favorite!

char_201_moeshd_CN_010.voiceText: Oy… I'm in for another lean month…

char_201_moeshd_CN_011.voiceText: The name's Croissant, and lemme tell ya, this is your lucky day, Boss! You ain't gonna find stronger or sturdier than me out there! And I like your style, so you hire me right now, I knock off 20%.

char_201_moeshd_CN_012.voiceText: I'll pump myself up and get more work!

char_201_moeshd_CN_013.voiceText: Listen, Boss, I gotta thank you for hookin' me up with such a sweet gig. I owe you one!

char_201_moeshd_CN_014.voiceText: Hey, Boss, I put that little bonus you gave me to work for us! Look! I shelled out for some new gear so I can protect you that much better!

char_201_moeshd_CN_018.voiceText: Listen up! We're gonna get this job done nice and smooth-like.

char_201_moeshd_CN_019.voiceText: You're about to be the happiest Boss at Rhodes Island.

char_201_moeshd_CN_020.voiceText: Here comes the enemy, and they brought us a bunch of free gear!

char_201_moeshd_CN_022.voiceText: I got some new toys to try out!

char_201_moeshd_CN_029.voiceText: Think maybe they left us a nice chest full of tchotchkes out there?

char_201_moeshd_CN_031.voiceText: Some of 'em got away... Oy, that ain't gonna be good for business.

char_201_moeshd_CN_032.voiceText: Ahh, damn it… First I lost the fight, and now my wallet...

char_201_moeshd_CN_033.voiceText: Don't suppose you got a treasure chest or two stashed in here?

char_201_moeshd_CN_036.voiceText: Hey, Boss, got any cool stuff on you? Lemme at it!

char_201_moeshd_CN_042.voiceText: Welcome, Boss! Please, take a look around!

char_118_yuki_CN_002.voiceText: Princess Fumizuki is my master, and you're my employer.

char_118_yuki_CN_003.voiceText: My hobby? Standing on the coast, watching the snow fall.

char_118_yuki_CN_006.voiceText: My weapon? A shuriken, the Silver Wind, made by Eastern Heavy Industries.

char_118_yuki_CN_011.voiceText: I am Shirayuki. Princess Fumizuki told me to assist Miss Ch'en and follow all your orders.

char_118_yuki_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? I, Shirayuki, am honored.

char_118_yuki_CN_014.voiceText: I, Shirayuki, may devote greater strength to you.

char_118_yuki_CN_020.voiceText: A snowstorm will bury this battlefield.

char_118_yuki_CN_029.voiceText: The enemy dies, I advance. I advance, the enemy dies.

char_118_yuki_CN_030.voiceText: The enemy has fallen. Total victory.

char_118_yuki_CN_031.voiceText: Of their ranks, some flee. Wariness, a must.

char_118_yuki_CN_032.voiceText: Should we fight again, we will return the favor one hundredfold.

char_118_yuki_CN_036.voiceText: Your consideration, I, Shirayuki, will engrave upon my heart.

char_136_hsguma_CN_001.voiceText: Relax, Doctor. I'll keep you safe.

char_136_hsguma_CN_002.voiceText: Lots of new recruits lately, many new faces. Don't let your guard down.

char_136_hsguma_CN_003.voiceText: If something happens, don't forget to use the emergency communication channel. Just call me and I'll come running.

char_136_hsguma_CN_004.voiceText: I sound cold when I talk? I'm on the clock. I'm a lot less serious when I'm off.

char_136_hsguma_CN_005.voiceText: Rhodes Island needs more than just combat Operators. You need experts in education, PR, and all kinds of stuff.

char_136_hsguma_CN_006.voiceText: I used to only get called in for the nastiest fights, but now every fight is a nasty one.

char_136_hsguma_CN_007.voiceText: This shield has a name: Hannya. I brought it from my hometown. Its 'father' and mine were old friends. Back in the L.G.D., my superiors would always tease me about it, but together we've proven that a shield makes a great weapon, and so do I.

char_136_hsguma_CN_008.voiceText: Hannya's tasted plenty of Lungmen gangster blood. I never thought it'd win me many friends, but the ones who looked down on me started showing me some respect after all that had happened. Or maybe they're just scared of how big I am? What do you think?

char_136_hsguma_CN_009.voiceText: How about another shot...? Oh, you've had enough? Don't sweat it... I can carry you back to your room if you pass out. What? That worries you even more? C'mon, don't be a buzzkill.

char_136_hsguma_CN_010.voiceText: Hm? Heh. Nothing. Just guarding you, Doctor.

char_136_hsguma_CN_011.voiceText: Hoshiguma, Defender Operator. I'll be your shield, your blade, your fortress. Very glad to meet you, Doctor.

char_136_hsguma_CN_012.voiceText: It's all thanks to your teaching, Doctor.

char_136_hsguma_CN_014.voiceText: No one tells me where I'm going, and no one can stop me once I make up my mind. And now—I've made up my mind to follow you, Doctor.

char_136_hsguma_CN_018.voiceText: Protecting Rhodes Island is my responsibility too.

char_136_hsguma_CN_019.voiceText: I want everyone to get home safe.

char_136_hsguma_CN_020.voiceText: If you've got a reason to fight, you've got a reason to die!

char_136_hsguma_CN_026.voiceText: If you want to hurt my friends, you have to go through my shield first.

char_136_hsguma_CN_028.voiceText: Hannya, unleash the rage your father poured into you!

char_136_hsguma_CN_029.voiceText: The harder the journey, the stronger you'll become.

char_136_hsguma_CN_030.voiceText: Hurting my friends right in front of me? I'll make you pay!

char_136_hsguma_CN_031.voiceText: Are you hurt? I'm sorry. I failed.

char_136_hsguma_CN_032.voiceText: Fall back, now! I'll bring up the rear!

char_136_hsguma_CN_033.voiceText: With my size... it's kind of hard to get through the door.

char_136_hsguma_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, you should take a load off now that we finally got a break.

char_106_franka_CN_001.voiceText: We're changing shifts right now, Doctor. Just ignore me and get on with your work.

char_106_franka_CN_002.voiceText: Back in BSW, I was appointed as a BPRS... you know, Biochemical Protection Response Staff. You can probably imagine what it was like... bulky hazmat suit and all that...

char_106_franka_CN_003.voiceText: Hmm? You think I'm a clean freak? Well, Doctor, I see you're unexpectedly direct! I admire your courage.

char_106_franka_CN_004.voiceText: Some of the Operators' rooms are in dire need of cleaning. For example, the one belonging to that high-and-mighty teacher's pet. What do you think?

char_106_franka_CN_005.voiceText: You want to see the intricate pattern on my sword up close? Sure, hold it tight, then. Don't let go—it'll heat up to 2,500 degrees Celcius in 3 seconds! Haha, just kidding! Don't be scared!

char_106_franka_CN_006.voiceText: Stay clear of that room full of chemical haze, toxins and harmful radiation... that's right, I mean Dr. Kal'tsit's lab.

char_106_franka_CN_007.voiceText: You're asking me for advice regarding the prevention of biochemical contamination? Well, for example... always brush your teeth after eating?

char_106_franka_CN_008.voiceText: Liskarm's been looking so flashy since she got her promotion. 'Hey! Hot girl here! Get your gunsight on me!' I bet that's how she greets the enemies.

char_106_franka_CN_009.voiceText: Good golly, if this is how free life is at Rhodes Island then I might just quit my job at BSW. Liskarm would be upset, though.

char_106_franka_CN_010.voiceText: There's a mosquito on your arm, Doctor.

char_106_franka_CN_011.voiceText: I'm chemical specialist operator, Franka, here to do my bit to help minimize the pollution wrought by Originium.

char_106_franka_CN_012.voiceText: I could perform these techniques anywhere, anytime!

char_106_franka_CN_013.voiceText: Wooow, you're giving me a promotion? I'm having a lot more fun here than at BSW.

char_106_franka_CN_014.voiceText: *Giggle*, you want to see my sword at its most glorious? Too bad, Doctor—you're not qualified yet! If you work at it, maybe one day you'll gain the privilege!

char_106_franka_CN_018.voiceText: The best thing about training capable subordinates, is that I get to let them handle all the annoying stuff for me.

char_106_franka_CN_020.voiceText: Too bad... these people have already been contaminated. In that case...

char_106_franka_CN_023.voiceText: Offense isn't what I trained for, but hey...

char_106_franka_CN_024.voiceText: Heavy defenders are SO scary... Hehe, just kidding.

char_106_franka_CN_029.voiceText: Obsession with power is a fool's game.

char_106_franka_CN_030.voiceText: That was perfect from start to finish. Well done.

char_106_franka_CN_032.voiceText: What, you still have time for that upset face? Fall back now.

char_106_franka_CN_033.voiceText: Say, do you have black tea here?

char_106_franka_CN_036.voiceText: Want to hear about my time at BSW?

char_107_liskam_CN_002.voiceText: Take all missions seriously: that's the guiding rule for us security professionals.

char_107_liskam_CN_003.voiceText: I'm actually not that good at dealing with people like Franka. I'm not even sure how we became partners in the first place...

char_107_liskam_CN_004.voiceText: There's a strict selection process before you qualify for BSW. I'm short, have no outstanding Arts talents, and I'm not from any particularly prestigious bloodline. No one believed that I would make it... not even myself, once upon a time.

char_107_liskam_CN_005.voiceText: BSW is a top security contractor and a great fit for me, I think. But I do enjoy a little more freedom here when dispatched to Rhodes Island.

char_107_liskam_CN_006.voiceText: Isn't it amazing how far I've come? I feel like a real dragon... uh, ahem, forget I said that... Anyway, I'm okay with whatever as long as it helps our side in battle!

char_107_liskam_CN_007.voiceText: Thank you, Doctor, for trusting me this much.

char_107_liskam_CN_008.voiceText: People who know me always say I'm more easygoing than I seem. Do you think so too, Doctor?

char_107_liskam_CN_009.voiceText: Franka is telling you about our time at Blacksteel again?  Ahhh, for the love of... Just don't believe anything she says, okay?

char_107_liskam_CN_011.voiceText: Defender Liskarm, awaiting orders. I've been involved in multiple special operations like VIP protection, assaulting fortified positions, rescuing hostages, and clearing out threats.Your safety is my mission, and I will use every tool at my disposal to guarantee it.

char_107_liskam_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you for appointing me to this position, Doctor.

char_107_liskam_CN_014.voiceText: Thank you, Doctor! I will devote myself to defending Rhodes Island, as your trusted Operator.

char_107_liskam_CN_018.voiceText: Understood. I will ask my team to rigorously adhere to the guidelines and procedures of Rhodes Island.

char_107_liskam_CN_029.voiceText: This is nothing. Franka and I have been through much worse.

char_107_liskam_CN_031.voiceText: All green. This area has been secured.

char_107_liskam_CN_032.voiceText: Emergency squad, retreat with the injured Operators! Everyone who can still fight, follow me and hold back the enemy!

char_107_liskam_CN_033.voiceText: Is this room protected against electrical discharge?

char_107_liskam_CN_034.voiceText: Watch out you don't get shocked.

char_107_liskam_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, is Franka still being treated? By the way, you need to rest after work.

char_117_myrrh_CN_001.voiceText: Pardon, but that report you submitted to Dr. Kal'tsit... we could barely read the last few lines as they are nearly indecipherable... Please don't stay up late so much...

char_117_myrrh_CN_002.voiceText: So many things in here I've never seen before... Oh, sorry, I shouldn't be looking around... sorry...

char_117_myrrh_CN_003.voiceText: I know herbs are rather bitter, but people could pay more attention to how effective they are…

char_117_myrrh_CN_004.voiceText: Um, Doctor... is Harmonia still not getting any better? ... I see... I'll attend to her as soon as I finish work.

char_117_myrrh_CN_005.voiceText: I know my herbs aren't popular because they're bitter... Aww...but I don't know how to make them taste better... Oh, you mean I should ask around for tips? Bu-bu-but... I'm not that good at small talk... I guess I'll try my best…

char_117_myrrh_CN_006.voiceText: Harmonia and I would explore all sorts of places together when we were kids. Yeah, we grew up in the city ruins, and were really hoping to see the world outside back then...

char_117_myrrh_CN_007.voiceText: Harmonia is both my oldest and best friend... But I'm the one to blame for her Oripathy infection, and what she is right now... I will find the cure and make up for the life Oripathy has taken away from her. I promise.

char_117_myrrh_CN_008.voiceText: Ms. Perfumer suggested that I add some spices into my herbs and now they taste much better! I'm so glad I managed to summon the courage to ask everybody for their advices...

char_117_myrrh_CN_009.voiceText: Harmonia says I'm in higher spirits these days. Do you agree as well, Doctor? It's all thanks to your timely advice. I wouldn't know what to do without you…

char_117_myrrh_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor... oh, are you asleep? Yay! Now I can look around the office to my heart's content.

char_117_myrrh_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, I'm Myrrh, an herbalist. Dr. Kal'tsit gave me this title... she said myrrh symbolizes the ephemerality of life and wanted me to keep this in mind.

char_117_myrrh_CN_012.voiceText: Thank you so much! This way I'll be able to concoct even better medicine.

char_117_myrrh_CN_013.voiceText: This is called a... promotion? Is that it...? Um, I don't really know much about stuff like that…

char_117_myrrh_CN_014.voiceText: This reminds me of childhood with Harmonia, when we explored secret places and abandoned buildings. The more dangerous the place was, the rarer the ingredients we could find.

char_117_myrrh_CN_017.voiceText: Uh... I'll try my best not to drag everyone down...

char_117_myrrh_CN_018.voiceText: I'll start by doing my best to make eye contact...

char_117_myrrh_CN_019.voiceText: Ah, Doctor, I'm ready to go.

char_117_myrrh_CN_020.voiceText: I'll do my best to make sure no one gets hurt...!

char_117_myrrh_CN_029.voiceText: We won? Really? Even against those really tough opponents? Wow... you're so cool, Doctor!

char_117_myrrh_CN_030.voiceText: How's the medicine this time, everyone? ...Um, I guess I'll ask when we get back...

char_117_myrrh_CN_031.voiceText: So much to do in so little time... Thank goodness I didn't mess up too badly…

char_117_myrrh_CN_033.voiceText: Uh... I can still smell herbs on my clothes...

char_117_myrrh_CN_036.voiceText: Excuse me, Doctor. I made you some herb soup good for soothing the body and calming the mind. It's just... a bit bitter…

char_193_frostl_CN_001.voiceText: Want to listen to some music? I'll lend you my headphones.

char_193_frostl_CN_002.voiceText: Sorry, please keep a little distance from me.

char_193_frostl_CN_003.voiceText: I never imagined that I'd have the chance to become a rescue worker.

char_193_frostl_CN_004.voiceText: I picked up this axe a long time ago, maybe even before I learned to read.

char_193_frostl_CN_005.voiceText: The songs I like are probably not so popular. They're only good for humming to myself when I'm alone.

char_193_frostl_CN_006.voiceText: Don't blink—you have but one moment to witness this epic move.

char_193_frostl_CN_007.voiceText: Want something to drink? My treat. You should relax a bit after work, you know.

char_193_frostl_CN_008.voiceText: I only realized how precious life is after everyone around me died, one by one. Ironic, huh? I think so, too.

char_193_frostl_CN_009.voiceText: I'm a mercenary. I just do my job. As for the purpose of my mission and its consequences, I don't have a say in any of that. So, from now on, all my responsibilities are your concern.

char_193_frostl_CN_011.voiceText: Frostleaf, former mercenary. From now on, I'm your operator. Assign me any job you want, I can do pretty much anything.

char_193_frostl_CN_013.voiceText: Things are on the right track now.

char_193_frostl_CN_014.voiceText: Whew... not bad. Feeling fulfilled for the first time in a while.

char_193_frostl_CN_018.voiceText: Go your own ways and do your own jobs.

char_193_frostl_CN_019.voiceText: Great, I feel like some exercise.

char_193_frostl_CN_025.voiceText: My bodily fluids aren't the only thing that's chilling.

char_193_frostl_CN_027.voiceText: Life, brittle as frost, fragile like leaves.

char_193_frostl_CN_028.voiceText: Let's chill down some hot heads.

char_193_frostl_CN_029.voiceText: I've been through countless battles... seen the carnage, witnessed the silent nothingness at the end.

char_193_frostl_CN_030.voiceText: I remember every enemy I fought. Not a single one escapes.

char_193_frostl_CN_031.voiceText: We didn't lose anyone, did we?

char_193_frostl_CN_033.voiceText: I'd like... a more private space.

char_129_bluep_CN_001.voiceText: Greetings, Doctor. You're glowing today. To see you so well... it's all I could ever hope for.

char_129_bluep_CN_002.voiceText: I prepared an antidote to nullify the effects of any common poison. I'd like you to take one dose before every battle. Do you mind?

char_129_bluep_CN_003.voiceText: Actually, the toxin in my body is an ingredient in some high-quality medicines. That's why Dr. Kal'tsit needs me in her lab a lot.

char_129_bluep_CN_004.voiceText: Hmm, why do you keep staring at me... You mean, it's because my eye color is special? Is that a compliment, Doctor?

char_129_bluep_CN_005.voiceText: I'm the one our enemies fear the most. After all, who wouldn't want to kill me before I can torture them to death with my poison? What really worries me is that my teammates might think the same…

char_129_bluep_CN_006.voiceText: Why am I staring at this cake? Actually... I baked it to share with everyone, but no one wanted it... Would you like to try it, Doctor?

char_129_bluep_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, you're always wearing the same outfit. How about I choose some new clothes for you? I think I have pretty good taste. Oh... it's a uniform? So you can't change it? Okay…

char_129_bluep_CN_008.voiceText: I'm 'toxic'... so people prefer to stay away from me. But now I have you by my side, Doctor, and I'm really, really happy.

char_129_bluep_CN_009.voiceText: My body isn't that different from everyone else. I may be 'toxic,' but nothing bad will happen if someone touches me. Doctor, if you can prove this to everyone, then maybe they won't always keep away from me. Could you... hold my hand out there?

char_129_bluep_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor? Oh, already asleep. Gotta find a blanket to keep the Doctor warm...

char_129_bluep_CN_011.voiceText: Nice to meet you, I'm Blue Poison. I'm sure Dr. Kal'tsit must have told you about me. In that case, it'll be up to you to decide how to use my 'toxic' powers.

char_129_bluep_CN_012.voiceText: I think I hear the sound of toxic liquid boiling, like music to my ears.

char_129_bluep_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you so much... I'm so glad I get to help out in all these battles. It's like a dream come true.

char_129_bluep_CN_014.voiceText: I used to hold back and hide my 'toxic' self, but now I've accepted what I am, trying to move forward to change my fate. I have you to thank for helping me make this shift, Doctor. You have my sincerest gratitude.

char_129_bluep_CN_017.voiceText: Great. I'm good at supporting assaults.

char_129_bluep_CN_018.voiceText: I'd be much better off supporting the others. Wouldn't want my poison to harm you, Doctor...

char_129_bluep_CN_019.voiceText: Everyone, there's no need for you all to stand so far from me...

char_129_bluep_CN_020.voiceText: I prepared a 'gift' for you. Like it?

char_129_bluep_CN_022.voiceText: Please don't be scared of me.

char_129_bluep_CN_023.voiceText: Don't worry, my poison is not contagious.

char_129_bluep_CN_025.voiceText: My toxins will slowly burn your life away...

char_129_bluep_CN_027.voiceText: Honey to me, poison to you.

char_129_bluep_CN_029.voiceText: Use poison to fight the evils and crimes... Isn't that ironic to you?

char_129_bluep_CN_030.voiceText: I've got a poison to melt away all these remains in an instant. Want me to show you?

char_129_bluep_CN_031.voiceText: Good, finished before my clothes got dirty.

char_129_bluep_CN_032.voiceText: How ridiculous. Feels like I killed myself with my own poison...

char_129_bluep_CN_033.voiceText: Resting when you're tired helps you focus on your work.

char_129_bluep_CN_036.voiceText: D-Did you just touch me? C-Can you do that again? Please?

char_143_ghost_CN_001.voiceText: Good day. Please allow me a moment of prayer... before I resume my work for the day...

char_143_ghost_CN_002.voiceText: O benevolent Herald, hear my prayer: please watch over my dreams and ward my soul…

char_143_ghost_CN_003.voiceText: Hehehe… Cutting things... cutting things is such fun... Yes, some things were disconnected from the very beginning, their integrity only a false fiction...

char_143_ghost_CN_005.voiceText: Ehehe…Why were you dodging my sight? So pointless... because I already know exactly what your heart desires...

char_143_ghost_CN_006.voiceText: I have always, always wanted to bring you to a special place... A place where secrets are imparted...

char_143_ghost_CN_007.voiceText: What did you do to me...? Why was I made to drink that strange medicine? Who brought me to this place? PLEASE ANSWER ME!

char_143_ghost_CN_008.voiceText: That person's words are the complete and utter truth... Dissecting them, dismembering them, disemboweling them... it all grants them salvation...!

char_143_ghost_CN_009.voiceText: You see many things in your dreams that are hard to comprehend?... Those things you see are that soul's despairful tidings... And I, as the messenger, here to convey this exhortation to you... heh…

char_143_ghost_CN_010.voiceText: Hearken... Hear the whispers of vast creation's master, echoing from the deep...

char_143_ghost_CN_011.voiceText: I am Specter, that is what the spirits call me... That kind doctor informed me that I may receive further treatment by helping Rhodes Island... Yes, of course, my powers are yours to command.

char_143_ghost_CN_013.voiceText: I have no right to go against your will...

char_143_ghost_CN_014.voiceText: Will this position be a new source of joy for me...? Or... will working for you become my life's joy...?

char_143_ghost_CN_017.voiceText: Good night, my brothers and sisters.

char_143_ghost_CN_019.voiceText: This will be a path paved with sacrifice.

char_143_ghost_CN_020.voiceText: All these lost souls on the battlefield... I offer them to you.

char_143_ghost_CN_022.voiceText: Please let me know the results.

char_143_ghost_CN_023.voiceText: I come from the depth of the ocean…

char_143_ghost_CN_024.voiceText: You are the one who woke me.

char_143_ghost_CN_027.voiceText: I care not for valueless ones.

char_143_ghost_CN_029.voiceText: I have conquered all trials you gave me... Were you watching me?

char_143_ghost_CN_030.voiceText: Please guide these lost souls to peaceful enlightenment...!

char_143_ghost_CN_031.voiceText: None of you shall leave this place!

char_143_ghost_CN_032.voiceText: They shall pay for this... They must pay…

char_143_ghost_CN_033.voiceText: May I ask you to assign me to a room where I can see the starry sky?

char_143_ghost_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor... What is it inside you… that is driving me to this blissful ecstasy?

char_143_ghost_CN_042.voiceText: You are... Ah, the Doctor, isn't it?

char_181_flower_CN_001.voiceText: You'd better listen to me, Doctor!

char_181_flower_CN_002.voiceText: This fragrance... how was it? Do you feel all healed? I got the inspiration from Melantha's samples.

char_181_flower_CN_003.voiceText: Thanks for building a greenhouse for my flowers. I think it'll be a good place for everyone to rest.

char_181_flower_CN_004.voiceText: Oh, are you awake? You feel all refreshed, right? My aromatherapy is definitely working. I'm really confident in it!

char_181_flower_CN_005.voiceText: Narcissus, rabbitear iris, kalanchoe, boronia... I always carry seeds of all sorts of flowers on me.

char_181_flower_CN_006.voiceText: Oh, you mean this little one? It's still a baby, but quite helpful for concocting all sorts of things.

char_181_flower_CN_007.voiceText: The society of ants is maintained based on smells. The relationship between perfumers and their clients is the same.

char_181_flower_CN_008.voiceText: You seem to visit the greenhouse a lot these days. Oh, there's some pollen here on your sleeve. Let me wipe it off for you...

char_181_flower_CN_009.voiceText: You seem to have been sleeping for quite a while. What did you dream about, I wonder?

char_181_flower_CN_010.voiceText: Oh, Doctor? Hm, the lavender was much more effective than I imagined!

char_181_flower_CN_011.voiceText: Nice to meet you, Doctor. I'm Lena, a perfumer. Interesting job, right? Did you know it existed?

char_181_flower_CN_012.voiceText: Please check and tell me how I did.

char_181_flower_CN_013.voiceText: The promotion... are you here to tell me about it? Aw, sorry, Doctor... give me a sec... your collar... it's wrinkled, so I smoothed it out. That's all.

char_181_flower_CN_014.voiceText: Fighting when you could have just talked it out... I don't like that kind of unnecessary violence. But I'll still do my best to get used to it for you, Doctor.

char_181_flower_CN_018.voiceText: No matter as a perfumer or healer, I promise to fulfill all your expectations.

char_181_flower_CN_020.voiceText: What kind of battle would it end up being, I wonder...

char_181_flower_CN_027.voiceText: How do you like this smell?

char_181_flower_CN_029.voiceText: I've always believed that victory will be ours as long as you're the one giving orders.

char_181_flower_CN_031.voiceText: Good job, everyone. Get some rest.

char_181_flower_CN_032.voiceText: Too bad we didn't win, but I will not be discouraged because of it.

char_181_flower_CN_033.voiceText: I belong at your side, after all.

char_109_fmout_CN_001.voiceText: Alright, Doctor, your tarot card for today is...

char_109_fmout_CN_002.voiceText: Would you like to learn more about your future?

char_109_fmout_CN_003.voiceText: Bear it in mind that excessive reliance on unfathomed power will eventually backfire on us.

char_109_fmout_CN_004.voiceText: Tarot cards aren't divine, all-seeing tools. Instead, we use them for guidance when we feel lost.

char_109_fmout_CN_005.voiceText: Destiny is like the world we walk upon—no one can escape it.

char_109_fmout_CN_006.voiceText: Humans might never be able to escape this world... but we can change it. Our actions belie endless possibilities.

char_109_fmout_CN_007.voiceText: There are countless topics for which you can consult the tarot, the most common one being your luck in card games. To change it, however, you must be brave enough to change your fate first.

char_109_fmout_CN_008.voiceText: We have a ritual among diviners that's all the rage these days. We call it the 'Hand of Fate.' Would you like to try it?

char_109_fmout_CN_009.voiceText: It's a divination taboo to do readings concerning death. But I don't believe death is the end—it's the beginning of something new.

char_109_fmout_CN_010.voiceText: Dreams can often enlighten you in strange ways. If you have an enlightening dream like that, you'd best remember every detail, Doctor.

char_109_fmout_CN_011.voiceText: Following the guidance of the arcana, our paths have finally converged. Nice to meet you, Doctor.

char_109_fmout_CN_013.voiceText: I'd already foreseen this promotion in my crystal ball. Heheh, just kidding.

char_109_fmout_CN_014.voiceText: You want to know your destiny, Doctor? Too bad, I can't help you. I'm not the one to share it with you, for the fate forbids me to do so.

char_109_fmout_CN_017.voiceText: Wait a minute, let me predict the results of this battle.

char_109_fmout_CN_018.voiceText: Well then, let me pray for everyone.

char_109_fmout_CN_019.voiceText: Fate is a fickle thing... only the victorious will be forever revered.

char_109_fmout_CN_020.voiceText: I can see the outcome. Victory belongs to Rhodes Island.

char_109_fmout_CN_028.voiceText: All will fall before the Priestess's might.

char_109_fmout_CN_029.voiceText: Will fate have us in a chokehold… or will we turn the table?

char_109_fmout_CN_030.voiceText: I have moved all of them to the graveyard.

char_109_fmout_CN_032.voiceText: Impossible... this isn't what I saw in the cards...

char_109_fmout_CN_033.voiceText: Bad omens seem to lurk inside this room. May I use my powers to help you manage them?

char_109_fmout_CN_034.voiceText: Hm? What can I do for you?

char_109_fmout_CN_036.voiceText: Want me to do a reading on your future? All right, please give me a minute.

char_109_fmout_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor, you're blessed by the winds of luck.

char_126_shotst_CN_001.voiceText: I sense something familiar in the wind. Where are we?

char_126_shotst_CN_002.voiceText: Do you feel the wind from Kazimierz?

char_126_shotst_CN_003.voiceText: Rhodes Island is very different from the places I used to live. There's nowhere to start a campfire here... too bad. Maybe on the deck? I'd like to create a space where everyone can talk and grow closer together.

char_126_shotst_CN_004.voiceText: Umm, how does this mission signup system actually work? I'm really bad at electronics…

char_126_shotst_CN_005.voiceText: There have been lots of new faces at Rhodes Island. I'll gladly help them adjust to the environment.

char_126_shotst_CN_006.voiceText: That Kazimierzian knight... Oh, it's her. I knew that girl years ago. She used to be a shy, bookish type. I wonder what made her change so much.

char_126_shotst_CN_007.voiceText: Shh... look what I found! A solitary Doctor... gotta catch this one! Oh, did I scare you? Haha…

char_126_shotst_CN_008.voiceText: I sometimes recall the time back home in the forest. We had lots of different competitions every year…ah, the good old days. I wonder what my hometown is like now.

char_126_shotst_CN_009.voiceText: I'll always have your back, Doctor.

char_126_shotst_CN_010.voiceText: So you can fall asleep without a care, just like that? Heheh...

char_126_shotst_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, I'm Meteor, the archer from the woods. Do you need an Operator who excels in long-distance support?

char_126_shotst_CN_012.voiceText: Archery requires constant practice. No one can afford to slack off for even one day.

char_126_shotst_CN_013.voiceText: I'm honored to receive this promotion.

char_126_shotst_CN_014.voiceText: Thank you, Doctor, for recognizing my skill. I'll continue to do my best to serve you.

char_126_shotst_CN_017.voiceText: Leave the long-distance support to me.

char_126_shotst_CN_020.voiceText: Time to show them what we can do.

char_126_shotst_CN_022.voiceText: I've been waiting for a while.

char_126_shotst_CN_023.voiceText: The wind is blowing in the right direction.

char_126_shotst_CN_029.voiceText: No matter how difficult the battle, we can handle it, as long as we work together as one.

char_126_shotst_CN_031.voiceText: All injured personnel, please stay put, don't move. I'll be right there.

char_126_shotst_CN_032.voiceText: I'm sorry... I didn't want it to end up like this...

char_126_shotst_CN_033.voiceText: It's hard to get used to such a small room.

char_126_shotst_CN_036.voiceText: Being by your side feels like basking in the spring sunshine. So warm, so comfy.

char_127_estell_CN_001.voiceText: Uh... w-where should I stand? O-oh, you want me to sit? Then... where should I sit?

char_127_estell_CN_002.voiceText: That little bird is my friend. But it's always disappearing on me these days... Oh no... It's not disliking me, is it...

char_127_estell_CN_003.voiceText: The way I look... is nothing like an Operator at all... And I understand having someone like me in your team won't make you pround... But don't worry, I won't go around saying I'm with Rhodes Island.

char_127_estell_CN_004.voiceText: You've probably noticed, but my hair is quite difficult to sytle... So I have to let my hair down like this... It's not very appropriate, is it?

char_127_estell_CN_005.voiceText: My mutant horns... they don't really fit in with the crowd... I thought I was used to other people staring at them... but … but it's still embarrassing...

char_127_estell_CN_006.voiceText: The friends I made in the wilderness... they're all coming to Rhodes Island too. So... I'll feel less lonely. I'll do my best to fight hard and protect everyone.

char_127_estell_CN_007.voiceText: Actually, ever since my childhood, I've always been dreaming to be a... a princess... I-I mean it's okay if you find it ridiculous...

char_127_estell_CN_008.voiceText: The bad guys always call me 'freak'... but… yeah, I'm a freak, a freak that wants to protect you and everyone else.

char_127_estell_CN_009.voiceText: Um... that really energetic doctor... she's an Archosaurian too, huh? I do want to talk to her... but I'm still a bit scared…

char_127_estell_CN_010.voiceText: No one's staring at me now, right? Ah, finally...

char_127_estell_CN_011.voiceText: H-hello... Uh... s-sorry, my horns... I accidentally broke your office door with my horns...

char_127_estell_CN_012.voiceText: Powers stronger than what I already have... can I really control them...?

char_127_estell_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion? What's that?... I don't really get it, but I think it means that I've been helpful, right?

char_127_estell_CN_014.voiceText: Thank you, Doctor, for giving me a bit more confidence... Now I am starting to understand what to do and how to wield my power.

char_127_estell_CN_018.voiceText: Wahh... me? R-really? Is that really okay?

char_127_estell_CN_019.voiceText: Uh, everyone... it's... it's time to attack! I-is this how I'm supposed to give orders?

char_127_estell_CN_020.voiceText: I... I won't let the bad guys win!

char_127_estell_CN_023.voiceText: My pushover look should pull a lot of enemies here...

char_127_estell_CN_024.voiceText: To intimidate the enemy... I... I'm capable of that, right?

char_127_estell_CN_027.voiceText: I won't let you escape this easily!

char_127_estell_CN_029.voiceText: I can do better... yes, even better!

char_127_estell_CN_030.voiceText: Are you proud of what we've achieved, Doctor?

char_127_estell_CN_032.voiceText: In the end... I'm good for nothing... just as expected...

char_127_estell_CN_033.voiceText: Wow, this place... it's so spacious! I love it!

char_127_estell_CN_036.voiceText: You're always so kind to me... I... I'm so happy!

char_141_nights_CN_001.voiceText: Didn't notice me behind you, eh? It's only natural. I'm a cat. We're known for being silent prowlers!

char_141_nights_CN_002.voiceText: Hey, don't touch my hat... it's crazy, you know! If it feeds you too many secrets, Doctor, you'll be in trouble.

char_141_nights_CN_003.voiceText: So rare to see a pharma take in runaway kitties from a jail. Did you all want a peek at my maps? Or,  was it some advice on prison breaks?

char_141_nights_CN_004.voiceText: We thieves have our own principles and standards too... perhaps. Who can say?

char_141_nights_CN_005.voiceText: Meow, meow, meow... Meow? Never you mind, I'm just talking to myself.

char_141_nights_CN_006.voiceText: Anytime you want. Don't you worry, I have friends everywhere. Eyes everywhere.

char_141_nights_CN_007.voiceText: Curiosity can kill a cat, you know.

char_141_nights_CN_008.voiceText: I'm in a good mood right now, so here's a riddle for you. 'Why is a raven like a writing desk?'

char_141_nights_CN_009.voiceText: Thank you, for this 'Haze' I'm now.But... did you catch a peep of any of them, along the way? Any of, well... my secrets?

char_141_nights_CN_010.voiceText: Asleep like a baby... Time to get 'meown to business,' then.

char_141_nights_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, I'm Haze. I like relaxing work environments,  and an employer who knows better than to bother me with too many questions.

char_141_nights_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion? What's that? Does it taste good?

char_141_nights_CN_014.voiceText: Finally out of those old shackles... and here I am, straight into new ones. The destiny of a thief's no wonder.

char_141_nights_CN_017.voiceText: Give me a bit of freedom and I'll be happy.

char_141_nights_CN_018.voiceText: What do we need a leader for? Can't everyone just fight on their own?

char_141_nights_CN_019.voiceText: Meow... It's driving me wild... this sweet, sweet smell of freedom!

char_141_nights_CN_020.voiceText: Everyone, no need to have cold feet here.

char_141_nights_CN_026.voiceText: Careful, kittens. Don't lose your mittens.

char_141_nights_CN_027.voiceText: You think you've got all the trimmings, don't you?

char_141_nights_CN_029.voiceText: No one stands above a kitty in the end!

char_141_nights_CN_030.voiceText: Perfect victory? Whatever. A victory's a victory afterall.

char_141_nights_CN_031.voiceText: Do you know how many enemies you let go? That will be a spanner in the works.

char_141_nights_CN_032.voiceText: I'm no stranger to running for it, but this is just too embarrassing...

char_141_nights_CN_036.voiceText: Meow? I'm not satisfied yet. You know my rule: if I can't have it, I want it.

char_145_prove_CN_001.voiceText: If you need your room cleaned, I'd be glad to help, Doctor.

char_145_prove_CN_002.voiceText: You seem really interested in my tail, don't you? You say it's furry and looks cute? Well, wanna touch it? No one else has a tail like this, you know!

char_145_prove_CN_003.voiceText: Water is precious in the wild. Rhodes Island is in no danger of having a drought right now, but that doesn't mean we should waste water.

char_145_prove_CN_004.voiceText: It's my duty to search for and rescue those who encounter Catastrophes. I rarely find any survivors though...

char_145_prove_CN_005.voiceText: Retrieving beacons, exploring mineral deposits, and recycling... Then we can call it a day!

char_145_prove_CN_006.voiceText: Mr. Grape is my buddy and a capable partner I can rely on! Where he came from, you ask?... Uh, hmm... Now that's a good question. Where did we first meet?...

char_145_prove_CN_007.voiceText: W-what's with that red one...? I... can't stop trembling... uh... Doctor, can you lend me your arm? I'd feel much safer that way...

char_145_prove_CN_008.voiceText: Those who do Catastrophe relief work often develop all kinds of mutations. What mutation do I have? Well, it's better not to ask. The more you know, the more dangerous it gets for you, Doctor.

char_145_prove_CN_009.voiceText: Catastrophe relief workers in the wilderness... don't usually come out unscathed. No need to worry about me, though! I'm already very happy to have a chance to rest at Rhodes Island.

char_145_prove_CN_010.voiceText: Aw, falling asleep in this kinda place again... Guess 'safety' isn't a part of your vocabulary.

char_145_prove_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Provence, your average Catastrophe relief worker. Hmm, why are you staring at me like that? Interested in my tail?

char_145_prove_CN_012.voiceText: So... does this bring me closer to what you imagined I should be?

char_145_prove_CN_013.voiceText: It's fun working with you, Doctor!

char_145_prove_CN_014.voiceText: I sense a storm approaching Rhodes Island. But don't worry, leave the evacuation to me! I'm an expert at Catastrophe prevention!

char_145_prove_CN_017.voiceText: Who will I be teaming up with this time?

char_145_prove_CN_018.voiceText: Don't worry. Everything will be fine.

char_145_prove_CN_019.voiceText: My job is to bring everyone home safely.

char_145_prove_CN_020.voiceText: I despise natural Catastrophes and enemies equally!

char_145_prove_CN_023.voiceText: Let's greet 'em with a warning shot.

char_145_prove_CN_025.voiceText: I've warned ya! Now time for Crowd Control!

char_145_prove_CN_028.voiceText: The wilderness has its own rules.

char_145_prove_CN_029.voiceText: Compared to natural Catastrophes, these enemies are really powerless.

char_145_prove_CN_030.voiceText: Disaster assessment report: we received zero damage!

char_145_prove_CN_031.voiceText: Everyone worked hard. Even if we suffered some damage,  let's not be discouraged!

char_145_prove_CN_032.voiceText: Aw... my assessment was off. This'll leave a spot on my record for sure...

char_145_prove_CN_033.voiceText: It'd be nice to have a room to rest in!

char_145_prove_CN_036.voiceText: I've got a fluffy tail~ a fluffy tail~♪

char_183_skgoat_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, I've picked out the Originium from the pile of other ores according to your orders. Any other requests?

char_183_skgoat_CN_002.voiceText: Oripathy is really troublesome. I can't even go on operations without the okay from Dr. Kal'tsit. And patients will lose some years of their lives, you say? Yeah, that's true, but I'm okay with that.

char_183_skgoat_CN_003.voiceText: This tuning fork? It's actually a wand. It's not only a weapon but also useful for geological surveying. I find it really handy.

char_183_skgoat_CN_004.voiceText: Without Rhodes Island, I'd probably still be a full-time geological researcher. And without you people... I'd probably already be dead.

char_183_skgoat_CN_005.voiceText: Oh? I have dark circles under my eyes? Aw, I knew it...

char_183_skgoat_CN_006.voiceText: What's that behind me, you ask? Well... ah, never mind, it's really hard to explain. I'll tell you when we have more time.

char_183_skgoat_CN_007.voiceText: Some rocks talk to me, you know... and they talk a lot! Some of them even squabble... so much that I lose sleep over it. You think I'm kidding? Do I look like I'm kidding?

char_183_skgoat_CN_008.voiceText: Provence is as careless as always. She needs to be careful or she'll end up like me, seriously ill. You'd better give her a good talking-to.

char_183_skgoat_CN_009.voiceText: Look at this! Look at this! This surface... it couldn't have been formed without pressure in the earth's crust since 350 thousand years ago. Isn't it wonderful? You know, Doctor, those people who refuse to believe geological studies are truly fools.

char_183_skgoat_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor—oh, you're sleeping? You must be tired from all the hard work.

char_183_skgoat_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Earthspirit, a geology scholar and Caster, reporting in. I work eight hours each day. Make me work any more and you'll have to pay me extra.

char_183_skgoat_CN_012.voiceText: Hm, is this academic data or something else?

char_183_skgoat_CN_013.voiceText: Methods of scientific research must continue to be improved on.

char_183_skgoat_CN_014.voiceText: Forgive me for my bluntness, but do remember that I only receive the salary for one person, so you can't make me do the work of more than one person even if you promote me.

char_183_skgoat_CN_018.voiceText: I hope this squad could work well in all kinds of extreme environments.

char_183_skgoat_CN_019.voiceText: Don't worry, we'll be right back.

char_183_skgoat_CN_020.voiceText: We can't let them misuse the Originium like this.

char_183_skgoat_CN_028.voiceText: You shouldn't have set foot on this land.

char_183_skgoat_CN_029.voiceText: What the enemies are doing... will only bring disaster.

char_183_skgoat_CN_030.voiceText: All enemies have been dealt with.

char_183_skgoat_CN_033.voiceText: This environment is quite suitable for research.

char_183_skgoat_CN_036.voiceText: This piece of ore... for me? Really? But... it's expensive, right?

char_183_skgoat_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor, time to get to work.

char_187_ccheal_CN_001.voiceText: Yeah, yeah, I get it, you deserve a nice rest in your off time. But you gotta get your treatment right now.

char_187_ccheal_CN_002.voiceText: Huh? You want me to be gentle and caring? That's nurse stuff, pal. I'm a doctor, from top to toe. That means healing. Treatment. Don't waste my time with the fluff.

char_187_ccheal_CN_003.voiceText: Strange, why does Dr. Kal'tsit keeps telling me to 'be nice to patients'? She's been doing it ever since I got here.

char_187_ccheal_CN_004.voiceText: Your average doctor's biggest concern is keeping herself safe. Mine, on the other hand... it's getting my patients to stop being scared of me.

char_187_ccheal_CN_005.voiceText: Treatment time, ears open! Eyes on me! Hands up! Don't move!

char_187_ccheal_CN_006.voiceText: Doctors and fighters... life-savers, life-takers. People think we're polar opposites, but I think we're one and the same—we both sacrifice.

char_187_ccheal_CN_007.voiceText: Huh? I didn't beat anyone up, I just wanted to say hi. Watch, lemme demo... I initiate physical contact, and that's how I get closer to people, see?

char_187_ccheal_CN_008.voiceText: I'm kinda missing my homeland... I chose to be a medic myself, but it's crazy it all turned out the way it did. Life sure took me down some wild paths, huh?

char_187_ccheal_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor... you and I are both travelers on a lonely road. I guess that's why we understand each other so well.

char_187_ccheal_CN_010.voiceText: What the... you're asleep, huh? Heheh.

char_187_ccheal_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Medic Operator Gavial. First things first... Don’t judge me by the way I look. Got it?

char_187_ccheal_CN_012.voiceText: Tch, I thought we were gonna have combat class.

char_187_ccheal_CN_013.voiceText: Everyone's so scared of me treating them... You're the only one who accepts me for what I am. Thanks for that.

char_187_ccheal_CN_014.voiceText: All right, no more fooling around. I'll be serious from now on.

char_187_ccheal_CN_017.voiceText: Leave the rear to me. Go show what you're made of!

char_187_ccheal_CN_018.voiceText: All right, get in line, everyone!

char_187_ccheal_CN_019.voiceText: All right, ladies. Let's keep it cool.

char_187_ccheal_CN_025.voiceText: If you want treatment, you gotta come closer!

char_187_ccheal_CN_029.voiceText: Meh, pushovers. I wasn't even breaking a sweat.

char_187_ccheal_CN_030.voiceText: Man those guys were weak. I regret not giving 'em a few whacks with the staff here.

char_187_ccheal_CN_031.voiceText: Have you guys never taken emergency response training courses?

char_187_ccheal_CN_032.voiceText: Darn it... I'm not giving up yet!

char_187_ccheal_CN_033.voiceText: Let's see if there are any interesting people here!

char_187_ccheal_CN_036.voiceText: You want me to just nod and listen? No. Freaking. Way.

char_241_panda_CN_001.voiceText: So... I have to just stand here and not do anything? Laaaame.

char_241_panda_CN_002.voiceText: These gauntlets aren't that heavy. See? Even a dainty little girl like me can carry 'em around real easy.

char_241_panda_CN_003.voiceText: You remember fighting by my side before? Can't say I remember fighting by yours, sorry... I just fight for what's right, that's all.

char_241_panda_CN_004.voiceText: Hah. That boxer, Beehunter? She's really something! I enjoyed sparring with her so much, I had to throw out some serious moves. And she's got an amazing honey collection too. Wanna visit her with me next time? You gotta learn some kung fu first, though.

char_241_panda_CN_005.voiceText: Reading a movie magazine...? Well, guess what? The 'hot kung-fu actress' mentioned in this article is ME! What? You don't believe me? Come on, look! This is me, can't you tell? C'mon, that's definitely me!

char_241_panda_CN_006.voiceText: Do I regret forgoing my previous life? Well, sometimes, of course. But the world ain't kind to us Infected. Lots of places I'm not allowed to go. It blows.

char_241_panda_CN_007.voiceText: There's a street full of food stalls in the neighboring city. And... a candy shop over there? And a theme park? Aww, Doctor, can I get a day off? I wanna check out these places!

char_241_panda_CN_008.voiceText: Am I satisfied with life at Rhodes Island, you ask? Hm, to be honest... It's even sweeter than what they show in the movies! I got cool opponents to practice with, top-notch food, and by working here, I'm doing something good for the world! What could be better!

char_241_panda_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, look! What do you think about this script? Oh, who's gonna act in it, you wonder? You and I are gonna be the main characters! There's this scene where we leap from the roof of a thirty-story building and slide all the way down. Isn't that cool? Hey! Come back! Wait!

char_241_panda_CN_010.voiceText: You're catching some z's, eh? Guess I'll slack off for a bit too. Man, this couch is so fluffy!

char_241_panda_CN_011.voiceText: You swear you've seen my face before? Probably saw it in a movie I was in! Call me FEater, and what I do from here is your call!

char_241_panda_CN_012.voiceText: It's over? Come on, let's watch just a while longer. We're almost at the fun part!

char_241_panda_CN_013.voiceText: Oooh! A promotion! Thanks so much, Doctor!

char_241_panda_CN_014.voiceText: This here's the perfect opportunity to show you some REAL kung fu!

char_241_panda_CN_018.voiceText: Huh? I'm the leader? Not sure how it'll go, but...

char_241_panda_CN_020.voiceText: I'm FEater. Pleased to beat you!

char_241_panda_CN_026.voiceText: This is straight out of one of my movies!

char_241_panda_CN_028.voiceText: Who says a movie star couldn't be a real kung-fu master!

char_241_panda_CN_030.voiceText: It's over already? I was just starting to get warmed up.

char_241_panda_CN_031.voiceText: Hey, it's no biggie. Just a few scratches and bruises.

char_241_panda_CN_032.voiceText: Aw... I just wanna go home and sleep...

char_241_panda_CN_036.voiceText: Hey, Doctor, want my autograph? I'll take a pic with you if you want, too!

char_241_panda_CN_042.voiceText: Did you have breakfast yet, Doctor?

char_180_amgoat_CN_001.voiceText: Professor, I've finished all my Catastrophe studies notes. Do you have any more I could read?

char_180_amgoat_CN_002.voiceText: Huh? What? Why do I call you 'Professor'? Well, you're an expert on Catastrophe studies, so you're like a professor, right? Aren't we all supposed to address our superiors with respect?

char_180_amgoat_CN_003.voiceText: Pardon me? Please say that again? Oh, you're wondering why I'm hard of hearing? Well, I got infected with Oripathy back when I was doing research near a volcano...

char_180_amgoat_CN_004.voiceText: Besides completing the tasks you give me, I have to go to Dr. Kal'tsit regularly for checkups. The doctor said my symptoms are pretty serious...

char_180_amgoat_CN_005.voiceText: I have to work hard to finish the research my parents began! I want to prove that their work was meaningful, and that it could maybe even change the world!

char_180_amgoat_CN_006.voiceText: My parents... they've passed on. A pyroclastic flow hit them when they were conducting studies near a volcano... I have to pick up where they left off and finish their research, no matter what!

char_180_amgoat_CN_007.voiceText: My playmates? I'm pretty friendly with Mousse and some others, so I don't feel lonely at all! If possible, I'd love to start a book club with them too. Could we hold our club meetings in your office, Professor?

char_180_amgoat_CN_008.voiceText: Dr. Kal'tsit told me... I'm losing not only my sense of hearing, but my sense of sight too. …Well, what else might this disease do to me?

char_180_amgoat_CN_009.voiceText: How could I tell you were behind me? Because I could feel your warmth! My eyesight and hearing aren't as sharp as they once were, but my other senses are still the same. Can't bring me down this easily, you know!

char_180_amgoat_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Eyjafjalla. My career before joining Rhodes Island was in the field of volcanology. I'm a bit hard of hearing due to my Oripathy. I just hope I won't be a burden to you, Professor.

char_180_amgoat_CN_012.voiceText: Please teach me all you can, Professor.

char_180_amgoat_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion? Really? I'm so happy to have your approval, Professor!

char_180_amgoat_CN_014.voiceText: My mother gave me these little lambs. They're cute, aren't they? Huh? They're scorching hot? Be careful! You have to put on oven mittens before touching them!

char_180_amgoat_CN_018.voiceText: Don't forget to prepare emergency supplies as well as weapons!

char_180_amgoat_CN_019.voiceText: We can take care of ourselves, Professor. You just focus on giving orders.

char_180_amgoat_CN_026.voiceText: This may be a little hot...

char_180_amgoat_CN_029.voiceText: I'm so glad you're safe, Professor...
