char_180_amgoat_CN_030.voiceText: Why must our world be enveloped in strife?

char_180_amgoat_CN_031.voiceText: Is everyone okay? Anything I can do?

char_180_amgoat_CN_032.voiceText: Ow... It's... It's okay... I'm fine...

char_180_amgoat_CN_033.voiceText: This room makes me feel safe.

char_180_amgoat_CN_036.voiceText: Thank you, Professor, for helping me become a stronger person.

char_185_frncat_CN_002.voiceText: Laterano cakes are so delicious! But we operators have to pay attention to our diet, right?... aww...

char_185_frncat_CN_003.voiceText: Not my gloves... I'm sorry, I can't take my gloves off... I don't want you to see my hands. That's the one thing I ask... sorry…

char_185_frncat_CN_004.voiceText: A-Are we departing now? Al-Alright, let me just prepare one moment...!

char_185_frncat_CN_005.voiceText: Do you think it's odd that I have two tails? Do-do-do I look even stranger than I thought? Umm...

char_185_frncat_CN_006.voiceText: When my symptoms aren't flaring up, my hand stays all normal... It feels so nice, just being able to hold the kitties like this...

char_185_frncat_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, what kind of cake do you prefer? Mango, or matcha? I tried making a few, and... you already ate? Oh, umm, Okay...

char_185_frncat_CN_008.voiceText: D-Doctor! Sora... sh-she's the super idol, Sora, isn't she?! I'd recognize her anywhere! I'm her biggest fan! Why is she here at Rhodes Island? And... and... can I ask her for an autograph?

char_185_frncat_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, have you heard of the Avenue des Champs-Élysées? Yes, I happened to be born there. I really wish I could go back and visit one day... what? Oh, no, I appreciate it, but I'm not lonely. I have you, after all! You're my family.

char_185_frncat_CN_010.voiceText: Aw... Doctor... why are you ignoring me...

char_185_frncat_CN_011.voiceText: Good day... p-please call me Mousse. And... and please don't stare at my hand so much...

char_185_frncat_CN_012.voiceText: This is a favor I'll never forget!

char_185_frncat_CN_013.voiceText: Huh? Pro...promotion?! I-I'm not prepared for this...

char_185_frncat_CN_014.voiceText: Doctor, I know there's a limit to what I can accomplish, so I swear... I'll do all that I'm able, as well as I'm able! It's... It's the only way I could ever repay you, Doctor...

char_185_frncat_CN_018.voiceText: This is in my hands! You can do this, Mousse!

char_185_frncat_CN_019.voiceText: I essentially blend into the walls, so I'm a good choice for scouting...

char_185_frncat_CN_020.voiceText: Scouting complete. Sending you enemy coordinates.

char_185_frncat_CN_024.voiceText: From now on, this is my battle...!

char_185_frncat_CN_029.voiceText: It was a tough fight... but I stayed steady through it all...!

char_185_frncat_CN_030.voiceText: Yay... Oh, oh, sorry, it's not that I like battles that much, but...

char_185_frncat_CN_031.voiceText: D-Did I drag us all down?

char_185_frncat_CN_033.voiceText: E-Excuse me... May I come in...?

char_185_frncat_CN_036.voiceText: D-Doctor... I really can't hold it in anymore... do we have a scratching post? Urghh...

char_150_snakek_CN_001.voiceText: Here I am! What should we play, baseball or board games? Oh, you're working?

char_150_snakek_CN_002.voiceText: Where was I born, you ask? Well, umm...no idea. But that doesn't matter, right?

char_150_snakek_CN_003.voiceText: Hello, Professor Rhodes Island! Wait, am I calling you by the right name?...

char_150_snakek_CN_004.voiceText: Hm, what's my assignment today? To capture some long, sleek animals?

char_150_snakek_CN_005.voiceText: Hey! Don't knock on my backpack! Oh, sorry, I'm not mad, I'm just worried. If you're not careful, you could hurt your hand! Here, let me show you how it's done.

char_150_snakek_CN_006.voiceText: If anyone dares to hurt you, I'll smash them with my baseball bat. Oh, uh... so... there really are people who hurt you? Um... actually, I'm not that good at fighting, hehe…

char_150_snakek_CN_007.voiceText: I love spending the whole day just walking down the street. I get to watch the people, enjoy the sunshine, and then… lose my way!

char_150_snakek_CN_008.voiceText: You've been treating my sickness, and you gave me a place to live... you're really so kind...

char_150_snakek_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, are you my big brother? Or big sister?... Well, does't matter! I'm not leaving you, even if you throw me out! It's not like I can walk far anyway.

char_150_snakek_CN_010.voiceText: Oh, the Doctor is busy. I'll just play by myself then...

char_150_snakek_CN_011.voiceText: Hm? Where am I? Who am I?

char_150_snakek_CN_012.voiceText: I can make myself super tough! It's my only special skill!

char_150_snakek_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion? What's a promotion?... Whatever, let's play for a bit longer! You and me, together!

char_150_snakek_CN_014.voiceText: New position or not, I don't really care. All I want is to be by your side every day. Can you grant this tiny wish of mine?

char_150_snakek_CN_017.voiceText: I've got lots of friends here!

char_150_snakek_CN_019.voiceText: We'll be fine if we stick together!

char_150_snakek_CN_026.voiceText: C'mon, show me what you got!

char_150_snakek_CN_029.voiceText: Was that tough? Didn't feel much different from any other battle.

char_150_snakek_CN_033.voiceText: Just don't throw fireballs at me, okay?

char_150_snakek_CN_036.voiceText: Hey Doctor! Can we play a little bit longer? Just a little bit!

char_130_doberm_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, are the new recruits keeping up with my basic training regimen?

char_130_doberm_CN_002.voiceText: A balanced, regular diet is also an important part of daily training. Any complainers get fifty laps around the deck.

char_130_doberm_CN_003.voiceText: As a military instructor, it's important to achieve the perfect balance between strictness and leniency. To be honest... I may be a bit too hard on Fang...

char_130_doberm_CN_004.voiceText: When putting your Operators into squads, it's crucial to assign them positions where they can exercise their skills to the fullest. It's true that Operators' ability is important, what's really being tested here is your judgement.

char_130_doberm_CN_005.voiceText: Doctor, when training Operators, you need to work on spiritual fulfillment as much as improving their physiques and skills. After all, they need to be mentally strong enough to survive interrogations and all sorts of attacks on their minds.

char_130_doberm_CN_006.voiceText: You're looking for the newbies? They're training out on the deck. Yes, I do realize what the weather's like right now. Of course I do.

char_130_doberm_CN_007.voiceText: Anomalies... ha. You can never fool the eyes of the 'Hound'.

char_130_doberm_CN_008.voiceText: If you believe that command allows you to slack off whenever you want, then I WILL correct your misconception, Doctor.

char_130_doberm_CN_009.voiceText: If I hope to remain at your side through all the difficulties to come, I must be even harder on myself. After all, with the world around us being what it is... the only way we can keep it together is to keep training our mental strength.

char_130_doberm_CN_011.voiceText: Attention! I am Dobermann, former military instructor for the Bolívarian armed forces. Now, let's cut to the chase. Hand over the list of Operators in need of training.

char_130_doberm_CN_012.voiceText: This is how our training pays off.

char_130_doberm_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion, huh? Thanks. I'm just doing my job.

char_130_doberm_CN_014.voiceText: The responsibility for training the future of Rhodes Island is on my shoulders. I will do my best to be worthy of that responsibility.

char_130_doberm_CN_018.voiceText: Then show me the briefing docs for the mission.

char_130_doberm_CN_019.voiceText: Calling all hands. This is not a drill!

char_130_doberm_CN_029.voiceText: No matter the challenges we face, strong fundamental combat skills can mean the difference between life and death.

char_130_doberm_CN_030.voiceText: Come back when you're less mediocre.

char_130_doberm_CN_031.voiceText: The operation was successful, but we still have room for improvement.

char_130_doberm_CN_032.voiceText: We have failed. I am the one to blame.

char_130_doberm_CN_033.voiceText: The newbies are intimidated by me, you say? That's only natural.

char_130_doberm_CN_036.voiceText: You want to cheer me up? Hm, let me interrogate someone, then.

char_163_hpsts_CN_001.voiceText: Hm? You want to watch me forge weapons? Sure, but be careful not to get singed.

char_163_hpsts_CN_002.voiceText: Only weapons that are never in use will remain undamaged. Therefore, leaving a weapon spotless is actually the worst sacrilege for it.

char_163_hpsts_CN_003.voiceText: The modernized weaponry and equipment manufacturing processes have left many traditional craftsmen jobless. But those who can't keep up with the times will of course be left behind... that's only natural.

char_163_hpsts_CN_004.voiceText: Firearms... these weapons will truly change the world completely.

char_163_hpsts_CN_005.voiceText: My right leg? Oh, it's fine. You know, all craftsmen make mistakes.

char_163_hpsts_CN_006.voiceText: Thank you for giving me a chance to show what I can do.

char_163_hpsts_CN_007.voiceText: You saw my name engraved on some equipment? No... that's not me.

char_163_hpsts_CN_008.voiceText: With steel and copper as the core...

char_163_hpsts_CN_009.voiceText: My greatest wish is for the hammer I forged to come in useful to you.

char_163_hpsts_CN_010.voiceText: They're promoting new drinks at the bar. What should I have today?

char_163_hpsts_CN_011.voiceText: They call me Vulcan. I can do maintenance for your damaged weapons if you want. Oh, by the way, the forging equipment I need is all listed here in this blueprint.

char_163_hpsts_CN_012.voiceText: Ah, I'm feeling inspired. Get the blower machine ready, it's time to get down to business.

char_163_hpsts_CN_013.voiceText: I see that you, too, understand the importance of an excellent craftsperson to a military organization.

char_163_hpsts_CN_014.voiceText: Keeping your weapons in good condition is the best way to keep yourself safe. Ah, you agree with me? I see that I've finally found my soulmate.

char_163_hpsts_CN_017.voiceText: I just want to... focus on my work.

char_163_hpsts_CN_018.voiceText: Leader? Well, if I have to... Still, compared to giving orders, I'm much better at designing and manufacturing weapons.

char_163_hpsts_CN_019.voiceText: Can't I just stay behind and work?

char_163_hpsts_CN_028.voiceText: I'll destroy your weapon with my next blow!

char_163_hpsts_CN_029.voiceText: If you pick up some enemy equipment, show it to me. Could be useful for future development.

char_163_hpsts_CN_030.voiceText: A victory, just as expected! That's why we need high-quality weapons.

char_163_hpsts_CN_031.voiceText: Please submit a damage report for each of your weapons. I will work on repairs when we get back.

char_163_hpsts_CN_032.voiceText: My crafting skills are still lacking...

char_163_hpsts_CN_036.voiceText: Any equipment you have in mind? I can try making it for you.

char_144_red_CN_002.voiceText: I prefer to work alone, by myself.

char_144_red_CN_003.voiceText: Name, bounty, kill. Simple. That's the agreement with Kal'tsit.

char_144_red_CN_004.voiceText: Wolves have fangs, I have my blade. Wolves do not rest, neither do I.

char_144_red_CN_005.voiceText: Granny's calling... I can hear her.

char_144_red_CN_006.voiceText: Bleak wind, corpses on the ground, screams under the stars... I smell them all, the scent of wolves. I join the hunt.

char_144_red_CN_007.voiceText: Family? I have no family. I am always alone. Do you need a family, Doctor?

char_144_red_CN_008.voiceText: They avoid me... I just want to touch their tails. Provence's and Texas's... I like their scent.

char_144_red_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, sometimes I wonder... if I weren't a wolf hunter, would my life be different? Oh, you mean… I should answer the question... myself?

char_144_red_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor... no, nothing. I thought you fell asleep. Don't sleep, not now.

char_144_red_CN_011.voiceText: Projekt Red, wolf hunter, smells wolves.

char_144_red_CN_012.voiceText: As long as it helps me hunt.

char_144_red_CN_014.voiceText: A promotion? This will disguise me. I accept.

char_144_red_CN_028.voiceText: Your death... is in my eyes.

char_144_red_CN_030.voiceText: The one way a hunt can end.

char_144_red_CN_032.voiceText: Sorry... My blade... not sharp enough.

char_144_red_CN_033.voiceText: I prefer to be outside. But… it's okay.

char_144_red_CN_034.voiceText: Watch your hand. I might cut you.

char_140_whitew_CN_001.voiceText: Hey, Doctor. Hope you don't mind if I bring my weapons inside. I'll plop myself right over here.

char_140_whitew_CN_002.voiceText: Somebody out to get you, huh? Then have a long, hard think about who you might've wronged in the past.

char_140_whitew_CN_003.voiceText: If someone's out for revenge on you, don't hesitate, just take them out. Once you decide to pick up a weapon, you don't need a reason to kill.

char_140_whitew_CN_004.voiceText: It's been a while... I see that Texas made some friends. Hehehe.. Fascinating! Can't wait to get to know them!

char_140_whitew_CN_005.voiceText: You think I'm an assassin, huh? Yeah, alright. Call me whatever you want. I can be anyone, do anything, kill anyone anytime. Just so long as I want to!

char_140_whitew_CN_006.voiceText: I love power, Doctor. And you offered me a job where I can use my power to my heart's content... Love it. Honestly, the only joy I get out of this insane world is using my power to conquer it.

char_140_whitew_CN_007.voiceText: Texas? Ha, she's afraid of me, but I don't wanna do anything to her, except maybe try to bring back the old Texas. The one we got here's a cowardly pup.

char_140_whitew_CN_008.voiceText: That red one... oh... Doctor, keep her away from me! She'd definitely kill me in a fight. But I have this feeling... this feeling... ugh, why do I want to fight her so bad?

char_140_whitew_CN_009.voiceText: You want to know what happened between me and Texas? Hehe, you don't have a single idea of what you are sticking your nose into. You'll find out the truth someday, but not from me.

char_140_whitew_CN_010.voiceText: Sleep tight... enjoy your sweet dreams while you still can.

char_140_whitew_CN_011.voiceText: A great evil stands in the way of justice. My master, in the name of hatred and revenge, lead the weak onward!

char_140_whitew_CN_012.voiceText: Don't you just love how I keep getting more and more powerful?

char_140_whitew_CN_013.voiceText: Hahaha! Yeah, I love how much you trust me. Can't say the same for Texas, huh?

char_140_whitew_CN_014.voiceText: Ohh yeah, that's more like it! Strength, unfettered and unchained! That's what I'm talking about!

char_140_whitew_CN_019.voiceText: Haha, you people... I don't think I'll even remember your faces after this one... Anyway, let's just get started.

char_140_whitew_CN_020.voiceText: We're fighting you guys? Then please do your bestest job, or I'll be reeeally bored.

char_140_whitew_CN_025.voiceText: Come on, just a little bit more! You almost got me!

char_140_whitew_CN_028.voiceText: You'll have to try harder than that!

char_140_whitew_CN_030.voiceText: Hahaha, sliced 'em up like a mille-feuille. How do you like it?

char_140_whitew_CN_031.voiceText: Not my best work. You can lay it on me for letting a few get away.

char_140_whitew_CN_032.voiceText: Perfect! Now I want to crush them that much harder! Hahaha!

char_140_whitew_CN_033.voiceText: Hm? Did I see a red shadow flash by?

char_140_whitew_CN_036.voiceText: The more I get to know you, the better I understand Texas. Love it.

char_171_bldsk_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, Dr. Kal'tsit sent me to take a blood sample from you. We can chat as I'm getting the needle ready.

char_171_bldsk_CN_002.voiceText: Can I control the urge to feed, you ask? How dare you underestimate me! I'm a trained professional. Of course I can tell patients from food!

char_171_bldsk_CN_003.voiceText: It's my job to track blood indicators for all our operators, even if they aren't exactly happy about it—huh...? These blood bags? They're samples, of course! What were you thinking!?

char_171_bldsk_CN_004.voiceText: There's another one of my kind here. And she's an... engineer? Hm…maybe she likes the smell of machine oil more than blood?

char_171_bldsk_CN_005.voiceText: Why I chose to become a doctor? I can't say it was any sort of lofty calling. It's just that, you know, OUR kind... we don't exactly have the brightest prospects. But it turned out my skills were actually in surprisingly high demand, so... I just went with the flow.

char_171_bldsk_CN_006.voiceText: How do we fight the urge to feed? We actually have a course that helps us control our desires. And we've invented artificial blood, so we drink that if we need. We can be very resourceful, you know.

char_171_bldsk_CN_007.voiceText: This is the standard procedure. It's the same for everyone getting blood drawn. Don't move, Doctor. Ah... blood... your blood... it smells delicious... It's just… it's just… captivating...

char_171_bldsk_CN_008.voiceText: Replenishing saline solution! Changing filters! Sterilizing sand and charcoal canisters... all done! Doctor, you'd better keep your medical supplies well-maintained. As Dr. Kal'tsit said, when your kidneys give out, these machines are going to save your life... aw, come on, just kidding.

char_171_bldsk_CN_009.voiceText: Fine, fine, I'll come clean... I have tasted lots of blood of many different types from all different races. And I do enjoy the subtle differences in flavor, okay? In fact, the only type of blood I've never tasted is... yours, Doctor. Heheh...

char_171_bldsk_CN_010.voiceText: Hm? So you still have time to sleep? I'm jealous.

char_171_bldsk_CN_011.voiceText: I am Warfarin, the blood-scientist-slash-doctor. Besides typical healing Arts, I also bring you specialized medical treatments, courtesy of my remarkable expertise in hematology and plentiful experience. Anyway, look forward to working with you.

char_171_bldsk_CN_012.voiceText: Hm, my work efficiency seems to have improved.

char_171_bldsk_CN_013.voiceText: Are you even listening? We're having trouble collecting rare blood types for the emergency blood bank. So—what? What did you say? A promotion? Now?

char_171_bldsk_CN_014.voiceText: This only means more work for me, right? Ha, I saw that a mile away! I'm an expert in this field after all. Don't worry, I am well prepared!

char_171_bldsk_CN_017.voiceText: Wait, I need to prepare my equipment first.

char_171_bldsk_CN_018.voiceText: A leader reports only to you, right?

char_171_bldsk_CN_019.voiceText: My equipment is ready. We can start any time.

char_171_bldsk_CN_020.voiceText: I don't have the leisure for enemy intel at the moment. Taking care of our operators has already occupied my whole schedule...

char_171_bldsk_CN_023.voiceText: Call for help immediately if you're injured!

char_171_bldsk_CN_029.voiceText: It's really nerve-wracking being in the medic squad. Support troops are really under lots of pressure! Good thing I'm already used to it.

char_171_bldsk_CN_030.voiceText: The battlefield is a place of tragedy. I hope they come to understand this one day.

char_171_bldsk_CN_031.voiceText: Forget about those fleeing enemies at the moment, our priority now is to help the injured.

char_171_bldsk_CN_032.voiceText: I am sorry, we've even ran out reserve medicine…

char_171_bldsk_CN_033.voiceText: I guess I'm more accustomed to figuring things out myself...

char_171_bldsk_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, isn't it almost time for your annual checkup?

char_002_amiya_CN_002.voiceText: Dr. Kal'tsit told me you have to be 100% focused on your work to maximize efficiency. So... yes, that's what I'm gonna do!

char_002_amiya_CN_003.voiceText: Rhodes Island has achieved cruising speed, Doctor. Would you mind sorting out the navigation log for me?

char_002_amiya_CN_004.voiceText: I still have a lot to learn as leader of Rhodes Island. I hope you'll be there to guide me on our path to the future.

char_002_amiya_CN_005.voiceText: Maybe it's just wishful thinking, but I hope Rhodes Island can be like a second home to everyone.

char_002_amiya_CN_006.voiceText: Making it this far has cost us so much. Sometimes, I can't help but ask myself... is it really worth it?

char_002_amiya_CN_007.voiceText: Sometimes I remember where I came from... It was cold, and the air smelled of rusted copper. Rhodes Island is a cozy place in comparison. I'll do everything I can to protect our home.

char_002_amiya_CN_008.voiceText: Hehe… Dr. {@nickname}, let me tell you something: I picked up the violin again.

char_002_amiya_CN_009.voiceText: We've still got a long, long way to go, Doctor. This might be a journey without an end, but as long as you're with me, we'll be okay.

char_002_amiya_CN_010.voiceText: There's still lots of work that needs to be done, Doctor. We can't afford to have you resting.

char_002_amiya_CN_011.voiceText: I'm so glad you're back, Doctor. Now we can walk this path together, me with you, and you with me.

char_002_amiya_CN_012.voiceText: I see... thank you, Doctor! I've learned so much from you.

char_002_amiya_CN_013.voiceText: I'm so excited to fight by your side again, Doctor!

char_002_amiya_CN_014.voiceText: What I saw that day... the despair stuck in my throat, hopelessly trying to scream... I want to bury it all deep inside my mind and never let it out…

char_002_amiya_CN_029.voiceText: No matter how difficult the mission, we can handle it as long as you're here, Doctor. I've never doubted you.

char_002_amiya_CN_030.voiceText: We may have achieved a perfect victory, but we still can't let our guard down.

char_002_amiya_CN_031.voiceText: Well done, Doctor! You must be exhausted. Be sure to rest when you need it.

char_002_amiya_CN_032.voiceText: I'm fine... Get it together, everyone!

char_002_amiya_CN_033.voiceText: You want something to drink, Doctor?

char_110_deepcl_CN_001.voiceText: Good morning, Doctor. Can I paint a portrait of you? And don't worry, I'll try not to... bring it to life. Besides, I'm not capable of bringing EVERYTHING to life, you know!

char_110_deepcl_CN_002.voiceText: I feel like I'm not supposed to appear here...

char_110_deepcl_CN_003.voiceText: Doctor... what color are you, reflected in my eyes?

char_110_deepcl_CN_004.voiceText: There are lots of fun creative resources here at Rhodes Island! I'm feeling inspired...

char_110_deepcl_CN_005.voiceText: See my adorable 'assistants'? Oh, you think they're scary? No way! They're the cutest babies!

char_110_deepcl_CN_006.voiceText: Ha, so this is your color? Look into my eyes, then... paint me in your colors.

char_110_deepcl_CN_007.voiceText: That's right. Even if no one understands me, I'll continue to make art. No matter what monsters my works turn into...

char_110_deepcl_CN_008.voiceText: We artists are a unique breed... we get stuck at least thirty days a month and think everything we produce is garbage. Also, we only become inspired after midnight.

char_110_deepcl_CN_009.voiceText: The battered world, paint peeling, finally closes its eyes in its dark depths—that's right, darkness is the true color of the ocean. Black is the only color you see, you say? Wait till I share all I know with you...

char_110_deepcl_CN_010.voiceText: Are you... dreaming? Is the world in your dreams as colorful as the beings in this world, Doctor?...

char_110_deepcl_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Deepcolor, a painter. That's right, just a 'painter', nothing more.

char_110_deepcl_CN_013.voiceText: Um, could you just... stop caring about me? If you keep treating me like this... like I matter... I-I don't know what will become of me...

char_110_deepcl_CN_014.voiceText: Thank you, Doctor. Now, let's complete this piece of art, shall we?

char_110_deepcl_CN_017.voiceText: Me? Going to battle? Are you nuts?

char_110_deepcl_CN_018.voiceText: I can't lead that many people.

char_110_deepcl_CN_025.voiceText: No need to be in such a hurry.

char_110_deepcl_CN_027.voiceText: You gotta get past my 'assistants' first.

char_110_deepcl_CN_028.voiceText: Can you defeat these little ones?

char_110_deepcl_CN_029.voiceText: If you really make me mad... you won't want to know what happens next.

char_110_deepcl_CN_030.voiceText: I need to sketch these victorious heroes.

char_110_deepcl_CN_031.voiceText: Aw, got my clothes dirty again...

char_110_deepcl_CN_032.voiceText: If only the end of the battle could be erased and redone, like a sketch.

char_110_deepcl_CN_033.voiceText: This room's got a nice design.

char_110_deepcl_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, since we happen to have some time off, wanna see my newest work?

char_166_skfire_CN_001.voiceText: The fire alarm's blaring? Sorry, must be because I was passing by your office. It... it causes my body to heat up, you know...

char_166_skfire_CN_002.voiceText: There's no language that's impossible to learn, no Arts that are impossible to understand. Isn't that the truth, plain and simple? ...What? I'm the exception to the rule, you say?

char_166_skfire_CN_003.voiceText: My life plans? ...Tch, it was all going swimmingly until that dreadful attack. But after Reunion murdered Phil, their eradication moved up to the top of my to-do list.

char_166_skfire_CN_004.voiceText: Rhodes Island's methods aren't nearly tough enough. They'll only drag King's Wand down.

char_166_skfire_CN_005.voiceText: Can you talk to Amiya for me? Poor girl, her kind heart clouds her judgment. As far as I'm concerned, total annihilation is the only fitting end for an undesirable.

char_166_skfire_CN_006.voiceText: Your current skills can't compare to even the average level of a King's Wand member such as myself. Ha, right, I'm powerful... and the power of all five of us put together... words can't begin to describe.

char_166_skfire_CN_007.voiceText: Shichiyou's blade was a gift from Shiro. Heard that the former owner before Shiro was a swordsmaster who could fell all the cherry blossoms of the Far East with a single swing. But even that legendary swordsmaster was no match for Shiro and had to surrender the blade.

char_166_skfire_CN_008.voiceText: What happened to your shirt? What? I burned it? But... impossible... my self-control is impeccable, I think...? I... well, I'm sorry. Really sorry.

char_166_skfire_CN_009.voiceText: We might be on opposite ends of the spectrum when it comes to ideals, but I do enjoy watching the people of Rhodes Island sweating away with bright hopes for the future. Yep, that's a compliment. It's a heartwarming sight.

char_166_skfire_CN_010.voiceText: How lazy. So you think it's fine to just sleep here and waste away the precious day?

char_166_skfire_CN_011.voiceText: I am Skyfire of King's Wand. I will remain at Rhodes Island until my objective is accomplished. What's my objective, you ask? To burn every last Reunion thug to ashes, of course.

char_166_skfire_CN_012.voiceText: This is no way to force me to unleash my true power.

char_166_skfire_CN_014.voiceText: Ha. Enjoying the privileges I deserve from time to time is a good way to relax.

char_166_skfire_CN_017.voiceText: The battlefield needs some heating up.

char_166_skfire_CN_018.voiceText: The rays of the sun are my shield.

char_166_skfire_CN_020.voiceText: Kneel before the flame of the heavens.

char_166_skfire_CN_023.voiceText: Bad luck is always lying in wait for the weak.

char_166_skfire_CN_024.voiceText: The wise always take the initiative.

char_166_skfire_CN_027.voiceText: The flames of the sun shall devour you!

char_166_skfire_CN_028.voiceText: The rays of the skies will set you aflame!

char_166_skfire_CN_029.voiceText: There is no soul that can survive the sunflame.

char_166_skfire_CN_030.voiceText: Pathetic... you're nothing but ashes now. Not a trace left behind.

char_166_skfire_CN_032.voiceText: No way... impossible... how could I have...

char_166_skfire_CN_033.voiceText: Can't you prepare a room with a lower temperature for me?

char_166_skfire_CN_034.voiceText: Are you trying to get your hand burnt?

char_166_skfire_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, can you explain this theory to me? All I need is 12 minutes of your time.

char_240_wyvern_CN_002.voiceText: The two seniors from the BPRS squad are here too? In that case... Could you assign me to their squards in future missions, Doctor?

char_240_wyvern_CN_003.voiceText: Huff... huff... three more sets of physical training and I'll be half-done for today. Doctor... please... fetch my water bottle for me...

char_240_wyvern_CN_004.voiceText: You want to know about my hometown? My hometown… it's a cruel wilderness. Even survival itself is a difficult feat there. Compared to that, Rhodes Island is like heaven.

char_240_wyvern_CN_005.voiceText: I've become stronger than when I was an intern for Blacksteel.

char_240_wyvern_CN_007.voiceText: The 22nd rule of Blacksteel: 'Anyone who loses her weapon no longer belongs here.' That's why I always bring my hellebarde with me wherever I go. The rule doesn't apply to everyday situations, you say? But... if I remember correctly... wait, let me check. 'This rule only applies to contracted Operators and new recruits under training.' What?... Ms. Franka didn't tell me about this part...

char_240_wyvern_CN_008.voiceText: Instructor Dobermann's really got a heart of stone! Why choose me other than anyone elase to deal with all those live Originium slugs? I... I just can't!

char_240_wyvern_CN_009.voiceText: I think I know now why Franka and Liskarm decided to stay at Rhodes Island. Compared to Blacksteel, this is a place we can call home. There's lots of fun things to do here besides the missions...

char_240_wyvern_CN_010.voiceText: Shh, the Doctor's having a rest now. Keep your volume down, would you?

char_240_wyvern_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Vanilla, trainee Operator from Blacksteel. Looking forward to learning from you, Doctor.

char_240_wyvern_CN_012.voiceText: It's time to organize my notes. I need to digest what I've just learned.

char_240_wyvern_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion medal? For me? My-my sincerest gratitude!

char_240_wyvern_CN_018.voiceText: Me, the leader? Are you sure about that?

char_240_wyvern_CN_020.voiceText: I will not bring shame to Blacksteel!

char_240_wyvern_CN_026.voiceText: This hellebarde isn't just for show!

char_240_wyvern_CN_027.voiceText: Battles aren't always won by the most experienced!

char_240_wyvern_CN_031.voiceText: If we worked a bit harder, we could have done better.

char_240_wyvern_CN_032.voiceText: I... I'm still not strong enough...

char_240_wyvern_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, would you like to dine with me tonight?

char_236_rope_CN_001.voiceText: Doc~tor~, you didn't forget anything, did you?

char_236_rope_CN_002.voiceText: Picking pockets to feed myself? Yeah, that was how I grew up. I didn't exactly have a choice. I woulda starved to death otherwise.

char_236_rope_CN_003.voiceText: If you want sturdy grappling hooks, the key thing's a good rope. Hm? Why do I like my hook so much? Well, go scale a building with your bare hands and you'll see.

char_236_rope_CN_004.voiceText: Fine, fine, your word's the word, Doctor. Can I go back to my room now? I've got stuff coming up. What? Still no? C'mooon, cut me some slack! Pleasie please?

char_236_rope_CN_005.voiceText: If it wasn't you Rhodes Island, I'd probably still be rotting in jail. Say, how'd you find me anyway? Hmm… Maybe you heard about my skill through the grapevine?

char_236_rope_CN_006.voiceText: There's lots of ways if you wanna survive in the slums, though more people simply die without a way at all. Never had much of a choice myself. Hope you can understand, Doctor.

char_236_rope_CN_007.voiceText: My parents kicked me out, and I had to fend for myself on the streets. Compared to my days in the gutter, life at Rhodes Island is a massive improvement.

char_236_rope_CN_008.voiceText: Saw a lot of people get same disease as mine who didn't end well. I kinda gave up on myself too, until I got lucky enough to be found by you guys… Tell me straight, Doctor. You can cure me, right? You...you can't? *Sigh*, I can live with that, I guess.

char_236_rope_CN_009.voiceText: Before, I was always looking for the next meal. Now I can really eat my fill. Gotta hand it to you, Rhodes Island's alright in my book. Huh? You wanna hear me say 'thank you'? Nah-ah, in, your, dreams. *Gasp*, I just said it...

char_236_rope_CN_010.voiceText: Ugh, this chair... ahhh….dangit... so comfy...!

char_236_rope_CN_011.voiceText: The name's Rope, nice to meet ya. Oh, here's your ID card, don't forget it. Huh? Why do I have it? That's a se-cret!

char_236_rope_CN_012.voiceText: Does watching this stuff actually help?

char_236_rope_CN_013.voiceText: C'mon, lets talk about payment. Promotions are cool, but my salary is what really matters.

char_236_rope_CN_014.voiceText: Fine, fine. Now that I've got my due, I guess I should give my best.

char_236_rope_CN_018.voiceText: I'm doing captain biz? I would've asked for a bonus usually, but I can let this slide since it's you.

char_236_rope_CN_019.voiceText: Look at the map and figure out your route before we get in there. This is experience talking.

char_236_rope_CN_020.voiceText: So, what kind of good stuff will our enemies be carrying today?

char_236_rope_CN_021.voiceText: I don't really do straight-up fights.

char_236_rope_CN_022.voiceText: Put me to good use, ooo-kaaay?

char_236_rope_CN_024.voiceText: Hmm, is this a good spot?

char_236_rope_CN_028.voiceText: Once I hook you, you're not getting away.

char_236_rope_CN_029.voiceText: A lot more excitement on that one than usual! A lot more profit too... whoo-hoo~!

char_236_rope_CN_030.voiceText: It'd be a waste to leave all that good stuff here. The enemies don't need them anyway, right?

char_236_rope_CN_031.voiceText: Some of 'em got away? Just leave them be. They might turn over a new leaf, who knows.

char_236_rope_CN_032.voiceText: Hey! Let's just bug out now, Doctor! We must save ourselves first!

char_236_rope_CN_033.voiceText: Is there an air vent in this room? Nothing, just curious.

char_236_rope_CN_036.voiceText: I mean, I'd like to figure out how a normal girl lives sometime... but, you know... I mean, maybe that's not really me?

char_237_gravel_CN_001.voiceText: Aaaahhh! You want me to stay by your side? I can barely keep my heart in my chest!

char_237_gravel_CN_003.voiceText: Don't mind me, just continue with your work.

char_237_gravel_CN_004.voiceText: Hmm? What am I looking at? Why, you, of course!

char_237_gravel_CN_005.voiceText: If that's what you ask, Doctor, I will do what it takes to become stronger.

char_237_gravel_CN_006.voiceText: Heheh... You don't need to worry about any ambushes or assassination attempts. Because I'll aaalways be here with you.

char_237_gravel_CN_007.voiceText: Are you finally... a little bit interested in me now? Well, I've always been a big bit interested in you.

char_237_gravel_CN_008.voiceText: Thanks for taking such good care of me these days. By my knighthood of Kazimierz, I hereby pledge to repay your kindness with my life—huh? You're not used to me talking this way? But I'm an honest-to-goodness knight. Surely I can improvise a speech or two.

char_237_gravel_CN_009.voiceText: Ever since I was taken away to Kazimierz, it's rare for someone to be so kind to me. So, if you don't mind, Doctor... I, Gravel—no, I Senomy, on my honor as a knight, shall serve you always at your side.

char_237_gravel_CN_010.voiceText: When I'm here with you, don't you feel your heart racing?

char_237_gravel_CN_011.voiceText: Mmmwah. Hm? What's wrong? Your face is beet red. That's just how I say hello. Don't think too much about it. Anyway, I'm Gravel, a knight of Kazimierz. It's a pleasure. Heheh.

char_237_gravel_CN_012.voiceText: Are you the one who comes up with all the Rhodes Island's battle tactics, Doctor? Oh~ that's even more intriguing.

char_237_gravel_CN_013.voiceText: You think I'm doing well, Doctor? Yaay!

char_237_gravel_CN_014.voiceText: This means you need me, doesn't it? Heheh.

char_237_gravel_CN_017.voiceText: You want to go together? Hehe...

char_237_gravel_CN_027.voiceText: You really think you'll get away?

char_237_gravel_CN_029.voiceText: Of course the Doctor's tactics are flawless~

char_237_gravel_CN_030.voiceText: My blade hasn't even been stained red yet... hehe...

char_237_gravel_CN_031.voiceText: Run all you like, Let's see how far you can get.

char_237_gravel_CN_032.voiceText: Sorry... did I... mess up again...?

char_237_gravel_CN_033.voiceText: Hmm, looks like there's a lot of good hiding places here in this room~

char_237_gravel_CN_036.voiceText: Yes. I'm right here, always and forever.

char_286_cast3_CN_001.voiceText: Thank you for choosing Castle-3! I am honored to serve as your assistant, Doctor.

char_286_cast3_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor, please do not be intimidated by my appearance. My sturdy metal shell, modified by Master Closure herself, will make you invincible on the battlefield.

char_286_cast3_CN_003.voiceText: Warning: be careful not to strike my case too hard. It may damage me.

char_286_cast3_CN_004.voiceText: The topography in the wild may be treacherous, but Castle-3 is fitted with an engine with outstanding performance and a 4WD mode, to whisk you away from danger.

char_286_cast3_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, if your life is ever in danger, just summon Castle-3! Castle-3 was created specifically for combat purposes. I am a top-class defensive warfighting robot.

char_286_cast3_CN_008.voiceText: Castle-3 is honored to be at your side. Doctor, should you require me to strike down your foes, I shall go through heaven and hell to see it done!

char_286_cast3_CN_009.voiceText: Castle-3's official manager is 'Master Closure,'but please understand that you are even more important to Castle-3 than Master is, in most cases. I am your devoted, trustworthy battle companion!

char_286_cast3_CN_010.voiceText: Entering sleep mode. Press any button to wake.

char_286_cast3_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, Doctor. Thank you for choosing Castle-3. Tap anywhere to initialize startup options.

char_286_cast3_CN_012.voiceText: Firmware upgrade complete. Restart required. Please click anywhere to restart.

char_286_cast3_CN_017.voiceText: Device scan complete. All communications working as normal. Castle-3 is on standby, awaiting your orders.

char_286_cast3_CN_018.voiceText: Understood. Castle-3 is your best choice, Doctor, to lead a squad against enemy formations!

char_286_cast3_CN_019.voiceText: Next, Castle-3 will show you its true power as an industrial battle platform!

char_286_cast3_CN_020.voiceText: Enemy unit located. Ready for attack.

char_286_cast3_CN_026.voiceText: Enemies, you are forbidden to advance.

char_286_cast3_CN_028.voiceText: Doctor, that was at last a worthy opponent!

char_286_cast3_CN_029.voiceText: Well done, Doctor. Castle-3 is your best choice on the path of justice!

char_286_cast3_CN_030.voiceText: What an exciting battle! Let's fight together again next time.

char_286_cast3_CN_031.voiceText: Is everyone all right? I hope Castle-3's performance has exceeded your expectations.

char_286_cast3_CN_032.voiceText: I will hold up the rear. Everyone, retreat!

char_286_cast3_CN_033.voiceText: Is there anything Castle-3 can help with?

char_286_cast3_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, would you like to grab a drink together? I might not be able to actually have a drink, but I can still treat you to one. It is fine, Master Closure will pay.

char_285_medic2_CN_001.voiceText: Do you need medical assistance, Doctor? You look quite energetic, though...

char_285_medic2_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor, you have been working far too late these days. Please get adequate rest, or Dr. Kal'tsit may give you an earful next time she sees you!

char_285_medic2_CN_003.voiceText: Please tell me where you feel uncomfortable. I could also do an examination, if you like.

char_285_medic2_CN_004.voiceText: You've worked hard. How would you like a cup of coffee, Doctor? I'd also like a sip of that coffee... but I can't... so I'll just have to be satisfied watching you enjoy yours.

char_285_medic2_CN_007.voiceText: I've printed out the standard blood test report I just did for you. Everything looks normal, but there's a very unique characteristic about your blood...

char_285_medic2_CN_008.voiceText: What do I like? I like 'lovely Ms. Closure.'Why, you ask? Uh... I'm not sure either! That's what my settings have been ever since Ms. Closure first initialized me...

char_285_medic2_CN_009.voiceText: I only feel useful when someone's sick or injured. But as long as you're healthy, as long as I get to be by your side... I'm okay with being useless! I'll still feel safe.

char_285_medic2_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, I made a recording of you snoring just now! Your sleep quality is normal. The length of your REM sleep cycle is—

char_285_medic2_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, Doctor. You want me to say something more interesting to you? I'm afraid I have nothing interesting to say. I'm just a medical robot...

char_285_medic2_CN_012.voiceText: Firmware upgrade complete. Restart required. Please click anywhere to restart.

char_285_medic2_CN_017.voiceText: Medical supplies: confirmed. Battery charge: confirmed. Ready to deploy.

char_285_medic2_CN_018.voiceText: I'm pretty cumbersome... not much I can do besides providing emergency treatment and healing. Yet you still want me to be the captain?

char_285_medic2_CN_019.voiceText: Deploying. I hope no one gets injured.

char_285_medic2_CN_020.voiceText: Be careful, everyone! Leave the first aid to me.

char_285_medic2_CN_029.voiceText: With every battle, ever more soldiers are injured. When will humans finally stop hurting each other?

char_285_medic2_CN_030.voiceText: Well done, Doctor. That was a tough one. The enemies looked sickly, don't you think? Can I treat them too?

char_285_medic2_CN_031.voiceText: Is everyone okay? Hold still, I'll perform first aid on your wounds.

char_285_medic2_CN_032.voiceText: Don't worry, we've successfully retreated. However... I'll have to clean your wounds now. It might hurt, please be brave!

char_285_medic2_CN_033.voiceText: 'Lovely Ms. Closure' told me that you need help here.

char_285_medic2_CN_036.voiceText: I asked 'lovely Ms. Closure' to change 'what I like the most' to you, Doctor. But she refused to do it... Waaahhh...

char_285_medic2_CN_042.voiceText: Welcome back, Doctor. You are in good condition. Keep it up!

char_192_falco_CN_001.voiceText: Don't worry, Doctor. No matter what happens, I'll protect you.

char_192_falco_CN_002.voiceText: Liberi have excellent eyesight. According to legend, some can even tell one droplet from another in a rainstorm. Sounds incredible, huh?

char_192_falco_CN_003.voiceText: I take everyday life too seriously? My apologies. I think that comes from my time serving as a Laterano Guard. I'll work on that in the future.

char_192_falco_CN_004.voiceText: To most Lateranos, heavy armor doesn't serve much of a purpose. Of course, when we perform the large-scale rituals of our homeland, we do dress up in ceremonial garb.

char_192_falco_CN_005.voiceText: I appreciate your faith in my abilities, Doctor. I won't let you down.

char_192_falco_CN_007.voiceText: Right... I submitted a request to the HR office... to become your personal bodyguard. I guess maybe I miss my old job too much.

char_192_falco_CN_008.voiceText: I grew up in Laterano and didn't really have the chance to learn about other cultures. Here at Rhodes Island, I get to see such diversity, way beyond my imagination. Actually...it's not so bad.

char_192_falco_CN_009.voiceText: I have no regrets. Yes, true, they did drag me out of Laterano against my will... but this has been a great adventure. I've enjoyed it.

char_192_falco_CN_010.voiceText: It is my duty to protect you, Doctor. Rest assured.

char_192_falco_CN_011.voiceText: My name is Plume, formerly of the Pontifica Cohors Lateran. I will be your sword, and your wings, as I defend your very life.

char_192_falco_CN_012.voiceText: Ah, so tactics can help you overcome a more skilled opponent, huh?

char_192_falco_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you, Doctor. As your bodyguard, your approval is the best reward I can ask for.

char_192_falco_CN_018.voiceText: As the leader, it's my responsibility to keep everyone safe.

char_192_falco_CN_025.voiceText: You think you're faster than me?

char_192_falco_CN_026.voiceText: No move can escape my sight!

char_192_falco_CN_027.voiceText: My resolve lies with my spear!

char_192_falco_CN_028.voiceText: I fight for the glory of Laterano!

char_192_falco_CN_030.voiceText: Like a wave crashing against an immovable stone, isn't it?

char_192_falco_CN_031.voiceText: Regroup! I'll look out for the remaining enemies!

char_192_falco_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor... it feels like I'm abusing my position...

char_278_orchid_CN_001.voiceText: I'll make the arrangements. Just leave it to me.

char_278_orchid_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor, I certainly hope my teammates won't cause any trouble while I'm here working for you... Aagh, the more I think of it the worse this headache gets...

char_278_orchid_CN_003.voiceText: An ordinary job, a peaceful life. That's all I ever wanted.

char_278_orchid_CN_004.voiceText: Yeah, it's not that I don't get along with the other A6 members... I just get a little headache whenever I see them...

char_278_orchid_CN_005.voiceText: My group members just bump into new troubles every day. There is the anti-social one, the never listening one, the awfully stubborn one… Just when will they ever settle down and work?...

char_278_orchid_CN_007.voiceText: I don't know how I ended up on this team either. All I wanted was an ordinary life. Why did I end up in charge of these... problem children?! Wait a minute, Midnight is a grown man!

char_278_orchid_CN_008.voiceText: Popukar... gotta pat her on the head. Catapult... gotta tie her up. Spot... never make him mad. As for Midnight, just knock him out. There, Doctor, now you know the proper protocol for dealing with Team A6.

char_278_orchid_CN_009.voiceText: I made a cake for my teammates. Wanna take a slice, Doctor? Everyone in A6 just love fruitcakes. They really are a bunch of kids, aren't they?

char_278_orchid_CN_010.voiceText: Not much time left. Done with your work for the day, Doctor?

char_278_orchid_CN_011.voiceText: Captain of Reserve Op Team A6, Orchid, reporting in. Are you the Dr. {@nickname}? I look forward to working with you.

char_278_orchid_CN_012.voiceText: I learned a lot from this video. I'll keep it in mind for sure.

char_278_orchid_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you so much. I'll work hard to improve my skills from now on and strive for better results for you!

char_278_orchid_CN_017.voiceText: I'll complete my mission to the best of my ability.

char_278_orchid_CN_018.voiceText: Please follow the tactical combat manual closely, everyone. Thank you for your cooperation.

char_278_orchid_CN_019.voiceText: The battle has begun! Be careful, everyone!

char_278_orchid_CN_020.voiceText: Please make sure you follow every detail on the plan. Alright, everyone, now spread out!

char_278_orchid_CN_028.voiceText: Oh come on, I already have enough work to deal with!

char_278_orchid_CN_029.voiceText: Well done, Doctor! Impeccable leadership even against such a tough opponent.

char_278_orchid_CN_030.voiceText: A perfect job! Looks like we can have a good rest today.

char_278_orchid_CN_031.voiceText: We need to work harder next time.

char_278_orchid_CN_032.voiceText: Is everyone okay? Let's get out of here!

char_278_orchid_CN_036.voiceText: Huh?! Overtime again?! Ugh, I knew it...

char_278_orchid_CN_042.voiceText: Greetings, Doctor. Let's start today's work just as planned.

char_235_jesica_CN_001.voiceText: I-Is there anything I can help with? Just say the word and I can do it.

char_235_jesica_CN_002.voiceText: Franka and Liskarm are so incredible! I really admire them. I want to become as great as they are someday. I... I will work harder! Will you help me, Doctor?

char_235_jesica_CN_003.voiceText: Um, I heard word that Vanilla's here too? She was in my squad when she first joined Blacksteel. We went on missions together. She's become such a reliable Operator now... but I'm still just me…

char_235_jesica_CN_004.voiceText: Dr. {@nickname}, do I come off as... spineless? I know I shouldn't let people walk all over me... I'm trying to change...

char_235_jesica_CN_005.voiceText: Sometimes I feel like I'm back in Blacksteel, even after going through so much with Rhodes Island. I'm not the old me anymore, either... it's weird. Is it because I miss how it was back then? No, no. I don't miss the person I used to be, I know that for sure...

char_235_jesica_CN_006.voiceText: Hard work doesn't mean anything without results. That's what I think at least. However, I don't want anyone to see me training alone. But, Dr. {@nickname}, it's really comforting to have you by my side.

char_235_jesica_CN_007.voiceText: I pulled a muscle training a couple days ago... but don't worry, I-I'm okay! Urk...! I won't let this get in the way of you or anyone at Rhodes Island, Doctor!

char_235_jesica_CN_008.voiceText: Freeze, hands in the air! Oh, did I scare you? I'm sorry, it's just Franka told me to be bold and assertive, and I only wanted to try it out... I'm really sorry...

char_235_jesica_CN_009.voiceText: Everyone at Blacksteel and Rhodes Island is so amazing and talented. I know I'm nothing compared to them... but, still, just every once in a while, I feel really happy when I get compliments from you...

char_235_jesica_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor... Doctor? Are you sleeping? I'll clean your desk up for you, then...

char_235_jesica_CN_011.voiceText: Um, are you Dr. {@nickname}? Nice to meet you. I'm Jessica from Blacksteel Worldwide. Sorry, I-I'm really bad at introducing myself…

char_235_jesica_CN_012.voiceText: This seems a lot more effective than training by myself.

char_235_jesica_CN_013.voiceText: Doctor... I'm... I'm so happy you're honoring me... Just... let me cry it out for a bit, I'll be fine...

char_235_jesica_CN_014.voiceText: Ah, Doctor, does this mean you think I'm a great Operator? Thank you so much for all your help. You were by my side all the way. That's why I was able to make it through...!

char_235_jesica_CN_017.voiceText: Just give your orders and I'll carry them out!

char_235_jesica_CN_020.voiceText: I'll definitely prove myself this time!

char_235_jesica_CN_029.voiceText: I'm going to climb to the top of the mountain… I won't allow myself to stop halfway.

char_235_jesica_CN_030.voiceText: I... I really did it? I managed to protect everyone by myself?

char_235_jesica_CN_031.voiceText: I could do better. I can't get complacent just because we won...

char_235_jesica_CN_032.voiceText: Requesting medevac! I dragged everyone down... it's all my fault! Sorry! I'm sorry!

char_235_jesica_CN_033.voiceText: I wonder if the people at Rhodes Island are nice...?

char_235_jesica_CN_036.voiceText: I can do a little cooking...

char_290_vigna_CN_001.voiceText: Hey, hey! I'm watching a rock concert, Doctor! Stop blocking the TV! I just missed the best part thanks to you!

char_290_vigna_CN_002.voiceText: You get people who say things like 'fight the power' and 'be yourself.' But for us Sarkaz, that's just life.

char_290_vigna_CN_003.voiceText: I like bands... no, I LOVE bands! As a guitarist myself, I know every beat, every chord is important. I gotta practice on and on, day and night. That's the only way to give the audience the ultimate face-melting solo!

char_290_vigna_CN_004.voiceText: I'm going exceptionally harsh on you, given I've been so nice to everyone else you say? Well, isn't it only natural? Those who shoulder the responsibility of management like you need more than their self-discipline to do their job, Doctor. I have high standards for myself, and I think it's only right for these standards to be applied to you as well.

char_290_vigna_CN_005.voiceText: Hmm, this smell... is this the lunchbox Hibiscus brought you? You want me to eat it for you? No way! This... this wasn't in my job description!

char_290_vigna_CN_006.voiceText: If there's something you want out of life, you gotta work hard for it. Like, I want to become stronger, so I train. I want a sharper weapon, so I customize this one myself. People can judge as they want, but I'll stick to my belief until I get what I want!

char_290_vigna_CN_007.voiceText: Wha?! It's pouring outside? I-I don't... believe it has anything to do with my outdoor concert! Now get aside if you hear me 'cause I'm setting off right NOW! I won't let this sprinkle dampen my passion by one bit!

char_290_vigna_CN_008.voiceText: You got an important mission you want me to handle? Hehee, you can count on me! Let's see here... 'You are to acquire the following products for Rhodes Island during a time-limited mega-sale...?' Th-that's impossible!

char_290_vigna_CN_009.voiceText: Even if the crowd starts booing, the show must go on. You can't quit in the middle of a performance just because you messed something up. Same is true for the Sarkaz and infected. We won't have anything left with us if we just call it quits.

char_290_vigna_CN_010.voiceText: Hey, you can't sleep over here! Ugh... you're too heavy for me to carry...

char_290_vigna_CN_011.voiceText: Excuse me, is this the office of the Dr. {@nickname}? I've been looking for the place quite a while and it'd be really appreciated if—what? YOU'RE the Doctor? Hmpf, I see. Operator Vigna, reporting in!

char_290_vigna_CN_012.voiceText: You gotta be willing to sweat a lot to keep up the battle tempo, (is that right)?

char_290_vigna_CN_013.voiceText: Am I wearing my elite medal right? Great! In that case, it's time to get a picture for this remarkable moment!

char_290_vigna_CN_014.voiceText: Pure strength might not be my forte, but my spear and unparalleled skills shall always leave them with a deep impression!

char_290_vigna_CN_017.voiceText: I'll learn from others' battle techniques.

char_290_vigna_CN_018.voiceText: I may be the team captain, but you can all let me know where and how I might improve.

char_290_vigna_CN_019.voiceText: Everyone, prepare to deploy. And please keep in mind that coordinated actions bring victory.

char_290_vigna_CN_029.voiceText: No matter how tough the bad guys are, I won't stop strumming! Oh… 'fighting' might be the better word here!

char_290_vigna_CN_030.voiceText: You all deserve a commendation from me, oh, but not you, Doctor, not yet! Your job's not finished until I see everyone back home safe and sound~

char_290_vigna_CN_031.voiceText: We're not out of trouble yet! Hold formation!

char_290_vigna_CN_032.voiceText: Ugh... This can't be it. We have to fight harder!

char_290_vigna_CN_033.voiceText: Is there a soundproof room here? My fingers are itching for guitar strings so BAD!

char_290_vigna_CN_034.voiceText: Hey! That just gave me a chill!

char_290_vigna_CN_036.voiceText: D-Don't pat me on the head! It might make me shorter!

char_289_gyuki_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, you gotta be hungry! Try some of my onigiri. They're great!

char_289_gyuki_CN_002.voiceText: I've actually got a lotta hobbies. They go way beyond martial arts. I'm also really into soccer, and flower arrangement. Wouldn't want you thinking I'm just some kinda bloodthirsty monster!

char_289_gyuki_CN_003.voiceText: My race eats other races? That's some old crap! Who told you that? Pff, what kinda coward goes around talking that crap behind my back? I'll give 'em a peace of my mind when I find 'em.

char_289_gyuki_CN_004.voiceText: My body? Heals right up whenever I get hurt. Even in the middle of a fight, the wounds close right back up. Handy, huh.

char_289_gyuki_CN_005.voiceText: Hey, Doctor, Rhodes Island's got a soccer tournament! Let's sign up together. When you got me on your team, it's in the bag, don't worry. Doctor, you better start thinking up a cool victory pose!

char_289_gyuki_CN_006.voiceText: You don't even recognize me on the battlefield? I just start cutting through enemies one by one with a blank expression on my face? Wow! Sounds hella badass! Wish I could watch myself out there.

char_289_gyuki_CN_007.voiceText: I got this problem where I kinda end up breaking stuff, so I'm working with my flower arrangement teacher to control my strength. Being around all those pretty flowers makes me real happy too.

char_289_gyuki_CN_008.voiceText: Strategy? Ehh, not really my specialty. That's why I keep hopping right into the enemy's plans. But with you, Doctor, you always stop me before I screw up too bad. Been a big help!

char_289_gyuki_CN_009.voiceText: I've always been pretty gullible. It's almost gotten me killed. But now I, Matoimaru, swear loyalty to you, Doctor! I know you'll never betray me, Doctor!

char_289_gyuki_CN_010.voiceText: Grrr... Hey, no falling asleep, Doctor! You gotta listen to my stories or I'm gonna die of boredom!

char_289_gyuki_CN_011.voiceText: Matoimaru has officially joined Rhodes Island! You let me do the fighting and I'll take the orders, Doctor!

char_289_gyuki_CN_012.voiceText: Hey now I can beat 'em even harder.

char_289_gyuki_CN_013.voiceText: Doctor, you put my strength to good work and I'll be a happy lady!

char_289_gyuki_CN_014.voiceText: Doctor, stand back a bit. I don't wanna hurt you swinging my naginata around. I, Matoimaru, will bring victory in the name of the Doctor!

char_289_gyuki_CN_017.voiceText: Hah hah! You all look pretty strong. Let's do some warm-ups!

char_289_gyuki_CN_018.voiceText: Ugh, you want me to play captain? That means I get to beat 'em as hard as I want, right?

char_289_gyuki_CN_019.voiceText: You guys ready to rumble? We'll wipe the floor with 'em.

char_289_gyuki_CN_020.voiceText: Sorry to keep you waiting, bad guys!

char_289_gyuki_CN_025.voiceText: You're standing up to Matoimaru. Ballsy.

char_289_gyuki_CN_029.voiceText: A sea of fire and a mountain of blades... That was awesome! It's the battlefield I've always dreamed of!

char_289_gyuki_CN_030.voiceText: Doctor, I got 'em all! Hey, what happened here? Everything's busted. Did I do that?

char_289_gyuki_CN_031.voiceText: I'll get 'em before they escape! Can't call the battle over until I do!

char_289_gyuki_CN_032.voiceText: Retreat! I'll cover your escape. Make sure you don't get hit!

char_289_gyuki_CN_036.voiceText: You look happy about something. You gotta tell me too!

char_277_sqrrel_CN_001.voiceText: Awaiting orders, ready when you are, Chief!

char_277_sqrrel_CN_002.voiceText: In the interests of safety, I am inspecting escape routes and fire fighting equipment. One moment please.

char_277_sqrrel_CN_003.voiceText: Please be aware, it is against regulation to light fires or smoke cigarettes in the corridors. Thank you for your cooperation, Operators.

char_277_sqrrel_CN_004.voiceText: Ensuring awareness of fire safety and fire fighting protocols is a key part of my duties. Allow me to begin with you, Chief.

char_277_sqrrel_CN_005.voiceText: I am very small, but that means I can do work no one else can.

char_277_sqrrel_CN_006.voiceText: Um, Chief, I'm very nervous… Actually, I'm not good at expressing myself… Thank you, for your concern.

char_277_sqrrel_CN_007.voiceText: When I start speaking sometimes I can't stop. I hope you forgive me, Chief... *sob*...

char_277_sqrrel_CN_008.voiceText: Chief, can you please help change this light bulb... I... can't reach it... Oh, it's working now. Thank you.

char_277_sqrrel_CN_009.voiceText: Chief... They they're barbecuing in the dorm again. Can you please stop them for me! Aaaah! Someone swapped my fire extinguisher with Ifrit's flamethrower! Are you okay, Chief?

char_277_sqrrel_CN_010.voiceText: Break time ends in a few minutes. Just to let you know, Chief.

char_277_sqrrel_CN_011.voiceText: Pleasure to meet you, Chief {@nickname}. I am Shaw of the Lungmen Fire Department, reporting for duty!

char_277_sqrrel_CN_012.voiceText: Exercise videos are part of the training?

char_277_sqrrel_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you for your trust, Chief!

char_277_sqrrel_CN_014.voiceText: This is... an elite medal? Thank you, Chief...I will continue to do my best for everyone, and for the Chief.

char_277_sqrrel_CN_020.voiceText: The fire is spreading this way. Get ready!

char_277_sqrrel_CN_026.voiceText: Outta the way! Outta the way!

char_277_sqrrel_CN_028.voiceText: You have violated the fire regulation!

char_277_sqrrel_CN_029.voiceText: A fire of this scale could not be extinguished without the help of the Chief and the others.

char_277_sqrrel_CN_030.voiceText: The fire is extinguished. Ready to return to base.

char_277_sqrrel_CN_031.voiceText: The fire is basicly under control. Should I begin the damage control process?

char_277_sqrrel_CN_032.voiceText: O-oh no! The fire is spreading in this direction!

char_277_sqrrel_CN_033.voiceText: I will stay here from now on then?

char_291_aglina_CN_001.voiceText: Dr. {@nickname}, I made a really strong brew with our new coffee machine. Wanna try? You can only have one cup a day, though. Don't want you up all night!

char_291_aglina_CN_002.voiceText: Being a Messenger isn't easy. Both the sender and the receiver might have some big ideas, and who knows if some shady secrets get inside your bag. If you're too absorbed in getting yourself moving, you could still end up in a pit for what you get yourself into.

char_291_aglina_CN_003.voiceText: My mother was from Higashi, so my name doesn't sound very Siracusan. A lot of people ask me if it's even my real name, so I decided to use Angelina as a codename too.

char_291_aglina_CN_004.voiceText: Good morning, Dr. {@nickname}! Yeah, I'm off to send out some documents. Dr. Kal'tsit says my skills could come in super useful in battle... but compared to fighting, I kinda prefer taking letters where they belong!

char_291_aglina_CN_005.voiceText: I actually don't know if I'm a good fit for Rhodes Island... I mean, a lot of really heavy stuff happens here, I'm not sure I can handle it. Croissant's always comforting me, but I am still not sure about myself. Do I really have what it takes?

char_291_aglina_CN_006.voiceText: I don't feel lost anymore. At the end of the day, it's more than a simple identification with you or Rhodes Island. If I can leap across the gaps between skyscrapers as a Messenger, then I know I could  bridge the gap between the Infected and Uninfected as an Operator!

char_291_aglina_CN_007.voiceText: Memories are precious. I always remember that the Infected, just like us, look forward to a better tomorrow. I don't know anything about your past, Dr. {@nickname}, but I promise to help you recall.

char_291_aglina_CN_008.voiceText: Dr. {@nickname}, don't be shy, come closer! That's right! Three, two, one, sorridi! See? It's a photo sticker of you and me. The perfect souvenir, right? I guess it's also a token of… some of my feelings, haha.

char_291_aglina_CN_009.voiceText: The view from the deck is great. Especially for stargazing! See that lone star over there? People say that one day, its companion star will appear, and then they'll embrace and dance together. Still... how long does it have to wait for the other one to show up? And how long do I have to wait... for the star to wink back at me?

char_291_aglina_CN_010.voiceText: Umm hmm~♪ Mmm, maybe the coral lipstick suits me more.

char_291_aglina_CN_011.voiceText: Ciao! I'm Angelina Ajimu, a Messenger from Siracusa. Just call me Angelina. Am I cool to call you Dr. {@nickname}?

char_291_aglina_CN_012.voiceText: The battlefield is a cruel place... but I'll try not to let you down.

char_291_aglina_CN_013.voiceText: Since you trust me, Dr. {@nickname}, I'll have to work much, much harder than I usually do! Like, Siracusan Messengers always say: 'A slow Messenger gets caught by the wind.'

char_291_aglina_CN_014.voiceText: I've made my decision. As long as you're still working to help the Infected, Dr. {@nickname}, I'll follow you. You've come so far, done so much... now it's my turn to do something for you.

char_291_aglina_CN_017.voiceText: In work or in battle, I'll give it all I've got!

char_291_aglina_CN_018.voiceText: I might not be the best, but I'll still do what I can.

char_291_aglina_CN_020.voiceText: When will all these conflicts ever come to an end…

char_291_aglina_CN_026.voiceText: We will overcome what confronts us.

char_291_aglina_CN_027.voiceText: I've got a magic touch on this.

char_291_aglina_CN_028.voiceText: Ever wondered how it feels to float in the air?

char_291_aglina_CN_029.voiceText: We only grow stronger after getting into a wolf's mouth, right?

char_291_aglina_CN_030.voiceText: We all worked hard for this. You'll cherish this victory, won't you Dr. {@nickname}?

char_291_aglina_CN_031.voiceText: Well, even I lose a letter sometimes...

char_291_aglina_CN_032.voiceText: The more difficult the situation, the harder we have to try!

char_291_aglina_CN_033.voiceText: This place is like home to me!

char_291_aglina_CN_036.voiceText: My hair looks nice? Heheh, I've got a secret for that.

char_009_12fce_CN_001.voiceText: Forgive me, Doctor... There are limits to what I can do, including in conversation... but I'm honored to be your assistant. I look forward to helping you with your work.

char_009_12fce_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor, time heals all wounds. Please have more confidence in yourself. Your Operators have chosen to follow you because we believe that you will bring positive change.

char_009_12fce_CN_003.voiceText: Many Infected have relocated to Rhodes Island... not because they have any particular goals to achieve, but simply because they want a place to call home. The world outside no longer accepts them, after all...

char_009_12fce_CN_004.voiceText: Owl may not seem very friendly, but she's got a good heart. Please excuse her and pay her no mind.

char_009_12fce_CN_007.voiceText: 12F? That was the day I 'came to' this world. You could consider it my birthday.

char_009_12fce_CN_008.voiceText: I might not be able to spend my entire life serving one person... but at least I can start working on it now.

char_009_12fce_CN_009.voiceText: She has finally found you, Doctor. What a perilous journey it's been. You're very important to her, as well as to everyone else.

char_009_12fce_CN_010.voiceText: I'll be by your side watching over you, Doctor, even in your sleep. So rest easy, you have nothing to fear.

char_009_12fce_CN_011.voiceText: You have my thanks for allowing me to join you. From now on, I will do my best to serve you, Doctor, with my alchemical skills. I have never had a name... but if you must call me something, you can refer to me as 12F.

char_009_12fce_CN_012.voiceText: I see, I understand now. Thank you for your guidance.

char_009_12fce_CN_017.voiceText: I may not possess outstanding skills, but I will do my best.

char_009_12fce_CN_018.voiceText: Will it be alright for me to be the leader? Anyway, thank you for your trust, Doctor.

char_009_12fce_CN_019.voiceText: Relax, Doctor. We will complete this operation in no time.

char_009_12fce_CN_029.voiceText: I'm used to failure... but a victory after countless defeats is always the most precious one. Don't you agree, Doctor?

char_009_12fce_CN_030.voiceText: This victory is all yours, Doctor. And I am honored to be a pawn in your game of chess.

char_009_12fce_CN_031.voiceText: That was a hard-won victory, but we did it. Are you all right, Owl?

char_009_12fce_CN_032.voiceText: Failure is only normal. Don't be discouraged. I've been in many wars, and my experience tells me that your victory will come soon.

char_009_12fce_CN_033.voiceText: If you'd like, I can help. No trouble.

char_009_12fce_CN_036.voiceText: I am so thankful for all that you have done for me. I feel ashamed I have so little with which to repay your kindness. Forgive me, Doctor.

char_230_savage_CN_001.voiceText: Heheh, Dr. {@nickname}, What can I do for you today?

char_230_savage_CN_002.voiceText: Combat missions take up most of my job, where I just havoc around with my hammer... It feels nice to get to sort files like this every once in a while.

char_230_savage_CN_003.voiceText: When I worked for RIM Billiton, I was in charge of a lot of things: mining ores, doing geological surveys with electromagnets, all kinds of stuff. Hmm... sounds like a mouthful, right? To put it simply, I smashed what blocks the way and kept digging down!

char_230_savage_CN_004.voiceText: Amiya has a lot on her shoulders. If only I could help share her burden a little... And perhaps yours too, Doctor. Don't hesitate to let me know if there's anything you need help with!

char_230_savage_CN_005.voiceText: Providing cover, trailblazing, area denial... I might not be able to literally shield my teammates like the Defender Operators, but I can still protect everyone in my own way!

char_230_savage_CN_006.voiceText: Did... did I manage to keep everyone safe?... *Sign of Relief* I'm so rapt... Please, Doctor, from now on, let me stay with you and Amiya!

char_230_savage_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, want a cabbage veggie salad with mushroom pies? Yep, I made three servings! Yours, mine, and another for Amiya. She loves the pies I make!

char_230_savage_CN_008.voiceText: The running backs on the football field are unstoppable. They just keep charging forward in spite of everything, all to clear a path for their teammates. And then they just fall down and leave it to everyone else to finish the job. Isn't that sort of like what I do? It's very cool! I hope I don't have to get tackled though.

char_230_savage_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, as long as I get to stay with you and Amiya, it's enough for me. Memories belong in the past, while the future is waiting for us to color it in. Amiya and I will continue to create more memories with you in the days to come!

char_230_savage_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, seems you've got some time to spare... Then let's go get groceries for tea tonight!

char_230_savage_CN_011.voiceText: Savage, from RIM Billiton, reporting for duty! The moment I got the message from you and Amiya, I rushed right over to see what I could do. Huh? You don't remember anything? Strewth!

char_230_savage_CN_012.voiceText: Ooh, I see. Uh-huh… I totally understand it now!

char_230_savage_CN_013.voiceText: I feel a lot better taking orders from you, Doctor. I won't let you down!

char_230_savage_CN_014.voiceText: Don't worry, Doctor. No matter how many enemies there are, as long as you're with me, I'll smash 'em all!

char_230_savage_CN_029.voiceText: Hmm, guess no mission's too difficult for us!

char_230_savage_CN_032.voiceText: It's too dangerous here! We have to fall back!

char_230_savage_CN_033.voiceText: Huh? You're really trusting me with work this detail-oriented?

char_230_savage_CN_036.voiceText: All done with work for the day!

char_282_catap_CN_001.voiceText: We got a lot to do today, Doctor. So how about we play some games first? Isn't getting nice and relaxed the best way to prepare for a hard day of work?

char_282_catap_CN_002.voiceText: Aw, I feel so lazy today for some reason! Maybe because Midnight isn't around? I love watching him chat up girls with that flashy smile of his. It's especially fun when the girls turn him down! Totally makes my day.

char_282_catap_CN_003.voiceText: Doctor, you know who's the most reliable in our group? Oh, you can't guess? It's Spot! He might be quiet, but he's very reliable. So why don't we get him here to offer a hand? After all there's so much work for only two of us, don't you think?

char_282_catap_CN_004.voiceText: Aw... Ms. Orchid yelled at me again today. She's such a nag! Must be work getting into her head and stressing her out. She should learn from me—I have the perfect balance between working hard and playing hard!

char_282_catap_CN_005.voiceText: Hey, where's Dobermann? She's out on business today? Yay, finally! I can slack off all day now, wonderful! I'm gonna go get some snacks first. Doctor, you want some chips or popcorn? I'll grab a bag for you!

char_282_catap_CN_007.voiceText: Uh, Popukar, sweetie, please listen to me, I'll do anything you say, okay? J-just put down the chainsaw! Oh no, she's out of control! This is the worst! Doctor, run! Run! We gotta jump out the window! Yeah, the window! Follow me!

char_282_catap_CN_008.voiceText: The town I came from... the mayor was a tyrant, a fat cat with no heart, no sympathy. Drove the townspeople nuts. I hated him too, so I blasted open his vault and handed out all the money I found to the townies. Now that was a good time!

char_282_catap_CN_009.voiceText: I don't care what anybody thinks of me—it's more important that I just enjoy every day doing what I like. My life belongs to me, so I alone decide what I do. Isn't that right?

char_282_catap_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor's asleep? Well, can't interrupt a beauty nap. Guess I'll go out and have some fun.

char_282_catap_CN_011.voiceText: Reserve OP Team A6, Catapult, reporting in! Hey, I can tell you're hella different from that stuffy old bit—I mean, that esteemed, honorable instructor Ms. Dobermann. Right? Like it's obvious!

char_282_catap_CN_013.voiceText: Hehe, I finally finished basic training. Wait, what? Dobermann will keep overseeing the newbies, even AFTER their promotions? You gotta be kidding me! No—

char_282_catap_CN_017.voiceText: It's not time to head out yet, right? Let me hang out for a bit longer...

char_282_catap_CN_018.voiceText: I'm the captain? Haha~I've been waiting forever to hear those words!

char_282_catap_CN_019.voiceText: Aw man, where did I leave my ammunition belt?

char_282_catap_CN_020.voiceText: Ugh, I hate fighting. But what else can I do?

char_282_catap_CN_025.voiceText: Watch how I get them with one shot!

char_282_catap_CN_029.voiceText: What an awesome formation! You got some great tactics, Doctor. And it all went down perfect!

char_282_catap_CN_030.voiceText: I love commanders that lead us to victory! Just like you, Doctor!

char_282_catap_CN_031.voiceText: Relax, I set a whole bunch of traps right where the enemy's gonna be running. What? They didn't step in any of them? No way!

char_282_catap_CN_032.voiceText: Oh shoot! Hurry up, Doctor. We gotta move!

char_282_catap_CN_033.voiceText: Psst, care to take a peek and tell me if Dobermann's in there?

char_282_catap_CN_034.voiceText: You can't catch me! ...Oh, you can.

char_283_midn_CN_001.voiceText: Thank you for choosing me, Darling. Now, what kind of secret are you going to share with me under this velvet of the night?

char_283_midn_CN_002.voiceText: Fiend of the Night? Ah, I can't hide anything from you. But past glory is nothing to me. After all, I have an even brighter future waiting.

char_283_midn_CN_003.voiceText: I may work in a different place now, but my job is still the same—to put a smile on everyone's face.

char_283_midn_CN_004.voiceText: I bet Ms. Orchid must have been born with a negative number on her happiness scale. Why else would she always look so stern whenever I'm there to light her up? If you know anything about her, please tell me.

char_283_midn_CN_005.voiceText: People say my swordsmanship is top notch. All due credit, I have to say. Practicing swordsmanship helps me maintain my figure and cultivate my elegance. It'd be a crime for me to slack off on the pratice. After all, you either keep the momentum and hold the lead or end up getting overwhelmed. Please keep that in mind.

char_283_midn_CN_007.voiceText: People used to say that I sold feelings as commodities, that I treated 'happiness' as a product. Fools, all of them. How can I expect my customers to open their hearts to me if I don't open mine to them first?

char_283_midn_CN_008.voiceText: I believe happiness can be contagious. It's a tangible atmosphere that truly exists. I feel the joy when others treat me with sincerity, and I will make sure my happiness reaches right into their hearts.

char_283_midn_CN_009.voiceText: My colleagues in team A6... they may be a bit weird, but they're truly kind souls. They're a gift from destiny, a gift that continues to remind me to cherish those important to me.

char_283_midn_CN_010.voiceText: Now that I have some free time, I should read.

char_283_midn_CN_011.voiceText: Show me your brightest smile, my esteemed customer! Happiness is at arm's reach when you're by my side. Midnight, at your service.

char_283_midn_CN_012.voiceText: It's important to never stop learning!

char_283_midn_CN_013.voiceText: Whoa, so my hard work really paid off! Let's set up a champagne tower to celebrate. My treat.

char_283_midn_CN_017.voiceText: With me on your side, success is guaranteed!

char_283_midn_CN_020.voiceText: Behold, here comes my flamboyant moves!

char_283_midn_CN_025.voiceText: O sword, pierce the moonlight that veils the night!

char_283_midn_CN_029.voiceText: Impressive, Dr. {@nickname}, truly impressive. Your blazing brilliance almost stole my show today.

char_283_midn_CN_030.voiceText: There's only one thing that's impossible for me: being imperfect.

char_283_midn_CN_031.voiceText: Not too shabby. Such a heart-warming result calls for a little celebration.

char_283_midn_CN_032.voiceText: No need to look back. We'll greet each other with a smile next time.

char_283_midn_CN_033.voiceText: A wonderful place. Let's have a drinking party tonight.

char_283_midn_CN_034.voiceText: There now, would you please leave my collar as it is?

char_283_midn_CN_036.voiceText: Thanks for taking care of me.

char_137_brownb_CN_001.voiceText: Boss, let's go grab a bite. You're buying. Huh? You bought last time? Nah, that don't sound right!

char_137_brownb_CN_002.voiceText: Use my head to win fights? Hmm... Hmm.. If I ain't strong enough to beat 'em down, I'll just train 'til I am. Nailed it!

char_137_brownb_CN_003.voiceText: Honey's sweet but getting it's a pain in the ass. I went for some the other day and the bees ate me for lunch.

char_137_brownb_CN_004.voiceText: My knucklers? My precious babies. Wouldn't have racked up all those wins without 'em!

char_137_brownb_CN_005.voiceText: There's a lot more to the underground fight scene than you might think. Lots of punks dove in before they had it figured out and ended up dead.

char_137_brownb_CN_006.voiceText: Oripathy? Who cares? Infected, Uninfected... They're all the same after I knock their lights out.

char_137_brownb_CN_007.voiceText: Huh? The fish in the kitchen? Hah! Right here in my belly now!

char_137_brownb_CN_008.voiceText: Huh? What's with all the names? Hah, use your brain, Boss! I gotta meet more people so I got more people to fight.

char_137_brownb_CN_009.voiceText: The only reason I joined the underground fight scene is 'cause I didn't have two dollars to rub together. But here on Rhodes Island I got that load off my mind. It's all thanks to you, Boss!

char_137_brownb_CN_011.voiceText: Yo! Boss, you know a winner when you see her! You got the world's strongest underground fighter, me, Beehunter!

char_137_brownb_CN_012.voiceText: I really don't wanna study. Send me out to fight already!

char_137_brownb_CN_013.voiceText: Hah hah hah! I got what I deserve!

char_137_brownb_CN_014.voiceText: You keep pushing me forward like this, and I ain't gonna let you down! Lemme show you what I can do in a fight, Boss!

char_137_brownb_CN_018.voiceText: Yeah! Chow's on me after we win this thing!

char_137_brownb_CN_019.voiceText: Relax, Boss. Ain't nobody can go three rounds with me!

char_137_brownb_CN_020.voiceText: So you're the ones looking for a beatdown. You guys?
