char_436_whispr_CN_029.voiceText: Sleep, now. May all dream well in the sound of rainfall.

char_436_whispr_CN_030.voiceText: This is how their story ends. One tragedy, following another...

char_436_whispr_CN_031.voiceText: Leave the pursuit for later. Please let me treat everyone first.

char_436_whispr_CN_032.voiceText: I'm sorry, I've been such a burden on everyone...

char_436_whispr_CN_033.voiceText: Such a peaceful place this is. I can hear the patter of rainfall.

char_436_whispr_CN_036.voiceText: P—please don't move! My hair's gotten tangled...

char_436_whispr_CN_042.voiceText: What will we be doing today, Doctor?

char_347_jaksel_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor, you've been sitting there for a while, that's really unhealthy. Come do some stretches with me! Exercise and recover your energy. That way, you'll be able to work better.

char_347_jaksel_CN_003.voiceText: Doctor, Doctor! She's here at Rhodes Island! Ah, her codename should be Dur-nar now. Anyway, she's really amazing! I've only ever seen her in recruitment ads before! She's also a really good person! She gave me so many snacks, ehehe.

char_347_jaksel_CN_004.voiceText: Doctor, I'm actually pretty lithe for my age, you know. Let me show you a standing backflip! Watch!

char_347_jaksel_CN_005.voiceText: This gun? Oh, it's a gun-type Arts... Arts something. Ah, right, Arts Unit! I applied for one out of habit when I came here, but I still prefer my fists over Arts.

char_347_jaksel_CN_006.voiceText: Even though I know I'm very lucky, I only realized how badly other Infected are doing after coming to Rhodes Island... Doctor, what can I do to help? I really want to help them!

char_347_jaksel_CN_007.voiceText: ...Hm? Ah, Doctor! I'm writing a letter to my dad. Eh, I haven't introduced my dad to you yet? He's a really amazing policeman, you know! Let me tell you how great he is!

char_347_jaksel_CN_008.voiceText: Actually, it was my dad who suggested Rhodes Island. After he found out you could treat Oripathy, he pushed really hard for me to be able to come here. I don't really want to be away from him, but I know that he'll be happiest if I live a healthy life.

char_347_jaksel_CN_009.voiceText: You're really reliable, although dad is still better. Yup, you're now the second most reliable person in my heart! Hehe. Ah, Doctor, I talked a lot about you in my letters to dad. He said he really wants to meet you!

char_347_jaksel_CN_010.voiceText: Doc——! Ah, Doctor's asleep. I'll have to be quieter...

char_347_jaksel_CN_011.voiceText: Nice to meet you, Doctor! I'm the new operator, codename Jackie! I used to be an auxiliary police officer in Columbia. Let's get along!

char_347_jaksel_CN_012.voiceText: Amazing... It feels even more amazing than dad...

char_347_jaksel_CN_013.voiceText: Eh, am I being promoted? Wow, that's great!

char_347_jaksel_CN_014.voiceText: I've learnt a lot living at Rhodes Island... Maybe I can even catch up to dad one day! Doctor, I'll continue to work hard. Please guide me well~

char_347_jaksel_CN_024.voiceText: Time for me to show my power!

char_347_jaksel_CN_028.voiceText: I'll do it in one go!

char_347_jaksel_CN_029.voiceText: I thought we were gonna lose a few time, but we actually won in the end. Doctor, you're amazing!

char_347_jaksel_CN_031.voiceText: Doctor, want me to chase after them?

char_347_jaksel_CN_032.voiceText: Sorry, Doctor. If only I'd put in more effort...

char_264_f12yin_CN_001.voiceText: It's a good thing to be alert, Doctor. Well, please continue with your work. Rest assured, I'm here to protect you.

char_264_f12yin_CN_002.voiceText: I've met plenty of people who claim to practice martial arts, but they are all just weaklings putting up a front. Not that girl, Waai Fu, however. She's an interesting one... and although she still has a ways to go, I look forward to fighting her once she grows up.

char_264_f12yin_CN_003.voiceText: Rhodes Island doesn't have a cellar, you say? Now that won't do. Alcohol is indispensable. Not only is it something that can be savored and enjoyed, you can also drown your sorrows with it. So there you have it, Doctor. Get a cellar built. I dare say I know a thing or two about alcohol, should you need my assistance.

char_264_f12yin_CN_004.voiceText: I built a library back in Mansfield, but most of the books I could get my hands on there were Columbian. It gets boring after a while. The collection there simply doesn't hold a candle to what Rhodes Island has. The library here has a sizable collection of literature from other countries. It's marvelous.

char_264_f12yin_CN_005.voiceText: When you find yourself in the face of oppression, it is futile to even try to come up with countermeasures... I used to believe that, but I later realized that there's no power out there that's absolute. At the very least, I don't have that kind of power, and that's why I'll never look down on anything again, no matter how insignificant.

char_264_f12yin_CN_006.voiceText: I used to think that Rhodes Island was just another Mansfield, a prison of 'freedom.' And you. You are me. You are a prisoner of freedom. You are the king. Yet now I know that's not the case. This is not a prison, and you are the friend of everyone here.

char_264_f12yin_CN_007.voiceText: Are the ones over there from Rhine Lab? Don't worry. I don't really have a grudge about Rhine Lab itself, and they are my colleagues now. I wouldn't do anything that gives you a headache. It's just I may have something to ask them one of these days.

char_264_f12yin_CN_008.voiceText: Doctor, do you have some time later? Let me take you out for a drink... Oh, it's nothing important. I merely have a few secrets that I'd really like to get off my chest. I haven't made a new friend for a long time, after all.

char_264_f12yin_CN_009.voiceText: You are a very good friend, Doctor. When I have everything sorted out, should I still be alive, do pay Mansfield a visit. That is my kingdom, and I am willing to share all that I have there with you.

char_264_f12yin_CN_010.voiceText: For you to fall asleep so defenselessly in the company of others... I can't tell if you are being trusting or negligent.

char_264_f12yin_CN_011.voiceText: I owe Rhodes Island my life, so allow me to be completely honest, Doctor. I am going after a certain department within Rhine Lab. If you don't want your relationship with them ruined, now is the time to turn me away.

char_264_f12yin_CN_012.voiceText: Battlefield experience, huh? Indeed, that's something that I don't have. Thank you, Doctor.

char_264_f12yin_CN_013.voiceText: Doctor, don't be afraid. I don't fight anyone undeserving of my rage.

char_264_f12yin_CN_014.voiceText: Doctor, take a good look. That mask of composure, calm, and politeness is off. This is the truest you'll ever find me. Bloodthirsty, violent, and destructive. Look at me and be my friend.

char_264_f12yin_CN_017.voiceText: Perfect. It's just about time to get a little exercise in.

char_264_f12yin_CN_018.voiceText: I'm the leader, so follow my lead.

char_264_f12yin_CN_024.voiceText: I won't let them go much further.

char_264_f12yin_CN_026.voiceText: Haven't had breakfast? Come with all you've got!

char_264_f12yin_CN_029.voiceText: A precarious situation is the perfect opportunity to better ourselves, but we must also know our own limits.

char_264_f12yin_CN_030.voiceText: Doctor, there is no need to put ourselves in the spotlight when the time's not right.

char_264_f12yin_CN_031.voiceText: Unnecessary violence is just a way to blow off steam. I got myself under control a long time ago.

char_264_f12yin_CN_032.voiceText: As long as we're still alive, that's hardly a defeat.

char_264_f12yin_CN_033.voiceText: The ceiling here is a little low, isn't it?

char_264_f12yin_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, why don't we discuss these books?

char_214_kafka_CN_001.voiceText: You give Kafka the work that needs doing, Doctor, and then I pass it all on... okay. This's just like how underground work goes!

char_214_kafka_CN_002.voiceText: Seeing as you're my friend now, Doctor, you can ask me for anything. Uh, apart from lending you my shears.

char_214_kafka_CN_003.voiceText: Rhodes Island's fulla people I never met before. Everywhere I go, I see what I wants. Hm? You're wonderin' WHAT it is I want? Thaaat's a secret, y'know. Seee-cret.

char_214_kafka_CN_004.voiceText: Hmm... still can't read your eyes. They're calm as a lake... but there'll come a day when I get your number, Doctor, just you wait!

char_214_kafka_CN_005.voiceText: Doctooor, Silence kicked me out againnn, I just can't take it, sob, sob... huh? I started it by messing up her experiment? Hmm, Silence got to you first... eh-hem, well, I'm just gonna go now!

char_214_kafka_CN_006.voiceText: Well, until I can get what I want, I guess I'll lend you a hand. Just lending it, though, okay?

char_214_kafka_CN_007.voiceText: Story goes, I used to live in a real baaad place, dealing with bad people almost everyday. Then ever since I came here, everyone's been nice with me, givin' me snacks and all! Mm-hm, that's why I like it here at Rhodes Island!

char_214_kafka_CN_008.voiceText: ...Y'know the secrets everyone tries their best to hide? They're like monsters, hidden in the dead shadows, waitin' for their chance. Beautiful... and dangerous. That's exactly why I do my darndest to collect them! Doctor, don't you got anything for my hoard?

char_214_kafka_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, if you've ever got a problem, we can always call my 'friends' from Columbia in to help... though you don't really gotta. One Kafka'll sort out all your troubles head to tail!

char_214_kafka_CN_010.voiceText: Bet you think I'm goofing off right now, Doctor. But I aiiin't~

char_214_kafka_CN_011.voiceText: What did you need me for...? Wait, not in front of everybody! Just treat me like a normal gardener, okay?

char_214_kafka_CN_012.voiceText: Just gotta figure what they're aiming for, and I can draw up some counterplans. C'mon, ain't I a wiz?

char_214_kafka_CN_013.voiceText: Seeing as you really need my power, Doctor, just c'mon and say it. Be like Kafka here, all serious and open, yeah?

char_214_kafka_CN_014.voiceText: Gardenin' or fightin', I didn't start doing either for compliments. But having my own efforts get noticed by you and the rest, well, that makes a Kafka real happy.

char_214_kafka_CN_017.voiceText: Wonder what we can harvest this time?

char_214_kafka_CN_018.voiceText: Just leave it to me. I guarantee you're all in for a fun time!

char_214_kafka_CN_019.voiceText: Ah, thinkin' sucks... I guess I'll be listenin' to you, Doctor.

char_214_kafka_CN_020.voiceText: Look at all these naughty li'l saplings. Ain'tcha cute... sit tight and Kafka'll trim ya up~

char_214_kafka_CN_025.voiceText: Watch your eyes... I see all your weakpoints in 'em.

char_214_kafka_CN_026.voiceText: You're all just hedges who know how to walk~

char_214_kafka_CN_028.voiceText: Kafka knows you're scared. Tremblin' li'l bare branches.

char_214_kafka_CN_029.voiceText: Smooth sailin' just like always, Doctor. Alright, makes a Kafka wanna go get 'em!

char_214_kafka_CN_030.voiceText: Man, were those enemies pushovers. If I'd known sooner, I woulda messed with 'em some.

char_214_kafka_CN_031.voiceText: Hmm, guess I gotta be more careful with the pruning next time.

char_214_kafka_CN_032.voiceText: So I guess I couldn't read their plans in the end, huh.

char_214_kafka_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, Kafka here wants to deck out your office with some bonsai. Don'tcha worry, I'll make 'em look real good~

char_214_kafka_CN_042.voiceText: What work you got for me today, Doctor?

char_451_robin_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor. Should I help with anything?

char_451_robin_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor. You always seem busy with work. Don't you have any hobbies? Me, I like seeing old movies people don't really remember.

char_451_robin_CN_003.voiceText: Truthfully, I learned how to fight because of this movie I saw when I was young. Main character used all these knives and homemade traps, and I thought it was really cool, so I started learning myself. My knives here, they're actually the same kind as the ones in that movie.

char_451_robin_CN_004.voiceText: In Columbia, anything can be bought with money. It sounds great, maybe, until you turn it around. Without money, nothing's yours at all.

char_451_robin_CN_005.voiceText: Rhodes Island feels just like a company in a movie. Medical corp on the outside, actually a private military underneath. Operating to save more and more people... feels pretty cool.

char_451_robin_CN_006.voiceText: Doctor, do you think I come off gloomy to others? ...Uh, I didn't used to be like this. It was ever since my pop got the way he did, and I had to start worrying about keeping the family afloat. *Sigh*...

char_451_robin_CN_007.voiceText: I don't hate Anthony. If we have to talk about the past, I think my pop's to blame too. And honestly, I thank Anthony. If he weren't where he was, I might've done something by now I could never take back.

char_451_robin_CN_008.voiceText: Pop never understood. Mom didn't leave because we had no money. It was 'cause his temper got worse every day. I've thought about if I went with Mom instead, but Pop used to be... so nice to me.

char_451_robin_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, there's times I'm following you, and I ease up so much I forget my own stuff. I have the money for treating my pop's illness now, but he's got troubles, and I can't cure that just on my own... Doctor, could you help me?

char_451_robin_CN_010.voiceText: So you drop right where you are when you're tired too, Doctor...

char_451_robin_CN_011.voiceText: Nice to meet you, Doctor. I'm a new Operator. Robin's the name. I've got money issues, so if it's okay with you, you can send me to do whatever.

char_451_robin_CN_012.voiceText: Intense. Feels just like I'm watching an action movie...

char_451_robin_CN_013.voiceText: Huh? I got a raise so quick...? That's great. Thank you, Doctor!

char_451_robin_CN_014.voiceText: I never stuck with my old jobs for very long. The company itself had problems, or it was something with my pop... This time, it feels like I'll be able to stick with Rhodes Island.

char_451_robin_CN_018.voiceText: I'm not too good at figuring teamwork...

char_451_robin_CN_019.voiceText: Wonder what kind of place we're going this time.

char_451_robin_CN_028.voiceText: I'm wielding more than knives here!

char_451_robin_CN_029.voiceText: Doctor, can we cut this sort of mission down a little? Bad for the heart...

char_451_robin_CN_030.voiceText: I bet everybody dreams of having a boss like you, Doctor.

char_451_robin_CN_031.voiceText: Doctor, need me to chase them?

char_451_robin_CN_032.voiceText: Doctor, you go! I'll cover you!

char_451_robin_CN_033.voiceText: Let's get to know this place, then.

char_451_robin_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor. Need me to guard you today?

char_440_pinecn_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor? No, I wasn't taking a nap! I... I was just spacing out!

char_440_pinecn_CN_002.voiceText: Is it raining outside? I used to really hate rainy days... There's mud everywhere, and the rain affects construction. My father always came home really late on those days. But it also feels really comfortable once the rain lets up, and it feels really nice to just stay inside my room, just like what we are doing right now.

char_440_pinecn_CN_003.voiceText: When I used to be a construction worker back in Columbia, every day was a struggle. I had to get up early every morning and go to bed late every night. Sometimes, I even had to work overtime and didn't have any time to sleep...

char_440_pinecn_CN_004.voiceText: Oh, Doctor, would you like to go somewhere together? Hm? Ahh...! W-Where's my tool bag...? Did I leave it at the construction site again? I-I'm sorry, I'll be back right away!

char_440_pinecn_CN_005.voiceText: What I want to do...? Hmm... as long as I have a stable job and get to live a honest life, I think that's good enough for me. In that case, why did I become an operator here, you ask? Well... The pay is a little better, and the work here isn't all that different, either... so I thought I'd give it a try... I guess?

char_440_pinecn_CN_006.voiceText: The Infected... There were a lot of Infected workers in Columbia... Everyone told me to stay away from them, but, just going by the way they work, I don't think they're any different from the rest of us.

char_440_pinecn_CN_007.voiceText: Oh... What was it that Ms. Closure wanted me to do for her again...? She's gonna be really mad if I go back and ask her... Um, Doctor? Do you think you can help me out...?

char_440_pinecn_CN_008.voiceText: My father always told me to study hard if I want a better life. Doctor, you know all sorts of things, right? Do you think you can teach me? I'll try my best to not zone out. I'll really try to.

char_440_pinecn_CN_009.voiceText: I never thought that much about the future before. I figured I would find work in the exploration teams and work as a craftsman my whole life. But now... I really need to thank the big guy. I wouldn't have met you if it wasn't for him... Uh... A-Anyway, I really appreciate what he did for me.

char_440_pinecn_CN_010.voiceText: Fwahh... I'm so tired... I guess maybe I'll take a nap with the Doctor...

char_440_pinecn_CN_011.voiceText: Codename Pinecone... I'm starting at Rhodes Island today... Um... Have you seen my portable battery?

char_440_pinecn_CN_012.voiceText: Um... Umm... I don't get it...

char_440_pinecn_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you, Doctor... But what should I do now? Oh... Do I just need to follow the others' examples? All right...!

char_440_pinecn_CN_014.voiceText: Hm...? Another promotion? Ehehe, you're pretty forgetful yourself, Doctor. Didn't you already give me a promot—This is a new one? Um... Okay. I'll always listen to what you say. So, when are we leaving?

char_440_pinecn_CN_017.voiceText: It's my turn to shine now.

char_440_pinecn_CN_018.voiceText: I guess it's just like being foreman at a construction site?

char_440_pinecn_CN_019.voiceText: Um... Where are we going again...?

char_440_pinecn_CN_020.voiceText: It's the enemy! Don't hold back, anyone!

char_440_pinecn_CN_024.voiceText: I'll stay right here like a nail.

char_440_pinecn_CN_026.voiceText: I still have lots of batteries on me!

char_440_pinecn_CN_028.voiceText: Just gotta think of it as driving nails!

char_440_pinecn_CN_029.voiceText: Phew... That was a lot harder than building a house. Doctor, that makes us kinda impressive, don't you think?

char_440_pinecn_CN_030.voiceText: That was perfect... Doctor, are you happy with how we did?

char_440_pinecn_CN_031.voiceText: Hmm... Maybe I did it in the wrong order...? I'm sorry. It didn't go as well as I was hoping.

char_440_pinecn_CN_032.voiceText: Eh? Why are there sparks... S-Sorry... It's all my fault...

char_440_pinecn_CN_033.voiceText: Yes, is there anything that needs maintaining?

char_440_pinecn_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, want to watch the rain together? There's not much to see, though...

char_332_archet_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, have you ever considered some more... practical ornamentation for Rhodes Island? Such as monastery brewing caskets, or...

char_332_archet_CN_002.voiceText: Landen Monastery's clerics form no normal clergy, you know? Rather than prayer, we're much more about taking up arms to defend Laterano... That's how it goes, but our finances have been in a sorry state these past few years. The justice of guarding others with the faith we harbor—surely the Lord permits us that.

char_332_archet_CN_003.voiceText: Doctor, do you have any interest in beer or bread? Landen Monastery Fermented Goods Contest CCCLXXVII first-place, at your service! No need? Ah, alright... Truly, I want our soft, springy bread and fragrant beer to be known across all of Terra. That would do wonders for our revenues!

char_332_archet_CN_004.voiceText: E—Exusiai? *cough*! I never thought the legend who blew up her alma mater seventeen times in three years would be here at Rhodes Island... She does seem to have some learned business experts at her side, but the risk of an explosion while rebuilding the Monastery... best not for now.

char_332_archet_CN_005.voiceText: Different kinds of arrows entail different uses. There may be plenty of capable archers amongst my sisters, but I don't boast when I proclaim that I'm the only one able to adapt multiple combat modes at once! Heheh! At least, out of my year I am!

char_332_archet_CN_006.voiceText: It was only once I left the Monastery that I realized my arrows may do more than defend the Apostle. It can aid so many Infected, beset by injustice... I'm very proud, but occasionally I'll remember the days gone past where I simply drew my bow, and loosed. Now, every arrow has become so much more weighty.

char_332_archet_CN_007.voiceText: So as to rebuild the Monastery, my sisters have left to seek cooperation across all of Terra. *sigh*! Landen Monastery, age-old guard of Laterano, is now a dispatch agency... If only those old men would grant a little more funding. What kind of an excuse is 'teach with gift, not with gifts!?'

char_332_archet_CN_008.voiceText: Rhodes Island is a world apart from Laterano. All with a different scape in their hearts, mingling together. It truly is an extraordinary thing. Doctor, you must consider coming to the Monastery to teach after you retire. Issues of faith? That'll be no problem! None of us will mind.

char_332_archet_CN_009.voiceText: At the start of spring, we'll prune the overgrown vines, and then open up the cellar come evening and retrieve the wine. The moment the setting sun catches through our glasses, we'll down them in one gulp. Ceremony? No, it's just a custom of ours. Life and faith became one long ago, and we don't want to lose it, that's all.

char_332_archet_CN_010.voiceText: I feel like I heard bells... mm, just my imagination.

char_332_archet_CN_011.voiceText: Cleric of Landen Monastery, Operator Archetto. Today on, I'll be in formal cooperation with you, for the rebuilding of the Landen Monastery famed far and wide! Doctor, if you would, please look over these contract terms!

char_332_archet_CN_012.voiceText: I see, I see, so this is how Rhodes Island's operators fight! Truly, they're exemplary!

char_332_archet_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? My greatest thanks. Hm? I seem at peace? Of course. When you spend five years partaking in commendation ceremonies for outstanding clerics where everyone sleeps the whole way through from hangover, these things don't get to you much.

char_332_archet_CN_014.voiceText: Another promotion? Hmm... all the companies outside seem to strongly emphasize a hierarchical structure. Well, seeing as my promotion's been set in stone, does that mean Rhodes Island is willing to agree and sign to long-term cooperative terms with our Monastery?

char_332_archet_CN_017.voiceText: May Rhodes Island see for itself the distinguished tactical accomplishments of Landen Monastery.

char_332_archet_CN_018.voiceText: Cooperating with my Sisters, everyone always drowned each other out... but under my command, things may be a little terser. I'll do my utmost.

char_332_archet_CN_028.voiceText: My bow has three choices, and the enemy three hardships.

char_332_archet_CN_029.voiceText: 'Long may the Monastery's bells sound.' This is a prayer for victory. Though we've already won!

char_332_archet_CN_030.voiceText: Right! I joined in this battle. Now nobody will think Landen Monastery's just an ornament of Laterano, will they?

char_332_archet_CN_031.voiceText: ...Please allow me the chance to remedy this! This is my mistake, and in no way represents the Monastery!

char_332_archet_CN_032.voiceText: Were battles beyond the walls... always so cruel?

char_332_archet_CN_033.voiceText: It's too stifling in here. There's near to none of the Monastery's sunshine!

char_332_archet_CN_036.voiceText: Ah, Doctor, I've been thinking whether I should invite you with me to come see Laterano. Perhaps you'd have more interest in the Monastery then...

char_332_archet_CN_042.voiceText: May the Lord bless you, Doctor.

char_338_iris_CN_001.voiceText: What? You think this work is going to do itself? Hmph! There's no such fairy who'd finish somebody's work off while they go dozing off. Forget your wild ideas and get your nose to the grindstone, Doctor.

char_338_iris_CN_002.voiceText: I and my companions will often receive children who come to the castle. Of course, on occasion we'll have a good and honest adult come lodging, but that sort of person is few and far between.

char_338_iris_CN_003.voiceText: I came to find a girl named Mabel. Ah, twenty years ago she was a girl. She's a woman by now. ...Codename? How would I know what her codename is? But I know for certain she's here, without a doubt!

char_338_iris_CN_004.voiceText: If there's nothing to keep us, then let me take my leave. I'm still quite busy. I have an appointment with the children being treated here, and I'll be telling them stories today.

char_338_iris_CN_005.voiceText: Children are much better off compared to adults. Children are much more innocent. They have fine qualities. They are the most valuable, cherished thing upon this world.

char_338_iris_CN_006.voiceText: A beloved rag doll, a pretty flower, a storybook turned until its pages are worn... Children who've come to Wonderland have left much to the castle. Things they believe are precious, that they haven't much way of keeping safe themselves, all can be put into our care.

char_338_iris_CN_007.voiceText: Now come wisplight and lamplight, come light up the way~ Come to our little tea party to stay~♪ Here come the guards, and they dance and sing for us, carrying scissors to chop-chop away♪ I sang this song about my friends to entertain the children with me. Learned the words? I shan't sing them to you again.

char_338_iris_CN_008.voiceText: I know. Mabel's no longer with us. You called her Bluishsilver, didn't you? I've seen records... asked after her with her teammates—her tale is so sad. How strange. Though this is the time we'd set, I can't help but feel I was too late...

char_338_iris_CN_009.voiceText: 'Wonderland,' 'Slumberland,' 'the Cradle'... have you never heard these names before? Oh, you poor soul. Had no-one ever told you any bedtime stories? ...Sigh. Oh, I suppose. Close your eyes, now. I'd rather not, but let's have you see for yourself, just once.

char_338_iris_CN_010.voiceText: Oh, really! How do you fall asleep somewhere like this? And the files are all still at sixes and sevens! ...Fine. Seeing that you work so hard normally, I'll help you just this once...

char_338_iris_CN_011.voiceText: I am Iris, Master of the Castle of Dreams, Keeper of the Cradle. As per our agreement, I've come to return something a guest once left to the castle... How strange. Why can I not find her?

char_338_iris_CN_012.voiceText: How barbarous, though it does have its merits.

char_338_iris_CN_013.voiceText: I'm the master of a castle. If we're to talk promotions, I ought to be giving one to you.

char_338_iris_CN_014.voiceText: Right, then! You'll see first-hand the full power of the Master of the Castle! Fairytales uphold such purity, such beauty, and they owe it only to their protectors' sufficient strength. Is Rhodes Island not like this, too?

char_338_iris_CN_018.voiceText: Listen to my orders, now. Agreements made are not to be violated.

char_338_iris_CN_019.voiceText: I will lead you all to the proper place.

char_338_iris_CN_020.voiceText: And those are the people we're driving off, then?

char_338_iris_CN_023.voiceText: The air is quite thick here.

char_338_iris_CN_024.voiceText: Hmph! I'll help you just this once.

char_338_iris_CN_025.voiceText: Would you all like a bedtime story too?

char_338_iris_CN_029.voiceText: How's that? I've driven them all off, now!

char_338_iris_CN_030.voiceText: So this is the taste of victory. Yet... I wonder why I can't feel happy about it...

char_338_iris_CN_031.voiceText: Hmph. They've run off by themselves. Doesn't that sort things?

char_338_iris_CN_032.voiceText: What's going on? Did you fall asleep?! Quick, with me, out of here!

char_338_iris_CN_033.voiceText: What a strange place. Is there no larger bed anywhere?

char_338_iris_CN_036.voiceText: Careful, there, don't ruffle the headdress... yes, quite, comb just like that...

char_452_bstalk_CN_001.voiceText: Want my help? Hehe, I'll think about it if you give my buddies three days of luxury pet food! How about it, sounds like a deal, isn't... Hey, wait up! I'm just kidding! Don't go!

char_452_bstalk_CN_002.voiceText: Outta the way, outta the way~ Beanstalk Breeding Center coming right through! Watch your feet! Careful not to step on any of us~

char_452_bstalk_CN_003.voiceText: Doctor! Click is here at Rhodes Island? I can't believe you haven't ever told me! I'm a huge fan of her outdoorsy videos! She called Pea cute, and she even said she'll bring Pea along the next time she goes on a shoot!

char_452_bstalk_CN_004.voiceText: There's been all these morons saying they'd go mining and then dug up a bunch of holes out in the wilderness. Fine, but how dare they make a mess of everyone's home! If I ever catch those bastards, I'm blowing a hole in their asses with my crossbow!

char_452_bstalk_CN_005.voiceText: Doctor, I'm done with my breeding proposal. Take a look, will ya? Huh? The budget doesn't add up...? Tsk, he found out, huh? Oh, my bad! I probably got the numbers messed up somewhere! I'll get it fixed right away~

char_452_bstalk_CN_006.voiceText: Before I came to Rhodes Island, I sent my resume to so many companies out there, and they all turned me down. Well, just look at how helpful my little buddies are now, both in the battlefield and in logistics. Those big shots only have themselves to blame. It's their loss!

char_452_bstalk_CN_007.voiceText: You see, Pea may be the smallest of the Metal Crabs I brought with me, but she's also the brightest of the bunch! She's gonna be so amazing in the future~! My little buddies are nothing like the normal Metal Crabs out there. They're so smart! They won't be controlled by anyone out there so easily!

char_452_bstalk_CN_008.voiceText: 1, 2! 1, 2! Line up! Defense position, and block! Okay! All of you are doing amazing! Here's your reward. Eat up~! Let's switch it up now. Attac—Whoa, Doctor, how long've you been here? How come you're always so quiet when you walk?!

char_452_bstalk_CN_009.voiceText: My old man doesn't really support me raising my little pals. He says they're useless, and that I'd be better off raising burdenbeasts. Hmph, I'm show him. I'll make it big with my buddies, and we'll see if he has anything to say then! Hey, Doctor, have you ever thought of investing in me? I guarantee you you'll be raking in lots of money!

char_452_bstalk_CN_010.voiceText: Alright, focus! Doctor, you can't just space out while you're working. Take a look at what a good girl Pea is. Be more like her.

char_452_bstalk_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, Doctor. My name's Beanstalk. Starting today, I'll be... Eh? What's in my case? Oh, this is Peacake. Here, Pea, say hi to the Doctor.

char_452_bstalk_CN_012.voiceText: Aha! That was awesome! Did you see that, Pea?

char_452_bstalk_CN_013.voiceText: Ehe, you're promoting us because of how well we did in the last operation, right?

char_452_bstalk_CN_014.voiceText: Doctor, thanks for giving me and my buddies a chance to prove ourselves! I'll cut the formalities. We'll get even more amazing than this! You're in for a surprise!

char_452_bstalk_CN_018.voiceText: Alright! Everyone, do what I say!

char_452_bstalk_CN_020.voiceText: Huh? Are these who we're up against?

char_452_bstalk_CN_023.voiceText: Go! Show them what we've got!

char_452_bstalk_CN_027.voiceText: I won't let you get past us!

char_452_bstalk_CN_028.voiceText: You assholes! I won't let you hurt my buddies!

char_452_bstalk_CN_029.voiceText: Hehe, you guys are no match for us~

char_452_bstalk_CN_030.voiceText: Mission complete~! How's that? My buddies did great, huh?

char_452_bstalk_CN_031.voiceText: Oh, some of them got through! Wait here, Doctor. I'll go after them!

char_452_bstalk_CN_032.voiceText: *Sob*. It's okay, everyone. Don't cry. I'll beat those jackasses up next time!

char_452_bstalk_CN_033.voiceText: I don't mind sleeping anywhere. Where's the breeding room, though?

char_452_bstalk_CN_034.voiceText: Why'd you do that? Stop pulling my ribbon!

char_452_bstalk_CN_036.voiceText: Hm? What's up? Wanna pet Pea?

char_402_tuye_CN_001.voiceText: You want me on work this boring thing...? Fine, fine. You're interesting enough to me. I'll go along with you.

char_402_tuye_CN_002.voiceText: If you want something moved, don't ask me. I'm not that brand of Forte.

char_402_tuye_CN_003.voiceText: This is some insanely precise instrument... huh? What, familiar sight? Huhhh. Oh, right. If that Mayer person comes 'round, don't tell her I'm here.

char_402_tuye_CN_004.voiceText: Never seen the equipment on my back before? Right, come over, put your hand here... keh-ka-hahahahahah! Look at your dumb face! You wanna know what just came out? It's water! And what's mixed in? Heh. You don't get to know.

char_402_tuye_CN_005.voiceText: My interest in helping others is zip. But higher efficiency is good for everybody.

char_402_tuye_CN_006.voiceText: Battles finish up faster now. Good to know, I guess.

char_402_tuye_CN_007.voiceText: Cake? Soft and squishy—not my speed. But. Mmp, mmnm... the umeboshi on top's not bad, sure.

char_402_tuye_CN_008.voiceText: No rain in the ship? Wow. Like I don't know that? Now try and predict how it goes down out there. Next time there's a storm, just try it, get a little closer. Bet you won't stop thanking me then.

char_402_tuye_CN_009.voiceText: Oi. How does a day trip in the desert sound? I'll take you. I mean, anywhere else is fine too. As long as we have my multifunction jetpack, following the scent of the wind... heh. You must be dumb happy, having a guide as stellar as me.

char_402_tuye_CN_010.voiceText: You out cold? Then let me just try this. Harder flow, greater spray area... And you get no right to complain.

char_402_tuye_CN_011.voiceText: You the Doctor? They all say you're the one here who knows more than the rest. You're gonna let me figure that out.

char_402_tuye_CN_012.voiceText: Combat's just like crossing the desert, where experience means nothing. Your only need is survival instincts.

char_402_tuye_CN_013.voiceText: Doesn't this Elite Medal have any other kind of function? No fun there.

char_402_tuye_CN_014.voiceText: Medical pro? It's a weird world where I get called that. Anyway, it's all about getting my jobs done, either way, right?

char_402_tuye_CN_017.voiceText: Out for field work again? Fine, fine. You're helping me test new equipment when we get back.

char_402_tuye_CN_018.voiceText: Leading team combat doesn't differ much from being a guide.

char_402_tuye_CN_020.voiceText: More boring than running into a sandstorm.

char_402_tuye_CN_026.voiceText: Time to test my upgraded equipment.

char_402_tuye_CN_027.voiceText: How's the newest nutritional fluid taste?

char_402_tuye_CN_029.voiceText: Tch. The sandstorms I've seen beat this any day.

char_402_tuye_CN_030.voiceText: Scraped through, huh. Wasn't a waste of time.

char_402_tuye_CN_031.voiceText: Efficiency lacking. Gotta head back and adjust my equipment, or switch reagents, maybe.

char_402_tuye_CN_032.voiceText: At least you figured a good retreat route...

char_402_tuye_CN_033.voiceText: You have a lot of rooms, huh...

char_402_tuye_CN_034.voiceText: You gotta stop the boring crap.

char_402_tuye_CN_036.voiceText: Wanna try touching my bag again? Won't hit your face this time. Promise.

char_402_tuye_CN_042.voiceText: Rain again. Good weather, huh, Doctor?

char_2015_dusk_CN_001.voiceText: Hm? Did I not explain that you were forbidden to enter without my express permission, after knocking? Oh? This is your office? You're working? Then have I not come out of my room to work as well? What is the meaning of 'your office'? Tsheq-chi (Get out)! I'm still sketching it out.

char_2015_dusk_CN_002.voiceText: You want to see my painting? You may. For you, I could even give you the painting. But if you like it, I won't give it to you. You don't like it? Huh, then you wouldn't want it anyway. This is who I am. Deal with it.

char_2015_dusk_CN_003.voiceText: Haa… I'm trapped on this ship. If anyone asks, you tell them so, and you do not let them into my room. I'm taking up space? I'm refusing to perform my operator duties? Hello, I am Dusk, the great painter trapped in this room.

char_2015_dusk_CN_004.voiceText: I'm not going out. Don't try to make me go out, I don't want to go out. I no longer care for the world outside. Do I dislike it? I like it fine. The mountains and rivers, the flowers and feathers, the pools and forests, the common folk, young and old, I could paint forever, I could watch forever, and yet, I will not go. It does not hold my interest forever.

char_2015_dusk_CN_005.voiceText: I loathe the word 'taste.' What gives these people the confidence to demand something good just as they open their mouths to lock the gates to others? It is unbecoming. If you are satisfied, you are satisfied. Should you enter, you must not bar the gate. Do you see the twin moons thinking only of themselves?

char_2015_dusk_CN_006.voiceText: An opportunity to watch me paint in earnest comes but once in a lifetime to one in ten thousand individuals. 'When the time comes, the strength of heaven and earth are one.' Ch'i, bone, shape, color, method, pouring out as a vast river, fine like the shadow of mountain bamboo, such is my brush, and it will not stop.

char_2015_dusk_CN_007.voiceText: I took the time to partake of some contemporary works. Films are not bad, they are like paintings. The good ones all have a unique strength of character, with form, and with decent meaning. Right, poetry and painting have a legacy. Do you have time to help me burn Nian's mountain of garbage? She is denigrating the very concept of cinema. Please.

char_2015_dusk_CN_008.voiceText: Food? Oh, thank you. Hm, where does this drink come from? It's good. Quite good. But I feel like it's missing something. You want to know what I usually eat? Then close your eyes. Ah~ You feel nothing, yes? That's because if you don't look, the food in my paintings does not exist.

char_2015_dusk_CN_009.voiceText: Take a look at Nian's carefree expression. You know the truth, don't you? She cares quite a bit about our lives, and our deaths. As for me? I may not get along with the wretched scribbler, but neither of us care much. When people die, the paintings remain. When I die, my work remains.

char_2015_dusk_CN_010.voiceText: Dreams are like unto life, like unto the scroll. One sleeps this sleep, will one sleep for millennia?

char_2015_dusk_CN_011.voiceText: Oh? {@nickname}? Another contract? Very well, please don't bother me again after I sign this one. Here... I should tell you here and now: I, Dusk, do not give out my paintings. Not to anyone. And I don't take commissions!

char_2015_dusk_CN_012.voiceText: Hm? A swing of an axe becomes rivers of blood. Do you mean... you want me to paint this?

char_2015_dusk_CN_013.voiceText: Why use a sword? There is a reason. 'With an inkstone sheath, one may learn the annals. With a brush sword, one may paint the celestial.' Is it true? Naturally, I speak off the cuff.

char_2015_dusk_CN_014.voiceText: Ahh, to make it this far with me... I should paint you a scroll. But be careful! Do not get caught up within it. The world I paint is much more fascinating than this one. How many have been lost, since ancient times? How many have escaped?

char_2015_dusk_CN_018.voiceText: Captain? What does a captain do?

char_2015_dusk_CN_020.voiceText: I'm in a good mood today. I'll give you this one I've titled 'Bones on the Sand'.

char_2015_dusk_CN_022.voiceText: Better leave the fine brush at home.

char_2015_dusk_CN_023.voiceText: Would any of you like to be my paint?

char_2015_dusk_CN_024.voiceText: This battlefield would do well with a splash of ink.

char_2015_dusk_CN_025.voiceText: Too difficult to explain, let me paint it for you.

char_2015_dusk_CN_026.voiceText: With the setting of the sun, the brush draws up the peaks!

char_2015_dusk_CN_027.voiceText: Copy the infinite with the tangible, bring the intangible to life!

char_2015_dusk_CN_028.voiceText: I am rather attached to you. Most of the time.

char_2015_dusk_CN_029.voiceText: Once, painting and war were quite different. But with this power, battle is art.

char_2015_dusk_CN_031.voiceText: Hm... a failed painting must be destroyed. It will bring shame.

char_2015_dusk_CN_032.voiceText: Slipped on a stroke? Start over.

char_2015_dusk_CN_033.voiceText: Do not bother preparing the room for me. I will handle it myself.

char_2015_dusk_CN_042.voiceText: What was your name again? Oh, {@nickname}?

char_362_saga_CN_001.voiceText: I shall come! Doctor, so long as I am here, thou mayst be at ease in thy work!

char_362_saga_CN_002.voiceText: I grew from childhood in the monastery. Though I could recite the texts from heart, I never fully understood their inner meanings, and my old head priest and the other great masters gave explanations from which I could comprehend even less. Doctor, thou art of learned stature. Mayst thou be able to teach me?

char_362_saga_CN_003.voiceText: Rhodes Island truly lacks none for novel machinery... hm? Doctor, underestimate me not. I may begin clueless, but I am no contrarian to the times. If I do not know how, then I need only learn. My personal music player even holds some songs of the good Miss Sora within it.

char_362_saga_CN_004.voiceText: So as to evade Catastrophe, I once accompanied my old head priest and fellow monastery apprentices over mountain and valley. My head priest spoke that Catastrophes were the wrath of the gods. Yet, I have never witnessed one by my own eyes. I am somewhat curious.

char_362_saga_CN_005.voiceText: I am not a true monk, merely raised by the monastery. At my departure, Saga was the name my old head priest gave to me. Its meaning is of high mountains and rugged roads. And only when I left the monastery, did I come to know how the world was no straightforward thing.

char_362_saga_CN_006.voiceText: I swallow hardship, and fear not fatigue, yet there is still one thing I cannot assent to. My master spoke that all living beings are equal. The Infected are people all the same, people only fallen ill. Why can they not be permitted to live?

char_362_saga_CN_007.voiceText: Ho-ho. I may have only erred upon a Rhodes Island recruitment spot at first, but whether the food or the beds, it is all of great quality, and the pay pales not. I truly have stumbled upon a wonderful place.

char_362_saga_CN_008.voiceText: When I left the monastery, I had thought that entering society would involve no more than dealing with pests, ridding some despots. I had never dreamt it would be so treacherous as this. There are times I do not even know what I draw my blade for. Doctor... I do not understand.

char_362_saga_CN_009.voiceText: I still puzzle over much in my heart, but I have understood at least that some answers I must seek myself, and some thoughts I must think through myself. Doctor, until I have sorted it all out, I wish to continue my training by thine side. Pray, allow me this!

char_362_saga_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor... ho, thou art quite skillful to fall asleep sitting. In that case, I shall meditate for a while.

char_362_saga_CN_011.voiceText: Thou art the Doctor? Hail and well... ah, ought not I be more serious at times like these? Ahem—my name is Saga. I am a wandering monk. Should there be any place thou mayst need me, refrain not in sending me!

char_362_saga_CN_012.voiceText: Ho-ho. To think such strategy does exist in the world. My horizons have broadened.

char_362_saga_CN_013.voiceText: A raise? Splendid! I have been watering at the mouth to try the deluxe set at the cafeteria for quite some time, yet have been embarrassingly out of pocket... today, I am finally able to feast!

char_362_saga_CN_014.voiceText: Dear head priest. In my heart yet is wild disarray. The ways of this world I still cannot see through, nor cut down. Though I am fortunate to have met with great people, and with their guidance, there will come a day in our turbulent mortal world where I cut through to the heavens!

char_362_saga_CN_018.voiceText: Am I the captain? Not a problem!

char_362_saga_CN_021.voiceText: Takuan-zuke... hah! I am right here!

char_362_saga_CN_029.voiceText: 'Twas truly an arduous trial. I have gained greatly for it.

char_362_saga_CN_030.voiceText: As expected of the Doctor! Alone, I would surely have let quite a few through.

char_362_saga_CN_031.voiceText: My head priest spoke that one must have a merciful heart, and I believe that this suffices, more or less.

char_362_saga_CN_032.voiceText: Doctor, go quickly! Leave the rear to me!

char_362_saga_CN_036.voiceText: Call, and I shall surely come running.

char_362_saga_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor, hast thou eaten? An unfilled stomach will surely leave thee powerless at work.

char_455_nothin_CN_001.voiceText: Hm. The office of the vaunted Doctor, then? Marvelous, truly. Allow me a brief moment to consult my feng shui crash-course guidebook...

char_455_nothin_CN_002.voiceText: I'm no mere braggart! Beyond a little kickboxing in a scuffle, I can rustle up meals, practice acupuncture, divine with feng shui, work masonry, tend to rice and angle fish alike—I'm a maestro of all kinds! Doctor, you need only give the order, and I'll see everything through!

char_455_nothin_CN_003.voiceText: D-Doctor, I was a little idle, see, and went to make myself useful at HR, and by carelessness glimpsed at a few operator files, and... er, well, could FEater be the very star of 'Fiends of the Gods Reincarnated Immortal' herself? Truly? Could I go get an autograph?

char_455_nothin_CN_004.voiceText: Who was my master? Hmm, a question as complex as a showdown of Yan cuisines. Normally I'd refrain from answering that, as slipping up would get me beaten sideways. That said... you need only know, Doctor, I'm the last descendant of the Lien line. Ah, but my family name's not Lien. I'm a Ch'u.

char_455_nothin_CN_005.voiceText: M-Miss Dusk really did... come to Rhodes Island with us, then? My, um... what was it now? My recollection's quite fuzzy now, yet I have the vague impression that within her painted dreams, I had a peek into my own miserable future. Ah, let's never we mind. Dear, oh, dear. You be quite careful too, Doctor.

char_455_nothin_CN_006.voiceText: Now, now, Doctor, don't worry about me. I and the Infected do get along well. Back at my old place, a Catastrophe once struck not too far away. It frightened all of us, seeing the world go pitch black. My master remarked then that Catastrophes were Heaven's false charge against the human realm. Ah, truly a bitter thing.

char_455_nothin_CN_007.voiceText: Benefactor Lava? Yes, I call her my benefactor. She once saved me, and as time went on, it became second nature. Throughout my life I've been saved thrice, and every time, I engrave it upon my soul. The gloompincer incident, you mean? No, not that. She showed to me a path, and that was true grace beyond all.

char_455_nothin_CN_008.voiceText: Say, Doctor, are people able to brush the past away as they live? Certainly not, hm? If the bonds you once left behind still hold fast, what ought you do? You've no idea either? Well, then. It seems we're companions in our misery. Here, what say we crack some sunflower seeds?

char_455_nothin_CN_009.voiceText: Countless, they were, the ancient parasol trees about Kou-wu City. Oh, just reminiscing all of a sudden. I remember the leaves scattered across the ground come fall, when my parents would visit me from the country. Only then would my strict master speak nothing but good, and her other disciples, my brothers and sisters, wouldn't bully me. No, well, just reminiscing.

char_455_nothin_CN_010.voiceText: Hmm. I've been pondering a fan for you too, but what ought we write on it?

char_455_nothin_CN_011.voiceText: My codename? 'Mr. Nothing.' The latter man of Tzu-hsu and Wu-yu; Nonexistent and Nothing indeed. And you, fine soul, are the Doctor? That is to say, my new boss? Well, then, would you like me to massage your back? Loosen up your legs?

char_455_nothin_CN_012.voiceText: Ho, what a hundredfold bouquet of martial prowess. You've got my eyes wide open now!

char_455_nothin_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion and a raise?! Ohh, ohh, I thank you, Doctor, in all respects possible! Be it for you, I would brave the greatest fires and waters, I would not hesitate to... well, that said, how much might my wages be growing by?

char_455_nothin_CN_014.voiceText: Sooner or later, I plan to return to Kou-wu City and set every debt in my books straight. My only worry is I may invite trouble and sweep others up in its path. You know this, dear Doctor, and yet you still wish to bestow such partiality on me...? Your kindness toward me is a grace, and I will never, in eternity, forget it.

char_455_nothin_CN_017.voiceText: Very well! Doctor, I'll see to it that you have nothing at all to worry about.

char_455_nothin_CN_018.voiceText: Me, the captain? Hold one moment, just let me find my secret tomes for the art of war, now...

char_455_nothin_CN_019.voiceText: As they say, all have their own methods, whether arms against a force or earth to a waterspout. There'll be a way!

char_455_nothin_CN_020.voiceText: I'm witnessing fiends, one and all! Quite frightening!

char_455_nothin_CN_023.voiceText: Very well! Leave this to me.

char_455_nothin_CN_024.voiceText: The Doctor, you are! What a sagacious decision!

char_455_nothin_CN_026.voiceText: A perfect technique makes freedom to act!

char_455_nothin_CN_027.voiceText: The moon waxes and wanes. The fan opens and shuts!

char_455_nothin_CN_028.voiceText: Let's have you make a move first, now.

char_455_nothin_CN_029.voiceText: More hands bring more fuel for the fire. When we concert our efforts together, yes, we truly can burn the sky a red to rival sunsets. Not bad, not bad.

char_455_nothin_CN_030.voiceText: As they say, those of just ways have much support, and those of lost ways find little. Seen as such, our victory is assured.

char_455_nothin_CN_031.voiceText: Pursue not the cornered. Suppose anything troublesome should happen, we'll just bear it together.

char_455_nothin_CN_032.voiceText: Go on ahead, everyone. No worries. My runaway act is first in class. I'll be just fine.

char_455_nothin_CN_033.voiceText: Oh-hoh, Rhodes Island truly is a wondrous land. I feel quite dizzy just looking.

char_455_nothin_CN_034.voiceText: Hoh? What's this for exactly, Doctor?

char_455_nothin_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, what say I teach you a thing or two about some moves?

char_455_nothin_CN_042.voiceText: Well, if it isn't the Doctor! What a happy coincidence!

char_1011_lava2_CN_001.voiceText: I have some free time, so I guess I could help you out... What's this? This has got nothing to do with disasters and Arts, just some normal paperwork? Hey!

char_1011_lava2_CN_002.voiceText: You wanna try some fortune-telling? Well, that brings me back. I haven't done it for a while. I could take a look at your fortune to kill some time, I guess. Hmm, if your luck isn't beyond words as always... Well, you're gonna have to prove my results wrong.

char_1011_lava2_CN_003.voiceText: I do research on Arts because it's part of my responsibilities as a Caster. If I can't even do that, how am I supposed to protect those who... Huh? You got sweets? For me? Uh, thanks...

char_1011_lava2_CN_004.voiceText: Hibiscus... My sister always helps people whenever they need, even if it's not part of her mission. It's like she's not a Sarkaz at all, what with how kind she is. She treats this world with kindness, but how many people know to repay it?

char_1011_lava2_CN_005.voiceText: Why I'm not into fortune telling anymore? 'cause the fear and curiosity that people have about the future usually has to do with natural phenomena. That, and I've realized the results you get with fortune telling don't really mean much, having come face to face with so many cruelties.

char_1011_lava2_CN_006.voiceText: In terms of performance, books and staffs are just about the same as Arts conductors. If you ask me, I think knives are much more practical. When you run short of your Arts and have to throw yourself into a melee, or you're out in the wilderness, just trying to survive, all those words in the books aren't going to do you much good.

char_1011_lava2_CN_007.voiceText: It's a pain to fight as a team, but when I look back on those times I fought side by side with my Reserve Ops teammates now... It brings back memories, I guess. If I get the chance to fight alongside them again... No, never mind.

char_1011_lava2_CN_008.voiceText: I wasn't that grumpy and curt now, was I? How come Hibiscus still treats me like a kid who hasn't grown up yet? It's like she's doing it to pick on me! We finally managed to make up, but it just ticks me off when I see her act so calm about it!

char_1011_lava2_CN_009.voiceText: The times we live in are so messed up, there's just way too much malevolence going around in this world. We have to change that. I can't stand all those rotten hypocrites acting all kindhearted treating my fellow Sarkaz like that... just because of who we are.

char_1011_lava2_CN_010.voiceText: Sheesh... You always look so peaceful in your sleep.

char_1011_lava2_CN_011.voiceText: Hey, what's the big idea? Who let you come in without knock—Oh, it's you, Doctor. Why am I wearing this? Well... I'm hitting the training grounds to test my limits once more. Wanna come watch, Doctor?

char_1011_lava2_CN_013.voiceText: There are lots of talented Casters out there, but I'm not so lucky. That's why I have to get stronger if I want to be able to save the world. Thanks for helping me out, Doctor.

char_1011_lava2_CN_014.voiceText: I've got the hang of fire Arts now. If I keep working on this, I might just make it to the boundaries of modern Arts theory... I might even be able to manipulate space and matter.

char_1011_lava2_CN_017.voiceText: I've got a good idea of the enemy's weaknesses. Let's go.

char_1011_lava2_CN_018.voiceText: I'm not good at this kinda stuff... Just gotta get this over with quickly, right?

char_1011_lava2_CN_019.voiceText: I'm counting on you to have my back while I take care of the enemies.

char_1011_lava2_CN_020.voiceText: You've strayed from the path of righteousness. Your sinful souls deserve no mercy.

char_1011_lava2_CN_027.voiceText: Too weak. There's no point in hiding!

char_1011_lava2_CN_029.voiceText: It's only by overcoming challenges that we manage to accomplish something.

char_1011_lava2_CN_030.voiceText: Hmph... Accept your defeat in pain and fear. Evil will always be defeated.

char_1011_lava2_CN_031.voiceText: This shows how powerful we are now. It's far from enough, though. I know I can do better than this. I have to do better.

char_1011_lava2_CN_032.voiceText: Gah... I gotta... eradicate all evil...

char_1011_lava2_CN_033.voiceText: I still have lots to do. Let me stay here.

char_1011_lava2_CN_036.voiceText: I'm reading. There's still a lot I need to learn... It's time for tea already? Let's get going, then.

char_456_ash_CN_002.voiceText: The most important thing my safta taught me was that life shouldn't have too many taboos.

char_456_ash_CN_003.voiceText: Focus on the work at hand and don't jump to any conclusions.

char_456_ash_CN_004.voiceText: Tachanka's taught me a thing or two about how to build defenses.

char_456_ash_CN_005.voiceText: I have some questions, Doctor. I hope you can answer them for me.

char_456_ash_CN_006.voiceText: Overcoming obstacles and breaking down barriers makes a lot of things easier.

char_456_ash_CN_007.voiceText: I'm willing to try, as long as the reward is commensurate to the risk.

char_456_ash_CN_008.voiceText: You think I'm strict, huh? I'll take that as a compliment.

char_456_ash_CN_009.voiceText: Do me a favor. You worry about the strategy and let me worry about the tactics.

char_456_ash_CN_011.voiceText: Rainbow Operator, codename Ash. I have my authorization and I'm ready for assignment.

char_456_ash_CN_012.voiceText: The more we can learn about their attack patterns, the better off we'll be.

char_456_ash_CN_014.voiceText: You can't really understand a conflict until you've been on both sides.

char_456_ash_CN_018.voiceText: Let's get our heads in the game.

char_456_ash_CN_019.voiceText: Let's show them what we can do.

char_456_ash_CN_029.voiceText: That worked out better than I expected.

char_456_ash_CN_031.voiceText: We knew the risks. We still have to see this through.

char_457_blitz_CN_001.voiceText: Instead of sitting here, why don't we walk out together?

char_457_blitz_CN_002.voiceText: I'm in the starting lineup for next week's football match. Come watch the game!

char_457_blitz_CN_003.voiceText: If you know how we can improve my G52 Tactical Shield, please submit a test application. I'll be there anytime.

char_457_blitz_CN_004.voiceText: Ease up, there's nothing to be nervous about. Should I invite Tachanka to dance a little ballet for you?

char_457_blitz_CN_005.voiceText: The doctors don't test me because I'm sick. They test me because I'm too healthy. Good thing I'm not afraid of needles!

char_457_blitz_CN_006.voiceText: Flash! Bash! Kapow! That's all you need to know.

char_457_blitz_CN_007.voiceText: Not only am I sweet, but I've got a great sense of humor.

char_457_blitz_CN_008.voiceText: If you find something interesting to play with, count me in.

char_457_blitz_CN_009.voiceText: We have a responsibility to look after one another. I take that very seriously.

char_457_blitz_CN_010.voiceText: This is really interesting, but not to me.

char_457_blitz_CN_011.voiceText: RAINBOW Operator, codename Blitz. Give the order and I'll bash 'em in the face with my shield!

char_457_blitz_CN_012.voiceText: This is pretty good. The popcorn, I mean. Want some?

char_457_blitz_CN_013.voiceText: Medals, awards, promotions. They go really well with my shield, don't you think?

char_457_blitz_CN_014.voiceText: I don't like photos of myself. The lighting is always wrong.

char_457_blitz_CN_017.voiceText: Should we go get the bad guys maybe? Just a suggestion.

char_457_blitz_CN_018.voiceText: Remember: point your guns at the bad guys.

char_457_blitz_CN_021.voiceText: Do think I have time to use the bathroom?

char_457_blitz_CN_022.voiceText: If anyone needs to sneeze, do it now.

char_457_blitz_CN_029.voiceText: Are we good? Can we go home now?

char_457_blitz_CN_030.voiceText: Everything will be fine, I'm here after all.

char_457_blitz_CN_031.voiceText: Am I going to need to save all your asses again?

char_457_blitz_CN_032.voiceText: Dammit, did anyone remember to bring the ammo?

char_457_blitz_CN_033.voiceText: Let's go say hello to our neighbors first.

char_457_blitz_CN_036.voiceText: You should invite me over for dinner. We are friends, after all.

char_458_rfrost_CN_001.voiceText: Here's the schedule. You'll also need to review the weekly reports, expense records, and meeting agendas. Which do you want to do first?

char_458_rfrost_CN_002.voiceText: We'll overcome any obstacle as long as we work together.

char_458_rfrost_CN_003.voiceText: Excuse me, sir, but do you mind if I tidy up the bookshelf?

char_458_rfrost_CN_004.voiceText: Sometimes humans behave exactly like wild animals. Understanding this makes me a more efficient operator.

char_458_rfrost_CN_005.voiceText: To see the really interesting things, you have to get out of the city. That's why I'm always so far away.

char_458_rfrost_CN_006.voiceText: Putting out the Welcome Mat is the first step. Luring the prey takes a bit more doing.

char_458_rfrost_CN_007.voiceText: No, no. This is all wrong. Let me reconsider for a bit.

char_458_rfrost_CN_008.voiceText: Is there anything I can help with?

char_458_rfrost_CN_009.voiceText: Who's the hunter? Who's the hunted? That's up to Mother Nature and the battlefield in question.

char_458_rfrost_CN_010.voiceText: Simply pull this string and there's the Welcome Mat...

char_458_rfrost_CN_011.voiceText: RAINBOW Operator, codename Frost. At your service, sir.

char_458_rfrost_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you for your trust, sir.

char_458_rfrost_CN_014.voiceText: There are two things we absolutely need in a survival situation: water and hope.

char_458_rfrost_CN_018.voiceText: Don't forget, we're a team and we have a plan.

char_458_rfrost_CN_019.voiceText: Time for all the planning to pay off.

char_458_rfrost_CN_020.voiceText: I've got eyes on the hostiles.

char_458_rfrost_CN_023.voiceText: Don't let them get the drop on you.

char_458_rfrost_CN_029.voiceText: Stay two steps ahead of the enemy at all times.

char_459_tachak_CN_001.voiceText: If you invited me, you must not be looking for a tactician.

char_459_tachak_CN_002.voiceText: I love my country, for better or for worse.

char_459_tachak_CN_003.voiceText: Have you met my sister? She's the one in the white coat in the photo, and those are her children.

char_459_tachak_CN_004.voiceText: Survive. Be a leader. You don't want your loved ones crying over your grave, do you?

char_459_tachak_CN_005.voiceText: I don't want my kids to follow in my footsteps. Being a soldier is too dangerous.

char_459_tachak_CN_006.voiceText: In my country, focusing firepower on a target is considered a simple and effective way to achieve victory.

char_459_tachak_CN_007.voiceText: I like the way you think.

char_459_tachak_CN_008.voiceText: Personally, I prefer the enemies come to us in search of death. How about you?

char_459_tachak_CN_009.voiceText: Relax, baby. When this is all over, I'll buy you some vodka.

char_459_tachak_CN_010.voiceText: Are you bored? Why not clean your weapon?

char_459_tachak_CN_011.voiceText: RAINBOW Operator, codename Tachanka. I'm ready. Where do you want me?

char_459_tachak_CN_012.voiceText: First, we learn about them. Then we outsmart them.

char_459_tachak_CN_014.voiceText: They told me I'd died. They were wrong. I was reborn.

char_459_tachak_CN_018.voiceText: Just don't play hero, it never works.

char_459_tachak_CN_023.voiceText: Guys, you are all lucky I was there.

char_459_tachak_CN_031.voiceText: We're not out of the woods, bratan.

char_459_tachak_CN_036.voiceText: Call me in for support if you need it.

char_472_pasngr_CN_001.voiceText: To be of assistance to you would be my great honor.

char_472_pasngr_CN_002.voiceText: The Originium crystal on my forehead is oft regarded as an adornment. A very convenient mistake; it lets me save the effort of concealing my Infected status. That said, every time pain crosses my brow, I'm deeply struck by my own foolishness. To say I leave Sargon asks just where my path now leads.

char_472_pasngr_CN_003.voiceText: Sesa is still a young one. Yes, I am only a scant few years his senior. But his approach to patience is slightly ungainly, and his resentment not firm enough. If he wants for a drop of verity to set his passion for vengeance alight, I would be much willing to provide... Ah, should you forbid it, I would not act out of turn.

char_472_pasngr_CN_004.voiceText: I abhor the black market. Only lowly, vapid ruses circle it. People all believe themselves the most veteran players, yet all end dismally. At times, you need only think with some care, and you can send someone to their demise—even a padishah's very own appointed lord ameer. Hm, might you be curious?

char_472_pasngr_CN_005.voiceText: That great fire, then? Do you look to fault me? Quite, I would not challenge it. But not a single innocent came to suffer in that fire. Nor did a single perpetrator survive. In the black market of Sargon, the good have only ever come in one variety; they are the ones who live on. And I have lived on.

char_472_pasngr_CN_006.voiceText: I and Kal'tsit... Dr. Kal'tsit, are indeed former acquaintances. To be precise, she was my rescuer and savior, but be at ease; I am yours now. Oh, was that not your concern? How remarkable, that as a coworker of our 'Kal'tsit,' you could yet be so unwary?

char_472_pasngr_CN_007.voiceText: 'Were I to return to Columbia.' I cannot say I've never entertained the possibility in these years, but such supposition would only serve to shake me. Doctor, I hope you should use me to the utmost. If such mild civilian techniques have become a stranger to me, I would now much rather renounce them.

char_472_pasngr_CN_008.voiceText: Elliot? How do you... Hm. Elliot. His parents gone before their time, his one beloved, esteemed teacher dead in Sargon, the work which bore his faith but a stepping stone in someone else's conspiracy. To this day, he is bereft of anything. Elliot Glover is merely a laughable life lived.

char_472_pasngr_CN_009.voiceText: I know a scientist. Of a brightest star, an elegant gentleness, as if a born leader. I admire him, depend on him, regard him as my elder brother. But his end is not a good one, considerably not. So you must protect yourself well, Doctor. After all, we do get along quite pleasantly.

char_472_pasngr_CN_010.voiceText: How long it has been—since such clear skies.

char_472_pasngr_CN_011.voiceText: Your Operator, Passenger. I have been looking forward to the day I work with you, Doctor; we will together enjoy this journey.

char_472_pasngr_CN_012.voiceText: Admirable tactics. I see great benefit is drawn from your command.

char_472_pasngr_CN_013.voiceText: I shall, for you and Rhodes Island both, offer ever more perfected service. I invite you to trust me, that the Reefsteep Black Market's 'Sand Soldier' still hides further means.

char_472_pasngr_CN_014.voiceText: I truly hope that my amusing Operator codename may be able to remind you—Doctor, there is no need to trust others, and you are capable of doing everything yourself. Oh? It seems you have other views. I shall duly accede, then.

char_472_pasngr_CN_017.voiceText: Allow me to show you how a true exceptional weapon of war may perform.

char_472_pasngr_CN_018.voiceText: I am quite familiar with strategy and planning. Of course, it is contingent, should you have other notions of your own.

char_472_pasngr_CN_020.voiceText: Now then, we have everything in place.

char_472_pasngr_CN_029.voiceText: You must pardon me; it seems my lowly weapons have barely served to accomplish this mission. Should you assent to my adopting more... extreme methods, we may thus have an easier time.

char_472_pasngr_CN_030.voiceText: Thunder and lightning are but a form of punishment, and they have paid the price for their ill deeds. How good it is, do you not think?

char_472_pasngr_CN_031.voiceText: I cannot permit the punished to leave my sight in peace. Doctor, I plead you permit me to perform this aftercare.

char_472_pasngr_CN_032.voiceText: It is not a sweet loss, Doctor, but have peace of mind. Those who have snatched away victory from your hands—will be privileged to enjoy suffering in full.

char_472_pasngr_CN_033.voiceText: It is a captivating landship, Doctor. Sargon has never accorded me such treatment.

char_472_pasngr_CN_034.voiceText: Oh. Might something be the matter?

char_472_pasngr_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, are you soon to take coffee? These are my own hand-tended coffee beans—it was my singular recreation in Sargon.

char_363_toddi_CN_001.voiceText: Just let 'em burn. You weren't gonna give those papers a second look anyway.

char_363_toddi_CN_002.voiceText: If you wanted me to lay defenses in here, I'd break up the floor for starters. Not that I mind, it's up to you to think about it.

char_363_toddi_CN_003.voiceText: You've got people from Royal Guard knocking about too? Heh—ain't that interesting.

char_363_toddi_CN_004.voiceText: Calibrate the sight? Nah, the stuff I ordered last should be here almost, I'll make the arrows first... Push off! Out my way!

char_363_toddi_CN_005.voiceText: Most who leave Vouivre don't agree with the mercenary life in Sargon. Move to Victoria, end up doing something else instead. You know, like... yeah, factory-working, farming. Right. Having their own little touch of land.

char_363_toddi_CN_006.voiceText: You could probably tell, but I didn't used to be artillery. Recon, infiltration, CQC, mainly learned all that. I know I didn't like it, and the instructors wouldn't let me switch, so I dropped out, simple as. Where's the point in learning things you hate?

char_363_toddi_CN_007.voiceText: Oh, you're helpless! How am I going to the workshop wearing this?!

char_363_toddi_CN_008.voiceText: It's meant for attacking nomadic cities, this weapon. Using it to help you lot cope with skirmishers? It's like a hatchet to a cupcake. Let me try hitting a city or two sometime for practice, won't you?

char_363_toddi_CN_009.voiceText: Don't you think these crystals on my shoulder here match well with my hair color? I like my off-the-shoulder clothes too, so it's perfect. Shame, though, it would've been nice if they covered the whole way like that Siracusan Messenger girl.

char_363_toddi_CN_010.voiceText: I'll be heading back to sort stuff out, then. No point wasting time on this rotter.

char_363_toddi_CN_011.voiceText: Arianrot, codename Toddifons. I don't like working for ordinary people. Here's hoping you can show me any signs you're not like them.

char_363_toddi_CN_013.voiceText: What goes on in those Logistics' minds, cleaning up my side projects... tch. Fine, I accept. Your feelings are loud and clear. See you.

char_363_toddi_CN_014.voiceText: You have to have seen a Draco's flames before. Ever imagined how it'd be to rain them down on the enemy? I... can make that your reality!

char_363_toddi_CN_019.voiceText: You lot go ahead. I've got things to prepare.

char_363_toddi_CN_025.voiceText: I don't need visuals. Give me the map.

char_363_toddi_CN_027.voiceText: Nothing remains after it rains arrows!

char_363_toddi_CN_028.voiceText: Hah! Why would fire go out before burning everything up?

char_363_toddi_CN_029.voiceText: Not that many people can make this thing shine—I guess you're one of them.

char_363_toddi_CN_030.voiceText: Out without too much ash on me. Good.

char_363_toddi_CN_031.voiceText: Ammo's more precious than that little lot. Deal with 'em yourself.

char_363_toddi_CN_032.voiceText: Still good to move? We're heading home. Grab on.

char_363_toddi_CN_033.voiceText: Like this titchy bit of space is enough? Let's break this wall down and I'll have the whole area behind, thanks.

char_363_toddi_CN_034.voiceText: Think it through before you put your hand out.

char_363_toddi_CN_036.voiceText: Go on if you need something. No point in waiting for me to switch my contacts.

char_363_toddi_CN_042.voiceText: So it's you. If you need something, out with it.

char_304_zebra_CN_002.voiceText: I may sit down? No, I mustn't. I'm a bodyguard. As a bodyguard, I must protect my target no matter the time and circumstance... Am I perhaps being a bother, standing here next to you?

char_304_zebra_CN_003.voiceText: I've met Spot before... Oh, no, the squad I was a part of traveled through a city he was stationed in, and he gave me a hand then. He most likely doesn't remember. It's okay.

char_304_zebra_CN_004.voiceText: (I'm not sure what the Doctor is doing, but that looks so amazing...) Eh? Uh... I-I didn't say anything. You misheard, Doctor.

char_304_zebra_CN_005.voiceText: Doctor, you mentioned this just now, so I thought I'd bring you some. Umm, I'm not doing anything unnecessary, right?

char_304_zebra_CN_006.voiceText: Doctor, I'm so sorry. I rushed ahead by myself on my last mission... I noticed somebody was wounded, and it felt like the blood in my head just started to boil. I forgot your order and ran straight to her. I didn't mean to do that. P-Please don't hate me...

char_304_zebra_CN_007.voiceText: Umm, Doctor, were you looking for me...? No, I wasn't trying to hide from you, and I definitely don't hate you... It's just that... Sorry, I'm not sure how to explain...

char_304_zebra_CN_008.voiceText: When I was in the Sargon army, most people didn't like me, but there was one person who treated me really well. She was my best friend, but... in the end... she betrayed me. Doctor, I don't know anymore. I'm not sure how to trust anyone now.

char_304_zebra_CN_009.voiceText: (The Doctor is such a nice person. Everybody hates me, but he talks to me willingly. There shouldn't be any problem if I put my trust in the Doctor, right?) Oh, Doctor, I'm listening. Yes, I will always trust you. Whoever makes an enemy of you, they're making an enemy of me too!

char_304_zebra_CN_010.voiceText: (I kind of want to... watch the Doctor sleep.)

char_304_zebra_CN_011.voiceText: (Looks like a kind person, but is this guy really going to be as easy to get along with as Amiya said...?) Uh, um, I'm sorry, I-I was spacing out. Operator codename Heavyrain, reporting in.

char_304_zebra_CN_012.voiceText: Yes, I should be able to reach this level too.

char_304_zebra_CN_013.voiceText: (Amiya is here too. Am I getting fired...?) Eh? I'm getting promoted?

char_304_zebra_CN_014.voiceText: Doctor, is it okay if I don't get promoted...? No, everyone is being so kind... I'm a little scared...

char_304_zebra_CN_019.voiceText: (I mustn't betray the Doctor's high hopes...)

char_304_zebra_CN_031.voiceText: Doctor, let me go after them.

char_304_zebra_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor, can I assist you in any way?

char_1012_skadi2_CN_001.voiceText: As I am now, will my presence inconvenience you? Will I remind you of the unbearable past? I... want you to allow me to remain at your side. When the time comes, we will leave this place together, okay?

char_1012_skadi2_CN_002.voiceText: You used to think that we could not survive if we completely left the sea? That's not the case. My kin and I will soon be able to swim through the air. In the end, even those places devoid of anything can become our ocean. We simply need to evolve, to continuously adapt.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_003.voiceText: My former colleagues wished to slay me. They refused to face themselves, but I will not resent them. I could not hurt them, even if they rejected me so vehemently... attacked me. Everything I did was bringing them harm, no? My regrets died along with them.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_004.voiceText: This box? This box contains my past... The fragments in it are all my past. Even these fragments can prove that I am not an empty shell... that I am not a ghost. Gradually, bit by bit, I have turned into what I am now.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_005.voiceText: Did the past you ever foresee a future like this, Dr. {@nickname}? Even if the current you can only hate me. I do not fear your hatred, Doctor. If you desire, continue to hate me... while you are still able to hate.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_006.voiceText: Your companions, Kal'tsit and Amiya, said that I could trust you in the end, but nobody can save others. I failed to save my colleagues, and you failed to save them. We have both lost everything, but I regained my life and my future. This is unfair to you.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_007.voiceText: In the past, before I left Ægir, my family was murdered. I always assumed it was the handiwork of the sea monsters, but... I never expected that it was all the doing of the Ægir. My blood kin and my songs are not scary at all. It is people who are scary.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_008.voiceText: I once struggled, I once resisted. What good did it serve? The traces of weak lifeforms will eventually be drowned by the tide. You are my very last friend. Will you also be like them, meaninglessly rejecting the ocean even if it costs you everything? Do you wish to become the old me?

char_1012_skadi2_CN_009.voiceText: Am I sick? Or am I still dreaming? I dreamt that the black sky was our ocean. When the others and I swam up, we did not feel ourselves sinking at all. Strange, so strange. Is this our future? Their faces are so blurry, they... They... No, no.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_010.voiceText: Dream... What kind of dream will you have? Where are you now? There... Is this also a dream?

char_1012_skadi2_CN_011.voiceText: I am waiting for you, Dr. {@nickname}. I've waited for you for too long, far too long, to the point that I have already forgotten why I am waiting for you here... But none of this is important anymore. It's not that important anymore.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_012.voiceText: These things... I have seen them too many times. Nobody needs things like these anymore.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_013.voiceText: Are the restrictions of the past still necessary? Nothing is left except for you and me. If you are willing to come closer to me, we can cast those things aside... Become my blood kin, Dr. {@nickname}.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_014.voiceText: My sword has eroded, my former colleagues are no longer here, the liquid flowing through my body is no longer blood, but I am satisfied. I have become one with the ocean. Come with me — your true form is still waiting for you beneath the wave's depths.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_017.voiceText: Fight alongside the others? Who will we fight?

char_1012_skadi2_CN_018.voiceText: No more lives should be lost.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_019.voiceText: What will it feel like... when they harm me with their weapons?

char_1012_skadi2_CN_020.voiceText: Don't treat me as a calamity. I do not wish death upon anyone.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_021.voiceText: What do you wish to do? I shall obey.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_022.voiceText: No longer do I walk alone. My blood kin are walking with me.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_023.voiceText: Now then, please listen to the song of the distant sea...

char_1012_skadi2_CN_024.voiceText: Don't worry. Everything will be fine.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_025.voiceText: The air and the land... are all too dry.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_026.voiceText: My song shall seep into your souls.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_027.voiceText: Follow me, follow me back to our eternal hometown.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_028.voiceText: Do not fear, my comrades... I will be there soon.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_029.voiceText: They will become our blood kin. They no longer need to feel the suffering of aridity. Their prior existence was already too painful.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_030.voiceText: Is this how you will treat me? Is this the ending you also wish for me to have? If that is your desire, I can accept it.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_031.voiceText: Why must you flee? This futile struggle will only bring about more senseless terror.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_032.voiceText: Run away, Doctor... Run away, from here, from me... Run away.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_033.voiceText: Sooner or later, this place too will return to its primordial form.

char_1012_skadi2_CN_034.voiceText: ...Why am I still wearing this hat?

char_1012_skadi2_CN_036.voiceText: We cannot protect anything. We can only hope for a harmonious future.

char_003_kalts_CN_001.voiceText: Dr. {@nickname}, please sit. I'm just here to check up on your body's state, so don't be so stiff. If there are any irregularities, please tell me in full. Meaning? We'll set aside what it means to Rhodes Island for now. To me, the meaning it holds is quite significant.

char_003_kalts_CN_002.voiceText: I will conduct scientific examinations on you at regular intervals, recording your vital signs and state of consciousness. Others do not have this authority. If anyone wishes to conduct an examination on you, you have the right to refuse. Do you understand?
