char_1014_nearl2_CN_009.voiceText: In this age on the verge of collapse, I once... felt alone. But Shining and Liz shone upon my fate, and Rhodes Island became my home to return to. I once was shone upon by others, Doctor, so I know profoundly, a beautiful vision and a faith identified, are enough to change the world.

char_1014_nearl2_CN_010.voiceText: Tiredness has not called on me yet. May you first rest.

char_1014_nearl2_CN_011.voiceText: Oaths and trust both are unchanging in the passage of time. Isn't that so, Doctor? The Radiant Knight, Margaret Nearl, rejoins you here.

char_1014_nearl2_CN_012.voiceText: The particulars of tactics have seen some adjustment. Hm...

char_1014_nearl2_CN_013.voiceText: That I could once again experience this gladdens me greatly. 'Fear neither hardship nor darkness.' Doctor, I shall go together with you.

char_1014_nearl2_CN_014.voiceText: So long as I hold radiance in my hands, so long as my heart beats with faith, the hardships of our world will not fetter my step.

char_1014_nearl2_CN_017.voiceText: Upon changing armaments, my combat style will also be obliged to adapt. Take due note when deploying me.

char_1014_nearl2_CN_018.voiceText: I will keep in mind your instruction.

char_1014_nearl2_CN_027.voiceText: This long night too shall now end.

char_1014_nearl2_CN_028.voiceText: To grasp bright power is so as to sweep all wrongdoing from this world.

char_1014_nearl2_CN_029.voiceText: I have never held the slightest hesitance to entrust my life to your hands.

char_1014_nearl2_CN_030.voiceText: There will come a day when we clear the mist of hardship and darkness, awaiting first light's rays, awaiting... an even better tomorrow.

char_1014_nearl2_CN_031.voiceText: I hope that they may seek a proper path anew.

char_1014_nearl2_CN_032.voiceText: The time has not yet come to give up, Doctor. Please allow me to defend the rear alone. I leave the regrouping to you.

char_1014_nearl2_CN_033.voiceText: Is my previous dormitory still left for me? Thank you, for going to the trouble.

char_1014_nearl2_CN_034.voiceText: Hahh... just a simple prank, then, Doctor...

char_1014_nearl2_CN_036.voiceText: I am delighted to once again browse your library. May I borrow this book to lend to Maria?

char_1014_nearl2_CN_042.voiceText: Have you been doing well lately, Doctor?

char_420_flamtl_CN_001.voiceText: Hm? Need a hand, Doctor? Or you got something interesting for me?

char_420_flamtl_CN_002.voiceText: Do you know how wild it is, as a Kazimierz Knight, to see a 'company' actually trying so hard to treat Infected? It's a mind-melter, trust me. Yeah, seriously. Justyna still keeps wondering how Rhodes Island turns a profit.

char_420_flamtl_CN_003.voiceText: Doctor, question? Can I take a look at Operator Nearl's battle records? Uh, no, I'm just a little curious—yeah? Thanks, Doctor! Let's see, uh... oh, man. Maybe I oughta tell Iwona to push back her sparring with Nearl…

char_420_flamtl_CN_004.voiceText: Ashley and me? We met through the Major. I just got a feeling we could get along. So I took it upon myself to talk to her after the match. Jeez, thinking about it, I've got a talent for scouting, don't I?

char_420_flamtl_CN_005.voiceText: Platinum,' huh. I know what happened with her after, but still, no plans to be her friend. Y'know, before, we said the Armorless Union, and the General Chamber of Commerce, were our greatest enemies. But to be real... ha, it's the whole age we live in we're dissenting against.

char_420_flamtl_CN_006.voiceText: The titans we call cities rumble forth. As people live on their backs, neon outshines the moonlight, and car engine silences bug chirps with its deafening rumbles. Too much gets tossed away, flattened undertread. Those people, they all deserve a different life... a better one. Infected or not, Doctor, we all oughta be searching for a new way forward.

char_420_flamtl_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor! Heard from Gravel and Amiya, you faced off with the Armorless Union during the Major? And you're the one who sniffed out the Area 0 plot? How'd you—wait, hold on, lemme bring a chair over and get some snacks while I'm at it. Alright, Teach! Take it away!

char_420_flamtl_CN_008.voiceText: Before I met Ashley, I honestly figured I'd be fine if I just kept living. But now, with Justyna, Iwona, Maria—and the Radiant Knight... I'm prepared to fight alongside them. Throw that life of mine out there for them. It's why I fight on.

char_420_flamtl_CN_009.voiceText: Maybe one day, when everyone figures out what 'Knight' deep inside their hearts really holds for them , and knights truly retire from the stage, Kazimierz can be peaceful in the truest sense. The Radiant Knight, she told me these words, and they spurred me into seeing more and further with my eyes. Maybe there's more I should be doing, you know.

char_420_flamtl_CN_010.voiceText: Take a rest, Doctor. Man, I wonder what Ashley and the others are up to right now.

char_420_flamtl_CN_011.voiceText: Pinus Sylvestris Knightclub Leader, Flametail Knight, Sona! You're the Doctor? Mmm, well, you're kinda not like I imagined, but hey. I'm under your wing from here on out, Doctor!

char_420_flamtl_CN_012.voiceText: Huh. The stuff you watch for real combat's pretty crazy different from the Major.

char_420_flamtl_CN_013.voiceText: It's a first for me to get promoted without commercials or camera flashes. Well, Pinus Sylvestris Knightclub Leader, Flametail Knight, Sona! Continuing the stride!

char_420_flamtl_CN_014.voiceText: I used to worry how an ever-heartless fight would lead us all down a messed-up way, but now... heheh, I guess ideals are something you oughta have. Aren't they, Doctor?

char_420_flamtl_CN_018.voiceText: Flametail' Sona, spearheading and rolling out!

char_420_flamtl_CN_020.voiceText: Enemy spotted. It'll be nice if they entered single file like the Knights do, though.

char_420_flamtl_CN_022.voiceText: Feels fresh every time when someone gives me orders.

char_420_flamtl_CN_025.voiceText: C'mon, let's pick up the pace.

char_420_flamtl_CN_027.voiceText: Feels bad to lose your target, doesn't it?

char_420_flamtl_CN_028.voiceText: 'Tail like a shooting star,' that's what they say.

char_420_flamtl_CN_029.voiceText: Maybe our life and times will make its own choice for us. But right now, we can only choose to fight to the last. Because we're Knights, because we're Infected. Because we're alive.

char_420_flamtl_CN_030.voiceText: We've won a lot of times before, Doctor. Here and now, though, we're struggling for our own destiny, our own future. That's the real fight, isn't it?

char_420_flamtl_CN_031.voiceText: This sure as hell isn't a competition, Doctor. Letting them off easy's not gonna win the crowd over, y'know?

char_420_flamtl_CN_032.voiceText: Everyone, retreat! Let me hold the rear! Don't worry, I'm an expert in escaping the pursuits.

char_420_flamtl_CN_033.voiceText: Wow, this sure beats the Grand Knight Territory sewers. Guesstimating a couple hundred times better?

char_420_flamtl_CN_036.voiceText: You're wondering how I usually dress? Mm, uhh... ahaha...

char_496_wildmn_CN_001.voiceText: Nah-ah, keep those documents away from me... I go all vertigo when I see too much text. Don't even think of making me help you on the paper work, Doctor, I'm just gonna stand here nice and good.

char_496_wildmn_CN_002.voiceText: Armor paint? It's gotta be gold. I love gold. It's the color of lightning, and when they say things are fast as lightning, that's fast!

char_496_wildmn_CN_003.voiceText: For combat, I got my own way of doing things. If you want 'em to respect you, just beat 'em down. If you want 'em to listen to you, go for a round, and let 'em know they could never ever win.

char_496_wildmn_CN_004.voiceText: Armorless Union assassins, Nearl family knights, the Pinus Sylvestris Knightclub... how's Rhodes Island hold all of them together? Your recruiting standards are mad out of sight.

char_496_wildmn_CN_005.voiceText: I‘ve been honing myself into a campaign knight since childhood. That's how I've learnt all my combat skills. But after I got infected…pssh, I still wanna be a 'knight.' If winning fights is the way to prove myself, then I'll win every fight to show'em all.

char_496_wildmn_CN_006.voiceText: Sometimes I don't really get what Sona says, yet I still believe she'll lead us to do right and proper. She's changing and improving herself to adapt, so maybe I'll try working on my own faults too. But, that doesn't mean I'm gonna take up everything she says, haha.

char_496_wildmn_CN_007.voiceText: When Justyna says things, her first sentence is the most important part! But if you don't listen to what comes after, you don't get what the first sentence was about. Good thing I'm already used to that, so I can grasp her point nice and clear.

char_496_wildmn_CN_008.voiceText: Justice Knight's my pet. I got people to give her a bunch of functions, so she's got the chops to do it all at least a little. Yeah, she's a real doer!

char_496_wildmn_CN_009.voiceText: I made the title 'Wild Mane' renowned through my own hard work. It's the symbol of a Knight as strong as hell, and an Infected Knight even. However, the General Chamber of Commerce takes our lives and our glory no more than products and consumables. Tch. Sucks I can't pound their masks to pieces right damned now.

char_496_wildmn_CN_010.voiceText: Man, I'm so bored... hey, let's go for a drink. It's always Ashley who drinks with me, and that's just dull.

char_496_wildmn_CN_011.voiceText: Wild Mane' Iwona, I'm a Knight from Pinus Sylvestris Knightclub. Sona says this place does good by the Infected? Sounds cool.

char_496_wildmn_CN_012.voiceText: Ooh... that's a sick surprise attack to make! Can we rewind that and watch it again?

char_496_wildmn_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? Then you can tell I've gotten stronger? Haha, fine by me, gimme a few more!

char_496_wildmn_CN_014.voiceText: Those hypocrites, wearing hollow masks and treading on the Infected as they want. Screw them, my lance is gonna run them all through!

char_496_wildmn_CN_017.voiceText: Who's got the guts to spar with me?

char_496_wildmn_CN_018.voiceText: Phalanx formation suits me most. If I'm the captain, then let's go with my kind of tactics!

char_496_wildmn_CN_023.voiceText: You guys think you're worth my full strength?

char_496_wildmn_CN_024.voiceText: Don't you dare go down in one!

char_496_wildmn_CN_029.voiceText: Keep on winning, and you'll never be forgotten. It's that simple.

char_496_wildmn_CN_030.voiceText: Cheers, Doctor. You're a solid commander.

char_496_wildmn_CN_031.voiceText: My Major Lance... *sigh* Gotta get repairs again.

char_496_wildmn_CN_032.voiceText: Leave any regrets for later! Go, I'll cover the rear!

char_496_wildmn_CN_033.voiceText: Any rooms in all gold around here? Just a little dream of mine.

char_496_wildmn_CN_034.voiceText: What, you wanna have a race with me?

char_496_wildmn_CN_036.voiceText: Skirts? Nuh-uh. I don't wear 'em 'cept for special days.

char_496_wildmn_CN_042.voiceText: Ready for the day, Doctor? Wanna try some breakfast from the Justice Knight?

char_4000_jnight_CN_001.voiceText: Beep-Beep. Understood. Classification program initiated. Now sorting the Doctor's documents. Will you want any snacks during work? Justice Knight could pick some up for you from the cafeteria.

char_4000_jnight_CN_002.voiceText: Ever since Closure and Mayer installed a human voice patch, Justice Knight's functionality as a smart assistant has gone right up! Being able to use natural language logic really has improved communication so much when helping out my masters.

char_4000_jnight_CN_003.voiceText: Justice Knight's master, the Wild Mane Knight Iwona, found Justice Knight in a scrapped state. She rebooted and fixed this unit. Ever since then, Justice Knight've been in charge of her and her partners' everyday lives, as well as supporting them on missions.

char_4000_jnight_CN_004.voiceText: Doctor... why does my master say things to this unit like 'Justice, you're too noisy these days. Go play somewhere else if you've got nothing to do!'? Beep-Beep…Beep-Beep... Justice Knight doesn't understand.

char_4000_jnight_CN_007.voiceText: Everyone in Pinus Sylvestris is incredibly hard-working, always putting meals off so they can train their knightly skills. There has to be a day where their bodies won't keep up. None of them have time to fetch their lunchboxes, so it's all up to Justice Knight to bring them over.

char_4000_jnight_CN_008.voiceText: A low battery? Sorry, this unit is not sure if any of my functions will be of help to you... What? it's the games console that's almost out? Please get this wire plugged in straight away!

char_4000_jnight_CN_009.voiceText: Beep-Beep. Doctor, you discovered Justice Knight's secret. Justice Knight has no other choice but to take firm action in order to protect the secret... Master? You'll allow Justice Knight to keep tending to the plants in the Convalescent Garden? Thank you, Doctor. You now have unlimited access to all services of Justice Knight!

char_4000_jnight_CN_010.voiceText: Beep-Beep, Beep-Beep. Apologies, Doctor. Justice Knight always forgets to disable the automatic timeteller feature.

char_4000_jnight_CN_011.voiceText: Beep-Beep, Beep-Beep-Beep, Beep-Beep…Beep! ('Justice Knight,' glad to be reporting in along with everyone from Pinus Sylvestris Knightclub... Justice Knight will be of great use to you all!)

char_4000_jnight_CN_012.voiceText: These are very useful resources for this unit. Justice Knight will apply to Miss Closure for installing even more new functions.

char_4000_jnight_CN_017.voiceText: Justice Knight, all ready and set!

char_4000_jnight_CN_018.voiceText: Are you leaving command to Justice Knight? It might be a little challenging for this unit right now…

char_4000_jnight_CN_020.voiceText: Beep-Beep. Justice Knight will provide you all with proper and timely support!

char_4000_jnight_CN_021.voiceText: Justice Knight, all good to go!

char_4000_jnight_CN_024.voiceText: Beep-Beep. Justice Knight is now in position.

char_4000_jnight_CN_029.voiceText: Beep-Beep, BeepBeepBeep-- Sorry, Justice Knight got too worked up. Doctor, master, Justice Knight has made it!

char_4000_jnight_CN_030.voiceText: Possiblilites of new function development detected! Justice Knight, awaiting for orders to return to Rhodes Island!

char_4000_jnight_CN_031.voiceText: There is still room for improvement. Anyway, we won! Congratulations, Doctor!

char_4000_jnight_CN_032.voiceText: Please don't... throw Justice Knight... away again...

char_4000_jnight_CN_033.voiceText: Beep-Beep, Justice Knight has plenty of things to do here.

char_4000_jnight_CN_034.voiceText: Beep-Beep! Don't treat this unit like that… Negative!

char_4000_jnight_CN_036.voiceText: The washing machine... doesn't seem too hard to use...

char_489_serum_CN_001.voiceText: Make the most of everything, hm? As you've given approval, I'll do my very best to provide you all additional joint effort and technological support necessary, within our agreement's scope, of course. Fortunately, assistant work was my exact vocation.

char_489_serum_CN_002.voiceText: Rhodes Island's ambience is more assuaging than I'd imagined, at least personally speaking. After all, you typically feel medical firms would be nothing but dour to almost insipid researchers. Not to even start on your armed force to keep the Oripathy-related technologies and personnel safe.

char_489_serum_CN_003.voiceText: In my time at Raythean, I took part in several project teams, but they mostly bored me. Obviously, one can't complain about their technological prowess, but if all it is is fulfilling orders to quota, without attempting to inject a little inspiration, doesn't work become just too dull?

char_489_serum_CN_004.voiceText: You seem somewhat mindful of my manner of speech. Hmm, if possible, I'd like if you could bear with it. My last project team, whether superiors or juniors, all took up overly polite address that only sent communication efficiency to rock bottom. It posed a headache to me too.

char_489_serum_CN_005.voiceText: True, work calls for strict treatment, and serious accomplishment. But after work is over, you also need to understand keeping a balance and relaxing, which is what lets you adjust your own state and achieve glowing results next time in your work. Do you believe so, Doctor?

char_489_serum_CN_006.voiceText: Have you heard the observation that though many find satisfaction in neat, orderly things, there's a set that feels apprehension in a space holding the same qualities? Yes, every time a rest day passes and I return to a work station that's been tidied up, I feel suffering.

char_489_serum_CN_007.voiceText: A pileup of overdue reports and files just won't do. The paper shredder? No, Doctor, don't tell me you wouldn't want to try this environmentally-friendly corrosive, able to turn a ream of paper to pulp with a dropper's worth. There's no use? That's true. How about I launch a project to develop a papermaking machine utilizing this pulp?

char_489_serum_CN_008.voiceText: The impression you give may not seem quite like my project manager at Raythean, but there's some similarities. However, saying this with a wide open heart, you as a superior outstrip that unpredictable, outlandish black box of a crackpot project-intending plan-addled trickster genius by miles.

char_489_serum_CN_009.voiceText: Both Raythean R&D projects and working together with you have been delightful experiences. I'm finding myself torn between choosing, and I don't mean it as a pleasantry. Perhaps, you'd mock my greed? But people like us might just all be greedy. What's your view?

char_489_serum_CN_010.voiceText: Only when you have finished everything at hand can you rest carefree and firm-willed. At this rate, I'm worried you'll... heh, whatever. With this little left, I can figure it out for you without any worry.

char_489_serum_CN_011.voiceText: Hello there, Dr. {@nickname}. Raythean Industries liaison, Corroserum. I'm sure you saw the relevant contracts and forms, despite your busy schedule. Now then, do share any upcoming workflow arrangements.

char_489_serum_CN_012.voiceText: Rhodes Island Pharmaceuticals Inc.'s battle records are more interesting than I expected.

char_489_serum_CN_013.voiceText: You've raised your evaluation of me? Thank you, this'll be good grounds to include when I apply for another tour here.

char_489_serum_CN_014.voiceText: True, it's worth taking joy in a project's smooth progress, but the evaluation you've given me, in my opinion, seems to have already outclassed my resume. That is to say, do you have further expectations of me, even greater than this?

char_489_serum_CN_017.voiceText: Ah, another assignment perfect for testing weapons. Of course, I'm very pleased to be working with you, Doctor.

char_489_serum_CN_018.voiceText: This is an anti-corrosive coating spray, with no toxic side-effect on the human body at all. Given you were all willing to sign the disclaimer and participate in this test, I sincerely hope none of you become collateral damage due to irregular operation in this weapon's test.

char_489_serum_CN_019.voiceText: The holiday's always over in the blink of an eye. Well, then, let's get to work.

char_489_serum_CN_020.voiceText: I'll be troubling you to make these test targets fall in line a little with our work, Doctor.

char_489_serum_CN_021.voiceText: Do you have any additional directives?

char_489_serum_CN_022.voiceText: You can order me for anything you'd like.

char_489_serum_CN_024.voiceText: The stressful test phase is now beginning.

char_489_serum_CN_025.voiceText: Can I make sure none of you will surrender just yet?

char_489_serum_CN_026.voiceText: I have an extra project here that needs all your cooperation for testing.

char_489_serum_CN_027.voiceText: I'd like to ensure you all persevere until I can gather enough data.

char_489_serum_CN_028.voiceText: Of course. This is part of work, too.

char_489_serum_CN_029.voiceText: Doctor, this has thrown a slight wrench in things. After all, you've obtained combat results beyond expectations, and made it marginally more difficult for my assessment of weapon performance limits to be universal and objective. I'll have to increase the quantity of test samples to ensure accuracy... was that in your plans too?

char_489_serum_CN_030.voiceText: A pleasing result. It seems once we return and I finish collating this data, I'll have some spare time for free movement. Well, then, do you have any free time coming up, Doctor?

char_489_serum_CN_031.voiceText: Not too ideal in terms of results. Deployment tactics still have room for optimization. Don't you think so, Doctor?

char_489_serum_CN_032.voiceText: Let's not feel down, Doctor, you will find a solution to break this deadlock. After all, you'd like the reports we'll be writing to be worth more than scrap paper, wouldn't you?

char_489_serum_CN_033.voiceText: Is there anything I'd be able to help with?

char_489_serum_CN_034.voiceText: I wouldn't trouble you with a matter this small.

char_489_serum_CN_042.voiceText: It's nice to see you, Doctor.

char_449_glider_CN_001.voiceText: Do we work so hard every day? Hohh... this is rough... Doctor, if the stress ever gets to you, please don't bottle it up. I'll chat with you anytime.

char_449_glider_CN_002.voiceText: Here, Doctor, this is for you. I sent an application to Dr. Kal'tsit, and remodeled an unused cabin into a conversation room. This is the leaflet I made myself!

char_449_glider_CN_003.voiceText: I've heard there's a mysterious snackseller here who can dodge the Medical Department's controls, and shows up when anyone needs them... Doctor, is this all true?

char_449_glider_CN_004.voiceText: As long as you take daily precautions, Oripathy is hardly that easy to catch! The sick aren't that dangerous, let alone their healthy relatives... Why do people always let ignorance scare them about this or that, and they're never even willing to look into it some more?

char_449_glider_CN_005.voiceText: Doctor, look at this! Ehehe, it's a notice that I'm qualified and approved for psychological counseling. I've been preparing forever, and I finally passed the test!

char_449_glider_CN_006.voiceText: My dad passed away when I was very little, because of Oripathy. The villagers were scared of getting infected, and they shunted us deep into the forest, far from the settlement. Life might've been very tough, but my mum still carried on as she took me through... Now I'm grown up, and it'll be my turn to look after her!

char_449_glider_CN_007.voiceText: My old home was in the woodlands in west Rim Billiton. I grew up in the forest all my life, so I'm a bit familiar with all kinds of herbals. That said, herbals can treat your surface injuries, but invisible wounds on your spirit just aren't that easily cured...

char_449_glider_CN_008.voiceText: Doctor, can I stay here? Would I be able to chat with you? I promise I won't interrupt your work! Everyone in the Medical Department has missions today, Mint's studying and she's not coming out for any fun, and there's no patients who need tending to. It's just me left now... I don't want to be alone...

char_449_glider_CN_009.voiceText: I believe that getting good sleep, eating good food, and sharing the glad and the sad times with friends can make people happy. There's times when enduring too much does more harm... Doctor, just to let you know if you've got any worries, share them with me. Don't forget about it, okay?

char_449_glider_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, did you fall asleep...? Hmm, no reaction, gotta be asleep. Okay, good chance! Let's find where the Doctor's been hiding all those snacks...

char_449_glider_CN_011.voiceText: Nice to meet you, I'm the new Medical Department intern, Honeyberry. I'm assuming you're the Doctor...? Hmm, it's just like Dr. Kal'tsit said. You're different enough from everyone else that I can tell you at a glance!

char_449_glider_CN_012.voiceText: So you can do emergency treatment like this too...!

char_449_glider_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? So that means, I've cleared my internship without any problems?! That's brilliant!

char_449_glider_CN_014.voiceText: I've learned and gained so much at Rhodes Island. It's all the experiences that build up, and all the beautiful memories, that give me the drive to keep going, to strive together with all of you!

char_449_glider_CN_017.voiceText: After our mission's over, why don't we all celebrate together?

char_449_glider_CN_018.voiceText: Please don't worry, leave your health to me...

char_449_glider_CN_019.voiceText: It's time. We should be departing any moment now.

char_449_glider_CN_020.voiceText: Before checking what methods the other side might use, each of you please watch yourselves!

char_449_glider_CN_022.voiceText: Do I have to jump down? I've got a real penchant for that!

char_449_glider_CN_023.voiceText: Arrived at designated position, treatment targets sighted!

char_449_glider_CN_024.voiceText: Everyone, focus on fighting! Just leave treatment to me!

char_449_glider_CN_025.voiceText: Get a hold of your breathing, and relax.

char_449_glider_CN_027.voiceText: I've got a way to treat you here!

char_449_glider_CN_028.voiceText: No matter what trouble we're in, I'll face it together with all of you...!

char_449_glider_CN_029.voiceText: Mission complete! Now it's time for a celebration party... why don't you join us, Doctor?

char_449_glider_CN_030.voiceText: It's finally over... you all worked so hard.

char_449_glider_CN_031.voiceText: We're not done yet, we need to treat the wounded as soon as possible...

char_449_glider_CN_032.voiceText: Don't get discouraged, we still have a chance!

char_449_glider_CN_033.voiceText: What do you think about building a treehouse?

char_449_glider_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, do you want some snacks?

char_449_glider_CN_042.voiceText: Wow! D—Doctor, I'll jump down right now! Catch me, please!

char_4004_pudd_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, can I borrow half of your desk? Thank you very much. Huff... Ah, it's a blueprint for a new electrical system. I need to get it drawn up by today. Are you busy too? Let's be partners in overtime, then?

char_4004_pudd_CN_002.voiceText: I've been into electricity ever since I was a kid. Just listening to currents crackling really soothed me. Huh? You think that's weird?

char_4004_pudd_CN_003.voiceText: You learn a lot when you're in Rhodes Island's Engineering Department. The Operators bring weapons and equipment from all over, all sorts of technological applications you've never seen before, and all of them worth plenty of research time. If I put more efforts to my work, I might be able to stay in the Engineering Department.

char_4004_pudd_CN_004.voiceText: This is 'Pillow,' a childhood friend of mine. Our family moved from somewhere way far all the way to Columbia, and I found myself very lonely at school. My mom gave me Pillow to keep me company. Oh, Doctor, you should know it can't speak!

char_4004_pudd_CN_005.voiceText: I got into an accident while I was on a lone study out in the country, and was unable to contact the rescue team. Pillow and I had to make it all the way back to inhabited land on foot. After that... I didn't really want to go out doors.

char_4004_pudd_CN_006.voiceText: My dreams... that I work well, and everyday is a nice day. Also, I want to buy a holiday villa in Sami, and after my parents are retired, they can live there together... yeah, I've gotta stay healthy, and keep on trucking until they retire.

char_4004_pudd_CN_007.voiceText: Since I was little, my mom and dad would find time every year to take me to the tundras on vacation. We're all really into cold places! Although if I wanted to cover the cost for my own vacations, I'd have to go pick up work in the city again.

char_4004_pudd_CN_008.voiceText: Haah, *yawn*... Sorry, Doctor, can I take a break here for a little bit...? Ever since this new project kicked off, the shift schedule's been completely crazy! I still have to go check over the base station later...

char_4004_pudd_CN_009.voiceText: To tell the truth, I've wanted to try going outdoors lately. I've gotten to know a lot of people in the same line as me at Rhodes Island, and I wanna experience more along with them. At least... I'm not ever going to be stuck on my own again, not now.

char_4004_pudd_CN_010.voiceText: Oh, the Doctor's asleep…? Well, I'd better turn this machine down a bit. It's kind of loud…

char_4004_pudd_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, I'm an electrical engineer from Columbia, codename... Well, Closure suddenly started calling me 'Pudding', but I don't know if that's too weird...

char_4004_pudd_CN_012.voiceText: So this is how professionals fight… Alright, I'd better put in some training if I'm gonna make it through this safely.

char_4004_pudd_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you for the recognition. I still have a ways to go compared to Rhodes Island's other Operators, so if there's any more high-effort work, throw it my way. If I just get enough sleep, I can hold out for some real long shifts.

char_4004_pudd_CN_014.voiceText: Combat missions in the tundra? At this point, I think I can be of help. Doctor, thank you, and all of Rhodes Island for always encouraging me. I'd like to pitch in some of my own strength now.

char_4004_pudd_CN_017.voiceText: I'm being assigned to combat? Just give me a bit more time to get ready... I... I can do this.

char_4004_pudd_CN_018.voiceText: I don't have much confidence in commanding, but I do know a thing or two about basic survival in the countryside.

char_4004_pudd_CN_019.voiceText: Pillow, don't you go leaving my sight.

char_4004_pudd_CN_029.voiceText: Mission complete. Right now, I got the same feeling I get seeing a blueprint come perfectly to life. What a relief!

char_4004_pudd_CN_030.voiceText: That wasn't too bad of a job... heheh, can you put this in my evaluation?

char_4004_pudd_CN_031.voiceText: Ugh... no. A discrepancy like this should be totally avoidable.

char_4004_pudd_CN_032.voiceText: Everyone, orderly retreat, please! I don't want anyone to fall behind!

char_4004_pudd_CN_033.voiceText: Phew, now where should I put Pillow...

char_4004_pudd_CN_036.voiceText: Ahh... please don't throw out any of the pink household goods in the Engineering Department. Those are for overtime use!

char_4004_pudd_CN_042.voiceText: Good morning, Doctor. *yawn*... I should probably catch up on some sleep.

char_206_gnosis_CN_001.voiceText: I can spend some time discussing matters with you before my next experiment.

char_206_gnosis_CN_002.voiceText: You are spending far too much time outside the laboratory, Doctor. As a researcher, you must know this only hinders you from making great strides.

char_206_gnosis_CN_003.voiceText: SilverAsh's sisters? Yes, I've met them several times... Hm...? What more do you want me to say? I know nothing about those frolicsome, ever-changing creatures, and I certainly am not interested in them.

char_206_gnosis_CN_004.voiceText: It is incredibly ignorant to simply write off the symptoms that arise upon Oripathy infection as a mere disease, and then to go on to think only about how to 'control' and 'heal' this disease. Don't tell me this is how you think as well.

char_206_gnosis_CN_005.voiceText: Shining. I knew I would find her here... Hm? No, she is an excellent scholar, and we collaborated for a period of time until she disappeared one day. That's all.

char_206_gnosis_CN_006.voiceText: I am not working for SilverAsh; our objectives merely overlap. Of course, I won't deny what he is trying to achieve holds great significance for the future of the Snow Realm.

char_206_gnosis_CN_007.voiceText: The best way you can earn my trust is by showing me your true academic strengths, and it seems you've already realized as much, Doctor. I am not like SilverAsh. I am not interested in deeper emotional exchanges.

char_206_gnosis_CN_008.voiceText: If you understand SilverAsh well enough, you know he is not a callous man. From my point of view, he might even be a little indecisive... That, is your weakness too, Doctor.

char_206_gnosis_CN_009.voiceText: Much like SilverAsh's, your endeavors require the help of countless supporters. However, the more supporters you have, the more you have to worry about. Since you cannot disregard them, you should avoid getting entangled. That is my one and only piece of advice for you, Doctor.

char_206_gnosis_CN_010.voiceText: It seems you are rather lax in maintaining your own health, Doctor.

char_206_gnosis_CN_011.voiceText: Pleasure to finally make your acquaintance, Doctor of Rhodes Island. I've been eager to meet you ever since Karlan began its relationship with your company. You may call me Gnosis.

char_206_gnosis_CN_012.voiceText: War is merely a means to an end. That said, if you claim there are more efficient ways, I'm happy to learn.

char_206_gnosis_CN_013.voiceText: I am far more interested in gaining access to Rhodes Island's databases than I am in a salary increase.

char_206_gnosis_CN_014.voiceText: If Rhodes Island is willing the cross the line, I am sure you will see results that far surpass what you are currently achieving... That said, with SilverAsh as an example, I do understand the reasons behind your convictions. Hmph, allow me to offer a helping hand, then.

char_206_gnosis_CN_017.voiceText: You're in luck. I just completed my experiment.

char_206_gnosis_CN_018.voiceText: Fulfill your roles, and leave the rest to me.

char_206_gnosis_CN_019.voiceText: I can only hope this mission won't prove to be a waste of time.

char_206_gnosis_CN_022.voiceText: You disrupted my train of thought, Doctor.

char_206_gnosis_CN_024.voiceText: Let's put an end to this as soon as possible.

char_206_gnosis_CN_028.voiceText: Do not disrupt my thought process.

char_206_gnosis_CN_029.voiceText: I look forward to seeing such spectacular results from you in your research, Doctor.

char_206_gnosis_CN_030.voiceText: Having prepared appropriately, these results are unsurprising.

char_206_gnosis_CN_031.voiceText: Sometimes, there is much to gain from the unexpected.

char_206_gnosis_CN_032.voiceText: Were there too many variables outside our control...?

char_206_gnosis_CN_033.voiceText: Time to head to the lab.

char_206_gnosis_CN_036.voiceText: I have an idea. Care to hear it?

char_206_gnosis_CN_042.voiceText: You should spend your time more efficiently, Doctor.

char_422_aurora_CN_001.voiceText: You can hand me whatever work you want, as long as I'm capable of handling it. After all, I'm here to let you catch your breath, Doctor.

char_422_aurora_CN_002.voiceText: My sickness isn't that bad. It hurts once in a while, but I can take it. Doctor, I'll continue working, be sure of that. I don't want to let anyone down.

char_422_aurora_CN_003.voiceText: I think… I ate them all. Eh...? Those were your snacks for the week? I'm so sorry... I can make you some cheese fondue for your afternoon teatime.

char_422_aurora_CN_004.voiceText: I still can't help but bow whenever I meet Master SilverAsh and the Saintess in the corridors, even though they tell me that at Rhodes Island, I should treat them as coworkers. I'll try, somehow.

char_422_aurora_CN_005.voiceText: I... wouldn't make a good explorer. I want to protect much more than explore. Driving the posts in, building a home. People as tenacious as you always need someone to watch your flanks, right? That's who I want to be, Doctor.

char_422_aurora_CN_006.voiceText: Master SilverAsh says that Kjerag can't forever rely on Kjeragandr, let alone another country. One day I hope to stand against the blizzard with this shield, for the sake of my family.

char_422_aurora_CN_007.voiceText: I have dreams of snowy mountains all the time. Dreams of... running across lakes frozen deep. But my home isn't just snow and ice. Grass covers the valleys, and trains weave swiftly between the slopes. Those, too, form the Kjerag of my memories.

char_422_aurora_CN_008.voiceText: ...I'm always asleep when you come to see me? No, I'm not feeling unwell or anything. It's a habit; I work for days at a time, and the moment I lie down, I fall into a long, deep sleep. But just call my name, Doctor, and I'll wake up straight away. Don't worry about me.

char_422_aurora_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, have you ever seen the aurora? When I was a student, I saw it just once in the northernmost tundra. It was very soon after I got sick, and I had to say goodbye to the survey group. If I can ever go back... would you come see the aurora with me?

char_422_aurora_CN_010.voiceText: Doct... you can have my jacket, okay? You'll catch a cold, sleeping somewhere like this.

char_422_aurora_CN_011.voiceText: Doctor, I'm Aurora. My boss Closure talks about you a lot. I promised her I'd protect you.

char_422_aurora_CN_012.voiceText: Is this... a record from the battle in Lungmen? So this is another way you can use shields... I've learned a lot.

char_422_aurora_CN_013.voiceText: Captain Sharp's assessment... is so high? And you agree as well? I... I'm so happy!

char_422_aurora_CN_014.voiceText: Could I send this medal home? I want my mother to know, I might be sick, but not everything looks bad. I have made my way.

char_422_aurora_CN_017.voiceText: A field mission again? I'm with you, Doctor.

char_422_aurora_CN_018.voiceText: You want me leading? I... I'll work to follow Captain Sharp's example.

char_422_aurora_CN_020.voiceText: You there, stay back! Don't come any closer.

char_422_aurora_CN_024.voiceText: Don't even think of coming through.

char_422_aurora_CN_025.voiceText: The snows of my home... are with me.

char_422_aurora_CN_026.voiceText: Snow, be what boils my blood.

char_422_aurora_CN_027.voiceText: Snow, be what freezes their blood.

char_422_aurora_CN_028.voiceText: Snow, be what warms my family.

char_422_aurora_CN_029.voiceText: I'll become stronger than I was, to make your victories easier.

char_422_aurora_CN_030.voiceText: Stay back, for just a second... I'm too icy now. Let me just rub a bit to warm up... good, that's better! Alright, now it's safe to high-five!

char_422_aurora_CN_031.voiceText: Next time, I won't let a single one escape.

char_422_aurora_CN_032.voiceText: Doctor, we have to retreat! Can you still move? Get on my back... no, I'll carry you!

char_422_aurora_CN_036.voiceText: Are you heading out? I'll be your bodyguard.

char_422_aurora_CN_042.voiceText: You're looking well, Doctor. Just say if you need anything.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_001.voiceText: The files that needed sorting have all been put away. I hope it'll help reduce some of your pressure, Doctor.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_002.voiceText: The atmosphere in here is duly soothing, much like my mountain forest. Doctor, you're free to come play when you're not busy.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_003.voiceText: I've talked a lot with the Medical Department's operators, and now I can understand what everyone's goal is. Doctor, allow me to rescue this land together with you.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_004.voiceText: This herbal pill... it's fine work. Myrrh's combined the properties of the medicinals and processed them in a special way. Hmm... I've never attempted such a manner of processing myself. In a little while, I'll see about learning from Myrrh.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_005.voiceText: Aid and sanctuary are unalike. The former cures the body, the latter saves the soul.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_006.voiceText: To live is an endless cycle, reaping what one sows, all beings beholden to this. I imagine you can understand, having been through so much. Leaving your own memories behind in a different incarnation, constructing your own view of the outside world; that is the purpose of this life.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_007.voiceText: These pills have not just the aroma of tea, but all sorts of flowers too. Many patients consider herbal pills bitter, so I've put my mind to diminishing that bitterness. I hope... the people of Rhodes Island won't dislike this flavor.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_008.voiceText: I very much agree with the tea here, its aroma calm, its true flavor apparent. As with tea, so with man. In this dwelling, those irrelevant rumors can be kept away; it's a rare place of respite.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, the operators can have the dishes labelled with my name to eat, as well as some bottles of drinks I made myself. Everyone's been to truly tiresome lengths as of recent, and I wanted to do a thing or two to help alleviate their fatigue...

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_010.voiceText: Are you tired? Rest well for a while. Don't worry; I'll protect you.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_011.voiceText: It's nice to meet you; I'm Nine-Colored Deer. Hm? Are these motifs so beautiful? Th-Thank you... please, observe them as you like.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_012.voiceText: May I go with you next time? I want to ensure everyone's safety.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_013.voiceText: You've endorsed me? So I have been of help to you, then. Wonderful...

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_014.voiceText: The things I've learned may save many, but there remain yet more in need of aid. Doctor, can I still be more powerful than I am now?

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_017.voiceText: Worry not, I won't betray your trust.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_018.voiceText: Am I taking command? No problem.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_019.voiceText: Don't worry, I'll bring everyone home safely.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_020.voiceText: Don't separate. We meet the battlefield now.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_021.voiceText: I see them... an unknown enemy.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_022.voiceText: Are these new orders? Mm, acknowledged.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_023.voiceText: This... is the chill of the battlefield.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_025.voiceText: The mind is as truth, a mirror reflecting all ways.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_026.voiceText: A thought leaving reality, delusion in all cases.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_027.voiceText: Heaven and earth come alike, all beings come together.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_028.voiceText: Everything has its way, per flame and per current.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_029.voiceText: Mm... this battle was very smooth.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_030.voiceText: Life is sincerely precious, but base and wicked life is punished in the end.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_031.voiceText: You needn't be sad. Though there were slight faults, with a little more of a try, you will always succeed.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_032.voiceText: If it has no power, no one should be shown that mercy.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_033.voiceText: What a strange place. So much I've never seen before.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_034.voiceText: 'Kindness' is something not to be exploited, Doctor.

char_4019_ncdeer_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, here's a scented tea for you. It'll perk you up.

char_4013_kjera_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor! Was it me you wanted? Or did you want me to find Enya for something?

char_4013_kjera_CN_002.voiceText: I can't just pop up anywhere I want like I can back in Kjerag, Doctor. So if you want something delivered for you, you'll want someone else.

char_4013_kjera_CN_003.voiceText: Doctor! Is your belly empty? I've learned how to use Rhodes Island's kitchen, so I can put something together for you.... ah, but I can only do Kjerag food for the time being. Hmm... how about some cheese fondue?

char_4013_kjera_CN_004.voiceText: Enya... Enya? Doctor, have you seen Enya? It's about time we return to Kjerag, and with all the things that need her attention, she has to come with us. Just where has that girl scurried off to now...?

char_4013_kjera_CN_005.voiceText: 'Prayer that will be found, devotion that will be rewarded...' If anything that convenient truly existed, I'd like to see it myself. Me? I'm hardly even perfect knitting sweaters—how could I grant anyone's wishes? Oh, but if you'd like a blizzard, that's something I can do for you.

char_4013_kjera_CN_006.voiceText: In a certain way, Enya and Enciodes are the same to me. Both siblings want to change Kjerag, after all. But if I had to say why I'm so much closer to Enya... it's because she became my Saintess. Not Enciodes.

char_4013_kjera_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, next time you visit Kjerag, would you like to see the view from the peak of Karlan? Standing at the summit above the clouds amidst the mountains, seeing the sun once again is a heavenly feeling. You'll love it—ah, but there is the chance you'll freeze to death before then. Tricky, that...

char_4013_kjera_CN_008.voiceText: Enya's attitude towards her brother, well... I'm sure you understand—the opposite of intimacy isn't hatred, but indifference. And she likes to say as much, though it's not actually quite that bad between them. That said, in time... I have no clue at all.

char_4013_kjera_CN_009.voiceText: The world outside sprawls vast and far, Doctor. But I've come to realize something. It's like people are the same no matter where you go. The palette of emotions outside does not differ from what I have seen in Kjerag. It truly is a fascinating thing, though just as dull too.

char_4013_kjera_CN_010.voiceText: Oh, my, your sleeping posture is terrible... I'll run you a bowl of water. You can wash your face as soon as you come round.

char_4013_kjera_CN_011.voiceText: Doctor... shh. I came out in secret with Enya. Make sure Ensia and the Karlan Trade people don't find out, or things will get messy for her.

char_4013_kjera_CN_012.voiceText: *Sigh*. No matter how advanced our weapons get, combat is still so barbarous...

char_4013_kjera_CN_013.voiceText: Oh! A promotion...Well, I've come here with Enya quite a few times now...

char_4013_kjera_CN_014.voiceText: The Rhodes Islanders by and large seem to know who I am now. Which means I can get a little closer to them, right...? Oh, can't I?

char_4013_kjera_CN_017.voiceText: Oh, won't you want me leading, Doctor?

char_4013_kjera_CN_018.voiceText: I'll see you all safely through.

char_4013_kjera_CN_021.voiceText: Dear me, I’m not done readying yet!

char_4013_kjera_CN_023.voiceText: Don't you fret. No matter the environment, I can 'see' them just fine.

char_4013_kjera_CN_024.voiceText: No need for mercy on the enemy, correct?

char_4013_kjera_CN_025.voiceText: You thought I couldn't see you?

char_4013_kjera_CN_026.voiceText: I'm aimed at you, you know?

char_4013_kjera_CN_027.voiceText: You didn't think it'd come from this angle, did you?

char_4013_kjera_CN_028.voiceText: You're not getting close to me that easily, you know?

char_4013_kjera_CN_029.voiceText: Doctor, you can't be overzealous in challenging your limits, or you might hurt yourself.

char_4013_kjera_CN_030.voiceText: What a splendid job, Doctor! You make me want to pat you on the head~

char_4013_kjera_CN_031.voiceText: Now, now, it's alright. These are fine enough results, aren't they?

char_4013_kjera_CN_033.voiceText: Let's see, here's... whereabout is this?

char_4013_kjera_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, would you like to go on a walk together?

char_4013_kjera_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor! Did you sleep well last night?

char_4025_aprot2_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, might these be the books and documents you were looking for? No, no need to thank me, I'm simply glad to be of help. How would I have known what you needed? Heheh. That would be... secret.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_002.voiceText: Phantom and I certainly have... our similarities, in what we've been through. Though now he pursues the truth, I only wish to be far removed from it.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_003.voiceText: Doctor. About that lady who came to borrow your books... was her name Mint? She seems to be curious about a great many things. Curiosity in excess usually invites disaster, you see, and I have my reservations.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_004.voiceText: It is quite the relief you were with us last mission, Doctor. I find myself dazed by the sight of you when you command. As if something crosses past the curtain of night and the stirring stars, leading your way...

char_4025_aprot2_CN_005.voiceText: Dance, music. Both soothe the soul, twin arts calling on us to focus and follow. But at times, too great a fixation can be our undoing. Such stories were already far too plenty where I formerly lived. Even I... am no exception to the rule.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_006.voiceText: Doctor? What are you standing there for...? I see... you overheard me talking with someone...? Cease with the jests, please. There is no one here... but me.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_007.voiceText: You wish to learn of the Crimson Troupe's affairs? Of course, I know of them all. But take caution, Doctor, for should you stray like they from the proper path... or come near to too many of them, you may be taken hold of. And that is not, whatsoever, desirable.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_008.voiceText: Here you are once more. Please, sit. Be reassured that I will not drive you out. So, what's the matter this time? Could Hibiscus have made another healthy meal? Or is Sideroca bound to whisk you away for training again?

char_4025_aprot2_CN_009.voiceText: My stories are hackneyed, bereft of novelty. Likely, not as engaging as you imagine. You would like to hear them nonetheless? Very well. Then I will tell you tales... but in exchange, Doctor, would you grant me a request?

char_4025_aprot2_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor. Doctor? Beg pardon, I know I should not disturb your rest... but it is far too still here for me to fully be at ease.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_011.voiceText: I envisaged the scene in which we would formally meet, Doctor, and this very moment brings it to life. Operator Shalem, pleased to make your acquaintance.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_012.voiceText: At times, I do feel the battlefield and the stage resemble one another, in ways.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion, did you say...? Ah, I'm sorry, it just startled me. Thank you for your acknowledgement, Doctor.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_014.voiceText: Unlike him, still wreathed in his struggle, I had long since fled the past, never to concern me again... yes, Doctor, so I once hoped.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_017.voiceText: Worry not, coordinating with others is a strength of mine. So long as nothing untoward happens...

char_4025_aprot2_CN_018.voiceText: I may lack for power, but I will do all that I can.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_020.voiceText: See those on the stage... knowing nothing of their fates.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_022.voiceText: Their future is clear to see.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_023.voiceText: I hope we may resolve this peacefully.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_024.voiceText: To kill and to be killed, to do battle. Far too many plays are penned on these themes.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_025.voiceText: And may this end as swiftly as can be.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_026.voiceText: The path you all now walk bears not one hope.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_027.voiceText: Surely, your skulls... would be mesmerizing to see, right?

char_4025_aprot2_CN_029.voiceText: This is far beyond my wildest dreams. The best outcome, Doctor.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_030.voiceText: It is done. Be at ease, for no danger remains. Well done, Doctor.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_031.voiceText: Our mission is complete, Doctor. As for those who escaped... they have their own fates to meet.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_032.voiceText: Haste not; ponder leisurely. We still have opportunities.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_033.voiceText: Shall we rest here a while? How about some music?

char_4025_aprot2_CN_034.voiceText: Ah... I'm sorry, I was lost in thought.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, could you hold my coat for me briefly? I'll be done in a moment. My thanks.

char_4025_aprot2_CN_042.voiceText: Welcome, Doctor. Indeed, I knew you would surely come.

char_476_blkngt_CN_001.voiceText: Your files are all fully sorted. Hm? Was that fast? I wasn't dozing off on your last shift, after all. I have your whole workflow noted right inside my head.

char_476_blkngt_CN_002.voiceText: Stop! You're triggering one of my traps. Move any further, and a bolt will blow your brains out. How could I fall asleep surrounded by traps? That's a strange question. I couldn't sleep at all without these little trinkets around me.

char_476_blkngt_CN_003.voiceText: What we stole from the Leithanian nobles, they plundered from the land before that. We're the children of the wilds, but we are not unreasonable. Lungmen traders do good to others, and Siracusans keep to the rules, so I told my team not to lay a finger on them.

char_476_blkngt_CN_004.voiceText: Is that Lee guy here too? He got me when I was careless, and now I want a rematch. No, no need to worry, none of the trinkets he carries interest me. You go tell him as much.

char_476_blkngt_CN_005.voiceText: Infected? Only city people would call themselves that. In the endless and cutthroat wilds, whether beast or human, survival means you can call yourself the strongest.

char_476_blkngt_CN_006.voiceText: There's plenty who think the wilds are a frightening place, but to me, they were my home. I made a mistake once. It torn my family apart,  and these slumberfoots are the only ones left to roam with me. I'll never make a mistake like it again.

char_476_blkngt_CN_007.voiceText: The name Blacknight was given to me by a Yan storyteller. I always used to do my work at night, pulling the floor from under them when those merchants were drowsy. Me and my slumberfoots would take away their wealth, and 'devour' their dreams too.

char_476_blkngt_CN_008.voiceText: Don't act so nice to me... you never know when my crossbow will be aimed at your head. You don't believe I'm like that? Up to you, then. I've got no interest in dealing with a penniless good guy.

char_476_blkngt_CN_009.voiceText: They called me their boss. So I protected them, gave them food and a place to rest. But now, for as long as I haven't beaten you, you're my boss. I'll protect you, and I'll follow your orders.

char_476_blkngt_CN_010.voiceText: ...Fell asleep hugging Helmet? Light, bring a blanket over. Keep your movements low.

char_476_blkngt_CN_011.voiceText: You're the best tactician on Rhodes Island? I'm Blacknight, and excuse me but we're going to need a showdown. If I lose, you'll be my boss from then on, and I ask to be trained properly.

char_476_blkngt_CN_013.voiceText: You're not worried I'll take the bonus and run? I'm joking. For that matter, a badge like this won't fetch any real money anyway.

char_476_blkngt_CN_014.voiceText: Work and earn a living. I wonder if my parents lived a life like this in Rim Billiton? It's fine, but I'm not letting my crossbow rust.

char_476_blkngt_CN_017.voiceText: Good timing. I need something to do.

char_476_blkngt_CN_018.voiceText: You want me leading? Then you'll want to watch how I do it.

char_476_blkngt_CN_019.voiceText: Listen up, darlings. Once we're on the battlefield, you need to listen to the Doctor too.

char_476_blkngt_CN_020.voiceText: You want to run? Before you do, remember to leave your valuables behind.

char_476_blkngt_CN_021.voiceText: I'm right by you. Don't make a sound.

char_476_blkngt_CN_024.voiceText: Let's clear this path up first.

char_476_blkngt_CN_027.voiceText: Cart, set mines in the bushes!

char_476_blkngt_CN_029.voiceText: How'd me and the darlings do? No compliments for us?

char_476_blkngt_CN_030.voiceText: Not bad! I've learned some more moves.

char_476_blkngt_CN_031.voiceText: I'll take a few to the next crossing. We need to get this cleaned up.

char_476_blkngt_CN_032.voiceText: No, you have to get out of here! Do as I said, or the enemy will have you trapped. We'll retreat for now and think of a better way to fight back.

char_476_blkngt_CN_033.voiceText: Roaming under the night sky is just one hundred times better than getting shut in here.

char_476_blkngt_CN_036.voiceText: Tired? You can have Helmet to hug for a little bit, then. At least until tomorrow.

char_476_blkngt_CN_042.voiceText: Hey, Helmet, no running about in the corridor! Don't think I can't see you just because you're hiding in someone's arms... oh, fine, I'll let you off, for {@nickname}'s sake.

char_2023_ling_CN_001.voiceText: Evocative so. Years and an age ago, the very palace rained and drizzled in the whisperers of consultants.

char_2023_ling_CN_002.voiceText: Yea, when Yan scholars speak of Sui, that is us, and It too. Facts hardly worth covering up; Nian's worries are not mine. After all, I am only me, and my death, no more than death is. The only shames would be this wine and world, for at day's end I love them long.

char_2023_ling_CN_003.voiceText: I was of the mind I would finally meet someone past, an old friend. Never did I think this is how you now present yourself. From knowing not one is one, isn't this like a dream? However, {@nickname}. It is fine to be as yourself. Long have I contended with myself; myself I shall prefer to act.

char_2023_ling_CN_004.voiceText: Where the heart is as will, and its utterance is as verse. If wells your chest with depths manifold, wouldn't failing their writing be shame to meet yourself? Hm? My tail? Ah, so too do I make use of a common brush, naturally. But it is at times inconvenient, as an extremity would be. My body is an unfettered one; who says I can't use my tail?

char_2023_ling_CN_005.voiceText: Poetry, speech, lyric, essay. Though they all differ as their own, they are common in places. A pity the people of now are, by and large unable to exercise patience. To listen to a song, to read a poem. I take no objection to it, but how must our present scholars suffer.

char_2023_ling_CN_006.voiceText: Nian is too impetuous, Dusk timid, yet to see the two as they are now, it seems they already know what they like, and want to do. So why probe at veracity or falsity or object or subject? To bicker and squabble every day, knowing emotion's gamut, is that not what a person is?

char_2023_ling_CN_007.voiceText: {@nickname}, would you want for me to compose you a verse? Hm? Nay, I'm simply in the mood. I need not write it, nor record it. Ah, wait, if it were a song... that would be quite good too! But to dance a song, I fear I would need some preparation. Good! You sit there, and await me a short while.

char_2023_ling_CN_008.voiceText: I am drunk? Hah... I have not yet seen the sky throw wide, moon rise, seas race, ice break, to wait true for all the world's sobriety would be but the withering of a bud, to want true for deep intoxication would be far too early still... {@nickname}, now, why do you say I am drunk?

char_2023_ling_CN_009.voiceText: Last night I dreamt of you. Nay! Perhaps it's you who dreamt of me. Oh, can you not recall? A shame; it delighted me so, yet I cannot share this revelry. Delighted how? Hmm. That eight thousand years of springs, eight thousand of winters, all dreamt, were no more than a brief handful of autumns. That is all.

char_2023_ling_CN_010.voiceText: Clouds ranged as billows, distant-run roads withered. I, departed of the vistas, sailed a ferry in late autumn.

char_2023_ling_CN_011.voiceText: Ling, you can call me. Have my two troublemaking sisters vexed you any? Hm? You've seen me before? Ah... perhaps so, in a dream.

char_2023_ling_CN_012.voiceText: Though antithetical at a glance, your nature is quite similar.

char_2023_ling_CN_013.voiceText: Hm... 'General, I heed thy order,' should I say? Ha, do not take it seriously. I only suppose that if you were truly a field marshal, then I may not mind once again serving as a strategist.

char_2023_ling_CN_014.voiceText: Nian was not wrong. This farcical dream of a thousand autumns is only right to wake from.

char_2023_ling_CN_017.voiceText: The river bends a thousand times, a city lone in desolation, vivid in the mind's eye.

char_2023_ling_CN_018.voiceText: To scatter the fill of a brimming cup, to share the sip for a soothed sorrow.

char_2023_ling_CN_019.voiceText: Plotted schemes, waged wars, crossed arms, shed blood. An eternity, unaltered and unfailing in its challenge.

char_2023_ling_CN_020.voiceText: To gaze the fire from afar, knowing not its heat.

char_2023_ling_CN_021.voiceText: Has it come to my turn?

char_2023_ling_CN_023.voiceText: And thus has autumn made reckoned her arrival.

char_2023_ling_CN_024.voiceText: For the marching, a warsong. For the fallen, a lament.

char_2023_ling_CN_025.voiceText: The split halberd sinks in the sand, great aspirations unrecompensed.

char_2023_ling_CN_026.voiceText: One word to address all beneath the heaven, one scope to spare none upon the earth.

char_2023_ling_CN_027.voiceText: When will the hate sunk beneath the battlefield disperse?

char_2023_ling_CN_028.voiceText: Speak as your heart wills, and be as your intoxication wishes.

char_2023_ling_CN_029.voiceText: Another song, sublime and majestic. {@nickname}, perhaps you and I truly are as two entwined friends.

char_2023_ling_CN_030.voiceText: Duly satisfying, as a cup filled to the brim. We should remain level and humble, yet... we ought to sing your praises, yes. You did well.

char_2023_ling_CN_031.voiceText: Mm... things disappoint on occasion; there's no need to blame yourself too hard. Leave the rest to me.

char_2023_ling_CN_032.voiceText: Victory and defeat are commonplace in war. As we have freedom to maneuver, this is not a complete loss.

char_2023_ling_CN_033.voiceText: Rhodes Island's interior... I'm lost as to whether I should say it's reminiscent or curious.

char_2023_ling_CN_036.voiceText: What is it? Would you like a cup? You wouldn't? What a shame.

char_322_lmlee_CN_001.voiceText: Sorting files? Whoa, I've suddenly gotten this headache. I can't take it, I need a break. Well, keep at it, Doctor. Such little paperwork should be a walk in the park for you, right?

char_322_lmlee_CN_002.voiceText: A job? Of course, I'm all ears. Or maybe you'd like something a little spicier than detective work? Some wet work? Haha, just pulling your leg. We don't do that sort of thing. We're fine, upstanding citizens running a legitimate business.

char_322_lmlee_CN_003.voiceText: Having Waai Fu and Hung around to keep an eye on that Aak boy really saves me a broken back. I'll admit, it's shameful, but I started out babysitting these kids, and now they're all taking care of me. Kids these days do more than we did when I was young, and that's great.

char_322_lmlee_CN_004.voiceText: It's thanks to your patronage that the agency is still running smoothly, give or take. Lungmen's a place with the human touch—live there long enough, and sooner or later you'll know a crowd, find the right connections. We don't like spilling blood in our line of work—always best to solve things friendly.

char_322_lmlee_CN_005.voiceText: How do you like it, Dr. {@nickname}? Jaye makes mean finballs, doesn't he? Old Tung taught that boy his trade and his way of treating people. It all combines for a flavor unique to Lungmen. Come on, have a try. It'll warm you up.

char_322_lmlee_CN_006.voiceText: Under this heading, you had the third row on the left here wrong, so I patched that up, no need for thanks. Oh, do I come off very fluent? Not at all, this is still my first time accounting on a scale so small outside of the agency. Things used to be very—ah, I'm getting distracted, don't you mind.

char_322_lmlee_CN_007.voiceText: Why are the lights all on at this hour... oh? Ah, Dr. {@nickname}. Are you still processing battle records? Well, I never thought you were such a workaholic. I'm impressed. But! You'd better turn in sooner. It's not worth it to break your body doing it.

char_322_lmlee_CN_008.voiceText: Everyone's chasing fame and profit. But after so many winning and losing, how many people get to end up as what they like? Living a decent little life of your own is sometimes a lot to ask for. Ah, what are we all doom and gloom for? I'll go stir-fry something up, so you wait for me, Dr. {@nickname}. A drink together would be even better, don't you think?

char_322_lmlee_CN_009.voiceText: My hexagram says to avoid going out, so I'll pass on this mission today... what, I can't? I have to go, no two ways about it? Hah, I see. Then this is a special exception, once only! I'm lending you a hand, so dinner's on you tonight! Look, I'm all decided! This is the joint!

char_322_lmlee_CN_010.voiceText: Why a busy life when you can have a leisurely cup of tea. *gulp* Dr. {@nickname}, you do keep some good tea leaves here.

char_322_lmlee_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, hello there, you must be the Dr. {@nickname}? You've been looking after my employees for me. They haven't made trouble for you, have they? Oh, that reminds me, here's a card for my agency. Take it, go ahead.

char_322_lmlee_CN_012.voiceText: How about a quick scrap? No, no, I'm just joking. I'm no good in a fight.

char_322_lmlee_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion...? There's a first for me. Feels quite fresh, too. I think times like these call for some magic words—thank you very much, boss?

char_322_lmlee_CN_014.voiceText: Life goes by in a flash. If you're always jostling for the lead, when do you stop to smell the roses? Don't think too hard about things. Enjoy the moment. No matter how paranoid you are, it'll happen if it's going to happen. And you've dealt with it, all's right with the world.

char_322_lmlee_CN_017.voiceText: Do I have to come along too? *Sigh*... fine, fine. Let's get going.

char_322_lmlee_CN_018.voiceText: Good. Follow my instructions closely, then. Alright, everyone, dismissed—wait, hold it, don't head off for real! I was joking! Joking!

char_322_lmlee_CN_019.voiceText: It's like we're on a school trip here, eh?

char_322_lmlee_CN_020.voiceText: Fortune favors the bold, but you still need a few tricks up your sleeves to win the battle.

char_322_lmlee_CN_021.voiceText: I'm sure you can sort them... wait, hold it. Am I up now?

char_322_lmlee_CN_022.voiceText: There, there. Put your worries to rest. I'm right here.

char_322_lmlee_CN_023.voiceText: Hello, friends, what are we talking about?

char_322_lmlee_CN_024.voiceText: Time for a little telling off. But not too harshly.

char_322_lmlee_CN_025.voiceText: Come on, man. Friendliness is good for business.

char_322_lmlee_CN_026.voiceText: Hey, buddy! Calm it down! You nearly spilled my tea!

char_322_lmlee_CN_027.voiceText: My friends, I implore you to reconsider-- Is there REALLY no room for negotiation here?

char_322_lmlee_CN_028.voiceText: *Grumble* I told you. Don't get so worked up.

char_322_lmlee_CN_029.voiceText: My thanks. It couldn't have happened without you, Dr. {@nickname}... I owe you for this one. I won't forget.

char_322_lmlee_CN_030.voiceText: Well done, Dr. {@nickname}. What, where was I just now? Well, given your capability, it was better for me to be your moral support. Cheered the whole time, you see.

char_322_lmlee_CN_031.voiceText: Now, now, hold it! Do not press an enemy at bay. Let them run free.

char_322_lmlee_CN_032.voiceText: Risky, risky. There's a terrifying fortune to get. Thank goodness we run fast.

char_322_lmlee_CN_033.voiceText: Dr. {@nickname}? Here, take this. Decorate your room with it. Ah, but not at the head of your bed. What does it do? Haha, now that would be telling.

char_322_lmlee_CN_034.voiceText: I'm sure we can talk this out, nice and easy. No need for physical contact, right?

char_322_lmlee_CN_036.voiceText: No smoking here? But this isn't a cigarette, it's white stick candy. You don't believe me? Go on, try some.

char_322_lmlee_CN_042.voiceText: Welcome to Lee's Detective Agency, do you have any work... Well if it isn't Dr. {@nickname}!

char_1021_kroos2_CN_001.voiceText: We'll be alright without sorting these files, won't we? Then you can lie down and sleep for a bit longer. It's good for your health. At least you can get rid of those bags under your eyes.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_002.voiceText: Got a heap of useful info from our mission in Yan this time. It's all written up in a report, submitted and filed. Come on, Doctor, I'm not a reserve op anymore. I can pull up my socks and write a report start to finish, easy enough.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_003.voiceText: At the end of the day, the best thing to do with apples is munch them outright, or bake them into pies so you can share with everyone—it's too wasteful using them as targets. And if you just want to split one in two, you're better off with a kitchen knife.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_004.voiceText: I've got a bucketload of magic tricks to bring friends closer. The 'marathon alarms,' the 'invisible warning tape,' the 'hollow cake,' they're all brilliant. Which ones do you fancy learning, Doctor?

char_1021_kroos2_CN_005.voiceText: I'm awake, Doctor. I'm not like I was then—it's not that easy to sleep even if I want to. So where do you need me? Any field missions? Maybe instructing the reserve ops?

char_1021_kroos2_CN_006.voiceText: Accidents always happen too quickly. Quicker than a bolt flies, even. And I can never react in time. And then I just watch things happen one after another, and... Sigh, it'd be nice if I could see things coming a mile away like you, Doctor. At least, when it comes to preparing, I've got confidence I don't botch anything.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, don't tiptoe behind me again! I know when you're close up most times, but on the off-chance you sneak a bit too well, I might just give you a bad scare out of reflex.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_008.voiceText: We all came out of that fight in Rim Billiton a bit more grown up, but... *exhale*... It'd be nice if getting better didn't come with a cost, you know...

char_1021_kroos2_CN_009.voiceText: There's no place you can escape to, and no dreams you don't wake up from. When we face something terrible, we can only choose to give it our all, hard as we can. Might leave a sting or an ache, but at the very least, you won't carry that regret all your life.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_010.voiceText: You know, it's a happy thing to fall asleep like that.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_011.voiceText: Hi-hiii~! Doctor! I'm back! Haven't got caught up in hassle lately, have you? Haha, that's good. Right, I'm heading back to my room to rest up. If there's anything you want dealing with, remember to give me a shout.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_012.voiceText: Some still fight the same as ever. It's nice to see.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_013.voiceText: I've gotten these badges how many times now? But whenever hand me one, Doctor, I'm as happy as could be.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_014.voiceText: Once you raise your crossbow, the only things left swimming in your eyes are your sight and your target. But before you pull the trigger, there's so much you've got to think about... I won't be careless or neglectful ever again.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_017.voiceText: Hi, everyone! I'm here to slack off~

char_1021_kroos2_CN_018.voiceText: Alright, time to assign the tasks.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_019.voiceText: We're heading out. Remember, mind your cover.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_020.voiceText: Relax, the targets aren't that bad.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_021.voiceText: Go ahead, I'm all ready and set.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_023.voiceText: Shh, don't make any more noise.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_029.voiceText: That's spot-on work. Have a rest, Doctor, I'll keep a watch on the follow-up.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_030.voiceText: So long as it turns out well, a little pain's no big problem.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_031.voiceText: They won't be much threat. Do you want me to catch up with them?

char_1021_kroos2_CN_033.voiceText: This place is nice! Maybe I can find some beauty sleep in here.

char_1021_kroos2_CN_036.voiceText: Not that way, Doctor. I've left an extra-special 'surprise' for my friends over there!

char_377_gdglow_CN_001.voiceText: Am I really going to be helpful? Um... alright, if you say so...

char_377_gdglow_CN_002.voiceText: Hmm... your hair is close to coming out of your hood. If you've got the time, remember to give it a trim.

char_377_gdglow_CN_003.voiceText: I can't use anything like a compass. No matter what I do, they all end up pointing at me. *Sigh*... I had no clue as a child, so I tried to use them to find my way home... Now that I think about it, I'm lucky I have a sense of direction.

char_377_gdglow_CN_004.voiceText: You wanna touch my ears? Of course, touch them however you want... but people usually only do it a tiny bit. Why? Heheh, you'll find out if you try, won't you?

char_377_gdglow_CN_005.voiceText: My Arts are... how do I put it? They affect a lot of things, but because they don't have a form, it's hard to grasp them properly... if I can get a handle on their nature some day, I might be able to live a normal life.

char_377_gdglow_CN_006.voiceText: Static electric pulse theory says... okay, okay, I see. I just need to apply my Arts Unit, and start the antistatic equipment up, and that should... Yagh! That's not working at all. Where did I mess it up...? Here? Alright, once more.

char_377_gdglow_CN_007.voiceText: Welcome~! Oh, Doctor! You finally decided to get your hair sorted, then? Good, sit down. Today, I'll be your... That's right, it's a salon in here, you're not imagining things. Um, don't go! This is my speciality, trust me, please! You won't regret this, I guarantee!

char_377_gdglow_CN_008.voiceText: My dad told me I should pick up another craft in addition to Originium Arts, so this is what I went with. It turns out the only hair I can't fix is my own... Okay! How's that? Are there any bits you want fixed? None? Heheh, I thought as much. Alright, I'm finished for the day, then.

char_377_gdglow_CN_009.voiceText: Before I got Infected, I was actually in really good shape. I got second place in a cross-country race! Once my Oripathy's a bit better, I want to start training again, and carry the gold medal back. Can I ask you to present it to me, Doctor? Heheh, then it's a promise.

char_377_gdglow_CN_010.voiceText: The circuit's grounded... okay, now my hair shouldn't poof out. I'll have a break while the Doctor's asleep.

char_377_gdglow_CN_011.voiceText: Finally made it here... nice to meet you, Doctor. I'm a new Operator onboard, Goldenglow. I look forward to working under you.

char_377_gdglow_CN_012.voiceText: Mmgh... it still doesn't really make sense. Maybe I should visit my Instructor and see if she can help.

char_377_gdglow_CN_013.voiceText: There's no tingling feeling, is there? If not, we should be fine. Okay! I'll accept this medal from you graciously, Doctor. Thank you!

char_377_gdglow_CN_014.voiceText: Doctor! Stay away from here! I just need a—a-are you alright?! Are you hurt anywhere? I took all the protective measures, didn't I? Why...

char_377_gdglow_CN_017.voiceText: Is there really a use for me on the front?

char_377_gdglow_CN_018.voiceText: Doctor, are you sure I should be the captain?

char_377_gdglow_CN_019.voiceText: I've got this, I've got this. I can do this!

char_377_gdglow_CN_023.voiceText: Now's the time to help everyone out.

char_377_gdglow_CN_029.voiceText: Huh? Oh—no, it's nothing! Let's get going!

char_377_gdglow_CN_030.voiceText: I managed to help a little, didn't I? Heheh.

char_377_gdglow_CN_031.voiceText: Phew, we're finally saved. Are you hurt?

char_377_gdglow_CN_033.voiceText: I need to keep away from the electronics...

char_377_gdglow_CN_036.voiceText: Could you help me comb my hair down? Thank you so much, Doctor.

char_377_gdglow_CN_042.voiceText: Hope you have another good day today.

char_492_quercu_CN_001.voiceText: Last time I was an assistant, I think I was still thirteen or fourteen, treating people with my mum. Of course, I can do much more than hand out herbals and sing well-wishing verses now. If you need my help, ask away! Don't be shy.

char_492_quercu_CN_002.voiceText: I think I've seen a few new faces this time after returning to Rhodes Island. Dr. {@nickname}, how does it feel to have more and more people under you? Do you feel that brimming and bursting vitality? We always say back home, rage against death with new life.

char_492_quercu_CN_003.voiceText: Rhodes Island Bridge-Climbing Competition? Dr. Kal'tsit shut that down midway, didn't she? Citing lack of safety ropes for all the contestants and so on. Well, I wasn't that likely to win it, and the look on Dr. Kal'tsit's face was a much greater sight to see anyway.

char_492_quercu_CN_004.voiceText: You look put out with all these reports on your desk. Don't worry, if there's any danger, I'll know it by the scent. But! If you just don't want to work, I can't help you there.

char_492_quercu_CN_005.voiceText: Of course it's much easier to gather intel when you're a lone operator. But every time I'm in the country, I pick a bag full of berries while I'm free, and I think to myself, maybe I want someone to share with after all. Otherwise, I've got no one to tell me how great I am at picking.

char_492_quercu_CN_006.voiceText: You get the sense I served from how I work? You only got that impression from seeing my files. Service members come in all shapes and sizes, too. Some only like to read and research their comms tech, some spend all day dreaming about going on holidays in the city to see idol concerts...

char_492_quercu_CN_007.voiceText: Dr. {@nickname}, you might be covering your face, but I can tell you've perked up a lot more compared to when you came back from Chernobog. But if you spend the whole time under this low of a ceiling, your mind'll get dull. Head out onto the deck every now and then. Get some fresh air. It's good for you.

char_492_quercu_CN_008.voiceText: When I looked after the ill back home, I ran across a couple Infected calling themselves 'Reunion'... and then I got into a fight with them. I can't stand it, seeing those children with firelight in their eyes lost in all the pointless violence, about to burn themselves through.

char_492_quercu_CN_009.voiceText: Those who depart us receive the land's forgiveness, and rest in her embrace... but some people go too quickly, the roots of the forests of their homes unable to hold onto their hands. Was that not like me, being so serious? You really should've seen me when I worked back home.

char_492_quercu_CN_010.voiceText: Not sure if the Doctor's a light sleeper... I'd better stand watch quietly.

char_492_quercu_CN_011.voiceText: Nice to meet you, Doctor. Call me Quercus. It's the first time we've met, but the intel on your desk about northern Victoria is straight from me... What, even you're going to tell me my reports aren't standard?

char_492_quercu_CN_012.voiceText: I wish I'd learned all this a little earlier.

char_492_quercu_CN_013.voiceText: What's this promotion come out of nowhere for? My candied fruit must make a strong impression.

char_492_quercu_CN_014.voiceText: In my hometown, you had to make a choice with Originium Arts. Whether to terrorize others, or to aid them... The result of my greed was that I couldn't commit properly to either. Even so, would you still have faith in me?

char_492_quercu_CN_017.voiceText: As long as it's your decision, I'll have no objections.

char_492_quercu_CN_019.voiceText: Shouldn't we consider marching routes other than on the ground?

char_492_quercu_CN_020.voiceText: The more defined a battle's goal is, the clearer tactics become.

char_492_quercu_CN_021.voiceText: Will the land shake with fury, or display her mercy?

char_492_quercu_CN_022.voiceText: If you're still hesitating, I can give some advice.

char_492_quercu_CN_025.voiceText: The land will forgive all in the end, but not now.

char_492_quercu_CN_026.voiceText: The wind blows through; the leaves tell stories of those who sleep.

char_492_quercu_CN_027.voiceText: Arbor, reach your hands to me.

char_492_quercu_CN_028.voiceText: I remember your face as well, now.

char_492_quercu_CN_029.voiceText: Wow, incredible! I've got the urge to snap a formal salute just to show my respect.
