char_4047_pianst_CN_034.voiceText: Watch that the noten in my pocket don't spill out.

char_4047_pianst_CN_036.voiceText: Perhaps you like to try learning an instrument? I could teach you; I'm qualified to tutor for the majority of them.

char_4047_pianst_CN_042.voiceText: I've written a new song. Would you like to hear?

char_4048_doroth_CN_001.voiceText: I was an assistant for other researchers before I got my own lab... That being said, shall I begin your day with a cup of coffee?

char_4048_doroth_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor... Doctor who? Oh, it's your codename? Sorry. At Rhine Lab, calling for a 'Doctor' usually gets a response from everyone in earshot. You must be very special to Rhodes Island, Doctor.

char_4048_doroth_CN_003.voiceText: The rumbling grapevine says Saria is at odds with Control. But I get the feeling they're both idealists, and those with a strong will tend to have an edge to them. I... am I any different? I hope you'll never see my edge.

char_4048_doroth_CN_004.voiceText: You think scientists are weird? Yes, obsession may drive us to ignore certain other things, including social and ethical norms. Our jobs aside, though, we're all normal people at heart.

char_4048_doroth_CN_005.voiceText: Research is like exploration; the further you go, the more dangerous it gets. But every step we take has a chance to change lives, which is why we keep going, even if death or public scorn await. We're kindred spirits, Doctor… And that is a fact.

char_4048_doroth_CN_006.voiceText: I made lots of friends in the world of science. They often discuss their dreams with me; some are not so good at expressing themselves, but I can guess. You say I've guessed wrong sometimes? Hm... perhaps. Maybe I should reflect...

char_4048_doroth_CN_007.voiceText: It's getting cool outside. Remember to dress warm when you go into the field... *sneeze* I, er, forgot to do so myself. I often forget these things if Elena isn't there to remind me. *Sneeze* Oh, thanks for the coat. That's so kind of you.

char_4048_doroth_CN_008.voiceText: I never thought of myself as a genius. I'm just fortunate. My father and other people in the Pioneer team saved the money to send me to school, while the government sponsorship also allowed me to pursue scientific research. I'm here today thanks to the help of many people. That's why I want to do my best to help others too.

char_4048_doroth_CN_009.voiceText: Sometimes, I wake up in the middle of the night in the labs and feel... scared. Scared that people will end up abandoning me, even after all I've done, and even... with hatred in their hearts. What should I do? All I want is to bring them happiness. Can you help me, Doctor?

char_4048_doroth_CN_010.voiceText: All work and no play makes it a sleepy day... We have so much in common, don't we... Let me turn up the temperature. Noise-canceling mode... Oh, seems your cabin isn't equipped with that…?

char_4048_doroth_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, I'm Dorothy, head of the Originium Art Section at Rhine Lab. Dr. Silence already introduced me? Then it saves both of us the formalities. Please, just call me Dorothy.

char_4048_doroth_CN_012.voiceText: Are these simulations or... hm, Rhodes Island feels different from how I imagined, but I understand.

char_4048_doroth_CN_013.voiceText: As a matter of fact, I was worried about not spending enough time on the Rhodes Island Landship... maybe I should apply to Kirsten for another long-term cooperation project.

char_4048_doroth_CN_014.voiceText: Doctor, how do you like my lab? I'm thinking about what equipment I should bring over. Mechanist says my command of resonance might come in handy in obstacle removal and weapon development.

char_4048_doroth_CN_017.voiceText: What sights will the Doctor show us this time?

char_4048_doroth_CN_018.voiceText: Don't worry, I'll take care of the others.

char_4048_doroth_CN_019.voiceText: The battlefield is an extension of the laboratory.

char_4048_doroth_CN_023.voiceText: Do you need the traps activated?

char_4048_doroth_CN_025.voiceText: The sand will reshape the land.

char_4048_doroth_CN_026.voiceText: The slightest vibration can change the result.

char_4048_doroth_CN_027.voiceText: Stay down, and you won't get hurt any worse.

char_4048_doroth_CN_028.voiceText: No, I won't let you take another step… I promised them.

char_4048_doroth_CN_029.voiceText: Whether it's by your calculation or instinct… All I could say is, marvelous.

char_4048_doroth_CN_030.voiceText: Your decisions were on the mark. Were you kissed by the goddess of truth? Can I touch your forehead? For good luck, you know, while I tackle my next experiment.

char_4048_doroth_CN_031.voiceText: 70% of my experiments don't turn out the way I want them to. The answer lies in the next attempt, Doctor.

char_4048_doroth_CN_032.voiceText: I won't let anyone hurt you! I'll take care of things here. Go, and never turn back...

char_4048_doroth_CN_033.voiceText: Rhodes Island is always so lively.

char_4048_doroth_CN_034.voiceText: Oh, it was you tugging at me? Thank goodness, I thought I skipped too many meals and was haullucinating...

char_4048_doroth_CN_036.voiceText: What is it that keeps you staring at me, Doctor? Did you find an interesting problem to tackle?

char_4048_doroth_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor, I was thinking about going out for a walk. Would you like to join me?

char_1027_greyy2_CN_001.voiceText: There's a limit to the types of documents I can help you with, Doctor. But I'll try to learn. I'm hoping to lead my own major engineering project someday, so I gotta accumulate knowledge from different domains.

char_1027_greyy2_CN_002.voiceText: Just spending some time reading. No, I'm not pushing myself too hard. Oripathy doesn't leave me too much time, so I must... Oh, sorry, I didn't mean to make things awkward.

char_1027_greyy2_CN_003.voiceText: I've gotten quite a bit taller in the last couple of years? Hehe, I'm still growing, after all. My ears have gotten perkier? Er, I guess it's also because I'm still growing...?

char_1027_greyy2_CN_004.voiceText: No, Doctor, I haven't gotten more talkative... but Engineering veterans say we have to sound certain of ourselves, in order for our skills and designs to feel certain... I'll keep working at it.

char_1027_greyy2_CN_005.voiceText: Looks like the upcoming courses are even more complicated, and Engineering's idea of an internship is a little… *sigh*… never mind, I can handle it. Yes, I'll be sure to get enough rest. Rest is important to studying efficiently.

char_1027_greyy2_CN_006.voiceText: Mankind may have learned to overcome the darkness of night, but there are always shadows that even the brightest lights cannot breach. If I can continue to improve this technology, and bring warmth and light to those who shiver in the cold night...

char_1027_greyy2_CN_007.voiceText: Though I now fully leave the line patrol work to my drones, it doesn't mean my early intership years are worthless. Look at my physique now, even Medical doesn't have to worry about me anymore... um, Doctor? Why are you crying?

char_1027_greyy2_CN_008.voiceText: Volvort Kochinski... I've seen their mark on Mamá's equipment. Not even Rhodes Island intelligence has been able to track down Mamá since the incident. Is she covering her tracks, running from something?

char_1027_greyy2_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, I'm going to visit a client to help with PLC testing. It won't take too long. You can use Rhodes Island Messengers to contact me if you need something... but I'm sure you can handle anything that comes up.

char_1027_greyy2_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor... Doctor? Asleep already?... I see... This next segment is prone to bugs. I should set alerts to silent...

char_1027_greyy2_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, Doctor. This equipment was my graduation project. My initial plan was to... huh? Putting it into service? Dios mío(My goodness), so this is the 'Doctor's Thesis Defense' that Closure talked about?

char_1027_greyy2_CN_012.voiceText: No matter how much I watch, I just can't help but feel… everyone's style is so individualized, it's hard to summarize anything for general application…

char_1027_greyy2_CN_013.voiceText: It's an honor to earn your recognition, and that of Engineering. I know this is just the starting point, and I'll keep working to make sure that I don't let you down.

char_1027_greyy2_CN_014.voiceText: Countless frontiers remain uncharted on this land named science, waiting to be mapped and discovered. Though our latest technologies help get their views from afar, we have yet to set our foot on them. My dream, Doctor, is to be the pioneer that explores these realms with engineering.

char_1027_greyy2_CN_017.voiceText: A practical field study... in combat?  Sure, no problem.

char_1027_greyy2_CN_018.voiceText: Understood. I'll compile a deployment report with suggestions for improvement.

char_1027_greyy2_CN_019.voiceText: We're into an assault mission. Before we breakthrough the enemy defenses, I'm counting on you to hold the line.

char_1027_greyy2_CN_020.voiceText: Battlefield is where soldiers and war machines witness their own prime… and their own end.

char_1027_greyy2_CN_029.voiceText: Things were worse than expected, Doctor. Even our contingency plan was pushed to its limit... but we still did it!

char_1027_greyy2_CN_030.voiceText: Phew… Everything went according to plan. All equipment in good condition. We're ready for the next phase.

char_1027_greyy2_CN_031.voiceText: Effect on target below expectations, risk of potential failure… The re-simulation of both Doctor and PRTS  are required for next steps.

char_1027_greyy2_CN_032.voiceText: No obstacles on the evacuation path. It's time to retreat, Doctor!

char_1027_greyy2_CN_033.voiceText: These facilities could use an upgrade...

char_1027_greyy2_CN_034.voiceText: One moment, I'm almost done here... just a few lines more...

char_1027_greyy2_CN_036.voiceText: Here so early, Doctor? Give me a moment, I'm almost done...

char_135_halo_CN_001.voiceText: No problem. I've done all of this before, and I won't have any trouble handling it, but let's be up front, Doctor: If you come to me in the evening with a stack of documents and tell me to sort everything out that night, chances are that you might not get what you want.

char_135_halo_CN_002.voiceText: Research is actually kind of a pain. Sometimes, you go all in on your research. Other times, you have to spend time going over progress with somebody else. You need to know your specialty like the back of your hand, and you also need people skills. If I wasn't already decent at both, my head would've exploded a long time ago.

char_135_halo_CN_003.voiceText: My sister Astesia is really good at our family's chicanery, but she only ever uses it to help people. To think there would be such a pure, kind-hearted shyster running around... Oh, Doctor, don't tell anyone about this! Please, I'm begging you! If she finds out I told, Astesia will whap me upside the head!

char_135_halo_CN_004.voiceText: Rhine Lab? Hmm... Sorry, I don't really want to talk about them right now. If that place were really so great, I wouldn't have asked for a transfer to Rhodes Island, right? Okay, break time's over! Back to work!

char_135_halo_CN_005.voiceText: I'm the one who got infected, but then even Astesia... *sigh*... You probably can't tell, but she's actually pretty depressed. Enough is enough, I gotta do something to help her.

char_135_halo_CN_006.voiceText: Columbia's technology keeps advancing, and as a researcher, I can almost see that future I'm looking for. My dream is right there, and I'm going to make it come true.

char_135_halo_CN_007.voiceText: Our family's... well, how should I say this? My parents are the old-fashioned type that like to order people around. They don't care about your opinions, only the joy of being in control. It sucks. That's why I haven't been back home since college. Now they can't stop me from studying the stuff I like.

char_135_halo_CN_008.voiceText: There are those who help because they really want people to have a better life, but there are also those who help so they can use people as stepping stones. Doctor, you know how to tell the two apart, don't you? It's easy. You just need to look at the way they smile.

char_135_halo_CN_009.voiceText: My dad's kinda famous back in the city, and our names are a little peculiar, so I thought I'd give myself a new name to get away from all that trouble. But feel free to call me whatever you want, Doctor. We're friends, don't sweat it.

char_135_halo_CN_010.voiceText: Yes, this is the Doctor's office. Yes, the Doctor is resting right now. Please call back later.

char_135_halo_CN_011.voiceText: Researcher Elena Urbica of Rhine Lab. A pleasure to make your acquaintance. We're supposed to call each other by codenames here, right? No problem. In that case, call me Astgenne. It's simple and easy to remember.

char_135_halo_CN_012.voiceText: I don't think I've seen a problem like that before. Gotta take notes...

char_135_halo_CN_013.voiceText: What a pretty medal! Let me help you pin it on. Hm? How come you're the one wearing it instead of me? Isn't this commemorating your good eye for people?

char_135_halo_CN_014.voiceText: Let's join together and break the shackles, Doctor! The future is unfolding right before our eyes!

char_135_halo_CN_018.voiceText: Hold on a sec. I'll finish reading the team leader's messages in a jiffy.

char_135_halo_CN_019.voiceText: All charged up and ready to go.

char_135_halo_CN_020.voiceText: I'll show you the power of technology.

char_135_halo_CN_025.voiceText: Miracles don't just drop out of the sky.

char_135_halo_CN_027.voiceText: I'm not gonna sit here and wait for my demise.

char_135_halo_CN_028.voiceText: My lightning will illuminate the starry sky!

char_135_halo_CN_029.voiceText: You had even the finest details under control. You must be a professional.

char_135_halo_CN_030.voiceText: I knew everything was going to be okay.

char_135_halo_CN_031.voiceText: Everything's under control~ Just a little scuffed, that's all...

char_135_halo_CN_032.voiceText: No way... How could my calculation have...?

char_135_halo_CN_033.voiceText: Let's see how far this is from my workstation...

char_135_halo_CN_036.voiceText: Oh, Doctor! What a coincidence running into you here! Why don't we go shopping together?

char_1026_gvial2_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, got any trouble for me to handle? What? Just haul these files for you?

char_1026_gvial2_CN_002.voiceText: I gotta hand it to her, Doctor, this axe Zumama made for me turned out great, but I've already got this muscle memory from whacking enemies with my staff. See, still carrying it with me. I'm here to save people, after all, not beat 'em up. Gotta work that out.

char_1026_gvial2_CN_003.voiceText: Doctor, check it out. Getting extra weapons' kind a juggling act, so I found a solution. Trained my tail a little, and now, I can use it to hold my staff. Only downside is—I think my tail got thicker after all that exercise.

char_1026_gvial2_CN_004.voiceText: How's that, Doctor? Shoulders feel much better, right? I told you, controlling my strength's a piece of cake, it's just none of you wanna believe me. I've been practicing medicine as a pro for years now. It's about time you recognized the fact, don’t you think?

char_1026_gvial2_CN_005.voiceText: Oh, right, Doctor, it’s been a while since your last trip to Acahualla, right? Join me next time I visit my home, if you can sapre the time. They told me it's a party there now. Even I'm wondering what my home's gonna be like when I visit again.

char_1026_gvial2_CN_006.voiceText: Doctor, you know there's times you can trust your intuition. You've got all these Operators who trust you, see. Even with your eyes closed, your fists are still real strong—What? Compared to mine? Hey... I could K.O. you before you even made it out of this office, so I'm the stronger one there!

char_1026_gvial2_CN_007.voiceText: Zumama can build machines, Tomimi can manage people, and Inam's a damn-good lord ameer... Man, my friends rule! But my medical skills aren't bad either! Huh? What do you mean that's the one thing they’d argue?

char_1026_gvial2_CN_008.voiceText: Y'know, Doctor, I never understood why you made everything so complicated all the time. But now, I kinda get it, in a small sorta way. To put it in plaintalk, you're just finding ways to get bigger fists. So let me get real here, Doc. It's time you worked out with me.

char_1026_gvial2_CN_009.voiceText: Zumama was right. All I gotta do is think about how to get stronger, and how to throw my fists. So I've got an extremely serious question to ask you, Doctor... If I get Zumama to build us a two-seater Raging Ironhide, do you wanna ride driver-side or passenger?

char_1026_gvial2_CN_010.voiceText: Alright, how should I wake the Doc up...?

char_1026_gvial2_CN_011.voiceText: Hold on, Doctor, I know what you wanna ask, and my files are still up in Medical. But, y'know, Dr. Kal'tsit's got a point. Doesn't reflect well on Medical to have a physician steamrolling around the front lines, so from now on, this is how I'm heading out.

char_1026_gvial2_CN_012.voiceText: There... wouldn't a quick axe chop do the job?!

char_1026_gvial2_CN_013.voiceText: *sigh* Just doesn't give me the same kick I get being endorsed for my medical skills...

char_1026_gvial2_CN_014.voiceText: Doctor, doesn't matter if I've got an axe or staff in hand, I'm just hoping to accomplish a little something, make everyone's lives a little bit happier. I've managed to do a bunch so far, and before my body gives out on me here, I'm gonna do more.

char_1026_gvial2_CN_017.voiceText: Leave the front to me. The rear's all yours!

char_1026_gvial2_CN_018.voiceText: You get to follow me under one condition—you all stay alive and well. Got it?

char_1026_gvial2_CN_019.voiceText: Let's go! Oh, speaking of which, what was our objective again?

char_1026_gvial2_CN_020.voiceText: Alright, guys! Let's make some noise!

char_1026_gvial2_CN_021.voiceText: Doctor, leave the big guys to me!

char_1026_gvial2_CN_024.voiceText: I'll take the lead! The rest is up to you guys!

char_1026_gvial2_CN_025.voiceText: Relax, it'll be over in an instant.

char_1026_gvial2_CN_029.voiceText: Uh... might be kind of weird to say at this point, Doctor, but nailing down a tough mission on nothing but trust for others—that's pretty damn neat.

char_1026_gvial2_CN_030.voiceText: Everybody good? We've got another battle waiting for us. Pump yourselves up! We're gonna crush this mission together!

char_1026_gvial2_CN_031.voiceText: No rush. Doesn't matter if we're chasing 'em down or watching for a counterattack, just leave it to me. I want anyone who needs it to rest up!

char_1026_gvial2_CN_032.voiceText: Doctor, hold on tight to my shoulders! Don't go blaming me if you fall off.

char_1026_gvial2_CN_033.voiceText: I guess I'll drop in at Medical before the mission.

char_1026_gvial2_CN_034.voiceText: What's the rush, Doc? Not like I'm gonna run away.

char_1026_gvial2_CN_036.voiceText: You look pretty free to me, Doctor. Just so happens I am too. Wanna take a walk?

char_1026_gvial2_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor! ...Oops, my bad. Didn't bruise you, did I?

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_001.voiceText: Hello, Doctor. I'll be acting as your assistant from here on. Please keep an appropriate distance from me; I'll be more at ease that way.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_002.voiceText: I recall my first time ordering a fountain pen from Zeruertza's artisans, where I didn't make my requirements clear. Then I ended up with this crossbow. It plagues me to have had the peace-loving Durin forges a weapon… Operator Myrtle? Calling herself Generalissimo? That's just a childish fan—Ahem, it's her own self-styling.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_003.voiceText: If you'll permit my frankness, it's my belief Rhodes Island should build work and living environments more suited to the Durin operators. At least the cafeteria menu should be decided by vote—they're all satisfied? They can't be! I'll go and ask them, lest you—lest someone be tricking them.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_004.voiceText: You require me to draft some slogans? I'd be happy to. It was routine work of mine in Zeruertza. You only need to provide me a typewriter, and that's all... Why do I not use a pen? My fountain pen is typically for more private things, more... not-so-Durin things.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_005.voiceText: I was a steadfast teetotaler back in Ursus, but to my surprise, I could keep more drink down than most in Zeruertza. Truth be told, I didn't immediately understand why they loved their drink so, but I did eventually come to realize. We only drink in excess when hope is lost, and a forever stagnant, easy life can lose us hope as well as anything.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_006.voiceText: I still hold that life in the Durin cities far surpasses that of the surface, but I have to admit, the flowerets that vie to bloom in the ruins have more of a power than all the blossoms of Durin greenhouses... Hah. All these years, and yet I'm a surface-dweller through and through.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_007.voiceText: Ursus desserts and wine? Let someone else have the pastries, please. 'Ursus-style' is an exceptional stranger to me by now. That said, do leave the liquor here. Zeruertzans love their drink, and I'm no exception—wait, this isn't mead. Is this pure spirits? Oh, my head...

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_008.voiceText: Noble?' Correct, I was once a noble. Until a conspiracy wrested my family away, and left me with the sole luck of escaping underground to Zeruertza. There was no avaricious nobility in the city, nor any commoners who'd take advantage for their own gain. Only kindhearted Durins... What more could I ask for?

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, I'd like to talk with you of beauty and virtue, of those things I consider vanished from the surface. I've witnessed their existence aboard Rhodes Island, and you've told me that more of their sparks are alight upon this land still... I don't dare trust. I have to go and see it for myself.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, are you asleep? No? Well, no matter. If you're planning to hold the same posture for a while, perhaps I might draw a fountain pen sketch of you.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_011.voiceText: I believe you're the Doctor? It's nice to meet you. Please accept my gratitude; thank you for allowing me to lodge here, a refuge on the unseemly surface.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_012.voiceText: I could never imagine. Do you show these violent, bloody tapes to the Durins as well?

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you for the gesture of confidence. I'll endure the urge to flee the award ceremony as best I can, so please, if you could wrap it up soon... There's no ceremony, it's just a normal presentation? O, гора с плеч(Oh, that's a relief).

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_014.voiceText: Another promotion, is it? Thank you. I'll accept this honor with my chest out in pride... And of course, we don't need to end this presentation as quickly as last time. Do not be afraid of those I should not fear—this is what life aboard Rhodes Island has taught me.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_017.voiceText: The day shall come for every land dweller, the day they find a cold weapon in their arms. And I learned it the hard way.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_018.voiceText: For those of you who've spent not a second out of the fight, decades-old tactical thinking from Ursus must be far past its prime.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_020.voiceText: Bраг (Enemy)... A noun I hardly want to reunite with outside of writing. It's been so long.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_023.voiceText: Good visibility. I'm ready to fire.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_025.voiceText: Bolt pierces deeper than nib on the battlefield.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_027.voiceText: Abandon resistance now, or I pull the trigger!

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_029.voiceText: Surface civilization is no different to the ferocious vile beasts, but perhaps you can become one who loops its reins.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_030.voiceText: The battle is over. It's time to return and write, and do something more meaningful than this.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_031.voiceText: Apologies, Doctor. I'm still unaccustomed to the sensation of combat.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_032.voiceText: Doctor, evacuate everyone as fast as you can, I—I'll bring up the rear! Don't mind me, go!

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_033.voiceText: Zeruertza has molded me. I'm still a little unused to moving about these narrow spaces.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_034.voiceText: Убери руки (Hands off)! ...Apologies, that wasn't intentional.

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, if you insist on chatting with me, what say we talk about your favorite books?

char_4055_bgsnow_CN_042.voiceText: *yawn*... Good morning, Doctor. The book you recommended was very interesting. I finished reading it overnight.

char_497_ctable_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, watch your hands. If you aren't careful around my weapons, you'll get hurt.

char_497_ctable_CN_002.voiceText: Here are the instruments I used to play. There aren't too many of them, but the gems on them are very valuable. Sell them, and they should cover my medical fees... Once my debt's cleared, I'd like to go back to living on my own. Would that be alright?

char_497_ctable_CN_003.voiceText: I've seen pets kept around your hospital here, and you have a training room. I've seen some of the children you're giving intensive care in the wards. 'Instructor?' 'Professor?' My previous savior brought me to those with the same title, and look how I ended up.

char_497_ctable_CN_004.voiceText: This? This is my lyre. I may be better with other instruments, but I like playing this one most. Listen. Such an airy, lingering timbre, and the hand moves so beautifully when playing. But when you fully lose yourself in the melody, the knife concealed inside will... I'm sorry, I got carried away.

char_497_ctable_CN_005.voiceText: Doctor, do you intend only to treat me here? Strange. You really don't need me to do anything? I can't trust kindness with no strings attached. Let me do a little something for you, okay? I'm sure you'll be satisfied, no matter the task—But, you must share with me your motivations.

char_497_ctable_CN_006.voiceText: I remember coming back from my first fulfilled mission when I was young, weeping and throwing up, scared I didn't do well enough, that I would starve to death in some forgotten corner, unknown to anyone... No longer do I fear these things. Thanks to the days with Rhodes Island, I now know how it feels to be truly alive.

char_497_ctable_CN_007.voiceText: The Originium on my arm... it hurts terribly, but it's much more manageable by now. I know none of the physicians, but I can tell how sincerely they're working to save me. Doctor, once my illness has stabilized to a point, can I... stay here?

char_497_ctable_CN_008.voiceText: A lot of my past mistakes were made out of fear. I was scared—I felt that if I didn't listen to them, I was dead. But after catching Oripathy, they threw me out there to die. I should have been terrified at that moment, but instead I was... relieved. The sun shining on my face—it was so warm, it really was.

char_497_ctable_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, could you take me with you on your next field mission? I want to know the reasoning behind your every decision. Why did you save me, a stranger? Just what does my life mean to you...? I want to figure you out, just a little clearer.

char_497_ctable_CN_010.voiceText: All the ones before you would sleep with one eye open, when I was around. Do you... trust me that much?

char_497_ctable_CN_011.voiceText: So you're the Doctor from Rhodes Island...? Thank you for what you did. I'll pay for my treatment in time. Otherwise, I'd like to be on my own for now.

char_497_ctable_CN_012.voiceText: I'm a fast learner, don't worry.

char_497_ctable_CN_013.voiceText: So this is how it feels... to hold my life in my own hands.

char_497_ctable_CN_014.voiceText: This isn't the first time someone saves my life. But, if I had a chance to get back to those barrens, a chance to weigh up what's behind those helping hands again, I would choose to starve to death there. Doctor, I've been thinking... how nice it would've been, if you were there offering your hand instead.

char_497_ctable_CN_017.voiceText: I trust your judgment. You won't lead me astray.

char_497_ctable_CN_018.voiceText: If I make any mistakes, please point them out to me.

char_497_ctable_CN_019.voiceText: Things are different. I don't want to hide myself any longer.

char_497_ctable_CN_023.voiceText: In time, I'll find the right place for myself too.

char_497_ctable_CN_025.voiceText: I'm aware of what I'm doing.

char_497_ctable_CN_026.voiceText: I know what it is I want.

char_497_ctable_CN_029.voiceText: That's one more step in the right direction, isn't it?

char_497_ctable_CN_030.voiceText: Someday in the future, I'll have as clear a direction as you do.

char_497_ctable_CN_031.voiceText: We have a few runaways. A little like I once was.

char_497_ctable_CN_032.voiceText: This isn't happening, don't abandon me... Doctor, where are you?

char_497_ctable_CN_033.voiceText: Are you interested in my instruments? I can teach you how to play.

char_497_ctable_CN_036.voiceText: If I leave someday, you'll send me off, won't you?

char_497_ctable_CN_042.voiceText: I heard the sound of your footsteps, Doctor.

char_4054_malist_CN_001.voiceText: You want me to do file collation work...? These documents of yours all look dusty. I don't want to touch them. And how was your office even planned in the first place? Did you genuinely not feel personally, utterly disgusted leaving this cabinet here?

char_4054_malist_CN_002.voiceText: I propose swapping for more corrosion-proof materials next time you do maintenance on the ship's core structure. Why? Because when all's said and done, it's not you or me that'll be left behind. It's this landship's skeleton. That's what's going to endure. That's what will stand for us.

char_4054_malist_CN_003.voiceText: You've got some planning work for me? I'll ask to review my partners' design styles first. As long as they aren't too complex about it, I might be able to accept—okay, okay, fine, I'll do it, I'll take it, it's not as if collaborations are some big deal. Besides, it's not that you have disastrous taste.

char_4054_malist_CN_004.voiceText: What is it... Ah, darn it, the pencil smudged my belt again. I just got it replaced... Last time it was Gavial, saying she'd get me a new one of the same look. As if! The emblem on the clasp was straight from my designs, and obviously she didn't even give those an honest look!

char_4054_malist_CN_005.voiceText: I know, I'll go to the infirmary in a bit. I don't want to interrupt my thought process at the moment. And you know, Doctor, the moment is the exact thing I most value—you called Gavial in? Was she on duty at the Medical Department today? You can't fool—hello, Gavial, no no, I wasn't just working on any designs.

char_4054_malist_CN_006.voiceText: I used to appreicate a fan base of one, one who can truly see to the core of my designs, rather than having a crowd of followers with their superfacial admiration. For me, the latter holds absolutely no significance. But now… I suppose it's not all bad to let the masses see them. Discussion swirling around my work means I'm still alive.

char_4054_malist_CN_007.voiceText: Why do I tend not to greet anyone? Because once I do, I have to make small talk, and that forces me to crane my head up to speak with them, which makes me seem insignificant. We should be seeing eye-to-eye, on EQUAL footing... Are you asking if it weighs on me? As if! It just makes my neck ache.

char_4054_malist_CN_008.voiceText: I was genuinely full of anxiety back then. I always felt I didn't have enough time, though I'd never even accomplished a thing. But nowadays, I've gotten to the point where I can appreciate my own designs. The only thing is, it's been years since I last saw my teacher. I wonder if he'd be proud of me?

char_4054_malist_CN_009.voiceText: A close look is all it takes to unearth the core sense of a man from his work. Just like how I used to disdain anything superfluous. I treated my own life in the same way. Doctor, an artwork is a microcosm of its creator's life. Yours, I can understand.

char_4054_malist_CN_010.voiceText: Hmm. Such a counter-conventional sleeping posture, such a complex yet stable load-bearing structure... miraculous. Is this not going to give you neck arthritis?

char_4054_malist_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Operator Minimalist, freshly dragged here by Gavial. So this is what a nomadic landship's like? You must have a much easier time avoiding Catastrophes than we do underground. Hmph, the only thing in those fools' heads is merrily drinking their lives away—ow, Gavial, what did you hit me for?!

char_4054_malist_CN_012.voiceText: ...If it's not architecture-related, I don't want to see it.

char_4054_malist_CN_013.voiceText: A medal? Decently tasteful. You just give this to me, and that's it, right? I've absolutely no need for any sort of commendation ceremonies, and I imagine you don't like to waste time anyway. But I will—ahem—thank you for acknowledging me.

char_4054_malist_CN_014.voiceText: Everyone's experiences are different, and the significance lying behind my works will be out of sight to most... but there are some, like you, like my mentor, that I hope can understand.

char_4054_malist_CN_018.voiceText: You want me for captain? What are you even... You're joking, aren't you? Hey!

char_4054_malist_CN_019.voiceText: Hm... alright, let me be clear, I don't have any prior combat experience. However, I am going to take this mission seriously.

char_4054_malist_CN_020.voiceText: Instrument debugging complete. I can begin any time.

char_4054_malist_CN_021.voiceText: I am aware. Don't push me.

char_4054_malist_CN_022.voiceText: If you break anything, you're paying!

char_4054_malist_CN_023.voiceText: Instrument is operating fine. Now scanning terrain.

char_4054_malist_CN_026.voiceText: We're not here to be courteous.

char_4054_malist_CN_027.voiceText: I just don't get you people...

char_4054_malist_CN_029.voiceText: Huh. You're mightier than you let on, aren't you?

char_4054_malist_CN_030.voiceText: *cough* *cough* *cough*... There's so much dust—it's filthy. Gah.

char_4054_malist_CN_031.voiceText: What are you looking at me for? You want me to chase them?

char_4054_malist_CN_032.voiceText: Snap out of it! Get running!

char_4054_malist_CN_033.voiceText: I don't want to open my eyes . I'm worried the interior design is going to scare the life out of me.

char_4054_malist_CN_036.voiceText: Phew... what time is it? No, what day of the week? Er... did I eat anything yet? I don't think I did...?

char_4054_malist_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor, sitting for too long can leave you prone to neck arthritis. I suggest you watch out for yourself.

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_001.voiceText: Let's get cooking! It's my turn to cook again today... Oh, it's snowing.

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_002.voiceText: Hoederer, what's wrong? Oh, the book you wanted me to check out? How should I know? What's that pile of ash in the fire? Hm... Oh! I 'mistook' the book for tinder a little while ago. Eh, it's fine. We're cooking dinner with knowledge tonight. It's gonna taste fantastic, don'tcha think?

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_003.voiceText: How much ammo I got? I just used ten grenades, so I have fifteen left. I used three mines yesterday, so I have six left... See, I'm right. Stop, I know what you're about to say. 'If only you applied that memory to learning something.' Really, you should've been a teacher, Hoederer.

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_004.voiceText: Potato, potato. Ines's a big Mrs. Potato Head—Hm? Now that I think about it, you could probably squeeze a bomb into a potato. Maybe a good trick to play on an unlucky dumbass. Hey, Hoederer, you want a potato?

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_005.voiceText: Hoederer, I've been thinking. If the two of us went at her together, how do you figure our chances of doing that nasty Kal'tsit in? Hm? You're always like, we gotta plan for all contingencies. We gotta plan for that one too, right? Hah, that look on your face is hilarious.

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_006.voiceText: Ines, maybe you should try to learn a thing or two from that {@nickname}. There's not a whole lot of people who can use you as bait without you noticing till halfway through. Me? One look at you and Hoederer's faces had my in stitches! Makes me wanna gift {@nickname} a potato next time.

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_007.voiceText: My name... my name... Hey, Hoederer, you're always reading books, so why don't you come up with a name for me? Theresa said I should come up with a new one... Hey, what's with all those books? Pick a name myself?! Go to hell!

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_008.voiceText: 'Hoederer, if you've got a death wish, just say so.' 'Ines, trust me. My head's reserved for just you, okay?' That's how your lovers' spat went last time, right, Ines? I'm just giving you my best impression.

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_009.voiceText: As soon as I'm done cooking, Ines always makes me help put up the tent, then Hoederer always drags me somewhere for recon. After that, there's always some kind of strategy meeting... Huh? Hey, Hoederer. Nothing. I was just talking about how I'll come collect your corpses when the two of you drop dead.

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_010.voiceText: Haghhh... I'll get some sleep before my next mission...

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_011.voiceText: I know what it means to take up the weapons of the dead, naturally.

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_012.voiceText: Your acting's too lame. Let me spice things up a little.

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_013.voiceText: How many pieces of candy am I worth now? I actually kinda like that method of valuing people. You sure we shouldn't go with that?

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_014.voiceText: Theresa called me over and told everyone what an amazing fighter I am, but she didn't look happy at all. How can I make her happy...? What if I invited her over and cooked her a nice dinner?

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_017.voiceText: Who's the unlucky one this time?

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_018.voiceText: As long as I'm not on the same team as Ines.

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_019.voiceText: I'll blow up what I want. You guys do what you want, too.

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_020.voiceText: Let me plant some potatoes first.

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_022.voiceText: The plan is to blow them all up, right?

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_023.voiceText: I'm in a good mood. Just your luck, huh?

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_024.voiceText: I'm in a bad mood. Just your luck, huh?

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_025.voiceText: You might not want to move your foot.

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_027.voiceText: Take a guess. Is this potato a bomb?

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_028.voiceText: Take a step and find out?

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_029.voiceText: Theresa always says that {@nickname} takes on these missions willingly. Must be trying to bite the dust.

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_030.voiceText: Not a single one left. Babel oughta pay me extra for this.

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_031.voiceText: Hmm... If memory serves, I have some potatoes planted over where they're running.

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_032.voiceText: If only I brought a few more mines, things would've been different.

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_033.voiceText: How come this door still hasn't been fixed?

char_113_cqbw_epoque#7_CN_036.voiceText: Isn't that the bunny who always follows the Doctor around?

char_511_asnipe_CN_018.voiceText: Alright, squad, keep your status updated.

char_511_asnipe_CN_020.voiceText: The enemy's moving as expected. Brace yourselves.

char_511_asnipe_CN_022.voiceText: I know the difference between sparring and a real fight.

char_511_asnipe_CN_025.voiceText: Don't worry, you won't escape the storm.

char_511_asnipe_CN_026.voiceText: This surge of energy has only one place to go.

char_511_asnipe_CN_027.voiceText: I've got a clear shot on target.

char_511_asnipe_CN_030.voiceText: Aggression is all part of the plan. Returning to base.

char_510_amedic_CN_026.voiceText: War is a plague, and I'm the cure.

char_510_amedic_CN_028.voiceText: No more suffering, no more pain.

char_510_amedic_CN_030.voiceText: Your commands were my thoughts as well, Doctor.

char_508_aguard_CN_018.voiceText: Read the briefing? Good, now here's your assignments.

char_508_aguard_CN_019.voiceText: Know your jobs? Then let's do this.

char_508_aguard_CN_020.voiceText: I prefer to keep my fight quiet.

char_508_aguard_CN_024.voiceText: I can handle this on my own.

char_508_aguard_CN_030.voiceText: It's always reassuring to carry out your orders, Doctor.

char_509_acast_CN_018.voiceText: Attention casters: set comms to operation channel.

char_509_acast_CN_020.voiceText: Opertaion is a go. Keep your support countersign in mind.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_001.voiceText: Man, I'm so bored... Might just go shopping... You know what, yeah, we're doing it! Come on, put your shoes on. Yeah, we're both going out, that's why I said 'we'!

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_002.voiceText: That lame look of yours is grinding my gears... Here, have a toy to lighten up. You're busy with work? Who cares about some boring-ass work? Just one thing: don't lose sight of this little doll, or it'll vanish in the blink of an eye.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_003.voiceText: Maaan, I'm so hungry... But as they say, gourmet food takes a gourmet cook. My brother's a great chef, you get hungry at one of our family reunions, just call him up and he'll take care of you. Now that's what I call service! Rhodes Island's food tastes like crap compared to his.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_004.voiceText: Lungmen's a pretty chill place, but their cuisine? It's got no kick to it! How can they eat that flavorless baby food? Listen up: spice is a way of life. Once you taste a little pleasant pain and feel that explosion of heat on your tongue, you'll realize what you've been missing all this time.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_005.voiceText: I used to just focus myself on what I needed for daily life, but I'm the type to really absorb my surroundings. And somehow or other I keep getting into fights. So I guess I could say it feels weird to NOT carry a weapon around. So it goes, I guess.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_006.voiceText: Rituals get passed down from generation to generation not 'cause they have any inherent meaning, but because people find their own meaning in them. A performance has its rewards, and a wish has its fulfillment. And when one of my favorite stories is involved, you bet your ass I'm gonna participate.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_007.voiceText: If you're out of touch with reality, you'll end up crushed beneath its boot, sooner or later. You'd think that's common freakin' sense, but some of my siblings ignore reality for what it is. Their dull lives are only gonna get harder for 'em as time goes on.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_008.voiceText: Your dreams turn to haze when you've lived as long as I have. But I've got better stuff to do than dream all day, and that's why l feel so alive. Sure, life is suffering, but seeing people carve something out for themselves is incredible. And as for you: think you got what it takes to be the anvil to my hammer?

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_009.voiceText: Blacksmithing may just be a regular old occupation, but it was also a part of early civilization. I'll keep metallurgy well and alive, even if everything else dies out. That's the future I chose for myself long ago. And you, you've made important choices before, haven'tcha? Don't ever go back on them. Stay true to the end and see it through. That's what it means to complete something.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_010.voiceText: You're sleeping AGAIN? Wake up, sunshine! We're going shopping! C'mon, hurry!

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_011.voiceText: Anybody home? Heard from one of your guys that I can make a comfy living here! Something about free lodging and food, with plenty of free time left over... Hm? This area is for staff only? Don't be like that! You make it sound like I don't belong here!

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_012.voiceText: Huh? What good do you think this stuff's gonna do me? Skills like these are only useful to people who value them.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? That takes me back... I got something like this once before. Anyway, that's cool, I guess. You have my thanks!

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_014.voiceText: People are like tools; you can classify 'em. And you, you're an interesting one... Or should I say 'unusual'? I could forge you a good sword, but since you ain't gonna swing it, let alone fight in the first place, it'd just be a waste of metal.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_017.voiceText: Guess one thing's never gonna change with time: swords will inevitably clash.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_018.voiceText: Say what? Lead the team? Never led anyone before, but I guess I'll try.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_019.voiceText: A smith's gotta be ready to pay the debts accrued by the weapons she forges.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_020.voiceText: My sword's gonna cleave your bodies and values alike.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_021.voiceText: Oh? You want me to handle this, personally?

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_022.voiceText: A knife, a life; weapons are the basis for society.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_023.voiceText: 'When 'tis a choice of life and death, why shouldst thou lay down thy arms?'

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_024.voiceText: Let's just get this done with.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_025.voiceText: You dare strike my shield with your spear? That's gonna end with you in pieces!

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_026.voiceText: My body burns at over 1,400 degrees!

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_027.voiceText: Even a virtuous king must, from time to time, look to the sword.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_028.voiceText: Why do I gotta waste my precious time on the likes of you third-rate amateurs?

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_029.voiceText: Not bad! I see some faint promise in you!

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_030.voiceText: These small fry ain't even close to quelling my hunger.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_031.voiceText: Man, you sure messed up. What'd I tell you about air bubbles weakening the iron?

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_032.voiceText: Terrible... If I really let myself loose, things would get a whole lot nastier... for everyone involved.

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_033.voiceText: Mind if I do some redecorating in here?

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_036.voiceText: Hold still! I'm making you a little something for your ear. It'll look great, just don't move!

char_2014_nian_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_042.voiceText: Yo, Doctor, you had lunch yet?

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_001.voiceText: Hm? Did I not explain that you were forbidden to enter without my express permission, after knocking? Oh? This is your office? You're working? Then have I not come out of my room to work as well? What is the meaning of 'your office'? [Tse-chi*]! I'm still sketching it out.

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_002.voiceText: You want to see my painting? You may. For you, I could even give you the painting. But if you like it, I won't give it to you. You don't like it? Huh, then you wouldn't want it anyway. This is who I am. Deal with it.

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_003.voiceText: Haa… I'm trapped on this ship. If anyone asks, you tell them so, and you do not let them into my room. I'm taking up space? I'm refusing to perform my operator duties? Hello, I am Dusk, the great painter trapped in this room.

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_004.voiceText: I'm not going out. Don't try to make me go out, I don't want to go out. I no longer care for the world outside. Do I dislike it? I like it fine. The mountains and rivers, the flowers and feathers, the pools and forests, the common folk, young and old, I could paint forever, I could watch forever, and yet, I will not go. It does not hold my interest forever.

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_005.voiceText: I loathe the word 'taste.' What gives these people the confidence to demand something good just as they open their mouths to lock the gates to others? It is unbecoming. If you are satisfied, you are satisfied. Should you enter, you must not bar the gate. Do you see the twin moons thinking only of themselves?

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_006.voiceText: An opportunity to watch me paint in earnest comes but once in a lifetime to one in ten thousand individuals. 'When the time comes, the strength of heaven and earth are one.' Ch'i, bone, shape, color, method, pouring out as a vast river, fine like the shadow of mountain bamboo, such is my brush, and it will not stop.

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_007.voiceText: I took the time to partake of some contemporary works. Films are not bad, they are like paintings. The good ones all have a unique strength of character, with form, and with decent meaning. Right, poetry and painting have a legacy. Do you have time to help me burn Nian's mountain of garbage? She is denigrating the very concept of cinema. Please.

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_008.voiceText: Food? Oh, thank you. Hm, where does this drink come from? It's good. Quite good. But I feel like it's missing something. You want to know what I usually eat? Then close your eyes. Ah~ You feel nothing, yes? That's because if you don't look, the food in my paintings does not exist.

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_009.voiceText: Take a look at Nian's carefree expression. You know the truth, don't you? She cares quite a bit about our lives, and our deaths. As for me? I may not get along with the wretched scribbler, but neither of us care much. When people die, the paintings remain. When I die, my work remains.

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_010.voiceText: Dreams are like unto life, like unto the scroll. One sleeps this sleep, will one sleep for millennia?

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_011.voiceText: Oh? {@nickname}? Another contract? Very well, please don't bother me again after I sign this one. Here... I should tell you here and now: I, Dusk, do not give out my paintings. Not to anyone. And I don't take commissions!

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_012.voiceText: Hm? A swing of an axe becomes rivers of blood. Do you mean... you want me to paint this?

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_013.voiceText: Why use a sword? There is a reason. 'With an inkstone sheath, one may learn the annals. With a brush sword, one may paint the celestial.' Is it true? Naturally, I speak off the cuff.

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_014.voiceText: Ahh, to make it this far with me... I should paint you a scroll. But be careful! Do not get caught up within it. The world I paint is much more fascinating than this one. How many have been lost, since ancient times? How many have escaped?

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_018.voiceText: Captain? What does a captain do?

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_020.voiceText: I'm in a good mood today. I'll give you this one I've titled 'Bones on the Sand'.

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_022.voiceText: Better leave the fine brush at home.

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_023.voiceText: Would any of you like to be my paint?

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_024.voiceText: This battlefield would do well with a splash of ink.

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_025.voiceText: Too difficult to explain, let me paint it for you.

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_026.voiceText: With the setting of the sun, the brush draws up the peaks!

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_027.voiceText: Copy the infinite with the tangible, bring the intangible to life!

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_028.voiceText: I am rather attached to you. Most of the time.

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_029.voiceText: Once, painting and war were quite different. But with this power, battle is art.

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_031.voiceText: Hm... a failed painting must be destroyed. It will bring shame.

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_032.voiceText: Slipped on a stroke? Start over.

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_033.voiceText: Do not bother preparing the room for me. I will handle it myself.

char_2015_dusk_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_042.voiceText: What was your name again? Oh, {@nickname}?

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_001.voiceText: Evocative so. Years and an age ago, the very palace rained and drizzled in the whisperers of consultants.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_002.voiceText: Yea, when Yan scholars speak of Sui, that is us, and It too. Facts hardly worth covering up; Nian's worries are not mine. After all, I am only me, and my death, no more than death is. The only shames would be this wine and world, for at day's end I love them long.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_003.voiceText: I was of the mind I would finally meet someone past, an old friend. Never did I think this is how you now present yourself. From knowing not one is one, isn't this like a dream? However, {@nickname}. It is fine to be as yourself. Long have I contended with myself; myself I shall prefer to act.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_004.voiceText: Where the heart is as will, and its utterance is as verse. If wells your chest with depths manifold, wouldn't failing their writing be shame to meet yourself? Hm? My tail? Ah, so too do I make use of a common brush, naturally. But it is at times inconvenient, as an extremity would be. My body is an unfettered one; who says I can't use my tail?

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_005.voiceText: Poetry, speech, lyric, essay. Though they all differ as their own, they are common in places. A pity the people of now are, by and large unable to exercise patience. To listen to a song, to read a poem. I take no objection to it, but how must our present scholars suffer.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_006.voiceText: Nian is too impetuous, Dusk timid, yet to see the two as they are now, it seems they already know what they like, and want to do. So why probe at veracity or falsity or object or subject? To bicker and squabble every day, knowing emotion's gamut, is that not what a person is?

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_007.voiceText: {@nickname}, would you want for me to compose you a verse? Hm? Nay, I'm simply in the mood. I need not write it, nor record it. Ah, wait, if it were a song... that would be quite good too! But to dance a song, I fear I would need some preparation. Good! You sit there, and await me a short while.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_008.voiceText: I am drunk? Hah... I have not yet seen the sky throw wide, moon rise, seas race, ice break, to wait true for all the world's sobriety would be but the withering of a bud, to want true for deep intoxication would be far too early still... {@nickname}, now, why do you say I am drunk?

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_009.voiceText: Last night I dreamt of you. Nay! Perhaps it's you who dreamt of me. Oh, can you not recall? A shame; it delighted me so, yet I cannot share this revelry. Delighted how? Hmm. That eight thousand years of springs, eight thousand of winters, all dreamt, were no more than a brief handful of autumns. That is all.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_010.voiceText: Clouds ranged as billows, distant-run roads withered. I, departed of the vistas, sailed a ferry in late autumn.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_011.voiceText: Ling, you can call me. Have my two troublemaking sisters vexed you any? Hm? You've seen me before? Ah... perhaps so, in a dream.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_012.voiceText: Though antithetical at a glance, your nature is quite similar.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_013.voiceText: Hm... 'General, I heed thy order,' should I say? Hahah, do not take it seriously. I only suppose that if you were truly a field marshal, then I may not mind once again serving as a strategist.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_014.voiceText: Nian was not wrong. This farcical dream of a thousand autumns is only right to wake from.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_017.voiceText: The river bends a thousand times, a city lone in desolation, vivid in the mind's eye.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_018.voiceText: To scatter the fill of a brimming cup, to share the sip for a soothed sorrow.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_019.voiceText: Plotted schemes, waged wars, crossed arms, shed blood. An eternity, unaltered and unfailing in its challenge.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_020.voiceText: To gaze the fire from afar, knowing not its heat.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_021.voiceText: Has it come to my turn?

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_023.voiceText: And thus has autumn made reckoned her arrival.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_024.voiceText: For the marching, a warsong. For the fallen, a lament.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_025.voiceText: The split halberd sinks in the sand, great aspirations unrecompensed.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_026.voiceText: One word to address all beneath the heaven, one scope to spare none upon the earth.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_027.voiceText: When will the hate sunk beneath the battlefield disperse?

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_028.voiceText: Speak as your heart wills, and be as your intoxication wishes.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_029.voiceText: Another song, sublime and majestic. {@nickname}, perhaps you and I truly are as two entwined friends.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_030.voiceText: Duly satisfying, as a cup filled to the brim. We should remain level and humble, yet... we ought to sing your praises, yes. You did well.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_031.voiceText: Mm... things disappoint on occasion; there's no need to blame yourself too hard. Leave the rest to me.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_032.voiceText: Victory and defeat are commonplace in war. As we have freedom to maneuver, this is not a complete loss.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_033.voiceText: Rhodes Island's interior... I'm lost as to whether I should say it's reminiscent or curious.

char_2023_ling_CN_TOPOLECT_CN_036.voiceText: What is it? Would you like a cup? You wouldn't? What a shame.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_001.voiceText: Hm? Ah, this soil... it can murmur. It can dance. It is my friend.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_002.voiceText: Miss Closure told me I shouldn't walk about Rhodes Island 'fully equipped'... but I'm not used to... revealing... myself. Sorry...

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_003.voiceText: Thank-you letters? Ah, from the Sarkaz workers yesterday? My equipment and type of Arts are a good match for physical work. Besides, their materials and fuel weren't featherweight. And they relied on the power of flesh and blood to ensure Rhodes Island sails smooth... it's incredible.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_004.voiceText: That elite operator... I thought I'd seen enough bizarre Originium Arts in Leithanien to write any wild fantasy. But the moment he pushed apart the fog with a wave of his hand, I understood, as a Sarkaz, he was young yet incredibly ancient.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_005.voiceText: I often think of the soldiers and companions that have left us. Sometimes, I have a sort of delusion that even now, I'm still fleeing... Doctor, have you been to Kazdel before? That was where my journey started, and once, where I'd thought it would end.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_006.voiceText: Dr. Kal'tsit, huh... She startled me, but she's reassuring in spades... One thing, though. Rhodes Island seems to get along well with another mercenary group, too. Could you tell me about them, Doctor? It's best I don't know? I see... then I think I can more or less guess who.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_007.voiceText: I became a Rhodes Island Operator so they could be treated properly, live on properly, and only then would those warriors... have died with meaning. But... since coming to Rhodes Island, I've seen clearly what I, myself, am truly fighting for. That was a first for me.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_008.voiceText: Me, alone, talking to a clay doll...? You're... you're telling you saw me? That was just a kind of ceremony... huh? So everyone already knew? Really? Then I'll be more careful next time, do it late when nobody's up... um, I shouldn't?

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_009.voiceText: From Kazdel to Leithanien, so many marks have been carved onto the suffering. The moment they had no choice but to fight, I realized I had nothing at all. How do you see me, Doctor? You trust me? Will that trust... allow me to live on?

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_010.voiceText: ...The person napping there is the Doctor. Remember that well. Our road together is sure to be long and far.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_011.voiceText: Sarkaz mercenary, Mudrock... You're the Doctor, then. Rhodes Island has saved me many times, and now, I'd like you to let me return the favor.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_012.voiceText: I've had a taste of how Rhodes Island fights before, but, well, this still makes a great reference...

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_013.voiceText: I used to be known as Reunion, and then under the Mudrock Squad, and now... I've been promoted by my former enemy. Is this what they meant by 'life is a rollercoaster?'

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_014.voiceText: Hm? This seems fresh? I never take my helmet off in battle, after all... There's a lot of reasons why, but things have changed now. S... staying like this? If I have to...

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_017.voiceText: I'm simply a Rhodes Island Operator, now. I'll obey your command.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_018.voiceText: The captain... I don't like leading, but... I'm used to it.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_025.voiceText: The land is as my friend.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_029.voiceText: Running is useless... resist it, even if you are not willing to resist. This is the only way I've come to know to face suffering.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_030.voiceText: My friends are whispering their celebration. They cheer our victory, Doctor.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_031.voiceText: Chase them... I'll watch over the battlefield with my friends' eyes.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_032.voiceText: It's not the first I've fled with my back to the enemy. If even more can live on this way... I'll cover your backs.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_033.voiceText: The ceiling's... a little lower than I imagined.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_034.voiceText: ...Mm? Did you touch me just now?

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor? Could you stay with me for a bit? I'd like... to ask you a little about Kazdel. Ah, and my friends have missed you, too.
